Data.Name: Allen's Triple Sec
Data.Description: Remarkable fresh flavors of this triple sec makes it the perfect mixer for your favorite drink recipes. Each of Allen's liqueurs and schnapps burst with the rich taste and aromas found in products costing twice as much.

Data.Name: Kura The Whisky
Data.Description:
A variation of Kura The Whisky blended malt whisky, which has enjoyed a finishing period in casks that previously held rum. We're rather fold of rum cask finished whiskies, as they help to bolster any lip-smacking fruit notes - and that's exactly what has happened here.

Nose: Toasted oak to the fore, before a kick of green apple and spiced mango chutney.

Palate: Tangy orange and lemon, followed by a touch of menthol. Still quite smoky.

Finish: Burnt sugar, stewed pears and heavy hints of clove.

Data.Name: Laddy's Irish Country Cream
Data.Description: A delicious Irish cream liqueur. Try it in your coffee, if you're an alcohol-in-the-morning kind of person.

Data.Name: Laphroaig 10 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: An all-malt Scotch whisky, malted barley is dried over a peat fire for a unique full, rich flavor. Aroma and flavors are of blue peat smoke, the sweet nuttiness of the barley, the delicate heathery perfume of Islay's streams.

Data.Name: Laphroaig 25 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Matured in second-fill Oloroso Sherry casks and American oak ex-bourbon barrels for 25 years(!), a well-aged release of this incredibly popular heavily-peated single malt from Islay. Laphroaig aged for quarter of a century and bottled, without chill filtration, at 48.9% ABV.

Data.Name: Knob Creek Straight Rye Whiskey
Data.Description:
Color: Shades of gold to light amber.
Taste: Bold rye spiciness with undertones of vanilla and oak.
Aroma: Expansive notes of herbs and rye with nuances of oak.
Finish: Warm and smooth with spice throughout.

Data.Name: Knob Creek 2001 Limited Edition Bourbon Whiskey
Data.Description: Made with extra patience, this robust Bourbon is over 14 years of age, Knob Creek's oldest expression to date. Produced in three batches of limited quantity (targeting 12,000 bottles per batch), it's a rare Knob Creek ready to be collected and shared, beginning with Batch #1.

Data.Name: Karlsson's Gold Vodka
Data.Description: Karlsson's Gold Vodka is a blend of several different varietals of virgin new potatoes from Cape Bjäre, Sweden. It is handcrafted, single-distilled and unfiltered to preserve the flavor and character of this rare and expensive raw ingredient. The varieties of potatoes include solist, gammel svensk röd, princess, sankta thora, hamlet, marine and celine. Each varietal is distilled only once through a continuous column still lined with copper. The varietals are then blended without charcoal filtration, which would remove valuable flavor elements. The resulting vodka is full-bodied and rich, with a distinct viscosity and mouth-feel that is unlike other vodkas on the market today. Although it is designed to be served neat, on the rocks or in a martini, also try Karlsson's Gold with fresh cracked black pepper or as a unique base for your favorite cocktail.

Data.Name: Fugu Habanero Vodka
Data.Description: In San Diego, there is some of the freshest, most authentic Mexican cuisine north of the border. So to flavor Fugu vodka, inspiration came from the tastes served up at neighborhood taco shops. This version is infused with spicy habanero peppers, and like your favorite salsa, it definitely has a kick. The result: a world-class vodka, infused with local flavor.

Data.Name: Deep Eddy Original Vodka
Data.Description: Deep Eddy original vodka is made in small batches from the highest-quality corn. It's distill 10 times in a state-of-the-art column still creating a cleaner, smoother vodka. Deep Eddy is then filtered gently over charcoal 4 times, ensuring the subtle smooth flavor remains in the finished spirit. The product is finished using only the finest Texas water, which is about as perfect as water gets! Because Deep Eddy is made from 100% corn, all Deep Eddy Vodkas are naturally gluten free.

Data.Name: Deep Eddy Sweet Tea Vodka
Data.Description: Deep Eddy Sweet Tea begins with 10x-distilled Original Vodka, to which Deep Eddy adds real, whole-leaf Indonesian Black Tea and sweeten with a hint of organic honey from a local Texas Hill Country apiary. Deep Eddy Sweet Tea Vodka was their first product, but like the rest of their vodkas, doesn’t take itself too seriously!

Data.Name: Deep Eddy Ruby Red Vodka
Data.Description: Deep Eddy Ruby Red Vodka starts with award-winning Original Vodka and is infused with real Ruby Red Grapefruit juice and lightly sweetened with real cane sugar for a deliciously tart, refreshing taste, perfect for day-drinking with family and friends.

Data.Name: Bully Boy Hub Punch Whiskey
Data.Description: The recipe uses Bully Boy Boston Rum as a base and is infused with orange, raspberry, lemon, and a select combination of botanicals. Because the resulting spirit is both fruity and herbal, it serves as a versatile base for cocktails. 1 part hub Punch, 2 parts something sweet (lemonade, ginger ale, sweet tea, ginger beer) and 2 parts soda water is ideal.

Data.Name: Bulleit 10 Year Bourbon
Data.Description: Aged in charred American white oak, select Bulleit Bourbon barrels were set aside to age for 10 years. The result is a special expression of Bulleit that provides a rich, deep, incredibly smooth sipping experience.

Data.Name: Blanton's Single Barrel Bourbon
Data.Description: A deep, satisfying nose of nutmeg and spices. Powerful dry vanilla notes in harmony with hints of honey amid strong caramel and corn. A medium finish composed of returning corn and nutmeg flavors.

Data.Name: Zapopan Reposado Tequila
Data.Description:
"Zapopan Tequila Reposado is 100% Puro de Agave, and produced at Fabrica de Tequilas Finos in Tequila, Jalisco. Zapopan Reposado is made and bottled in Mexico.

It is aged a minimum of 4-6 months and attains its natural color and rich flavor through the authentic resting process in oak barrels. Best enjoyed on the rocks, straight up or for the premium margarita!" WineChateau.com

Data.Name: Zapopan Tequila Blanco
Data.Description:
100% agave Zapopan Blanco Tequila has the true bouquet and flavor of the blue
agave. It’s sweet agave fruit and citrus aromas come from the heart of
the plant.

Data.Name: WhistlePig Straight Rye 10 Year Whiskey
Data.Description:
The spirit of entrepreneurship.
Nose: Allspice, orange peel, anise, oak, char and caramel
Palate: Sweet; hints of caramel and vanilla, followed by rye­spice and mint
Finish: Long finish; warm butterscotch and caramel.

Data.Name: Westcork Bourbon Cask
Data.Description: West Cork Irish Whiskey – Bourbon cask (40% abv/80 proof) – is a blended Irish whiskey containing 75% grain Irish whiskey & 25% malt Irish whiskey.  Patiently matured in first fill bourbon casks to deliver a smooth, subtle and quintessential Irish whiskey.

Data.Name: Suntory Yamakazi 12 Year Old Single Malt Whiskey
Data.Description: Spiritual and deep, made at Yamazaki Distillery, the soulplace of Japanese whisky, its signature multi-layered taste is highly praised by whisky connoisseurs all over the world. Today, Suntory Single Malt Whisky Yamazaki® Whisky is not only the No.1 single malt whisky in Japan, but is enjoyed in more than 35 countries.

Data.Name: Stolichnaya Stoli Razberi
Data.Description: Stoli® Razberi™ opens with an intense nose of raspberry jam, boiled sweets and hot berry fruit infusions. The palate has raspberry ripple creaminess, balanced by the sweet spice of rye and wheat grain vodka, and lifted by crisp citrus notes. Stoli Razberi is finished with hints of pepper and wild raspberry cane.

Data.Name: Stolichnaya Stoli Blueberi
Data.Description: Plump ripe berries lead the nose, with blueberry, black currant and lemon fruits, and to the back, a medicinal hint of juniper. Stoli® Blueberi™ offers a mouth feel that is smooth and creamy, with a buttery grain character and an aromatic note of eucalyptus.

Data.Name: Stolichnaya Stoli Citros
Data.Description: Stoli® Citros™ is delicately aromatic, with clear scents of sweet lemon at the start, building to a more intense blast of lime. Citros has a very natural and complex citrus smell, with no heavy overtones. The palate is subtle, zesty lemon with floral touches on the finish.

Data.Name: Soplica Vodka
Data.Description: "This is slightly sweet and neutral, with a faint citrus note on the finish." WineEnthusiast.com

Data.Name: Signature Whisky
Data.Description: Signature is the original expression of the Master Blender- Caroline Martin. In pursuit of her passion for whisky-making, master blender created a blend that was true to her character. Caroline married the most exquisite aged Scotch malts with 100% aged Indian malts, to create a balanced rare whisky with an inimitable peaty character.

Data.Name: Sho Chiku Bai Junmai DaiGinio
Data.Description:
This Junmai DaiGinjo is exceptionally smooth and well-balanced with a bright ginjo bouquet, rich fruity taste and an elegant finish. When served chilled, it has a fragrant nose with complex, fruity aromas and flavors of honeydew melon, cantaloupe, watermelon, Asian pear, and banana. Pale gold and bright in the glass, it is full-bodied in the mouth with a fine, silky texture, and a lasting, lightly juicy finish with building savoriness.

This is the first daiginjo sake produced with 100% American-harvested Yamadanishiki rice. This handcrafted daiginjo was born as the 30th Anniversary Commemorative prodcut of Takara Sake USA Inc. in 2013. Against sake from Japan and around the world, this American brewed daiginjo consistently ranks in the top of its class.

Data.Name: Shipwreck Coffee Rum
Data.Description:
The only coffee flavored rum sold in the US. Blended with natural Brazilian coffee. 

Notes of butterscotch, toasted marshmallow, toffee.

Data.Name: Newfoundland Screech Rum
Data.Description: An award-winning Jamaican rum, steeped in history – crafted in Newfoundland. Sweet taste of caramelized sugars, ripe fruits, vanilla and oak. A smooth, balanced blend with no sugar added.

Data.Name: Rombauer Chardonnay
Data.Description: Rombauer Vineyards began producing Chardonnay in 1982.  In 1990, the Rombauer family made their first Chardonnay from the Carneros region, where San Pablo Bay meets the southern end of Napa and Sonoma valleys.  There, the cool climate and clay soils offer ideal conditions for growing superior Chardonnay with the Rombauer hallmarks – intense fruit flavors balanced by fresh acidity.

Data.Name: Dekuyper Watermelon Pucker
Data.Description: This refreshing, sweet and sour liqueur is perfect addition for drinks. Crisp and refreshing, it is perfect for a unique margarita or a punched up martini.

Data.Name: Old Weller Antique
Data.Description:
A wheated bourbon with a full-bodied flavor and a balanced palate. Old Weller Antique is bottled at 107 proof, offering a complex taste and bold finish. It’s certainly a recognizable member of the Weller label, with its own unique characteristics to compliment the high proof. 

Sweet and unusual floral notes and coupled with vanilla. The taste is very well balanced with sweet fruit notes, strong vanilla undertone and sharp spicy tones, with a cinnamon finish.

Data.Name: Old Raj Gin
Data.Description: Old Raj gin has been produced since 1972 and is available at 46% and 55% abv. This quality floral gin has a slight yellow tint due to the addition of the saffron. This valuable and rare ingredient is added post distillation.

Data.Name: Noah's Mill Bourbon
Data.Description: One of the most lush and rich Whiskeys on the market. The nose is walnuts, prunes, and floral notes. The palate mimics the nose with walnuts, prunes, spices, intertwined with lavender and balanced with the perfect amount of acid, that leads you down a path of lingering burnt caramel.

Data.Name: Nikka Coffey Vodka
Data.Description: Coffey Vodka is a vodka with flavor and texture. The secret behind this extremely smooth mouthfeel and delicate taste is the quality of Coffey distillates and the preciseness in blending. Corn and barley are separately distilled into various batches with slight difference in ABV and taste profile. These batches are carefully blended by experts and then refined with white birch charcoal. This vodka with zesty notes, rich sweetness and milky mouthfeel perfectly captures the exquisite fullness brought by the Coffey Still.

Data.Name: Nautical American Gin
Data.Description: The aromatic ﬂavors come alive on the palate – the brightness of the citrus and juniper notes are complemented by the pepper and mineral. This combination of citrus and spice deliver a powerful yet elegant ﬂavor experience. The slight hint of sea salt rounds out the entire taste sensation.

Data.Name: Mejor Reposado
Data.Description: Experience Mejor Reposado, crafted using 100% private-estate highland blue agave of the highest quality. Reposado is aged 11 months in American oak barrels producing a sweet mellow maple aroma, caramel and citrus notes with an ultra smooth vanilla finish. Enjoy neat, on the rocks or in your favorite cocktail for the ultimate reposado experience.

Data.Name: Mejor Pink Tequila
Data.Description: Experience Mejor Pink, crafted using 100% private-estate highland blue agave of the highest quality. Pink is a Mejor Blanco tequila dressed up with a natural vibrant hue, contemporary packaging and the perfect hint of natural agave citrus. Mejor Pink is ultra smooth and the official tequila of girls night out!

Data.Name: Mejor Añejo Tequila
Data.Description: Experience Mejor Añejo, crafted using 100% private-estate highland blue agave of the highest quality. Añejo is masterfully aged 19 to 24 months in American oak barrels resulting in an Añejo tequila that exudes deep rich tones from the extra barrel time, and reveals a clean profile with notes of vanilla, chocolate, and caramel. Be sure to experience this true ultra premium tequila neat.

Data.Name: Maurice's Hard Root Beer Schnapps
Data.Description: "In 1929, Maurice S. Walker expanded his local apothecary business to include flavorings, extracts and syrups. He developed a secret recipe for Hard Root Beer Schnapps and after the repeal of prohibition, production was expanded. Crafted from our traditional family recipe, Maurice’s Hard Root Beer is filled with real root beer taste." Fourseasonswine.com

Data.Name: Putnam Rye Whiskey
Data.Description: Nothing says America more than Rye, America’s Original Whiskey. This Putnam rye is distilled meticulously to their Head Distiller’s “to the touch” standards.

Data.Name: Redemption Rye 7 Year Barrel Proof
Data.Description: Aged 7 years, this straight rye has a mash bill of 95% rye and 5% malted barley. As many as 10 barrels at a time are used to batch it. The whiskey is sourced from the Old Seagram's Distillery (a.k.a. LDI, a.k.a. MGP Indiana).

Data.Name: Wild Turkey Bourbon
Data.Description:
Originally crafted by Kentucky Bourbon Hall-of-Famer Eddie Russell as "Wild Turkey 81", Wild Turkey Bourbon is aged in American White Oak barrels with the deepest, No. 4 "alligator" char. With notes of sweet vanilla, pear, and hints of spice, this bourbon finishes with a flavor that is full and rich, whether enjoyed straight or with a mixer.

81 Proof.

Data.Name: Uncle Val's Botanical Gin
Data.Description: Premium gin infused with juniper, cucumber, lemon, sage and lavender for a unique aroma and flavor profile. Serve as a perfect compliment in cocktails or simply on the rocks.

Data.Name: Macallan 18 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: This 18-year-old whisky, which was aged in a combination of sherry-seasoned Spanish oak and sherry-seasoned American oak casks, was awarded a 92-point rating from Wine Enthusiast.

Data.Name: Macallan 15 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The Macallan Fine Oak Range is an exquisite series. Jim Murray calls it “jaw-droppingly” good, with great “depth and sophistication.”

Data.Name: Templeton Rye Whiskey
Data.Description: An unmistakable rye whiskey, Templeton Rye is smooth and spicy with a clean finish. There’s a reason people call it The Good Stuff. Rise up and taste Iowa’s most notorious whiskey.

Data.Name: St Remy Authentic VSOP Brandy
Data.Description: Made from a carefully selected blend of French wines, producing and exceptionally smooth brandy. An aromatic nose leads to a body full of fruit with light woody notes.

Data.Name: GrandTen South Boston Irish Whiskey
Data.Description: With the strong Irish-American heritage in South Boston, it's only right that GrandTen Distilling have released a South Boston Irish Whiskey. It is distilled in Ireland and bottled in South Boston, which, y'know, makes the name rather apt, don't you think?

Data.Name: Spy Valley Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This wine is fruit-driven in style, with complexity from lees ageing for several months in stainless steel tanks before bottling. This wine is a classic Marlborough Sauvignon Blanc with intense flavors and crisp acid in a dry style.

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Raspberry Vodka
Data.Description: Bursting with a true-to-fruit seediness of red raspberry puree.

Data.Name: Sangre de Vida Blanco Tequila
Data.Description:
Description:  Award winning, triple distilled, 100% blue webber agave tequila presented in a stunning anatomically correct glass heart bottle.

Tasting Notes: For the purest at heart and those who want that true agave flavor, Sangre de Vida Blanco captivates with a bouquet of banana, citrus, green bell pepper and white flowers. Once you have had a taste of the light peppery, agave with a hint of minerals from the earth your taste buds will long for another sip.

Awards & Ratings: Platinum Medal Tasting Award. Rated 94 POINTS by The Tasting Panel

Proof: 40% Alc/Vol (80 proof)

Data.Name: Sazerac Rye Whiskey
Data.Description: The One and Only New Orleans Original. Sazerac Rye Whiskey symbolizes the tradition and history of New Orleans. Rye Whiskey that dates back to the 1800’s, around the time when saloons, veiled as Coffee Houses, began lining the streets of New Orleans. It was at the Sazerac Coffee House on Royal Street where local patrons were served toddies made with Rye Whiskey and Peychaud’s Bitters. The libation became known as the “Sazerac” and America’s first branded cocktail was born. This is the whiskey that started it all.

Data.Name: Larceny Bourbon
Data.Description:
Made with wheat as the secondary grain, instead of the traditional rye, Larceny is a smoother tasting Bourbon.

Color: Bright new copper
Aroma: Fresh bread and toffee, with a note of butterscotch
Taste: Buttery caramel and honeyed notes, with a rich mouthfeel
Finish: Long, gently sweet and savory

Data.Name: Laphroaig Quarter Cask
Data.Description:
Still-maturing whisky from our standard ex-bourbon barrels is transferred to quarter casks and left to rest in our warehouse just a stone's throw from the Atlantic shore.

This process represents Laphroaig breathing new life into a once-defunct tradition: the use of the smaller cask size, which ensures increased contact with the oak, creating a soft and velvety edge to complement Laphroaig's distinctive peatiness.

On the nose the sensation is toffee and caramel, caused by the vanillas and tannins of the American oak, plus a dryness from the wood oil.

The finish is long and alternates between this sweetness and smoke.

Data.Name: Karma Anejo Tequila
Data.Description: Karma Tequila Añejo is aged inside American Oak Kentucky Bourbon barrels for nearly three years, suffusing the tequila with an alluring, soothing oaky aroma. Pamper your palate with our exquisite Añejo sipped neat or over ice.

Data.Name: Hibiki Suntory Whisky
Data.Description: "Kanzen" or complete, Hibiki Whisky is a harmonious blend of innumerous malt and grain whiskies which are meticulously blended to create a full orchestra of flavors and aromas. Seductive, blossoming and enigmatic, Hibiki Whisky celebrates an unrivaled art of blending, fine craftsmanship and a sense of luxury from the House of Suntory.

Data.Name: Buffalo Trace Bourbon
Data.Description: Buffalo Trace Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey is distilled, aged and bottled at the most award-winning distillery in the world. Made from the finest corn, rye and barley malt, this whiskey ages in new oak barrels for years in century old warehouses until the peak of maturity. The taste is rich and complex, with hints of vanilla, toffee and candied fruit. The smooth finish lingers on the palate. This will never change.

Data.Name: 2 Gingers Irish Whiskey
Data.Description:
This award-winning spirit is smooth, malty and
slightly sweet to start, with a tingle of honey
and citrus. A blended Irish whiskey, distilled
twice and aged four years in the mild climate,
the woody essence suggests caramel and
vanilla to the finish.

Data.Name: Appleton Estate 12 Year Rum
Data.Description: Appleton Estate Rare Blend 12 Year Old is a ‘minimum age’ rum as indicated by the number 12 displayed on the bottle. The rum is aged in Number One Select American Oak barrels.

Data.Name: Auchentoschan 12 Year Old
Data.Description: Triple distilled then matured for over twelve years. This Lowland Single Malt Whisky has the tempting aroma of toasted almonds, caramelised toffee and the signature smooth, delicate, Auchentoshan taste.

Data.Name: Barr Hill Reserve Tom Cat Gin
Data.Description: Tom Cat Gin is an expedition into uncharted territories. Once distilled, the gin is aged in new American oak barrels in search of a bolder expression. The robust character of the new oak barrel mingles with the coniferous quality of the juniper, yielding an enticing aroma. A touch of raw honey leaves this revolutionary spirit remarkably approachable, whether drinking neat or in a cocktail. When the world called for whiskey, the answer was this gin.

Data.Name: Barr Hill Vodka
Data.Description: Barr Hill Vodka is a tribute to the hardworking beekeepers. In late summer, they take delivery of hundreds of barrels of their pure raw honey. Their season’s work is what makes our vodka truly special. This recipe depends on two simple principles: never heat the honey prior to fermentation and never distill more than twice. This technique preserves the wild yeast and the rich aromatics of nectar - delivering the floral depth of wildflower fields straight to your glass.

Data.Name: Barrell Bourbon
Data.Description: Often, barrels and batches of bourbon are used as components of larger blends. Watered down, pulled too early, left too long, they forgo their singular characteristics. Barrell enjoys finding and identifying barrels that contain distinctive bourbons and then bottle them at cask strength to retain their authentic qualities.

Data.Name: Basil Hayden's Dark Rye
Data.Description: Deep, rich amber with ruby undertones. Complex blend of caramel, dried fruit, and oak with back notes of spice and a rounded mouth feel. Full in flavor, yet delicately nuanced, you’d be wise to grab a bottle of Dark Rye to experience this magical blend for yourself.

Data.Name: Basil Hayden's Two By Two Rye Bourbon
Data.Description: Rich caramel and brown sugar complemented by back notes of soft rye and vanilla. A balanced blend of sumptuous rye and brown sweets with an ample woody accent. The final blend is about 20% bourbon to 80% rye and is best served neat or on-the-rocks to experience the complexity created by meticulously blending four component whiskies.

Data.Name: Beluga Noble Vodka
Data.Description:
The first batch of Beluga Noble Russian Vodka was produced in 2002. It was the first and the dearest to our hearts! This was the result of the meticulous hard work of the Mariinsk Distillery masters. The refined, rich taste of Beluga Noble Russian Vodka results from its unique composition, mainly due to the malt spirit and the purest water of the Siberian artesian wells. This helps to smoothen the taste of vodka.

These carefully selected natural components pass through a triple filtering system. Afterwards, Beluga Noble is left to «rest» for thirty days. Such method helps to neutralize the harsh smell of the spirit and to enhance the rich taste and soft flavor of Beluga Russian Noble Vodka.

Data.Name: Black Fly Rum Punch
Data.Description: Pump up the party with this refreshing, slightly sour and not too sweet punch. Made with real strawberry, lime and pineapples juices.

Data.Name: Black Fly Long Island Iced Tea
Data.Description: Made with the perfect blend of spirits; Canadian Vodka, Genuine Mexican Tequila, notes of gin, rum pure lemon juice and a splash of cola this Classic Cocktail is a sure hit. Slightly sour. Balanced. & Not too sweet.

Data.Name: Black Fly Vodka Grapefruit
Data.Description: Serve up some sunshine with the fresh taste of pure pink grapefruit juice blended with smooth Canadian Vodka.

Data.Name: Black Fly Tequila Margarita
Data.Description: A light refreshing blend of pure lime juices and genuine Mexican tequila. Enjoy the real taste of tequila, the fresh flavour of pure lime juice and an authentic delicious margarita every time, 375 ml.

Data.Name: Bowmore Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: With more maturing history within its walls than anywhere else in Scotland, Bowmore No.1 Malt will unlock the door to a story of deeper character. Exclusively matured in first fill Bourbon casks, Bowmore No.1 Malt is singularly special. Vanilla sweetness, cinnamon spice and oak smoke beautifully complement the mouth-watering citrus, honeycomb and coconut flakes, culminating in a peat smoked, bourbon vanilla and lime finish.

Data.Name: Louis Roederer Cristal 2008 Champagne
Data.Description: Time has worked its magic. Cristal is a giant with a patient heart. It is still brimming with youth, even after many long years spent resting in the cellars. The chalk has concentrated its texture and given it its unique energy and surprising depth. Its pure tension, opulence and remarkable persistence take it above and beyond any limits. It asserts its presence, flowing as sweetly as a mountain stream, yet structured by the strength and concentration of the vintage.

Data.Name: Del Maguey Chichicapa
Data.Description:
Del Maguey brings you a collection of Single Village® Mezcal made in the lush, remote mountains, plains and valleys of Oaxaca (wa-haka), Mexico. Each mezcal is named for the village where it is made.

Chichicapa has a medium nose and a complex taste with lots of citrus and a long, smooth finish with overtones of mint. The pueblo elevation is 5052 ft. (1540 meters) in a broad valley with a desert and tropical micro-climate.

Del Maguey mezcals are twice distilled and unblended from 100% mature agave Espadin and are produced the original, 400-year-old hand-crafted way. Production is limited to exclusive quantities per year to preserve quality. There are no chemicals, colorings or additives ever used in any Del Maguey, Single Village® Mezcal.

Data.Name: Dunc's Mill Maple Rum
Data.Description: "Founded in 2011, Dunc's Mill is located in Vermont and ferments, distills, and bottles their rum on site. Their Maple Rum, one of three they produce, is a flavored rum adding real Vermont maple syrup tapped in the spring to their unaged rum, which uses organic evaporated sugarcane juice." Distiller.com

Data.Name: Eagle Rare Whiskey
Data.Description:
Eagle Rare Bourbon Whiskey is masterfully crafted and carefully aged for no less than ten years. Every barrel is discriminately selected to offer consistent flavor but with a seemingly individual personality. Eagle Rare is a bourbon that lives up to its name with its lofty, distinctive taste experience.

The nose is complex, with aromas of toffee, hints of orange peel, herbs, honey, leather and oak. The taste is bold, dry and delicate with notes of candied almonds and very rich cocoa. The finish is dry and lingering.

Data.Name: Four Roses Kentucky Straight Bourbon Whiskey
Data.Description: Mix up your favorite cocktail with a sophisticated, contemporary flair with this worldwide favorite. Enjoy this smooth and mellow Bourbon with its long and soft finish. Savor its unique aromas and flavors in your favorite Bourbon cocktail, on the rocks, or with a splash. 80 proof. 40% alcohol/volume.

Data.Name: Jean-Luc Colombo Cape Bleue Rosé
Data.Description: Soft, delicate salmon pink color. On the nose, subtle hints of peach, rose petal, watermelon, and tropical fruit. The palate shows dry, round, and full finesse with notes of fresh berries. A great rosé to enjoy on its own or with a wide range of appetizers, fish, poultry dishes and vegetarian fare.

Data.Name: Jack Daniel's Old No. 7 Tennessee Whiskey
Data.Description: Mellowed drop by drop through 10-feet of sugar maple charcoal, then matured in handcrafted barrels of our own making. And Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey doesn’t follow a calendar. It’s only ready when the tasters say it is. It's judged by the way it looks. By its aroma. And of course, by the way it tastes. It’s how Jack Daniel himself did it over a century ago. And how it is still done today.

Data.Name: Fabrizia Italian Margarita Cans
Data.Description: A Premium, Hand Crafted, Ready-to-Drink Cocktail. Fabrizia Spirits discarded over 100,000 peeled lemons (rinds of which were used to make Fabrizia Limoncello) in 2014 alone. By creating lemonade with those lemons, it created a fresh, all-natural base for its newest product, the Italian Margarita. About 60% of the product is real lemonade made from fresh lemons, cane sugar and includes no preservatives.

Data.Name: Irish Manor Irish Cream Liqueur
Data.Description: "This is truly a legendary Irish Cream made with only the finest Irish spirits and the richest Irish Cream. At the end of a cold day, Irish hunters would retrun from the forest to their favorite manor house. They would sit by a fire and relax with an Irish Cream Liqueur. One recipe was so delicious it was praised as "Legendary". It is this elixir one finds in this bottle" -Citywinecellar.com

Data.Name: Hirsch Special Reserve Whiskey
Data.Description: An American Tradition. Corn whiskey is historically the first commercial American whiskey, but today Kentucky Straight Corn Whiskey (KSCW) represents a tiny, but very important, classification of American whiskey. Through the stark landscape of authentic KSCW, we encourage you to venture into this pristine territory shepherded by an experienced guide, Hirsch Selection. KSCW is the predecessor to bourbon whiskey, which has at least 51% corn in the mash bill. Only when the corn content is at least 80% can a whiskey be designated as corn whiskey. Authentic whiskey selection is a recognizable strength of Preiss Imports. The Hirsch Selection hand picked series of single barrel whiskies is chosen expressly for connoisseurs of small batch fine spirits. In tradition, we invite you to savor this classic KSCW, which has been specially aged and mellowed in reused oak barrels. This KSCW is another true original Hirsch Selection.

Data.Name: Hirsch Small Batch Reserve Bourbon
Data.Description:
The rye is sourced from Northern Europe, and the corn comes from Indiana and Ohio. The high rye content adds a distinctive spice character that balances the sweetness of the corn, making this a bourbon that is excellent sipped on its own or used in your favorite bourbon cocktail.

The spirit is barreled at 120 proof, which is amongst the lowest in the industry and imparts a smoother taste profile. The oak is a #4 char around the base and a #2 char at the head of the barrel. 46% ABV

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Vitner's Reserve Syrah
Data.Description: This Vintner's Reserve Syrah is richly layered with flavors of plum, jammy blackberry, cola and just the right amount of spice followed by velvety, lingering tannins.

Data.Name: L'Ecole no. 41 Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: With its classic varietal Cabernet profile, this focused wine shows layers of dark fruit, espresso, violet, and herbal notes. Layers of blackberry and cassis mingle with dusty tannins through a persistent finish.

Data.Name: Corazon Del Sol Gran Reserva Malbec
Data.Description:
In the 2015 vintage, only a few barrels were selected from the 7 acres of Estate Malbec in pursuit of producing the finest Malbec in the world.

Planted in the ancient rock covered river beds of Los Sauces, Uco Valley - the 'Revana Vineyard' garners extremely low yields due to the arid climate and extreme terroir.

Nose - violets, red fruit, cassis, black currant

Palate - blackberries, plums, dark chocolate, firm tannins

Data.Name: Captain Morgan Black Spiced Rum
Data.Description:
"Crafted using only the finest Caribbean rum & select spices, Captain Morgan Black Spiced Rum is finished with double charred blackened oak for a taste as bold as the legendary buccaneer. Blackstrap Rum, Rich Clove Spice and Premium Cassia Bark.

Legend has it, the pirates of old stored their high proof rum in charred oak casks in order to give it a smooth mellow taste."

Data.Name: Absolut Oak
Data.Description: Oak by Absolut is a daring spirit born by breaking the rules. Resting on Swedish, French, and American oak, Absolut experiences an unbelievably delicious transformation. From clear to dark, our vodka develops a rich depth and bold character unlike any other.

Data.Name: Ed Hardy Original Sangria
Data.Description:
Produced in Spain and popularized throughout Europe for hundreds of years. Sangria is the first perfect party drink. Mix hundreds of different ways, or just poured over ice, fruity and delicious, Ed Hardy Sangria is everyone's favorite, fashionable party guest. 

This Sangria is a refreshing blend of red wine, citrus fruit flavors, and a special spice extract. Add sliced peaches, apples, and oranges or other fruits for a delicious aperitif.

Data.Name: Ed Hardy White Sangria
Data.Description:
Produced in Spain and popularized throughout Europe for hundreds of years. Sangria is the first perfect party drink. Mix hundreds of different ways, or just poured over ice, fruity and delicious, Ed Hardy Sangria is everyone's favorite, fashionable party guest. 

Ed Hardy White Sangria takes you away to a summer day on the beach in Spain. This Sangria is a blend of white wine, citrus flavors, and spices

Data.Name: Blackstone Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet Sauvignon shows vibrant blackberry and red cherry flavors with notes of cinnamon and toasted nuts.

Data.Name: Seven Deadly Zins Zinfandel
Data.Description: A sinful blend indeed! A vibrant, sweet bouquet of raspberry jam, molasses and cinnamon toast evoke the senses of carefree youthful nights. Excellent oak integration provides silken tannins.

Data.Name: Coppola Chardonnay
Data.Description: Coppola Chardonnay reflects the distinctive personality of Monterey vineyards, which give rise to juicy apple, guava and melon flavors.  Whole-cluster pressing and a combination of barrel and stainless steel fermentation ensures that the creamy texture and caramelized sugar finish is balanced by a crisp acidity.

Data.Name: Dancing Bull Zinfandel
Data.Description: No shortage of flavor here. Blackberry, black cherry and raspberry mix with spicy notes of pepper and vanilla, making Dancing Bull Zinfandel one of the best things to ever happen to barbeque. Originally introduced under the Rancho Zabaco label, this Zin remains a fan favorite for its bold, award-winning style. Pair this smooth, spicy wine with braised pork ribs and burgers, or try it with pasta in a rich tomato sauce.

Data.Name: Dancing Bull Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Crisp, fruity flavors of lime, kiwi, mango and citrus make this wine the perfect wingman for spicy shrimp or grilled seafood. One sip conjures memories of fresh-squeezed lemonade on a hot summer day. Vibrant citrus flavors and a touch of that traditional Sauvignon Blanc grassiness give this wine a crisp, inviting acidity. Stick to pork, chicken or fish with this wine, but throw in some basil or cilantro to match its unique flavors and texture.

Data.Name: Apothic Crush
Data.Description: A decadent red wine blend that combines red fruit flavors with notes of caramel and a velvety, smooth mouth feel.

Data.Name: Bella Sera Moscato
Data.Description: This delectable Bella Sera Moscato has aromas of fresh nectarine and peach, which offer a refreshing touch of sweetness on the palate. The perfect marriage of fruit and crispness makes Moscato a versatile partner for hearty Italian fare and spicy dishes as well as delectable fruit based desserts.

Data.Name: Las Perdices Red Blend
Data.Description: Cold prefermentative fermentation for a week between 6- 8 ºC (43-46 ºF), to highlight the fruity character of this wine. Growth of selected yeasts. Alcoholic fermentation for 10 days, at controlled temperatures between 24-26ºC (79 – 82°F). With 2-3 daily punchdowns and pumpovers at the beginning. Maceration post fermentation for 5 days.

Data.Name: Fetzer Chardonnay
Data.Description:
This attractive pale gold Chardonnay unleashes tropical aromas of pear, apricot, banana and pineapple, with hints of nuts and vanilla. This full-flavored wine delivers a palate of lingering peach and citrus notes, with a touch of toasty spice.

This Chardonnay was harvested at optimal ripeness in late September 2017. It was fermented in stainless steel tanks, with a mix of new French and American oak at different toast levels. The oak portion also completed malolactic fermentation, making the blend extra rich, a little buttery and the perfect amount of toast.

Data.Name: Sterling Merlot
Data.Description: By selecting grapes from various vineyards, Sterling created a comprehensive representation of this world-famous growing region. The cooler sites in the southern end of the Valley encourage fresh, bright fruit aromas. The hillside vineyards add structure and depth and the grapes from “up valley”, where soils are deep and temperatures warm, give dark fruit flavors and long, broad palate.

Data.Name: Sterling Meritage
Data.Description: The Sterling Vintner’s Collection Meritage is a fine blend of some of California’s most intriguing red varietals including Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon, Malbec and Petit Verdot. Sip Sterling Meritage with bold fare and friends, and savor the bright red fruit aromas and vanilla oak spices with notes of black raspberries and dark chocolate.

Data.Name: Sterling Sparkling Rosé
Data.Description: The wine offers upfront fruit flavors, yet is balanced by creamy texture and bright acidity. The effervescence of the wine lends to the crisp, clean finish. The Sparkling Rosé wine is an elegant pale salmon pink color in the glass with a delightfully persistent bead. The fresh aromas of strawberry, cherry blossom, rose petal and crisp apple lead to a lush palate where the aromas ring true.

Data.Name: Camelot Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Camelot Pinot Noir reveals a complex bouquet of strawberry and spiced orange with earthy overtones. Silky smooth on the palate, this delicious, medium to full-bodied Pinot Noir culminates in a nice, lengthy fruit finish.

Data.Name: Tisdale Shiraz
Data.Description:
Tisdale Shiraz offers flavors of black raspberry and pomegranate, complemented by vanilla oak aromas, creating a balanced and distinctive wine.

You're invited to enjoy and share this outstanding wine paired with entrees featuring pasta or grilled meats.

Data.Name: Tisdale White Zinfandel
Data.Description:
Tisdale experienced winemakers have crafted this medium-bodied White Zinfandel to have a brilliant finish with flavors of ripe raspberries, watermelon and fresh strawberries, complemented by sweet raspberry and cherry aromas.

You're invited to enjoy and share this exceptional wine paired with your favorite salad or pasta.

Data.Name: Tisdale Chardonnay
Data.Description:
Tisdale winemakers shaped this Chardonnay to have flavors of pineapple and citrus fruit, complemented by vanilla oak aromas.

You're invited to enjoy and share this exceptional wine paired with your favorite salad, grilled fish and lighter meats.

Data.Name: Tisdale Merlot
Data.Description:
Tisdale Merlot offers a smooth, full-flavored profile with medium body. Flavors of black cherry and mixed berries are complemented by spicy oak aromas creating a balanced and distinctive wine.

You're invited to enjoy and share this outstanding wine paired with your favorite salads, pasta or grilled meats.

Data.Name: Tisdale Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Tisdale winemakers have crafted a full-flavored Cabernet Sauvignon to have a medium body and an impressive finish. Flavors of blackberry and plum are complemented with elegant aromas of vanilla and toasty oak creating a balanced and distinctive wine.

You're invited to enjoy and share this exceptional wine paired with entrees featuring pasta or grilled meats.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Sangria Red
Data.Description: Inspired by the traditional drink of Spain, [yellow tail] Sangria combines premium red wine with a splash of sweet citrus for a party-starter in a bottle! Flavors of lemon, lime, orange. Enjoy in a jug with loads of ice, topped with diced lemon and orange

Data.Name: Black Opal Chardonnay
Data.Description: The Black Opal Chardonnay is bright straw in color. Aromas of peach, melon and citrus develop into a crisp and delicious finish. The palate is soft and round with rich and persistent flavors of a tropical fruit salad.

Data.Name: Allegro Moscato
Data.Description: Allegro Moscato was California’s first Moscato made exclusively from Muscat Canelli, the same noble grape used to produce Italy’s famed Moscato d’Asti. This wine is fresh and fragrant with orange blossom, apricot and peach aromas. Deliciously versatile, Allegro Moscato is refreshing on its own, but also makes a wonderful complement to brunch, desserts, spicy dishes and sweet and tangy sauces.

Data.Name: Oliver Apple Pie Wine
Data.Description: Oliver Apple Pie wine features fresh-pressed, 100% apple wine (no concentrates!). This wine combines the comforting taste of crisp baked apples, with warmth and gentle, sweet brown sugar and nutmeg spice. Add a healthy heap of vanilla 'a la mode.' No forks required for this delicious treat; help yourself. #losethefork

Data.Name: Gazela Vinho Verde
Data.Description: Gazela has a very light yellow citrine color, with a slight fizz that enhances its bouquet, flavors and freshness. Aromatic and engaging, Gazela adds to its citrine and tropical fruit notes a lively and stimulating acidity, very well balanced by a slight touch of sugar. The end product is a simple, versatile and very attractive wine.

Data.Name: Lab Red
Data.Description: From the region near Portugal's capital of Lisbon, Lab Red offers generous red and black fruit with fine-textured tannins. Spicy notes on the finish are contributed by four months ageing in oak. A stylish blend of syrah, cabernet and touriga nacional grape varieties.

Data.Name: Sandara Wine Mojito Cocktail
Data.Description: Sandara wine Mojito fuses the flavour of the Caribbean Mojito with premium Spanish White Wine. Indulge your senses with the lively flavours of fresh mint and lime. The nose displays range of citrus and green apple aromas with refreshing hints of mint. The taste is balanced between its sweetness, fine acidity and elegant fine bubbles.

Data.Name: Schmitt Söhne Riesling
Data.Description: This medium-bodied Riesling has peach and fine apple aromas, a firm and fruity palate and crisp acidity that results in a well-balanced, easy to drink wine.

Data.Name: Relax Pink Rosé
Data.Description:
RELAX Pink Rosé is a fun, fruity Spanish Rosé with fresh aromas of strawberries, raspberries and cherries. It is beautifully balanced with a refreshing crispness and soft, round finish. RELAX Pink Rosé is superb on its own or as a complement to cold salads, cheeses and spicy Indian and Asian dishes.

It’s the perfect wine for a day on the beach or a playful night out with the girls – truly a go-to choice for any occasion.

Data.Name: Don Julio Añejo Tequila
Data.Description: Prized for its enticing layers of flavors and softness as a result of time in oak barrel, Don Julio Añejo is best appreciated when enjoyed neat, over ice or as a mixed cocktail.

Data.Name: Gabbiano Chianti
Data.Description: Ruby red, dark berry aroma, typically sangiovese, dry, medium bodied, fruity flavours, medium tannin, , medium acidity and nice smooth finish.

Data.Name: Gabbiano Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: A pale green to straw with green nuances. the nose is broad with citrus and tropical fruits and some floral hints . The palate is vibrant and fresh with apple fruit notes. Pairing: Recommended on pastas with mushroom sauce, aromatised white meat, roast lamb, or half-mature cheese.

Data.Name: Gekkeikan Black and Gold Sake
Data.Description: This versatile sake has a smooth, mellow flavor and can be enjoyed warmed, room temperature or chilled. Serve from this traditional "tokkuri" container that was used when purchasing sake in the old days.

Data.Name: Glendalough Double Barrel Irish Whiskey
Data.Description:
A new and unique style of light and floral whiskey distilled in a Coffey still (like whiskey, another great Irish invention!) from a mash bill of Irish malted barley and corn. It spends three and a half years in American oak first-fill Bourbon barrels before being finished for six months in Spanish Oloroso sherry casks. 

cherry, raisin, fig (with Christmas pudding notes on the nose for those lucky enough to know what that is) along with floral lemongrass and a touch of nutmeg. The taste is sweet and creamy on the palate, with butterscotch, honey and peppercorn bringing along sweet Bourbon Cask notes with dried fruit returning through notes of maraschino cherries and a pinch of brown sugar. The finish has lingering notes of ginger spices with a faint glimmer of almond to end a complex Irish Whiskey from start to finish.

Data.Name: Glendronach 18 Year Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The GlenDronach 18 years old has been named after the renowned founder of the distillery, James Allardice. This exceptional sherried single malt is non chill filtered and of natural colour. Matured in the finest Spanish Oloroso sherry casks and bottled at 46%, this sublime richly sherried malt is truly unforgettable.

Data.Name: Glendronach 11 Year Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The youngest entry in the 16th batch of Glendronach single casks, this 11 year old whisky has been matured in a PX sherry puncheon and has already picked up a big whack of sherry cask flavour. Distilled on 19 January 2006 and bottled in 2017 from cask #1979.

Data.Name: Glendronach 12 Year Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: A dense, heavily-sherried dram from a distillery now producing again after a six-year layoff. A malt best suited to after-dinner sipping.

Data.Name: Glenfarclas 25 Year Old Scotch Whisk
Data.Description: Smooth, silky texture. Rich aroma of berries, tropical fruits and fruitcake. Notes of hazelnuts, toffee, dried fruits, milk chocolate and espresso on the palate. Finish is rich and everlasting, with hints of cherries, chocolate and nutty smokiness.

Data.Name: Glenfarclas 40 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The 2016 release of Glenfarclas 40 Year Old, presented in a box styled on the distillery's warehouse doors. This is a classic sherried Glenfarclas, with notes of Christmas cake, dark chocolate and orange.

Data.Name: Glenfiddich 15 Year Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Matured to perfection in three different types of oak casks. These are sherry casks, first used to age sherry, traditional bourbon casks from America and new oak casks, coopered from European timber.

Data.Name: Glenfiddich 18 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description:
Fine Spanish Oloroso sherry casks, and American oak mature Glenfiddich 18 Year Old, an intriguingly fruity yet full-bodied single malt. 

Glenfiddich 18 Year Old comes hand numbered and is married in small batches of no more than 150 casks so Malt Master Brian Kinsman can carefully control every element of the whisky’s robust aroma and rich taste.

ABV 43%

Data.Name: Glenfiddich Fire & Cane Scotch Whisky
Data.Description:
Fire & Cane is inspired by the early innovation of Glenfiddich Malt Master Brian Kinsman, who ran peated spirit through the Glenfiddich stills for the first time in 2003, birthing the concept. Fire & Cane boldly marries smoky whisky with non-peated whisky that had been maturing side-by-side in bourbon casks, highlighting Glenfiddich’s sweet and fruity signature style. Taking it a step further, Kinsman finished the married whisky in Latin rum casks, sourced from various South American countries, for three months to produce a surprising and unexpected overlay of flavors with added caramel toffee sweetness.
86 Proof.

Data.Name: Glenfiddich IPA Cask Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The first single malt scotch whisky finished in IPA craft beer casks. A bold and zesty IPA beer imbues the rich oak casks with extra hoppy notes. Results in zesty citrus notes and the subtle tang of fresh hops complimented by carefully hand selected malt whisky.

Data.Name: Glenrothes 1995 Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The Vintage 1995 was the first of the Vintage Expressions specifically laid in cask with the intention of, when mature, bottling as The Glenrothes. The palate is filled with exotic spices is followed by a citrus and fruity richness coated with honeyed butterscotch.

Data.Name: Grey Goose Cherry Noir
Data.Description: Aromas of cherry and a hint of sweet spices. Tart dark fruits and balanced acidity come through on the palate with a creamy mouth feel. Bright, long lingering finish. Very clean. A delicious sipper alone, but its versatility means it also shines with a huge range of ingredients.

Data.Name: Grey Goose Le Citron
Data.Description: This elegantly bright spirit is imbued with essential oils from the world’s finest lemons, including those from the renowned Menton region of France.

Data.Name: Grey Goose L'Orange
Data.Description: Conjured from the natural essence of one kilogram of fresh oranges in each liter, this orange flavored vodka has a light, crisp flavor perfectly mirroring the zest of an orange.

Data.Name: Svedka Citron Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: Always a party pleaser. Fresh lemon and lime flavored vodka.

Data.Name: Svedka Vodka 100 Proof
Data.Description: Smooth, yet bold. Imported from Sweden and distilled five times from Swedish winter wheat.

Data.Name: Black Box Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Stone fruit, fresh peach and floral notes unfold into refreshing citrus flavors and a crisp acidity. Black Box Wines Sauvignon Blanc has herbaceous undertones with a clean, dry finish. 3L box.

Data.Name: Black Box Rosé
Data.Description: Enticing aromas and flavors of fresh strawberry, watermelon and crisp white peach. Black Box Wines Rosé is light, refreshing and suitably fruit-forward, leading to a distinctively dry finish. 3L box.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Reserva Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: 120 Cabernet Sauvignon is a deep and intense violet-red in color. Notes of red and black fruits predominate on the nose with the touch of spice that is typical in Cabernet, plus the aromas of vanilla, cloves, and tobacco that come from the oak. Sweet, elegant, and smooth tannins lend depth to the well-rounded palate and lead to a fresh, fruity, and juicy finish.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Reserva Chardonnay
Data.Description: This wine is a bright golden-yellow in color with fruity aromas of peaches and melon. The palate presents good volume and balanced acidity with medium-high persistence and fruitiness that make this a pleasing, easy-drinking wine.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Reserva Syrah
Data.Description: Intense violet-ruby-red with great depth. Complex yet pleasing aromas of ripe fruits such as plums harmoniously mingled with notes of violet and nuts. The extremely well-balanced palate starts with a sweet attack, develops long, and finishes refreshing and fruity.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Carmenere
Data.Description: A very representative example of Chile’s emblematic variety. Intense and deep ruby-red in color with violet hues. Aroma dominated by assorted red and black fruits such as strawberries, cherries and blueberries with a touch of vanilla, cassis and spices. The palate is powerful, although the silkiness and depth of the tannins make this a friendly wine since it is juicy and long. Very versatile for pairing with a wide range of dishes.

Data.Name: The Beach House Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
A light and refreshing palate teaser, packed with sunny, tropical passion fruit and pineapple. Invigorated by a citrus twang and a lively lemon and lime surge on the dry, frisky finish. Almost any fish or seafood, especially sushi, shrimp, grilled prawns, oysters or mussels in a creamy white wine sauce. 

It’s delicious with roast chicken, smoked turkey salads, macaroni cheese or any other creamy pasta. It’s also a great wine on its own for social sipping.

Data.Name: AVA Grace Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Citrus, floral, refined. This Sauvignon Blanc boasts notes of tropical fruit flavors and balanced acidity. Fresh aromas of grapefruit, gooseberry and melon fill the nose while the rich body leads to a refined finish on the palate.

Data.Name: Starborough Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Bright, approachable and refreshing, Starborough Sauvignon Blanc from Marlborough, New Zealand is like wind-whipped seagrass on a warm summer day. It’s the perfect pairing for a casual catch-up and a quick bite. Touched with hints of fresh guava, sweet kiwi, zesty citrus, and tropical passion fruit.

Data.Name: La Playa Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: A delicate pale gold. On the nose, aromas of lemon, fresh pineapple with hints of lavender. It is a bright well balanced wine with a clean minerality on the finish.

Data.Name: Harbor Town Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Straw green color. Fruity, savory, smoky aromas and flavors of green and jalapeño peppers, reduced grapefruit, and match with a satiny, dry-yet-fruity medium body and a seamless, cheery finish with notes of lettuce and grass with no oak flavor. A tart, smoky sauvignon blanc for the table.

Data.Name: Oyster Bay Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: The wine that started it all. The first Oyster Bay. Which happened to win the best Sauvignon Blanc in the world. Its brilliant clarity, extraordinary aromatic flavors and refreshing zest are both thrilling and enthralling. Flavors that are uniquely Marlborough, and undeniably Oyster Bay.

Data.Name: Frontera Moscato
Data.Description: The wine is a bright yellow color with golden notes. On the nose, fresh fruit and floral perfume aromas are complimented by hints of honey. Fresh, lightly sweet on the palate with slight acidity with good persistence.

Data.Name: Rosé All Day Rosé
Data.Description: The Languedoc-Roussillon region of France was chosen for Rosé All Day because of the area’s increased focus on quality. It shares many of the terrain and climate characteristics with the neighboring regions of Southern Rhone and Provence, however this region offers far greater value.

Data.Name: Trapiche Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Slight ruby in color with fruity aromas of plums and cherries. Smooth and light, this Pinot Noir offers freshness with a velvety texture.

Data.Name: Alamos Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Alamos Cabernet Sauvignon expresses the deep, rich dark berry fruit notes that are classic hallmarks of the variety, complemented nicely by slight herbal characteristics. Firm tannins and oak aging merge to add complex layers of vanilla, clove and black pepper to the Cabernet wine. Because of the intensity of the sun and the dramatic cool temperature shifts at night, both qualities that come from high elevation vineyards, Cabernet Sauvignon grapes develop thicker skins with wonderfully concentrated aromas and riper, softer tannins. High-elevation Alamos Cabernet is flavorful and powerful while remaining elegant and round with an appealingly light, velvety-smooth mouthfeel, which sets our Argentine wine varietals apart from other new world wine regions.

Data.Name: Alamos Chardonnay
Data.Description:
With high elevation vineyards, Alamos Chardonnay vines experience intense sunlight days and very cool and crisp nights, a sizeable temperature shift that preserves the fruit’s incredible acidity while still giving full, ripe flavors. The result is a lush, complex, food-friendly Chardonnay that features tropical and citrus notes and a refreshing palate, with added weight from partial malolactic fermentation and subtle oak aging. Its balance of richness and acidity is one of Argentina’s unique hallmarks, a product of our adventurous winegrowing locations.

Alamos Argentinian Chardonnay offers layered aromas of tropical fruit, apple, vanilla and citrus blossom. On the full and round palate, flavors of pear, pineapple and fig are balanced by attractive notes of caramel, toast and sweet brown spice. A lingering finish is accented by clean acidity and citrus zest.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Beautiful aromas of Oro Blanco grapefruit, orange blossom, and Kaffir Lime rise from the glass, then follow on the palette where layers of ripe mango, gooseberry and white peaches join in. The beautifully balanced fruit and acidity leave the finish clean and crisp with citrus and floral notes still lingering and begging for another sip.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Expressive notes of raspberry, pomegranate, and cranberry, are supported by dried tea leaf and tobacco on the nose. The palate is layered texturally and has rich, pronounced blackberries and ripe plum. Soft, fine-grained tannins and smoky, dark chocolate linger through the finish.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Rosé of Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Layer Cake Rosé is perfectly pale pink and reminiscent of rose gold liquefied in the glass. Aromas of passion fruit, pink grapefruit and dried rose petals mingle with the slightest hint of dark chocolate and cranberry. On the palate, tropical flavors of guava and crushed loquat harmonize with field-ripened strawberries, picked fresh for the farmers market. The vibrant acidity is layered with pink grapefruit zest, rhubarb and pineapple that culminates in a bone dry, refreshing finish.

Data.Name: Las Perdices Malbec
Data.Description: Intense purple red color. Complex berry aromas with delicate oak touches. Soft in mouth, balanced, plum and cherry notes. Ideal to serve with red meat, pasta, fish and white meat with spiced sauces.

Data.Name: Los Cardos Malbec
Data.Description: Intense purplish red color. Sweet, spicy and intense aromas, with notes of red fruits and herbs (such as Herbes de Provence). In the mouth, this wine is soft, velvety, fresh, and well balanced.

Data.Name: Capriccio Sparkling Sangria
Data.Description: Capriccio Sparkling Sangria is made from an excellent recipe with premium grape wine, real fruit juices (pineapple, orange and grape) and 100% natural fruit flavors such as pomegranate. It has no preservatives, and it is the only sangria on the market with carbonation. It's bursting with fruits and bubbles!

Data.Name: Ed Hardy Original Sangria Box
Data.Description:
Produced in Spain and popularized throughout Europe for hundreds of years. Sangria is the first perfect party drink. Mix hundreds of different ways, or just poured over ice, fruity and delicious, Ed Hardy Sangria is everyone's favorite, fashionable party guest. 


This Sangria is a refreshing blend of red wine, citrus fruit flavors, and a special spice extract. Add sliced peaches, apples, and oranges or other fruits for a delicious aperitif.

Data.Name: Ed Hardy White Sangria Box
Data.Description:
Produced in Spain and popularized throughout Europe for hundreds of years. Sangria is the first perfect party drink. Mix hundreds of different ways, or just poured over ice, fruity and delicious, Ed Hardy Sangria is everyone's favorite, fashionable party guest. 

Ed Hardy White Sangria takes you away to a summer day on the beach in Spain. This Sangria is a blend of white wine, citrus flavors, and spices.

Data.Name: DaVinci Chianti
Data.Description: DaVinci Chianti is a well-balanced wine of medium weight with jammy flavors of ripe plums, cherries and red fruit. It has a deep crimson color and is a lively wine with a soft mineral finish and round tannins that linger in long, peppery finish. This wine pairs perfectly with all starters, pastas and meat dishes and is best when served slightly below room temperature (64°F).

Data.Name: Santa Margherita Pinot Grigio
Data.Description:
Santa Margherita pioneered the modern winemaking methods of Pinot Grigio and are proud to be known as a benchmark of quality and innovation for the category. In 1960, the winemaker was inspired by traditional sparkling wine vinification techniques to ferment this wine without skin contact. Driven to capture the delicate fruit and floral notes in this wine, they realized that by moving away from the then-standard “Ramato” method, these precious aromas and flavors could be preserved as they were meant to be tasted. 

Let the clean, dry, and versatile Pinot Grigio that inspired an entire generation of Italian white wines inspire your next picnic, dinner party, or spontaneous get-together.

Data.Name: Ecco Domani Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Ecco Domani embodies the stylish, contemporary side of Northern Italy, resulting in one of the best Italian wines around. Go ahead. Make a bold statement. Because good taste is always in style.

Data.Name: Primo Amore Moscato
Data.Description: This refreshing and fruit Moscato wine comes from the warm Southern vineyards of Puglia. Primo Amore, or first love expreses the joy of discovery experienced when a wine drinker first encounters the sweetness amd enticing fragrance of the delicate wine.

Data.Name: Grillo Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: A dry, easy-drinking Sicilian white with a floral aroma and flavors of citrus, apple, pear, vanilla and almonds.

Data.Name: Roscato Rosso Bianco Dolce
Data.Description: Roscato offers a perfect complement to any cuisine. Roscato Bianco is an irresistible, delicately sweet, frizzante wine from the northern Italian region of Lombardy. Made from a blend of Moscato and Chardonnay, Roscato Bianco makes a wonderful aperitif and is also incredibly food-friendly. It seamlessly combines a long-held grape growing tradition with the flair of modern winemaking techniques and style. The result is a wine of enticing character that perfectly meets the surging demand for sweet, slightly sparkling wines. With a low alcohol of 8% and a touch of sparkle to flawlessly balance the sweetness, Roscato Bianco is the ideal complement for today's cuisine. Enjoy it with white meats, classic Italian dishes, spicy foods and more.

Data.Name: El Tesoro Añejo
Data.Description: Remarkably balanced in flavor, this is considered to be one of the better sipping tequilas out there. Mexican law requires Añejo ("year") tequila to age for at least one year, but this Añejo is aged two to three years in oak barrels for that extra smoothness.

Data.Name: El Tesoro Blanco
Data.Description: "Clear with a platinum cast. Layered, complex aromas of olive, cheese rind, herbs, and roasted pepper follow through on a rich, silky entry to a dryish medium-to-full body with fantastic depth and balance. Finishes with a very long, delicately spice dried tropical fruit, cherry, and pepper fade. A wonderful blanco that shines on its own and will transform cocktails."

Data.Name: El Tesoro Reposado
Data.Description: "Pale golden straw color. Robust aromas of dill pickled peppers, hard cheese rind, olive, dates, and suede with a silky dry-yet-fruity medium body and long, sweet potato, polenta and peppery spice flourish. A superb reposado to enjoy on its own or to elevate cocktails."

Data.Name: Veuve Clicquot Silver Label
Data.Description:
Veuve Clicquot Rich is an innovation on the house's signature blend and features both a higher dosage as well as a greater presence of Meunier which emphasizes the fresh, fruity and gourmand notes.

Veuve Clicquot Rich is the first champagne inspired by mixology. Veuve Clicquot Rich is best enjoyed over ice with fresh ingredients, including grapefruit, cucumber and even pepper.

Data.Name: Riunite Rosato
Data.Description: Produced from soft pressing selected grapes and then refermenting, our Riunite Rosato has a light, fruity bouquet, and a fresh, sweet taste. It's a soft and delicious wine that pairs well with any variety of foods.

Data.Name: Riunite Moscato
Data.Description: Fruity with the haunting fragrance and flavor of the seductive Moscato grape. The taste of this moscato is soft, lively and sweet.

Data.Name: Riunite Lambrusco
Data.Description:
Color: Lively red with violet reflections. 
Bouquet: Fruity, soft and harmonious. Taste: Light, well-balanced. 
Pairings: Riunite Lambrusco is perfect for every occasion. Enjoyable and straight forward, its easy drinkability make it a favorite with a wide variety of foods, including spicy fare.

Data.Name: Arbor Mist Mixed Berry Pinot Noir
Data.Description: A tasty blend of blueberry, ripe raspberries and peach flavors is added to Pinot Noir to create one perfectly refreshing flavor. Go ahead, mix it up! Just be sure it's nice and cold.

Data.Name: Beringer White Zinfandel Moscato
Data.Description: Distinctive raspberry perfume with lychee, tropical fruit and enticing floral notes. This wine has mouthwatering fruit flavors with a moderately sweet palate. Beringer White Zinfandel Moscato is a relatively full-bodied wine with a refreshing finish.

Data.Name: The Dreaming Tree Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Bright ruby in color with ripe flavors and aromas of cherry, wild strawberry, vanilla, and caramel.

Data.Name: Estancia Pinot Grigio
Data.Description:
Estancia Pinot Grigio is grown in select California vineyards, where chilly ocean breezes produce grapes with balanced taste and concentrated flavors.

APPEARANCE
Pale straw with a slightly golden tint

AROMA
Pear, green apple, figs, and honeysuckle

FLAVOR
Lively, zesty, and refreshing flavors of green apple, Asian pear, lemon-citrus with a soft mid-palate and notes of grapefruit on the finish

PAIRINGS
Smoked salmon, tuna, citrus sauces, seafood, poultry, pork

Data.Name: Cupcake Red Velvet
Data.Description: Experience a wine as rich, soft and elegant as red velvet. Cupcake Red Velvet blend delivers over-the-top aromas of chocolate, deep dark blackberries and luscious red fruits that follow through to the palate. Finish with a hint of coconut and creamy mocha that shows unmistakable intensity and length. Red Velvet combines Zinfandel, Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon and Petite Sirah. Each varietal adds distinct characteristics and lends structure, aroma and depth of flavor. We ferment each varietal separately before blending. Finally, a unique oak regime infuses creaminess.

Data.Name: Cupcake Petite Sirah
Data.Description: Cupcake Petite Sirah is crafted with grapes from some of the coolest climate Central Coast areas, making for a plush, full-bodied wine. Bursting with flavors of blackberry, dark cherry and vanilla bean, this wine is anything but petite. Enjoy with Portobello penne pasta or backyard barbeques.

Data.Name: Motto Backbone Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Sometimes all you want is a really good, uncomplicated, reasonably priced red. Meet Motto Cabernet.  This bold fruit-forward Cab has a lot going on for the price with ripe blackberry, roasted coffee and a hint of wood smoke.  Pair it up with your favorite burger!

Data.Name: Milagro Añejo
Data.Description:
Triple-distilled. Aged 18 months. Smooth and refined. Notes of caramel, coconut, chocolate, tobacco and banana. Sweet yet spicy finish. 
40% ABV

Data.Name: Medlock Ames Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This Sauvignon Blanc is a stunner, offering a balance of power and finesse that really highlights our unique location. It shows up-front aromas of orange blossom, grapefruit, and honeysuckle with a hint of star anise. On the palate, flavors of stone fruit, apricot, and lemon custard predominate. The wine takes its time to come to a long finish with tangerine, lemon zest, and key lime notes that seamlessly wrap together with a touch of minerality. The overall effect is creamy with a harmonious balance of acidity and structure.

Data.Name: Medea Vodka
Data.Description:
Medea’s patented LED technology allows the user to program the bottle with a personalized message. The first response the Medea bottle evokes is “Wow!”  As the world’s first personally programmable bottle, it is the perfect gift for any occasion. Give a gift of Medea Vodka and watch someone’s face light up!

This exceptionally clean vodka boasts enticing aromas of lemongrass, apple, and cream. With a full body and a rich texture, the palate delights with complex hints of orange zest, white pepper, and beeswax. The finish is incredibly smooth, displaying a subtle vanilla sweetness.

Data.Name: McWilliam's Hanwood Estate Shiraz
Data.Description: A vibrant crimson colored Shiraz with fragrant pepper and black cherry, licorice and plum fruit flavors combining with spicy, coffee bean characters derived from oak. The sweet berry fruit flavors are supported by a fine and balanced structure.

Data.Name: Chopin Potato Vodka
Data.Description: Subtle aromas of powdered potatoes, toasted Brazil nuts, and vanilla yogurt with a silky, off-dry light to medium body and a sweet whipped cream, nougat, and mossy riverstone accented finish. 93pt Beverage Testing Institute 2011.

Data.Name: Ipswich 1620
Data.Description:
Hazy with a rainbow of hop aromas and flavors, this NEIPA features Mosaic, Citra, Amarillo, and Idaho7 hops, with a full body that is sure to please.

ABV: 6.3%

Data.Name: Founders KBS
Data.Description: "What we've got here is an imperial stout brewed with a massive amount of coffee and chocolates, then cave-aged in oak bourbon barrels for an entire year to make sure wonderful bourbon undertones come through in the finish. Makes your taste buds squeal with delight."

Data.Name: Beck's Blue Non-Alcoholic
Data.Description: Beck's Blue is a non-Alcoholic, Euro Pale Lager that pours a clear pale yellow. It has a mildly sweet, malty aroma with hints of bitter hops, grain, and yeast. A grainy, slightly bitter taste with hints of rice, grass, and just a touch of caramel malts.

Data.Name: Wormtown Brewery Be Hoppy
Data.Description: Reddish-gold hazy unfiltered brew; Pungent aroma of citrus, floral spice, and grapefruit; Decidedly bitter palate with a medium light body; Flavors of hoppy grapefruit give way to a dry finish; Wormtown's Hop Back and Double Dry Hop process ensures that aromatics are in your face coupled with an obscene amount of kettle hops that should make all bitter beer fans and hop heads swoon.

Data.Name: Amstel Light Cans
Data.Description: 3.5% ABV. The recipe's grown out of a 140 year old tradition. Amstel Light beer is a lager beer with less calories, a refreshing taste and a mild bitterness.

Data.Name: Allagash White 16oz Cans
Data.Description:
Allagash White, the classic Belgian witbier (wheat beer), gets an American spin with this lightly golden and inviting brew. The nose is fruity and floral, yet it also comes off as warm and spicy. The taste is a delightful treat: heavy wheat mixed with banana, coriander, hay, honey, lemon zest, and pepper. The finish is rather dry, but it keeps that flavorful mouthfeel right to the mellow, creamy end. 

Some newcomers to the witbier approach may be shocked at the cloudiness of this beer, but the suspended yeast means that this beer is true to its parent style. Compared to most Belgians, Allagash White has a low alcohol percentage. Serve in a chilled tulip-style glass.

Data.Name: 1911 Original Hard Cider
Data.Description: Enjoy the crisp, refreshing light taste of Original 1911 Hard Cider. 1911's unique fermentation process creates a clean cider that has a subtle hint of fresh apples with citrus overtones. This is the flavor that started it all.

Data.Name: Midnight Moon Moonshine Blueberry
Data.Description: When life gives you blueberries, throw 'em in a jar of 'shine to soak. Midnight Moon Blueberry is hand-filled with delicious blueberries so the flavor and color can infuse with the 100 proof (50% ALC./VOL.) Midnight Moon. As the spirit ages, the flavor intensifies for a sweeter side of the Moon.

Data.Name: Midnight Moon Moonshine Apple Pie
Data.Description: Moonshine and apple pie - it doesn't get more American than this. Midnight Moon Apple Pie is a mix of Midnight Moon, apple juice and a cinnamon stick. As these ingredients blend and age, they create a 70 proof (35% ALC./VOL.) spirit that tastes just like homemade apple pie. No fork necessary.

Data.Name: Firefly Moonshine Peach
Data.Description: Firefly Peach Moonshine is a neutral grain spirit naturally flavored with peaches and bottled at 60.9 proof.

Data.Name: Firefly Moonshine White Lightning
Data.Description: Firefly Moonshine is 100.7 proof – just the right number to release the true flavor of raw corn whiskey.

Data.Name: Glenfiddich 12 Year Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Glenfiddich 12 is carefully matured in the finest American bourbon and Spanish sherry oak casks for at least 12 years. Married and mellowed in oak, results in complete harmony of aroma and flavor. A single malt Scotch whisky with distinctive fresh pear, creamy with subtle oak flavours and a long smooth and mellow finish.

Data.Name: Berkshire Mountain Ice Glen Vodka
Data.Description: "Clear. Mild honeydew and cream aromas. A supple entry leads to a dryish medium body with hints of eucalyptus honey. Finishes with a peppery, light minty fade. Excellent." -Beverage Tasting Institute

Data.Name: Berkshire Mountain Greylock Gin
Data.Description:
"Light, subtle and complex, dominated by classic flavors of juniper, citrus and coriander." The New York Times Tasting Report, Best Value

Berkshire Mountain Distillers' Greylock Gin is hand crafted in small batches at the Berkshire's first legal distillery since prohibition. Our proprietary blend of botanicals, packed into a gin head suspended over a pot still, infuses the distillate with its unique essence. We use this time honored and labor intensive method to bring you a London dry style gin of exceptional quality.

Data.Name: Graham's 10 Year Old Tawny Port
Data.Description: A younger tawny port from Graham's, aged for 10 years and balancing the direct sweetness of a younger wine with some of the richer flavours that develop with age.

Data.Name: Graham's Six Grapes Port
Data.Description: Dark red in color, with a seductive rich perfume of ripe plums and cherries. On the palate, complex, with good structure and a long lingering finish. Best served at the end of the meal, for example with rich, nutty or chocolate desserts, as well as strong cheeses.

Data.Name: Gnarly Head Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Aromas of bright citrus and nectarine bursting with crisp flavors of honeydew melon and green Granny Smith apple.

Data.Name: Gnarly Head Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Beautifully balanced with bright cherry and raspberry fruit flavors followed by hints of spice on the finish. Bright fruit and gentle tannins.

Data.Name: Gnarly Head Old Vine Zinfandel
Data.Description: Rich, dark berry flavors with layers of spice, plum, pepper and vanilla.

Data.Name: Glenlivet Founder's Reserve
Data.Description: Founder's Reserve skillful selection of casks enhances the signature fruity flavors of Glenlivet. Traditional oak casks complemented by selective use of American first-fill casks to give a hint of creamy sweetness for an exceptionally well-balanced and smooth malt.

Data.Name: Gemma di Luna Pinot Grigio
Data.Description:
Gemma di Luna Pinot Grigio DOC is a fresh, friendly wine crafted from premium grapes grown in Italy’s Delle Venezie. Fruity aromas of white peach and mango taffy meet elegantly plush fruit flavors that culminate in a smooth, medium-length sweet yogurt, lime zest and underripe strawberry finish with soft, fruit tannins and no oak. 

ABV: 12%

Data.Name: Christian Brothers Honey Brandy
Data.Description: Smooth Christian Brothers Brandy blended with rich honey to create this delicious liqueur! Distinctive grape, vanilla and caramel flavors from the Brandy, infused with pure honey and an added hint of orange peel to make for a perfect combination.

Data.Name: Burnett's Whipped Cream Vodka
Data.Description: Burnett's vodkas are quadruple distilled and triple charcoal filtered to remove impurities created by the distillation process. It is no suprise that the flavored vodka collection has been hailed as more expensive than its pricetag would suggest. Flavors are robust without the over-sweetened qualities of schnapps and flavored rums. But watch out, at 70 proof they also carry more of a wallop.

Data.Name: Bota Box Shiraz
Data.Description: 3 Liters. Bota Box Shiraz is a medium bodied, succulent wine offering complex aromas of blackberry, plum and white pepper.  On the palate, the wine forms a soft, supple mouth feel, bursting with blueberry jam and cherry.

Data.Name: Smuttynose Whole Lotta Lupulin
Data.Description:
Brewed with a "rock-and-roll" combination of Citra, Amarillo, and Simcoe. Anchored by a sturdy malt foundation - this beer drinks dangerously easier than the ABV may suggest!

8.6% ABV

Data.Name: Smuttynose Old Brown Dog
Data.Description:
Old Brown Dog has been cited as a classic example of the “American Brown Ale” style of beer. Compared to a typical English Brown Ale, Old Brown Dog is fuller-bodied and more strongly hopped.
6.7% ABV

Data.Name: Smuttynose Mysterious Haze
Data.Description: Smuttynose Mysterious Haze 6/4 from Smuttynose Brewing Company is an New England IPA style beer, medium in color, is moderate hoppy, has an ABV of 6.7% and is available to be delivered from your pal Tapster!

Data.Name: Smuttynose Finestkind IPA
Data.Description: Light golden in color, this IPA’s citrusy hop flavor is pleasantly balanced by a smooth bitterness, light body, and crisp finish. The FinestKind IPA is dry-hopped and unfiltered, and the result is an award-winning brew, year after year.

Data.Name: Woodchuck Granny Smith Hard Cider
Data.Description: Granny Smith is a tart green apple cider. Crafted with Granny Smith apples, tree-ripened in the Yakima Valley of Washington. This varietal cider is pale in color with a tart and crisp taste that finishes dry and tangy.

Data.Name: Woodchuck Amber Draft Cider
Data.Description: Woodchuck Amber is the original Woodchuck Cider. It's made from a blend of apples and fermented with champagne yeast to produce a great tasting and refreshing alcoholic drink.

Data.Name: Twisted Tea Hard Iced Tea Raspberry
Data.Description:
Twisted Tea Raspberry blends the smooth, refreshing taste of Southern iced tea with a splash of raspberry flavor. The fruity aroma and smooth taste will make any day feel like summer.
Twisted Tea is real tea blended with smooth, triple-filtered alcohol for an authentic Southern-style iced tea taste. The perfectly balanced blend of alcohol and tea create a refreshing, smooth beverage that’s just a little twisted. Created in 2001, Twisted Tea beverages are the perfect drink for any occasion, from a day at the beach to backyard BBQs.

Data.Name: Twisted Tea Hard Iced Tea Half & Half
Data.Description: Twisted Tea Half & Half is real iced tea with lemonade flavor that’s blended with smooth, triple-filtered alcohol, resulting in an authentic Southern-style iced tea taste.
