Data.Description: Features an unbelievable balance of flavor and refreshment with 0 grams of sugar, 90 calories, 4.5% ABV and gluten free. Inspired by the French word “Bon Vivant” meaning one who lives well, who has refined taste and enjoy’s life’s luxuries.

Data.Name: Bon & Viv Spiked Seltzer Cranberry
Data.Description: Introducing BON & VIV Spiked Seltzer, a unique combination of bright and refreshing taste and great nutritional claims - 0 grams of sugar and 90 calories per 12 oz can and 0 grams of sugar and 120 calories per 16 oz can.

Data.Name: Bon & Viv Spiked Seltzer Black Cherry Rosemary
Data.Description: Introducing BON & VIV Spiked Seltzer, a unique combination of bright and refreshing taste and great nutritional claims - 0 grams of sugar and 90 calories per 12 oz can and 0 grams of sugar and 120 calories per 16 oz can.

Data.Name: Bon & Viv Spiked Seltzer Lemon Lime
Data.Description: Features an unbelievable balance of flavor and refreshment with 0 grams of sugar, 90 calories, 4.5% ABV and gluten free. Inspired by the French word “Bon Vivant” meaning one who lives well, who has refined taste and enjoy’s life’s luxuries.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Spiked Sparkling Seltzer Piña Colada
Data.Description: The first seltzer flavor of its kind, this premium spiked seltzer has natural Piña Colada flavors with only 90 calories, 0 carbs and 0 sugar.

Data.Name: Itaipava Malzbier
Data.Description:
Cervejaria Petrópolis is a Brazilian brewery (cervejaria) company headquartered in Petrópolis. The company has 6 industrial plants located in Petrópolis, Boituva, Teresópolis, Rondonópolis, Alagoinhas and Itapissuma, and operates in Brazil, Germany and Paraguay.
Produced with 100% selected ingredients, 100% crystalline water and respecting the right time, Itaipava is a clear beer, light, tasty and refreshing.

Data.Name: Itaipava Premium
Data.Description: Itaipava Premium is a differentiated, heartier beer made with selected malt and hop imported from Europe. It is part of the Itaipava range of beers that also include Pilsner, Malzbier, Chopp, and Zero Alcohol varieties.

Data.Name: Hard Frescos Guava Citrus
Data.Description: Mother Nature’s Tropical Superfruit. A blend of citrus and real pink guava are added into every batch for a flavor that’s bold and colorful. There’s a reason this is our flagship hard agua fresca – its crisp, fruity, and damn-near perfect.

Data.Name: Hard Frescos Cucumber Lime
Data.Description: We have a crush on cucumber. And lime. So we crushed up that cucumber and blended it with the lime (along with other citrus fruits) for a hard agua fresca that makes for the ultimate refreshment.

Data.Name: Lord Hobo Glorious Pineapple IPA
Data.Description:
Take a sip and experience a liquid vacation. This tropical, fruit soaked beer was born from the daydreams of basking in the sun on porches, patios and beaches. Each sip transports you to the sweetness of summer, with refreshing hints of pineapple and the familiar taste of New England's IPA, GLORIOUS.

6.5% ABV

Data.Name: Bag of Ice
Data.Description: Well well well... would ya looky there. It's your run-of-the-mill bag of ice!

Data.Name: Ruffino Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Full aroma of sweet fruits with a faint lemon/lime which all carry over to its taste. I served this wine with a mild Indian Korma chicken curry, a mild creamy curry enhanced with raisins, almonds and coconut milk.

Data.Name: Banrock Station Shiraz
Data.Description:
The Banrock Station Shiraz exhibits intense blackberry and mulberry fruit over coffee and oak aromas with a hint of clove and cinnamon. This wine displays good fruit weight supported by a rounded tannin structure. A wine rich in fruit with savory tannins and a lingering blackberry finish.

Enjoy served with a creamy mushroom pasta or steak.

Data.Name: 19 Crimes Shiraz
Data.Description: This full and round bright-red wine with crimson hues give way to a subtle sweetness on the palate. The criminally intense vanilla aromatics are balanced with ripe raspberry and plum fruits. The vanilla aromatics carry through on the palate and complement subtle flavors of raspberries, dark plums and chocolate. Red berry fruit and plush tannins provide a lingering finish perfect for any evening.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Pinot Noir
Data.Description: We’ll make you feel like a real star. First, we’ll seduce you with our pretty violet aromas, leading to a symphony of juicy Bing cherry flavors and hints of toast on the palate. Then we’ll wrap you in our soft loving embrace, which feels so real you’ll smile, and know that our love is a deep passionate one for life.

Data.Name: Cupcake Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Escape to Italy with our Pinot Grigio sourced from Trentino. Full and complex, this wine has a nose that hints of pineapple, pears and sweet lemons. Tropical fruits are integrated with the zest of citrus fruits and give way to a creamy mid-palate. We achieved depth and complexity through a combination of winemaking methods. First, grapes were hand-picked, de-stemmed and crushed prior to undergoing cool fermentation in steel tanks and an extended maceration. A small portion of the wine was made with the traditional passito method: we dried harvested grapes on straw mats for several weeks, then gently pressed and fermented them before blending. Tapster loves and delivers this tasty Pinot!

Data.Name: AVA Grace Chardonnay
Data.Description: AVA Grace celebrates the delicate beauty and rich terrain of the vineyard where sunshine, soil and flavors abound. This Chardonnay shines with bright fruit flavors of white peach, apple and lemon which fold into a smooth, rich finish.

Data.Name: AVA Grace Rose
Data.Description: AVA Grace Rose is delicate and soft bursting with aromas of red berries and stone fruit. The palate is filled with raspberry, citrus and apricot that leads into a balanced, dry finish.

Data.Name: AVA Grace Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Straw color. Aromas and flavors of struck match, pear, and green apple with a soft, vibrant, dryish light body and a sleek, swift finish revealing accents of lime candies and creme fraiche with no oak flavor. A solid go-to pinot grigio for party-pleasing.

Data.Name: Barefoot Rose
Data.Description: A savory and scrumptious rosé from the classic wine brand, Barefoot. Kick your feet up, take a sip, and enjoy!

Data.Name: Chateau Ste Michelle Riesling
Data.Description: Inviting and easy to drink with flavors of white peach, apricot, pear and zesty grapefruit. This is a classic Columbia Valley Riesling that is versatile, charming and fun to drink.

Data.Name: Noblio Icon Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: "...Aromas of white tea, pear, and grapefruit are charming in this full-bodied wine. With a palate of pineapple and mango seasoned with oregano, a certain nobility arises in this white as minerality graces the palate on a long finish."

Data.Name: Awaken Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Awaken your senses with this crisp and refreshing New Zealand Sauvignon Blanc. e palate is powerful and fruity with notes of citrus, grapefruit, tomato leaves, and lime. Refreshing acidity and excellent mid palate weight. Your new favorite Sauvignon Blanc!

Data.Name: Ballast Point Lager
Data.Description:
Ballast Point Lager is the quintessential cooler beer for lively adventures or leisurely days. At only 99 calories, this incredibly bright lager still packs a ton of flavor. Brewed with 100% 2-Row barley and a light touch of Apollo hops, Ballast Point lager is a refreshing choice for any occasion. Whether you’re docked or at sea, it’s the perfect companion for whatever destination lies ahead.

ABV: 4.2%

Data.Name: Ballast Point Bonito Blonde Ale
Data.Description:
Bonito blonde ale is inspired by perma-sunny days. This brew draws you in with its golden color and soft malt character, while the light mouthfeel and dry finish keeps you coming back. And what would set a San Diego blonde apart? A subtle hint of hops, naturally.

ABV: 4.5%

Data.Name: 21st Amendment Variety Pack
Data.Description: 21st Amendment's variety 15pk gives you 3 extra reasons to celebrate with each pack! This 15pk contains 5 of our favorite beers and will feature new beers throughout the year, including seasonals and exclusives!

Data.Name: 21st Amendment A Terrible Idea
Data.Description:
21st Amendment brings you A Terrible Idea, a hop-forward, Hazy IPA in a can. Discover malt clouds supporting silky yeast with a creamy mouthfeel, then brace yourself for a MAMMOTH dry hop charge — 4 pounds of hops per barrel to be exact — which is twice their typical rate.

Was inventing a triangle wheel a terrible idea? Ok yes, maybe so. Was making this beer? Absolutely not. 21st Amendment stands behind the claim that the strong hop flavors and aromas, coupled with juicy notes of peach, orange, mango and pineapple will spark your taste buds back from extinction.

ABV: 6.8%

Data.Name: Stella Artois Cidre
Data.Description: Welcome to Cidre season, when winter blankets are packed away and picnic blankets lay down to play. Add a splash of spontaneity to your repertoire, and raise a glass to it all coming together just so. As golden afternoons unfold, savor the taste of Stella Artois Cidre, a bubbly cider described as such. Pairs a soft, apple-y sweetness with a crisp dryness. As bubbly as the personalities on your blanket. The perfect partner for any alfresco gathering.

Data.Name: Mike's Harder Lemonade
Data.Description:
The original Don. Head of the flavor fam. The taste of tart lemons and just the right amount of carbonation makes it extremely refreshing.

ABV: 8%

Data.Name: Leroux Peach Schnapps
Data.Description: A low alcohol liqueur with sweet natural peach flavor.

Data.Name: Corona Familiar
Data.Description:
The best beers are made to be shared. That’s why Corona Familiar embraces the bright, crisp taste Corona is known for with a slightly fuller flavor, higher ABV, and shareable 32oz packaging. With strong ties to authenticity and heritage, Corona Familiar is best served in small gatherings with close friends and family, using the tradition of sharing to create meaningful experiences.

ABV: 4.8%

Data.Name: Admiral Nelson's Rum Spiced 101 Proof
Data.Description:
Admiral Nelson’s Premium Spiced Rum 101 boasts the same award winning flavor as the original, but with a higher proof that adds to the spice experience. This gold rum is smooth, bold and Admiral Nelson’s 101 Proof Spiced Rum is carefully blended with savory spices, mixing perfectly as a ready base for any rum cocktail.

Serving Suggestions: As a shot, over ice or in a variety of mixed drinks and cocktails, including a rum and coke.

Data.Name: Malibu Pineapple Rum
Data.Description: Take delight in the laid-back spirit of the Caribbean with new Malibu Pineapple Rum. We recommend trying it over ice with just a dash of lemon lime soda.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider The Dirty Mayor
Data.Description: Citizen Cider offers this cider to the honorable and fully infamous mayor of the only non-town in America, Fort Ethan Allen, USA. The mayor likes his cider with a ginger nip, so in Citizen CIder's current effort to ensure local harmony and diplomacy we offer this cider up to the mayor and his fellow citizens. No added sugar, never from concentrate. Pair with fried chicken, Thai cuisine, pan-seared seabass, vegetable Phó.

Data.Name: Straw-Ber-Rita
Data.Description:
Sweet, it’s Straw-Ber-Rita®! This tasty margarita is red not just because strawberries are red, but also because red is the color of love…and you’ll love this strawberry sweetness flavor. #HAVEARITA

ABV: 8%

Data.Name: Grape-A-Rita
Data.Description:
straight up more flavor with Grape-A-Rita®! Juicy grape flavor combined with a classic margarita for GRAPE taste. You will be GRAPEful. #HAVEARITA

ABV: 8%

Data.Name: Blue Moon White IPA
Data.Description:
A pronounced citrus and fruity hop taste, perfectly balanced by wheat, coriander, and orange peel.

Bold, flavorful seafood dishes, spicy Mexican food, and strong cheeses such as sharp cheddar and blue cheese.

ABV: 5.9%

Data.Name: Blue Moon Summer Honey Wheat
Data.Description:
A filtered beer crafted with clover honey balanced by a hint of citrus. Pair with grilled summer fare such as marinated chicken or pork with honey mustard sauce.

ABV: 5.2%

Data.Name: Bass Pale Ale
Data.Description:
"England and New York- English Pale Ale- Bass has an accessible yet distinctive taste: malty with hints of toffee and mild hoppy flavors. It is brewed with a selection of the finest English malts, aromatic hops, and water rich in essential salts and minerals." Totalwine.com

ABV: 5%

Data.Name: Angry Orchard Rosé Cider
Data.Description: Angry Orchard Rosé Cider is made with rare, red flesh apples from France. Each apple is crisp, juicy and red to the core, adding an irresistible rosy blush and apple-forward taste with a refreshing dry finish.

Data.Name: Mama's Little Yella Pils
Data.Description: Mama's Little Yella Pils is an uncompromising, handcrafted version of the great Pilsner beers of Bavaria and Bohemia. Unlike mass market pilsners diluted with corn and rice, Mama's is built on pilsner and honey malt, then hopped with Saaz and Aramis hops. While it's rich with flavor, its 33 IBUs and 4.7% ABV make it a luxurious but low-dose refresher. It's damn good, crushable beer.

Data.Name: New Belgium Voodoo Ranger Imperial IPA
Data.Description:
New Belgium Voodoo Ranger Imperial IPA is a rare blend of choice hops that creates an explosion of fresh-cut pine and citrus flavors for a complex, rich and delicious flavor. Initial sweetness moves quickly to bitterness that lingers alongside a pleasing sweetness.

ABV: 9.0%

Data.Name: Leinenkugel's Summer Shandy
Data.Description:
Leinenkugel’s® Summer Shandy® is a traditional weiss beer with refreshing natural lemonade flavor that makes it the perfect summer beer.

ABV: 4.2%

Data.Name: Elysian Dayglow
Data.Description:
A touch of wheat hazes the malt bill, softening this bright and crisp IPA. Dayglow is packed with juicy hops featuring pineapple and tropical fruit flavors and aromas.

ABV: 7.4%

Data.Name: Cidergeist Semi Dry Hard Cider
Data.Description:
Cider fermented to amplify the fragrance and essence of the apples whilst achieving a delightful, lip-smacking dryness.

ABV: 6.2%

Data.Name: Flaming Leprechaun Irish Whiskey
Data.Description:
Nose: Wood, toffee and notes of sweetness
Palate: Oak, peach, slightly sweet and notes of spice
Finish: Smooth and zesty

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Coffee Brandy
Data.Description: Made from carefully selected and percolated coffee beans for a deep coffee color and fresh roasted coffee flavor.

Data.Name: Ricura Horchata Cream Liqueur
Data.Description:
A delicious combination of the finest Barbados rum with cream and natural cinnamon flavors, Ricura has aromas of bread and rice pudding with a creamy cinnamon finish.
 5% ABV 25 Proof

Data.Name: Wray & Nephew White Overproof Rum
Data.Description: The world's top selling, award-winning high strength white rum that is an intricate part of Jamaican culture, tradition and every day life. Has a complex bouquet and a variety of unique flavor characteristics that make it an excellent base for cocktails.

Data.Name: Calico Jack Mango Rum
Data.Description:
As a well traveled pirate, Calico Jack always appreciated a little flavor in his life.

Imported rum with natural flavors.

42 Proof.

Data.Name: Bumbu Rum
Data.Description: Rich and complex aromas of Madagascar vanilla, soft caramel and toasted oak. Bumbu has notes of cinnamon, roasted nuts and allspice perfectly blended to achieve a mild sweetness and light, smooth finish. A all-natural craft rum aged up to 15 years in small batches.

Data.Name: Black Roberts Spiced Rum
Data.Description: Named after legendary pirate Bartholomew Roberts, this Caribbean spiced rum tingles with cinnamon and nutmeg, playing with the full, smooth vanilla and almond flavors.

Data.Name: RumChata Cream Liqueur
Data.Description:
When you want to get the party started, make RumChata your go-to. A little bit rum, a little bit horchata, RumChata is a unique cream liqueur that highlights the best of these two fun-focused beverages. It's made with Caribbean rum, fresh cream and plenty of authentic horchata spices.

Take a sip, and you'll notice cinnamon, vanilla and plenty of sweet notes. Thanks to its smooth taste, RumChata is incredibly easy to drink. Sip it on the rocks to enjoy every bit of the spiked horchata flavors. Cool down by mixing RumChata with root beer, or heat things up by mixing it with coffee or hot chocolate. Got the munchies? RumChata even adds spice to cake, pancakes and bread pudding recipes.

Data.Name: Rubinoff Key Lime Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Key Lime flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot. Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Vanilla Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Vanilla flavor. Enjoy on the rocks, or as a shot. Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Green Apple Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Green Apple Vodka is naturally flavored with fresh, crisp, juicy apples. A great choice for the base of your appletini or favoriteapple flavored mixed drink. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Pink Lemonade Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff vodka in a savory Pink Lemonade flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot. Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Grape Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff vodka in a savory Grape flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Blueberry Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in savory Blueberry flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot. Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Lemonade Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in savory Lemonade flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot. Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Coconut Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Coconut flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Peach Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Peach flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Cream Soda Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Cream Soda flavor. Enjoy on the rocks or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Whipped Cream Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory whipped cream flavor. Enjoy on ice or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Orange Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory orange flavor. Enjoy on ice, or as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Citrus Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Citrus Vodka is naturally flavored with lemons and limes. A great addition to tonics, cranberry juice, cosmos, or to any mixer for that great citrus flavor. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Mango Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Mango Vodka is naturally flavored with real mangoes. It is a wonderful addition to tonics, mixers, or even tropical juices for a refreshing cocktail. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Watermelon Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Watermelon Vodka is a summer favorite that can be enjoyed all year long. Goes great with mixers and soda, and can be used in a watermelon margarita! Enjoy!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Cherry Vodka
Data.Description: Classic Rubinoff Vodka in a savory Cherry flavor. Enjoy as a shot! Woohoo!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Raspberry Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Raspberry Vodka is naturally flavored with real raspberries. A great choice to mix with soda such as raspberry soda, or any other mixer - you pick! Enjoy!

Data.Name: Rubinoff Vodka
Data.Description: Rubinoff Vodka is a clean, neutral, and smooth vodka throughout. A true value for the vodka connosiuer that is perfect of mixing or served as a shot. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Blood Orange Vodka
Data.Description: Skyy Infusions All Natural Blood Orange is an alluring infusion of premium SKYY Vodka made with real blood orange, displaying the natural sweetness; deep, refined complexity; and mouth-watering juiciness of the sinful blood orange. It has an enticing aroma of sweet orange zest followed by juicy real orange pulp and hints of spice and caramel.

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Sun-Ripened Watermelon Vodka
Data.Description: Skyy Infusions Sun-Ripened Watermelon offers a mouth-watering and slightly sweet spirit, where the real-fruit flavor bursts forward to stand out with most any mixer. Fans of Skyy Infusions will open a bottle and immediately notice the aroma of fresh Watermelon paired with Skyy’s premium smooth vodka made from American grain for an elevated true-to-fruit experience. Skyy Infusions Sun-Ripened Watermelon is the perfect complement for outdoor cocktails with its bright fruitiness, and can be enjoyed on the rocks, muddled with fresh fruit, or used to put a surprising twist on a classic favorite.

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Citrus Vodka
Data.Description: This citrus vodka is a blend of lime, lemon and orange flavors.

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Pineapple Vodka
Data.Description:
Real fruit goes in. Real taste flows out. Skyy calls it “true to the fruit. Sweet pineapple juicy orange citrus peel and throw a party."

35% ABV 70 Proof

Data.Name: Skyy Infusions Coastal Cranberry Vodka
Data.Description: Skyy Infusions Coastal Cranberry is filled with the mouthwatering all natural flavor of tart, crisp cranberry, making it quite easy to drink on the rocks and surprisingly delicious with fresh squeezed orange juice!

Data.Name: Three Olives Jacked Apple Vodka
Data.Description:
From the most innovative flavored vodka brand comes Three Olives Jacked Apple, an incredible blend of imported English vodka and the natural taste of red apples and cinnamon.

The base of Three Olives Jacked Apple is handcrafted from the finest winter wheat harvested in England. The unmatched method of quadruple distillation and filtration remove natural impurities, yielding a vodka of exceptional purity and smoothness. Three Olives is vegan, nut free, lactose free, and developed to be gluten free.

Data.Name: Three Olives Bubble Vodka
Data.Description: An intriguing vodka based liqueur from American company Three Olives, this is a delicious blend of English vodka and classic fruit flavours in a bubble gum style.

Data.Name: UV Coconut Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: It's actually the first white vodka, a naturally-flavored spirit sweetened (considerably) with sugar cane, distilled four times, and left in a murky/milky color. Blown in from the tropics by a fresh breeze and naturally flavored with coconut, mix it up with pineapple juice or cola for some seriously refreshing sipping.

Data.Name: UV Chocolate Cake Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: It’s delicious any way you slice it. And that it’s made with all-natural flavors is just icing on the cake. Try UV Chocolate Cake in your next confectionary cocktail or on the rocks.

Data.Name: UV Cake Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: The official celebration spirit. For birthdays, anniversaries, weddings, Friday nights or any special occasion! Celebrating UV Vodka's 10th anniversary with a celebratory flavor.

Data.Name: UV Blue Raspberry Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: Who says the blues get you down? Naturally flavored with fresh raspberries for just a little sweetness, UV Blue is true happiness. Especially uplifting with lemonade, lemon lime sodas, or pretty much any mixer.

Data.Name: Flaming Leprechaun Vodka
Data.Description: Made with natural ingredients; water and wheat. Prior to distillation the wheat is ground down to an extremely fine flour in a dry mill. This fine flour is then fermented and distilled to create a high strength spirit.

Data.Name: Flaming Leprechaun Gin
Data.Description:
Ronan's Gin is one of the Flaming Leprechaun brand of spirits...in this case a traditional London dry style of gin with juniper, coriander, cassia, angelica, nutmeg, orange, and lemon. All of these very traditional and classic botanicals for a gin profile.

Flaming Leprechaun is a brand of spirits that takes its inspiration from the Irish faerie creature leprechaun and a light said to spark on Uisneach Hill.

Data.Name: Generous Gin
Data.Description: On the outside, the bottle looks like it was plucked from a Ming Dynasty palace of fine porcelain. Even the shape … classic, yet new … exotic, yet familiar. It’s really nice. On this inside you will find a “generous” helping of botanicals. Juniper … well duh! But interestingly, the juniper takes a back seat to citrus zest, elderberries, and blood orange. You will also get a whiff of lime, pepper, and other fruits. It’s as if classic a London Dry Gin had a winter fling with a luscious tropical Mojito in Miami.

Data.Name: Bogart's Gin
Data.Description: Small batch, hand-crafted, and distilled with Italian juniper berries, vine ripened cucumber, coriander, lavender, macadamia nuts, and citrus zests. Incredibly smooth and complex with a crisp taste that finish with a round and full mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Mionetto IL Prosecco
Data.Description: The perfect everyday Prosecco! Fresh and crisp with aromas of apple and peach.

Data.Name: Kona Longboard Island Lager
Data.Description: Longboard Island Lager is a smooth refreshing lager fermented and aged for weeks at cold temperatures to yield its exceptionally smooth flavor. A delicate, slightly spicy hop aroma complements the malty body of this beer. Exceptionally smooth. Pairs well with lighter fare, but has enough body to stand up to heartier foods too.

Data.Name: Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Ale
Data.Description:
American Strong Ale: 8+%ABV. 

A unique sipping beer with the distinctive nose of a well-crafted bourbon. Aged for up to 6 weeks in freshly decanted bourbon barrels from some of Kentucky's finest distilleries. Subtle flavors of vanilla and oak. Pleasantly smooth and robust.

Data.Name: Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Stout
Data.Description: Carefully crafted by Alltech’s master brewers, Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Stout builds on the success of its barrel-aged brother, the beloved Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Ale. Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Stout is brewed and aged with Alltech Café Citadelle Haitian coffee and aged in world-famous Kentucky bourbon barrels. The result is a complex stout with dark-roasted malts, hints of caramel and vanilla and a lightly roasted coffee finish.

Data.Name: Left Hand Milk Stout Nitro
Data.Description: Dark & delicious, America’s great milk stout will change your perception about what a stout can be. Pouring hard out of the bottle, Milk Stout Nitro cascades beautifully, building a tight, thick head like hard whipped cream. The aroma is of brown sugar and vanilla cream, with hints of roasted coffee. The pillowy head coats your upper lip and its creaminess entices your pallet. Initial roasty, mocha flavors rise up, with slight hop & roast bitterness in the finish. The rest is pure bliss of milk chocolate fullness.

Data.Name: Lookout Farm Cider
Data.Description: "Lookout Farm Hard Cider is a true craft cidery, using our expertise in modern fermentation and traditional aging techniques to produce a uniquely refreshing hard cider. We carefully select the most flavorful apple blends and add the finest ingredients, like our own raw honey, to create a cider that is both exceptional and true to our heritage."

Data.Name: Mike's Hard Limeade
Data.Description: Do you enjoy your drink with a splash of zesty lime? Mike's believes it's the perfect way to spice up hard lemonade! Now with even more limes, Mike's gives you that signature citrusy flavor without having to jam limes into a bottle.

Data.Name: Mike's Hard Black Cherry Lemonade
Data.Description: From the beach to the boat to the backyard BBQ, it’s ALWAYS a good time for a refreshing mike’s. Mike's Hard is passionate about making the best-tasting, most refreshing beverages to give you cold. Hard. Refreshment. Anywhere, anytime. Mike's Hard Black Cherry Lemonade is not too sweet, just incredibly refreshing.

Data.Name: Michelob Ultra Cans
Data.Description:
Brewed using the finest barley malt select grains all imported hops and a pure cultured yeast strain. The special choice of grains combined with the extended mashing process produces a smooth refreshing beer with fewer carbohydrates. 

4. 2% ABV

Data.Name: Modelo Negra
Data.Description:
In 1925, our Brewmasters set out to create a unique lager with rich flavor and smooth taste. The result was Modelo Negra, a Munich Dunkel-style Lager made with slow-roasted dark malts, brewed longer to enhance the flavors.  

As a dark beer with a surprisingly light finish, Modelo Negra will defy your expectations of a Mexican beer. Modelo Negra's rich, smooth taste brings out the flavors of Mexican-inspired dishes as well as many other cuisines. 

This balanced, easy-drinking beer contains 173 calories, 0 grams of fat, and 5.4% alcohol by volume per 12 ounce serving. Best served chilled.

Data.Name: Narragansett Lager
Data.Description: Narragansett Lager is old reliable. It was the first beer brewed by “The Original Six” back in 1890, and the best selling beer in New England from the 1930’s to the 1970’s. It has crossed paths with Dr. Seuss, it was famously crushed by Captain Quint in Jaws, and it was the first alcoholic beverage to partner with a professional sports team – the Boston Red Sox from 1944-1975. Drinking a Lager is drinking to New England history. Hi Neighbor! Have a ‘Gansett!

Data.Name: Sixpoint Sweet Action
Data.Description:
Since it's part blonde ale, part wheat beer, and part pale ale, you might be wondering, what exactly is Sweet Action? Sink one… your palate just gets it.

Early-harvested Simcoe hops give Sweet Action a peachy aroma, while Canadian White Wheat smoothes out the body and gives the beer that hazy look.

Data.Name: Sierra Nevada Torpedo Extra IPA Cans
Data.Description:
Sierra Nevada Torpedo is an American IPA brewed with a copious amount of pungent, bitter, flavorful hops. Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. is credited with brewing one of the first widely available craft beers in America in 1979 with Sierra Nevada Pale Ale. Sierra Nevada Torpedo is a more aggressive and hopped up version of the popular Sierra Nevada Pale Ale. Sierra Navada utilizes dry-hopping, which is very popular today among hop heads in the craft beer boom sweeping across the United States. Dry-hopping is a technique used by brewers adding whole cone hops to fermentation tanks. This process allows the oils and resins to add flavor and aroma to the beer without increasing bitterness.

This beer pours a clear yellow, with a small white head that doesn't recede immediately, and has medium carbonation. It smells of citrus, orange, resin and pine. Torpedo leads with orange and citrus, followed by a bitter bite with earthy pine on the back end.

Data.Name: Sierra Nevada Hazy Little Thing Cans
Data.Description: From Sierra Nevada: "As brewers, we get the privilege to sample our beers straight from the tanks in all their raw glory. Some beers need a little polishing to get ready to go out into the world, while others—the hop-heavy, rowdy, crowd-pleasers—should just be left alone. We wanted to share this brewery-only treat with you, so we present this Hazy Little Thing, our unfiltered, unprocessed IPA, straight from the tanks and into the can."

Data.Name: Sierra Nevada Pale Ale Cans
Data.Description: Sierra Nevada Pale Ale began as a home brewer’s dream, grew into an icon, and inspired countless brewers to follow a passion of their own. Its unique piney and grapefruit aromas from the use of whole-cone American hops have fascinated beer drinkers for decades and made this beer a classic, yet it remains new, complex and surprising to thousands of beer drinkers every day. It is—as it always has been—all natural, bottle conditioned and refreshingly bold.

Data.Name: Samuel Adams Summer Ale
Data.Description: An American Wheat, brewed with malted wheat, lemon zest and grains of paradise - a rare pepper from Africa first used as a brewing spice in the 13th Century to create a crisp and spicy flavor and body.

Data.Name: Frontier Red
Data.Description:
Frontier Red is a down-to-earth wine that celebrates the simple gifts in life like spending time with friends and family while sharing your favorite meal. You don't have to over-think this wine; simply enjoy this tasty blend with everyday cuisine, backyard cookouts, and BBQ's. 

A complex blend that is sure to please, Frontier Red serves up loads of lush red & black fruit flavors complemented by enticing spice, vanilla and oak notes. 

Blend: 51% Syrah, 24% Grenache, 8% Petite Sirah, 4% Sangiovese, 4% Alvarahao, 2% Merlot

Data.Name: Folie à Deux Chardonnay
Data.Description:
Appellation:
Shaped by cooling fog from the Pacific Ocean, the Russian River Valley enjoys a long, even growing season, and Chardonnay thrives in the region’s alluvial soils.

Winemaking:
Fermenting the Chardonnay grapes in a combination of French, American and Hungarian oak barrels adds complexity to the variety’s rich fruit flavors.

Tasting notes:
Indicative of its cool-climate origins, with bright acidity beneath notes of pear, apple, pineapple, apricot, nutmeg and vanilla—all framed by a richly textured palate.

Data.Name: Folie à Deux Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Appellation:
The Alexander Valley’s warm climate, marine-cooled evenings and well-drained, volcanic hillside soils translate to rich wines with smooth, well-structured tannins.

Winemaking:
Following harvest and fermentation, aging in a combination of French and American oak barrels gives this Cabernet a plush, layered palate.

Wasting notes:
Aromas of black currant, cherry, dark plum and violets are balanced by notes of sage, fennel, olives, black tea and tobacco—all layered over soft, fine-grained tannins.

Get it from Tapster now!

Data.Name: Domaine Chandon Blanc De Noirs
Data.Description: Blanc de Noirs is characteristically marked by cherry, currant and strawberry aromas and flavors. These red fruit flavors build in the mid-palate and finish with a soft, lingering creamy texture.

Data.Name: Dom Perignon Brut
Data.Description:
Founded in 1668, Dom Pérignon is vintage only, created from the fine grapes of one single year. Only ever a vintage, Dom Pérignon is an act of creation, constantly renewed after each harvest; the 2009 is majestic, ripe, fleshy and profound. 
Winemakers had to overcome many obstacles and take risks on their way to encouraging the chardonnay and pinot noir grapes of the 2009 harvest to reach their fullest expression.

The fruit is majestic: Ripe, fleshy and profound; beyond the richness and a certain voluptuousness is a strong impression of consistency that prevails - The wine's power is remarkably restrained and the various sensations - silky, salty, sappy, bitter and briny - converge and persist.

Paired well with: lobster, crab, caviar, foie gras.

Data.Name: Decoy Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
Duckhorn Vineyards has been crafting Napa Valley Sauvignon Blanc since 1982. Expanding on this winemaking tradition, Decoy Sonoma County Sauvignon Blanc allows our winemaking team the opportunity to explore a different expression of this great grape from another recognized California appellation.

This bright and aromatic wine offers enticing layers of lemon and lime zest, as well as lovely notes of honeydew and nectarine. On the palate, refreshing acidity mingles with a subtle undercurrent of sweet fruit that carries through to a refreshing, vibrant finish.

Data.Name: Decoy Red
Data.Description:
Rich and concentrated, this wine reveals voluptuous layers of blueberry, cassis and dark chocolate. On the palate, hints of salted caramel and exotic spices add depth and complexity to the fresh fruit flavors, while carrying the wine to a long and silky finish.

Varietal Content: 51% Merlot, 23% Zinfandel, 18% Cabernet Sauvignon, 6% Petite Sirah, 2% Petit Verdot; Cooperage: 85% French oak, 15% American oak

Data.Name: Decoy Merlot
Data.Description:
This lush and inviting Merlot displays enticing aromas of blueberry, raspberry and cassis, underscored by a French oak-inspired hint of cocoa. The layers of luxurious fruit continue on the palate, where lively acidity adds poise and structure, and silky tannins carry the wine to a long, juicy finish.

Varietal Content: 96% Merlot, 4% Cabernet Sauvignon; Cooperage: 100% French oak

Data.Name: Castle Rock Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Delicious Castle Rock Pinot Noir was produced from grapes grown in Northern California's beautiful Mendocino County, where vineyards were first planted in the early 1860s. There, the headwaters of the Russian River carve a fertile and rugged landscape. The warm summers, cool springs, crisp falls and wet winters make ideal growing conditions for Pinot Noir grapes, in a climate similar to that of the Burgundy region of France, where the grapes were first established.

This elegant and medium-bodied wine has delicate aromas of violet and rose petals, complex flavors and long silky textures, with layers of strawberry and raspberry leading into a long refined finish. Yum!

Alcohol 13.5% by volume

Data.Name: Bonanza Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: A delicious Cabernet featuring flavors of dark berry, vanilla, cassis and toast. Aromas of currants and oak are met by a subtle smokiness. Silky tannins create a smooth, easy to drink wine with a long finish.

Data.Name: Bogle Phantom Red
Data.Description: Bright red cherry fruit and black pepper tempt you to take that sip, with hints of brawny juniper, rich blackberry and briary boysenberry in the background. Succulent in mouthfeel, the wine showcases its versatile grape varietals: Petite Sirah, Zinfandel, Cabernet Sauvignon and Mourvedre. Aged for over 24 months in 1 and 2 year old American oak, tones of spicy vanilla and toasted coconut moderate the firm tannins and create a focused and intense finish. Enjoy this passionate and commanding red wine, yet another vintage impossible to ignore.

Data.Name: Bogle Phantom Chardonnay
Data.Description: This is a rich white wine from California. Phantom Chardonnay entices with its rich layers. Green apple and pear transform into spicy flavors of freshly baked apple pie, while barrel fermentation imparts a creamy, luscious mouthfeel. French oak whispers sweet notes of vanilla and melted caramel.

Data.Name: Kinky Pink Vodka, Mango, Blood Orange
Data.Description: A naughty fusion of super premium vodka distilled 5 times with succulent mango, blood orange liqueur and passion fruit.

Data.Name: Luc Belaire Rare Brut
Data.Description:
"Luc Belaire Rare Brut is a refreshing, crystalline sparkler made exclusively from Chardonnay grapes – an authentic French Blanc de Blancs bursting with elegance and style.

The Belaire Brut bottle speaks volumes about the quality of the wine inside. The signature black bottle with silkscreened gold and white labels is topped by a sleek, richly textured black foil top, complete with gold accents." PremierChampagne.com

Data.Name: Moet & Chandon Nectar Imperial
Data.Description: Nectar Impérial is a delicious expression of the Moët & Chandon style, a style distinguished by its bright fruitiness, its seductive palate and its elegant maturity.

Data.Name: Pommery Pop
Data.Description: A blended wine in the best sense of the term, it combines the three Champagne vines: pinot noir, pinot meunier and chardonnay. Pinot Noir is the dominant grape, affording roundness and fullness in the mouth. Pinot Meunier, to back up the pinot noir, adds that dash. Chardonnay, largely from the Grands Crus and the Reims vineyards, procures that pleasurable freshness.

Data.Name: Mi Amore Sparkling Red Semi-Sweet
Data.Description: Mi Amore meaning “my love” salutes the love that two people share. The two doves kissing represents peace, harmony and passion. Mi Amore Red embodies these attributes in each and every glass.

Data.Name: JP Chenet Sparkling Rose Dry
Data.Description: Subtle aromas of red fruit - raspberry, strawberry. Beautiful pink bubbles with salmon pink hints.

Data.Name: JP Chenet Sparkling Brut
Data.Description: Crisp elegance is on the programme tonight. Fruity aromas with notes of white peach and apricot, golden with delicate bubbles. Enjoy an aperitif as you gaze at the stars...

Data.Name: El Xamfra Cava Brut
Data.Description: "Dusty aromas of yellow apple and cream soda are creamier than the palate, which is tangy, lemony and green. This tastes of briny citrus and green apple, while tangerine, lime and green-herb flavors define the finish." Winemag.com

Data.Name: Philippe Deval Brut Cremante De Loire
Data.Description: Light pale color, zesty lemon and butter brioche notes with green apple and balanced minerality. It is dry with pronounced acidity, and bubbles are very small. The finish is crystal clear.

Data.Name: Cielo Prosecco
Data.Description: A dainty, savory bouquet and very refreshing “bollicine” make for a flawless aperitif.

Data.Name: Le Contesse Prosecco Spumante DOC
Data.Description: Sparkling wine obtained with refermentation in pressurized vats, with selected yeast and controlled temperature. The aroma is fruity with a touch of golden apple, Williams pear and white blossoms.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Prosecco
Data.Description: Josh Cellars Prosecco grapes come from the Prosecco DOC in the Veneto region of Northern Italy - vineyards lie between Conegliano Veneto and Valdobiadene. Josh Cellars is well known and liked for it's more popular Cabernet Sauvignon and Chardonnay, but as a former sommelier and global wine executive, our founder Joseph Carr has always had a special place in his heart for Prosecco. Josh Prosecco is fermented cold to ensure maximum retention of bright fresh fruit aromas and to create a crisp, elegant rosé. It is the perfect wine for pairing with almost any cuisine or occasion.

Data.Name: Moet & Chandon Ice Imperial
Data.Description: Ice Impérial, the first and only champagne especially created to be enjoyed over ice. A new champagne experience combining fun, fresh and free sensations while remaining true to the Moët & Chandon style, a style distinguished by its bright fruitiness, its seductive palate and its elegant maturity. It has broad, fleshy, voluptuous flavour of a fresh fruit salad, the captivating sweetness of caramel and quince jelly, and the refreshing acidity of grapefruit and ginger notes.

Data.Name: Moet & Chandon Imperial - Limited Edition Gold
Data.Description: The color is an elegant golden straw yellow with amber highlights. Its aromas reveal an exotic fruitiness – yellow peach, plum, pineapple and honey – with floral nuances (lime blossom) and elegant blond notes (brioche and fresh nuts). The palate is seductive and generous, combining intensity with roundness, fullness with suppleness, followed by a lively crisp finish to reveal the magical balance of champagne.

Data.Name: Louis Pommery California Sparkling Brut
Data.Description: This well-balanced and smooth wine is the debut California offering from French producer Pommery. Made from 96% Chardonnay and a dab of Pinot Noir, it carries aromas of toasted baguette and flowers, with crisp apple and white peach flavors on fine-beaded bubbles. The concentrated fruit amplifies on the palate and lingers on the finish.

Data.Name: Cook's Extra Dry California Champagne
Data.Description: Semi-dry, with crisp fruit flavors, complexity, and a long, smooth finish. The aromas of apple and pear are balanced with a bouquet of toasty yeast notes and floral nuances.

Data.Name: Chevalier De Grenelle Saumur Cuvée Réservée
Data.Description: Since 1859, La Maison Louis de Grenelle has been energized by a passion for great wines. It remains today as one of the greatest independent houses Saumur. At the heart of its cellars carved into the limestone, it develops sparkling delicate styles of wine that are refined and complex.

Data.Name: Charles Heidsieck Brut Réserve
Data.Description: Thanks to the 40% of reserve wines, the blend offers a complex, elegant, voluptuous nose with a touch of freshly baked brioche, rich toasted notes and sun-drenched fruits - mango, apricot and mirabelle plum - accented by dried fruits, pistachio and almond.

Data.Name: Domaine Chandon Sweet Star
Data.Description: The nose pops with aromas of bright peach, nectarine, grapefruit and tropical fruits complemented by floral notes. The fruit aromas extend onto the generous palate which is rich and sweet but with a distinctive, refreshing acidity that brightens the mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Luc Belaire Rare Brut Gold
Data.Description: Balanced and elegant, the wine begins with aromas of stone fruits, ripe pear and brioche. Tropical notes of mango complement fresh Chardonnay fruit and limestone on the palate. Finely structured and delicate, the wine has a light, dry finish.

Data.Name: Beau Joie Brut Champagne
Data.Description:
A unique, zero-dosage champagne with none of the added sugars common in other champagnes, BEAU’s true, uninhibited flavors rise through to the palate, boasting the perfect balance of dryness and sweetness resulting in a clean, crisp taste from start to finish.

Because of the lack of added sugars, BEAU pairs well with all foods and desserts.

Data.Name: Delamotte Brut Le Mesnil-Sur-Oger
Data.Description: "The NV Brut is a gorgeous, deep wine endowed with an attractive core of rich fruit. This is an especially mid-weight, expansive Champagne with commendable balance and a long, finessed finish. Smoke, minerals and earthiness add complexity on the close." Cellar.com

Data.Name: Apothic Sparkling Wine
Data.Description: This new, limited release wine blends red and white grapes together, leading to a sparkling white wine with a darker disposition. Flavors of strawberry and white peach combine with a hint of vanilla for a wine that is best served with a chill.

Data.Name: Cook's Brut California Champagne
Data.Description: Medium-dry with crisp fruit flavors. The aromas of apple and pear are balanced with a bouquet of toasty yeast notes and floral nuances.

Data.Name: Underwood The Bubbles
Data.Description: It’s hard to keep your pinky up when you’re drinking wine from a 375 mL can. Whether you’re sitting in a hot tub after a good day of riding or heading where other wines dare not travel, Underwood has you covered without sacrificing the craft taste Union is known for. Enjoy flavors of ripe citrus, tropical fruit, and white flowers.

Data.Name: Riondo Prosecco Spago Negro
Data.Description: Riondo Prosecco Spago Nero is an authentic sparkling wine that celebrates the easy-living spirit of Italy. This vino frizzante boasts fresh aromas of Golden Delicious apple, pear, and acacia blossom. Its persistent effervescence is followed by a crisp, clean finish. While delicate and fruity on the palate, this prosecco is the perfect choice to either sip by itself or mix to make a bubbly cocktail.

Data.Name: Riondo Blu Prosecco
Data.Description: Blu presents fresh and intense aromas of pear, peach, wisteria and hints of citrus aromas. It's a perfect balance of acidity while its concentrated fruit and residual sugar please the palate. The inviting union of flavor and a lively sparkle makes this prosecco perfect for every occasion.

Data.Name: Martini & Rossi Asti
Data.Description: The steep and sun-drenched hills in the heart of Piemont are an ideal growing environment and a habitat that would enable Moscato to become one of the world's most famous wines. The cool, fresh sensation of a glass of MARTINI & ROSSI® Asti, with its fragrance and low alcohol content, always allows the freedom of another toast.

Data.Name: Domaine Chandon Brut Classic
Data.Description: Brut Classic consistently expresses Chandon's signature flavor profile of apple, pear and citrus flavors and aromas with a hint of spice that leads to a soft, dry finish.

Data.Name: Mionetto Prosecco Brut
Data.Description: The grapes from the province of Treviso, an area that has always produced high quality Prosecco, give this sparkling wine a luminous straw yellow hue and for its emphatic yet stylish mousse. The bouquet is redolent of Golden Delicious apple, while the palate is appealingly marked by aromatic notes of honey, white peach and honey.

Data.Name: Ayinger Celebrator
Data.Description:
A beer that has a dominant malty taste. This beer’s origins in a monk’s recipe are reflected in its heartiness. The Pope of Beers, Conrad Seidl, describes it as: “Almost black with a very slight red tone, a sensational, festive foam and truly extraordinary fragrance that at first summons up visions of greaves lard. The first taste is of mild fullness with an accompanying coffee tone, which becomes more dominant with the aftertaste. There is very little of the sweetness that is frequently to be tasted with doppelbock beer.”

6.7% ABV

Data.Name: Fortaleza Blanco
Data.Description: Aromas of fruit, baked fully-ripened agave, green olive, and earth are invitingly present. Slightly brighter and a touch more rustic than the regular blanco, the accents of butter, olive, earth, black pepper, and vegetal qualities in the flavor are enhanced because it comes straight from our small copper pot still, without adding water prior to bottling.

Data.Name: Fat Tire Amber Ale Cans
Data.Description: Fat Tire Amber is the easy-drinking Amber Ale born in Colorado from New Belgium Brewing Company, the employee-owned leader in environmental stewardship.

Data.Name: Woodbridge Riesling
Data.Description: Woodbridge Riesling features delicate aromas of lemon tea and orange blossom. On the palate, lush flavors of orange touched with honey and spice are enhanced by an excellent balance of light sweetness and crisp acidity. The perfect wine for those seeking an alternate white variety, Riesling's slightly lower alcohol content makes it a great partner for many foods. Try this sweet wine with fresh crab salad, smoked salmon, and spicy Asian dishes. Serve chilled.

Data.Name: Pares Balta Blanc de Pacs
Data.Description: Blend of the 3 traditional varieties from the Penedès: Xarel·lo, Parellada and Macabeu. Three varieties grown especially to create a white wine that obtains its intense aroma from the freshness of the fruit.

Data.Name: Napa Cellars Chardonnay
Data.Description: The Napa Cellars 2017 Chardonnay displays classic Napa Valley Chardonnay characteristics indicative of this region. Aromas of baked apple, ripe Bosc pear, crème brûlée and lemon curd excite the senses. A soft mouthfeel supports flavors of green apple flavors with orange zest and almond pastry balanced with late, crisp acidity pulling together this well balanced, full-bodied Chardonnay. .

Data.Name: Montes Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: The intense and very cheerful nose offers aromas of lime and grapefruit accompanied by attractive notes of fresh pineapple, passion fruit, and orange blossom, while a light touch of green chili lends complexity to the coastal aromatic profile.

Data.Name: Mezzacorona Chardonnay
Data.Description: The highly drinkable Chardonnay shows subtle flavors of peach, nectarine, pear and spice. The Chardonnay is cultivated on the highest hillside vines of Trentino. These vines benefit from optimum sunlight and cool refreshing night air which enhance the crispness of the fruits.

Data.Name: Menage a Trois White Blend
Data.Description: The 2017 Ménage à Trois White is a trip to the islands without the worry of sunburn or bugs. It’s undeniably fruity and unabashedly easy. It’s meant to be quaffed, not analyzed. The White blend brings together citrus and tropical fruit flavors with crisp acidity. Dare we say it’s refreshing? With food or without, alone or with two companions, this is one of the most exhilarating experiences imaginable.

Data.Name: Old Monk the Legend 21 Years
Data.Description: Sweet, thick molasses nose with vanilla notes and a butterscotch bite. A rush of sweetness defines the entry but is quickly smoothed out by spice and dry herb notes that linger into a quick finish.

Data.Name: Old Monk Supreme
Data.Description:
Old Monk Rum, a brand that made it to the top without ever spending a dime on advertising.

This variant, Old Monk Supreme XXX Rum, has aged for at least 18 years which makes it an oldtimer even by hors d'age standards. Its grade of quality and taste experience is unmatched by any other Old Monk variety.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam Red Berry
Data.Description: New Amsterdam® Red Berry vodka offers sweet, juicy flavors of ripe raspberries, strawberries, blackberries, and boysenberries. A touch of lime zest brightens the berry flavors on the palate and the flavors are rounded together with brown spice and sweet vanilla. Its silky smooth mouthfeel leads to an ultra-clean finish.

Data.Name: Allen's Ginger Brandy
Data.Description: "Allen's Ginger Brandy is prepared from extract high grade ginger root, 100% neutral fruit brandy, and sugar syrup, which highlight the valuable properties of the ginger root." Totalwine.com

Data.Name: Metaxa 5 Star Brandy
Data.Description: Metaxa 5 star is floral, versatile and smooth. With a look of luminous amber, with smells of orange blossom, rose petals and apricot. It is smooth with floral notes, vanilla, and hints of white raisins. The aftertaste is balanced with a floral finish.

Data.Name: Cardenal Mendoza Clásico Solera Gran Reserva
Data.Description:
Cardenal Mendoza Clásico is an exceptional Brandy de Jerez, aged for an average of 15 years in Oloroso and Pedro Ximénez Sherry Wine casks. Its appearance is bright, transparent dark mahogany with copper glints. 

On the nose it is clean, elegant and well-rounded with hints of the Sherry which seasoned the barrels.

On the palate it is beautifully balanced, warming and smooth while it has a very long finish where all the subtle nuances come together leaving a lasting impression of personality with hints of raisin and prune.

Data.Name: E&J Apple Brandy
Data.Description: E&J's freshest flavor, Apple didn't fall far from the family tree. Smooth and balanced like you expect an E&J Brandy to be, E&J Apple brandy is blended with apple liqueur, giving it a sweet, crisp flavor with just a hint of vanilla and caramel. If you're wondering how to drink apple brandy, sip it over ice or in one of our signature E&J cocktails.

Data.Name: E&J Peach Brandy
Data.Description:
E&J Peach brandy is ripe and sweet for the sipping. It's a smooth, balanced brandy mixed with peach liqueur, making it a unique twist on classic E&J VS. With notes of vanilla spice and juicy, fresh peach flavor, E&J Peach brandy finishes smooth and always satisfies.

Enjoy it over ice or in a tasty peach brandy mixed drink.

Data.Name: Hennessy Cognac VSOP Privilège
Data.Description:
The world’s first, and favorite V.S.O.P Cognac blends over 60 eaux-de-vie to achieve perfect harmony – a testament to the enduring expertise of the Hennessy Master Blenders. A natural balance of strength and smoothness with a long-lasting finish.

The balance and complexity of Hennessy V.S.O.P Privilège makes it ideal for drink recipes that highlight the quality of the spirit, especially in classic Cognac cocktails.

Data.Name: Menage a Trois Chardonnay Gold
Data.Description: Indulge in the extravagant pleasures of Ménage à Trois Gold—an opulent Chardonnay blend like nothing you’ve ever experienced. Every glass offers an abundance of riches, from the wine’s brilliant gold color and luscious aromas to its deep, layered flavors and full, round mouthfeel. An irresistible fragrance of crème brulée, honeyed pineapple, and exotic floral notes rises from the glass, hinting at delights to come. On the palate, a wealth of ripe tropical fruit flavors meld with luxurious French vanilla and hints of sweet spice before culminating in a smooth, buttery finish. Brimming with beautifully integrated flavors and a sumptuous, seamlessly creamy texture,

Data.Name: Vizcaya VXOP Cask 21 Rum
Data.Description: The velvety bouquet of Vizcaya VXOP rum hints at its warm, smoky spice. Notes of cinnamon, vanilla, clove and ginger are followed by a whisper of tropical fruit. The first taste brings a voluptuous but balanced sweetness, reminiscent of maple and butterscotch. Vizcaya's smooth finish integrates all of these elements into a sensory, satisfying harmony.

Data.Name: Macollo Black Rum
Data.Description: While Mexico is better known for their agave-based spirits, there are actually a few Mexican rums kicking about - like the Macollo Black, boasting loads of caramel and zesty fruit notes.

Data.Name: Club Caribe Mango Rum
Data.Description: Clear. Bright watermelon candy and tropical fruity punch aromas and flavors with a soft, sweet medium body and sugary, mineral accented finish. Vibrant, if confected, tropical flavors for mixing.

Data.Name: Club Caribe Coconut Rum
Data.Description: This flagship line of award-winning, full-flavored, tropical rums is distilled to 55 proof providing the only flavored rums in the industry above 42 proof creating a full bodied tropical cocktail. Only the highest quality ingredients go into each bottle to create the rums that bear the name of our Puerto Rican distillery. Grab Club Caribe today and experience the fruits of the Caribbean.

Data.Name: Centenario Añejo Especial 7 Year Old Rum
Data.Description: Centenario Añejo Especial is undoubtedly the result of the most sublime spirit of the oak. A careful selection of barrels and its exquisite blend of rums aged, give this great body, texture and color all-knowing of a good rum preferred. Sweet and elegant with a rich aroma of tropical fruits, molasses, tobacco, and oak, this rum is meant to be enjoyed neat or on the rocks.

Data.Name: Bully Boy White Rum
Data.Description: Bully Boy's process starts with a high grade molasses, which is full of butterscotch and vanilla aromas. They then allow the molasses to undergo an unconventionally long fermentation that lets the flavor fully evolve. The final step is a distillation that ensures only the cleanest spirit is kept. The result is a crisp, clean, dry rum that features hints of pineapple, burnt sugar, and raisin. Perfect for enjoying on the rocks or mixed in a classic cocktail.

Data.Name: Zaya Gran Reserva 12 Year Rum
Data.Description: Zaya’s extraordinary blend of rare rums aged up to 16 years captivates the senses with a vibrant and alluring island experience. It is rich with sweet caramel, vanilla, banana, and cherry. The finish is heavy, velvety, and smooth.

Data.Name: Cruzan Velvet Cinn Horchata
Data.Description: Velvet Cinn is Cruzan’s spin on a spiked version of the classic Mexican rice-meets-almond-meets-cinnamon beverage. The almondy nuttiness comes through clearly on the nose here, along with cinnamon notes. The body is very sweet and cinnamon-fueled, with an authentic-feeling sweet cream finish. The texture isn’t particularly viscous, but it does coat the mouth and leave a lingering impression for some time after you sip it." Drinkhacker.com

Data.Name: Ron Diplomático Reserva Exclusiva
Data.Description: This rum is complex and characterful, with notes of maple syrup, orange peel, brown sugar and liquorice. Enjoy it neat or on the rocks. It can also be used in elegant and sophisticated cocktails such as Old Fashioned and Sazerac.

Data.Name: Ron Barceló Imperial Rum
Data.Description:
Bright copper-amber color. Aromas of buttercream, dried cherries, intense vanilla, pineapple jam and caramelized walnuts followed smoothly by a dry fruity lush medium body, full of depth and balance. 
Ending on a note of carrot cake, kola nut, mocha and a strong toasted flavor that slowly fades.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam Pineapple Vodka
Data.Description: New Amsterdam Pineapple vodka has bright, refreshing aromas of pineapple and tropical fruit. Flavors of juicy, freshly cut pineapple and coconut cleanse the palate and offer a crisp, refreshing finish.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam Mango Vodka
Data.Description: New Amsterdam Mango vodka adds a subtle tropical flavor to your drink without demanding a frilly, little umbrella. Liven up your drink with a splash of our mango-flavored vodka.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam Peach Vodka
Data.Description: Five times distilled for unparalleled smoothness, and is filtered three times to create a soft finish. Vibrant, sweet, succulent peach flavor. Subtle hints of floral and vanilla with a soft, refreshing mouth feel. Smooth, clean finish.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam 100 Proof Vodka
Data.Description: New Amsterdam Premium, 100 proof vodka made from some of the finest quality corn. Five times distilled for unparalleled smoothness, filtered three times to create a soft mouthfeel. New Amsterdam 100 Proof Vodka has aromas of sweet frosting and light citrus with an impressively smooth, clean finish.

Data.Name: New Amsterdam Original Vodka
Data.Description: New Amsterdam 80-Proof Vodka is 5-times distilled from the finest grains then filtered three times. It’s so smooth you can create a perfect cocktail or drink it straight, making it one of the best vodkas available. Our premium process makes our distilled vodka as iconic as the cityscape on the bottle. Our flavors are crafted using our award winning original 80-proof vodka.

Data.Name: Burnett's Mango Vodka
Data.Description: Burnett's flavored vodkas are produced under the same standards as their original, yet lovely infusions of exotic and satisfying flavors contribute to the formation of a vodka with a much different character. F. Paul Pacult of Spirit Journal comments, The first whiffs pick up a pleasant mango meat/pulp freshness; overtime, the aroma becomes slightly spicy. The taste is nicely ripe and mellow.

Data.Name: Burnett's Mango Pineapple Vodka
Data.Description: There's a reason mango and pineapple always get invited to the smoothie. They're both totally sweet and delicious. Burnett's Mango Pineapple takes everyone's favorite smoothie flavors and mashes them up into one unbelievably fun in the sun drink.

Data.Name: Burnett's Grape Vodka
Data.Description: From juice to bubblegum to jelly to cartoon apes, there is no denying the massive appeal of the grape. With Burnett's Grape Vodka, you can add a sour touch to your most popular cocktails.

Data.Name: Burnett's Watermelon Vodka
Data.Description: Burnett's Watermelon Vodka makes a sweet and juicy addition to any party or barbecue.

Data.Name: Burnett's Hot Cinnamon Vodka
Data.Description: Burnett's Hot Cinnamon packs the sweet yet spicy flavor of your favorite hot cinnamon flavored treats.

Data.Name: Burnett's Lime Vodka
Data.Description: Dull cocktails make for dull parties. So keep the sour punch of refreshing Burnett's Lime Vodka handy. The bright citrus flavor puts a little zing in any drink.

Data.Name: Burnett's Vanilla Vodka
Data.Description: Decadent and elegant, the rich taste of Burnett's Vanilla Vodka will make you feel like you're wearing a cocktail dress or tuxedo even when you are in flip-flops and shorts.

Data.Name: Burnett's Cherry Vodka
Data.Description: Fresh, ripe cherry is a favorite flavor in a variety of cocktails. Bring a bottle of Burnett's Cherry Vodka and you will be invited to every party forever.

Data.Name: Burnett's Coconut Vodka
Data.Description: Burnett's Coconut Vodka offers a sweet taste of the tropics. Close yours eyes and this fruity favorite will take you to a place with warm sand and island breezes.

Data.Name: Burnett's Pineapple Vodka
Data.Description: The tropical sweet taste of pineapple comes to life in your cabana cocktail. The official drink of the hammock lifestyle.

Data.Name: Burnett's Pink Lemonade Vodka
Data.Description: The sweet memories of summer are embodied in Burnett's Pink Lemonade. Get together with friends, mix yourself a great seasonal cocktail and make some new memories.

Data.Name: Burnett's Strawberry Vodka
Data.Description: Juicy all-natural strawberry makes Burnett's Strawberry Vodka a sweet choice. Pairs well with the first day of vacation.

Data.Name: Burnett's Blueberry Vodka
Data.Description: Enjoy the fruitness of Burnett's Blueberry to enhance your favorite summer-themed cocktail.

Data.Name: Burnett's Sour Apple Vodka
Data.Description: Sweet and sour like a Granny Smith apple. But fits much nicer in a martini glass.

Data.Name: Burnett's Espresso Vodka
Data.Description: The robust coffee flavor of Burnett's Espresso Vodka is a complement for any coffee drink or after-dinner cocktail.

Data.Name: Burnett's Peach Vodka
Data.Description: Life's just peachy with Burnett's Peach. Try it in your favorite cocktail for a ripe and fruity flavor.

Data.Name: Burnett's Raspberry Vodka
Data.Description: Ripe red raspberries give a berry burst to many great Burnett's recipes. Gives you all the flavor of picking fresh raspberries without the hassle of leaving the house to go pick fresh raspberries.

Data.Name: Ciroc Amaretto
Data.Description: Ciroc Amaretto is the fourth flavor-infused varietal from the makers of Ciroc Ultra-Premium Vodka. Ciroc Amaretto offers a rich, cherry-almond flavor with a touch of vanilla and a silky smooth finish. The spirit has been masterfully infused with amaretto flavors, resulting in a taste experience that is lusciously different and elegantly smooth. The unique mixability of Ciroc Amaretto allows for a broad range of cocktail creativity, whether mixed with cola, pineapple juice or in a classic sour.

Data.Name: Ciroc Summer Colada
Data.Description: Introducing the new Ciroc Summer Colada Limited Edition Bottle, a fusion of fresh pineapple abounds with a touch of coconut cream. Tropical collaboration that can't be denied. Limited-time only - get it before it's gone!

Data.Name: Ciroc Vodka
Data.Description: Ciroc Ultra-Premium Vodka is a rich tasting vodka distilled five times from fine French grapes and finished in a tailor-made copper pot still in Southern France. Smooth and lightly sweet, our ultra-premium vodka provides a taste experience that is lusciously different and elegantly smooth. Simply mix with lemonade and pour over ice for a refreshing tasting Diddy cocktail.

Data.Name: Rhum Barbancourt Reserve Speciale 5 Star 8 Year
Data.Description: Pale gold, a little more golden than the Three stars with green shades. It offers a rich and harmonious bouquet of vanilla and pepper. On the palate, the body is powerful, mellow, well balanced. The finish is powerful and complex, with some roasted notes, cooked fruits (prunes), and citrus fruits in compote (orange jam). Aged 8 years, the Five Stars rum, or "Special Reserve" is all in balance. It is excellent dry, but can be appreciated with ice cubes, decorated with a zest of lemon, to reveal all its subtleties.

Data.Name: Rhum Barbancourt 3 Star 4 Year Old
Data.Description: Pale gold, of medium intensity, but of a crystalline brilliance. This rum is elegant and fresh with hints of vanilla and spice. The finish recalls the aromatic freshness of the nose, and the characteristics of the rum with a hint of pepper. From 4 years of age, this Three Star rum has a light and delicate flavor. Pleasant in a mixture, it lends itself to the best cocktails as well as in recipes of cooking, for the pleasure of connoisseurs and gourmets.

Data.Name: Pyrat XO Reserve Rum
Data.Description: Pyrat XO Reserve is a complex yet mellow blend of select Caribbean rums, aged 15 years in French Limousin & American sweet oak barrels. Its handcrafted decanter is fashioned after relic rum bottles once hoarded by pirates and ship captains in the 1800s. In tribute to the true Pyrat spirit of social enlightenment, each bottle is adorned with the image of Hoti, patron saint and protector of fortune-tellers and bartenders.

Data.Name: Cachaca 51 Pirassununga
Data.Description: Aged in oak barrels, gaining wood characteristics, it has a balanced flavor with floral notes, vanilla and dried fruits. Perfect to be tasted as a digestive or aperitif or even in drinks.

Data.Name: Papa's Pilar Dark Rum
Data.Description: Complex notes of vanilla, cinnamon, coffee beans and honey with hints of sherry and port. The taste is intricately flavored. It is sweet mixed with earthy, vegetal tones. Mouth-coating with a touch of spice, bourbon, almond and apricot. This dark rum is robust with a long finish.

Data.Name: Palo Viejo White Rum
Data.Description: Lime, citrus, coconut and grape are the most prominent flavors in this Rum. Aged at least one year. One of the best known rums in Puerto Rico.

Data.Name: Mount Gay Silver Rum
Data.Description: Clean and aromatic in contrast to Eclipse’s rich smokiness, Silver offers a balanced, mellow harmony of sugar cane syrup and banana, infused with notes of peppermint and citrus.

Data.Name: Mount Gay Black Barrel Rum
Data.Description: Black Barrel is a small batch, handcrafted blend made of matured double pot distillates and aged column distillates. In a process called finishing, the blended rum is then matured for a second time in deeply charred Bourbon oak barrels. This unique process releases spicy aromas that are at once balanced, and bold.

Data.Name: Burnett's Vodka 100 Proof
Data.Description: When you want to take the party up a notch, there's Burnett's 100 Proof Vodka. With its exception mixability, Burnett's is a popular choice of party hosts everywhere.

Data.Name: Burnett's Vodka 80 Proof
Data.Description: Burnett's Vodka is quadruple distilled and triple charcoal filtered.

Data.Name: Svedka Clementine Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: "Clear. Bright sugared tangerine zest aromas follow through on a soft, creamy entry to a fruity sweet medium body with orange sherbet and cream notes. Finishes with a tangy orange gelatin candy and mineral oil fade. Nice candied tangerine/clementine flavor for cocktails." - Tastings.com

Data.Name: Svedka Cherry Flavored Vodka
Data.Description:
Cherry on on top? How about cherry in your glass! 
Vodka made with all-natural flavors of Montmorency cherries.

Data.Name: Dutchcraft Vodka
Data.Description: Dutchcraft Vodka is a small-batch artisan vodka produced & bottled in Holland. Using hand selected wheat, the grains are distilled five times for purity and then filtered through charcoal for a vodka of extraordinary quality and smoothness.

Data.Name: Khortytsa Platinum Vodka
Data.Description: The main feature of this vodka is its unsurpassed softness, which has been achieved thanks to an optimal balance of all ingredients. Created for those who appreciate delicate flavor. It is perfect for making cocktails. Double Gold at the San Francisco Spirits Competition.

Data.Name: Deep Eddy Cranberry Vodka
Data.Description: Distilled 10 times to create a smooth finish. New England cranberries and pure cane sugar are added to produce a light, sweet flavor that is perfect for a drink on the patio, porch, or by a swimming pool. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Deep Eddy Lemon Vodka
Data.Description: Column distilled ten times and infused with real lemon juice before bottling. The aroma is reminiscent of fresh squeezed lemonade. The body is slightly tart with hints of pure sugar cane. Mix with water and a squeeze of fresh lemon and enjoy!

Data.Name: Pinnacle Whipped Vodka
Data.Description: Pinnacle Whipped flavored vodka starts out smooth and goes down even smoother. Add a light whip of creamy delicate vanilla to your favorite fruit juice or hot chocolate for a vodka drink dessert that won't spoil your dinner.

Data.Name: Pinnacle Red Licorice Vodka
Data.Description: Pinnacle Red Licorice has a flavor profile that much more in line with Swedish Gummy Fish more than anything. Perfect straight up or mixed in a bomb with an energy drink over ice.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Amaretto
Data.Description:
Smirnoff Amaretto brings to life the delicious and sophisticated taste of bittersweet almond with hints of lightly sweet cherry by combining natural amaretto flavor and the Award-Winning Smirnoff No. 21 vodka.

Enjoy Smirnoff Amaretto with cola, your favorite mixers, over ice, or in your favorite mixed drink.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Coconut
Data.Description: Smirnoff Coconut lures you in first with a sweet coconut smell moving through a smooth drink with an easy finish to a nice long aftertaste.

Data.Name: Deauville Peach Schnapps
Data.Description: The makers of Deauville Cordials, combine natural Peach flavors in special formulas for delicious drinks in the French tradition.

Data.Name: Saint Brendan's Irish Cream Liqueur
Data.Description: This all-natural cream comes from happy dairy cows dining on the richest green grasses of the Emerald Isle. Made with a richer butterfat content than most Irish Creams, it’s pure decadence. Aged, triple-distilled premium Irish whiskey brings warmth and smoothness straight from the barrel to finish this 34-proof premium liqueur the proper Irish way.

Data.Name: Russo Lemon Limoncello Liqueur
Data.Description: Mainly produced in the South of Italy, this Italian lemon liqueur is Italy’s second most popular liqueur. With generous aromas of lemons, this limoncello has rich, sweet lemon flavors with a well rounded texture and smooth zesty aftertaste.

Data.Name: Rumple Minze Lime Schnapps
Data.Description: This lime schnapps recipe comes from Germany, known for its long history of creating intensely flavored Schnapps. Rumple Minze Schnapps delivers an extreme taste experience; both cooling and bracing.

Data.Name: Pama Pomegranate Liqueur
Data.Description: PAMA is made with all-natural pomegranate juice, premium vodka and a touch of imported tequila. Bottled at 34 proof, PAMA is highly mixable in a range of cocktails. PAMA captures the complex, sweet yet tart taste and seductive ruby color of all-natural pomegranates.

Data.Name: Grappi Chocolate Liqueur
Data.Description: Grappi is an irresistible blend of luscious, dark chocolate, rich cocoa powder, and special spirits, handed down for three generations. It is a rich chocolate fragrance, with an alcoholic scent of Grappa and a full bodied, fondant, persistent aftertaste. Drizzle over ice cream for a rich chocolatey taste, or pour inside coffee.

Data.Name: Galliano Ristretto Coffee Liqueur
Data.Description: Galliano suffused with all the power of a perfectly brewed ‘ristretto’ - the concentrated and short espresso adored by Italians.

Data.Name: Ballast Point Opah Herbal Liqueur
Data.Description: Ballast Point is introducing the newest product in its family of spirits, Opah, a herbal liqueur with spicy cinnamon and liquorice notes.

Data.Name: Tippy Cow Shamrock Mint Rum Cream
Data.Description: Proudly made by Wisconsin cows, Tippy Cow uses only the highest quality of Rum and other ingredients to ensure a perfect flavor experience. Savor Tippy Cow Shamrock Mint Rum Cream and remember your favorite Saint Patrick’s Day shake. Enjoy this classic taste on the rocks, straight up, or as a base for a variety of cocktails, but be prepared to share as Tippy Cow always draws a crowd!

Data.Name: Southern Comfort Original
Data.Description: Southern Comfort Original is inspired by the founder’s 1874 recipe, with core whiskey notes and iconic fruit and spice accents. Enjoyed best with mainstream mixers and in cocktails, it brings everyone together.

Data.Name: Sobieski Vodka
Data.Description:
Imported from Poland, Sobieski was inspired from the iconic king Sobieski, who defended Europe against the Ottomans. It is made with 100% Pure Rye. Crystalline water gives it an unmistakable silkiness, and continuous rectification, in the highest column still in Europe, creates one of the purest, smoothest vodkas in the world. As Rye Vodka, Sobieski is distinctive and different. No wonder why experts describe Sobieski as Real Vodka. 

How to drink Sobieski?  Up to you! Too many ways to appreciate it: neat, with ice, in a cocktail… your way is the right way!

Data.Name: St. George Spiced Pear Liqueur
Data.Description: Both elegant and earthy, this liqueur has all the complexity of a perfectly ripe Bartlett pear. Cinnamon and clove add a warm touch of spice.

Data.Name: Kahlua Gingerbread Liqueur
Data.Description: A blend of rum, 100% Arabica coffee, gingerbread, nutmeg, cinnamon and clove.

Data.Name: Patrón Citrónge Orange
Data.Description: Patrón Citrónge Orange is a premium reserve, extra fine orange liqueur that delivers a sweet and smooth, fresh orange taste. It is perfect for use in both cocktails and gourmet recipes.

Data.Name: Ouzo 12
Data.Description: Ouzo 12 is the Ouzo with the extraordinary aroma of history and tradition. Every single bottle is representative of the soul of Greece. It took its name in 1880 at the Kaloyannis Distillery from "Barrel No 12". This extract was preferred for its rich taste and its delicate aroma. Today, it still keeps the same taste that makes Ouzo12 one of the most consumed varieties of this aniseed-flavoured spirit of Greek tradition worldwide.

Data.Name: Old New England Egg Nog
Data.Description: Old New England Egg Nog is crafted using the freshest dairy base prepared by the finest dairy farms. It is made with imported brandy, smooth blended whiskey, imported rum and Kentucky bourbon.

Data.Name: Kamora Coffee Liqueur
Data.Description: Kamora brings you the finest beans, roasted to perfection, blended to a satiny smooth decadence with vanilla, chocolate and caramel notes. In a cocktail, in coffee or alone on ice, Kamora is just right, anytime.

Data.Name: Party Package 1
Data.Description:
This party package includes:

1/6 Keg House Lager Beer
Insulated Keg Bag
30 12oz Cans Bud Light
1.75 L Tito's Handmade Vodka
Tap Rental

Deposit fees for keg and keg tap apply. Deposits are returned to you upon successful return of your keg, You have 15 days to return your keg after your delivery day. Schedule your Keg Pick Up under "Orders" in your app!

Enjoy!

Data.Name: Kool-A-Keg Insulated Keg Bags
Data.Description: Keep your keg cool and frosty all party long with these insulated bags.

Data.Name: Hennessy VS Cognac
Data.Description: Aged in oak barrels for four years, Hennessy V.S. brings complex flavors such as apple, citrus, fresh grape, French oak and grilled almonds to your glass. What sounds like a delicious summer salad is quite nice in cognac form, and it's the perfect drink for conversation or sitting out on a patio and enjoying life. It's a true showing of the expertise and ingenuity of the world's finest cognac producer.

Data.Name: Jack Daniel's Tennessee Fire
Data.Description: Jack Daniel’s Tennessee Fire blends red-hot cinnamon liqueur with the smooth character of Jack Daniel’s Old No.7 for a classic spirit with a fiery finish. 70 Proof.

Data.Name: Grand Marnier Raspberry Peach
Data.Description:
COLOR
Beautiful rosé tone with a slight touch of amber, which gives a warm sensation.

AROMA
Complex aroma of raspberries and peaches blended with a hint of orange and citrus essence.

TASTE
Rich blend of raspberries and peaches from the South of France with the famous Grand Marnier orange essence. Very well balanced. Finish supported by the cognac notes.

Data.Name: Goldschlager Cinnamon Schnapps
Data.Description: Clear with gold leaf flakes. Cinnamon, spicy aromas give way to alcohol vapors. The palate is sweet and syrupy with hot spicy undertones. Enjoy as shot or sipped from a rock glass.

Data.Name: Galliano L'Autentico
Data.Description: Galliano, properly known as "Liquore Galliano L'Autentico", is a sweet herbal liqueur created in 1896 by Italian distiller and brandy producer Arturo Vaccari of Livorno in Tuscany. Vaccari named the spirit after Giuseppe Galliano, an Italian hero of the First ItaloEthiopian War at the end of the 19th century. Its vivid yellow color, currently derived from Tartrazine (a lemon-yellow azo dye), symbolized the Gold Rushes of the 1890s. Galliano is 60 proof (30% by volume). Among its approximately 30 herbal ingredients are star anise, Mediterranean anise, ginger, and citrus and vanilla.
