Galliano has a similar appearance to Strega (liqueur), another Italian herbal liqueur. Galliano is sweet and has a complex, vanilla-anise flavor with subtle citrus and woodsy herbal under notes.

Data.Name: Fabrizia Italian Margarita
Data.Description: A premium, hand-crafted, ready to drink cocktail made from fresh lemonade. This refreshing, all natural base creates a delicious and unique cocktail. Just pour over ice and enjoy!

Data.Name: Fabrizia Limoncello
Data.Description: Fabrizia Limoncello is entirely "homemade," produced in small batches, by hand in New Hampshire.

Data.Name: Viniq Shimmery Peach Liqueur
Data.Description:
A fusion of premium vodka, moscato and natural peach flavor. Make every moment special with the smooth, delicious drink.

Just shake it, then watch the shimmer!

Data.Name: Lucid Absinthe Supérieure
Data.Description: Lucid recalls the rich tradition of Absinthe, and is crafted using a full measure of Grande Wormwood, Green Anise, Sweet Fennel and other fine European herbs traditionally used in making fine Absinthe.

Data.Name: Efe Klasik Raki Fresh Grapes
Data.Description: Manufactured In Turkey, Efe Raki Provides A Traditional Blend Of Only The Finest Grapes And Green Anise. Efe Raki Is A Mandatory Selection For Families Of Turkey.

Data.Name: Dr. McGillicuddy's Butterscotch
Data.Description: Smoother than butter, the Doctor offered this classic flavor to mellow the saloon's most prickly patrons. A sip of this spirit has been known to turn curmudgeons into Casanovas.

Data.Name: Dr. McGillicuddy's Mentholmint
Data.Description: Dr. McGillicuddy was known to be quite the matchmaker, and he used his refreshing Mentholmint spirit to “encourage socialization” at the Shady Eye Saloon. It’s also great for covering beer breath!

Data.Name: Disaronno Trussardi Amaretto
Data.Description: "For the 2019 New Year celebrations, Disaronno is ready to amaze again with a new Limited Edition: 'Disaronno Wears Trussardi', once again choosing the Italian lifestyle brand to dress its trademark bottle. Trussardi’s typical texture is combined with the Greyhound monogram and the unmistakable shape of the Disaronno bottle, with fuchsia, green and light blue brush strokes framing the signature label." —Producer

Data.Name: Deauville Triple Sec
Data.Description: Clear with a bright platinum blue cast. Mild dreamsicle aromas and flavors with a glycerous sweet light to medium body and a simple syrup and candied orange zest finish.

Data.Name: Deauville Sour Apple Liqueur
Data.Description: The makers of Deauville Cordials, combine natural apple flavors in special formulas for delicious drinks in the French tradition. All natural flavor.

Data.Name: Celtic Crossing Liqueur
Data.Description: Celtic Crossing Liqueur celebrates Irish heritage. It was named in honor of the millions of Irish who have crossed the seas to settle around the world. A product of Ireland.

Data.Name: Caffo Sambuca Secolare
Data.Description: Made with the finest Calabrian Elderflower to reveal an aromatic anise & licorice flavor. The taste lingers, leaving a tingling sensation on the palate that is bursting with flavor. Fruitier and higher in alcohol than its cousin Anisette, this Sambuca is still 100% natural with no color or flavor added.

Data.Name: Borghetti Caffe Liqueur
Data.Description:
Strong palate, sweet and smooth taste, vigour, passion.

Borghetti is much more than a liqueur. It is an attraction arising from the embrace of the strong and enveloping palate of real espresso coffee with that warm and sharp of alcohol.

From a recipe of premium coffees consisting of the better selections of Arabia and Robusta, expertly mixed in huge espresso coffee-makers, Caffé Borghetti even today reflects the original process of an old recipe invented by Ugo Borghetti in 1860.

Drink it by itself, neat or on ice - also mixed as a base of long-drinks or sophisticated cocktails.

Data.Name: Baileys Strawberry & Cream
Data.Description: Perfect blend of delightful ripe strawberry flavor and the taste of delicious vanilla combined with the luscious Irish Cream found in Bailey's.

Data.Name: Baileys Almande
Data.Description: A delicious and light tasting spirit from Baileys made with real almondmilk. This smooth spirit blends the luscious, nutty flavors of real almondmilk and real vanilla to create a versatile drink. Serve over crushed ice or mix with coconut water for a delicious summer cocktail.

Data.Name: 99 Peppermint Schnapps
Data.Description: Peppermint Schnapps!

Data.Name: St. Elder Elderflower Liqueur
Data.Description: Pale yellow straw color. Aromas of lychee, yellow plum, elderflower, and medicinal bark with a soft, lightly tannic, sweet medium body and a tangy, honeyed spiced pear, pepper, and peach brandy accented finish.

Data.Name: Patron XO Cafe Liqueur
Data.Description: Patrón XO Cafe is a dry, low-proof coffee liqueur that’s a blend of Patrón Silver and the essence of fine coffee. It’s excellent for sipping, mixed in cocktails or as a dessert ingredient.

Data.Name: Limoncino Dell'isola Lemoncello
Data.Description: Limuni, the South Limoncello is made from an alcoholic lemon peels untreated, matured under the warm sun of Calabria. Lemons, from farms located near the Distillery Gruner, are processed the same day of collection. To get the infusion of Limuni is used only the most aromatic of the fruit that is the yellow part of the rind (epicarp) infused in neutral alcohol.

Data.Name: Grand Marnier Cordon Rouge
Data.Description: Created in 1880 by founder Louis-Alexandre Marnier Lapostolle, Grand Marnier Cordon Rouge is a premium blend of cognacs with wild tropical oranges from the Caribbean. Louis-Alexandre’s vision of blending the essence of wild tropical oranges sourced from Haiti with fine cognac from France was unconventional and truly the earliest form of spirits innovation of its time. Grand Marnier Cordon Rouge is a versatile spirit that can be enjoyed on the rocks or neat, yet exceptionally delicious in cocktails.

Data.Name: Amarula Cream Liqueur
Data.Description: A mixture of African wild marula fruit and fresh cream, this smooth, creamy liqueur is fruity and nutty. With hints of sweet cream, honey, caramel and toasted walnuts all folded into a full body for intense flavor. San Francisco World Spirits Competition 2017 Gold Winner.

Data.Name: Jagermeister
Data.Description: Dark, bold and packed with intense flavor, Jägermeister is unlike any liqueur you've ever sipped before. Originally a celebratory drink for hunters (hence the "jäger"), it's the ideal drink to mark every big win — or even a well-deserved weekend. Jäger is 70 proof, so you know this liqueur means business.

Data.Name: Lemon Hart 151 Proof Rum
Data.Description: A rich, well-rounded amber rum of oak with enticing hints of brown sugar, dried fruits, caramel, spices vanilla and baked apples that merry well into a smooth, velvety warm finish. Enjoy in a cocktail.

Data.Name: Kirk and Sweeney 12 Year Old Dominican Rum
Data.Description: Aged for twelve years in American oak casks, this Dominican rum earned a score of 95 points from Wine Enthusiast, which called it one of the Top 50 Spirits.

Data.Name: Flor De Cana 12 Year Centenario Gold Rum
Data.Description: This stunning amber rum is full-bodied, with a rich complexity of flavors and a smooth finish that stays with you, long after the swallow. The 18 year Centenario Gold is almost two decades in the making, and you can taste the craftsmanship and tradition in every drop. Palate: A rich entry leads to a viscous, dryish, full-bodied palate with dark chocolate, caramel, roasted nuts, and brown spice flavors. Finishes with a long, charred oak, vanilla, and burnt nut fade.

Data.Name: Captain Morgan White Rum
Data.Description: Five times distilled means five times the fun. Captain Morgan White Rum is as smooth as the Captain himself, and it definitely tastes better. Try this blend mixed into a tropical shot or as a substitute in any of your favorite cocktails.

Data.Name: Captain Morgan Coconut Rum
Data.Description: Sweet, delicate and creamy taste of fresh coconut balanced with rum notes of vanilla, brown spice, citrus and molasses. Sweet full bodied finish. Enjoy on the rocks or create a tropical cocktail.

Data.Name: Captain Morgan Rum Apple Mash
Data.Description: "750ML CAPTAIN MORGAN APPLE SMASH BLENDS OUR CARIBBEAN RUM WITH A BURST OF GREEN APPLE FLAVOR THAT IS SURE TO BE A FAVORITE AMONGST THE CREW. THIS TASTES DELICIOUS AS A CHILLED SHOT, A MIXED SHOT, OR SIMPLY MIXED WITH CLUB SODA FOR A FRESH TASTING COCKTAIL." - Bacardi

Data.Name: Bacardi Orange Rum
Data.Description: Bacardi Orange is a carefully crafted product that infuses Bacardi rum with the essence of Mandarin Oranges from Sicily, Valencia Oranges from Florida and Dancy Tangerines from Brazil, Israel and Florida.

Data.Name: Bacardi Black Razz Rum
Data.Description: Bacardi Black Razz features Bacardi's juiciest raspberry flavor yet, and enhances it with a hint of black sapote, a fruit that hails form Mexico and has a mild chocolate-like taste.

Data.Name: Atlantico Platino Rum
Data.Description:
Atlantico Platino White Rum is a fine, easy to drink white rum with subtle tones of mint and herbal flavors and a pleasant sweetness.

The nose is clean, sweet and fruity - bananas notes. The Palate is creamy and sweet with a hint of mint - chocolate mint creams - with some herbal notes. Finish with lingering herbs and a touch of chocolate. Nice rum and great in all manner of Rum cocktails.

Data.Name: Ron Zacapa Centenario Sistema Solera 23 Rum
Data.Description: An awesome rum – winner of a Platinum medal and ranked in First Place by the prestigious Beverage Testing Institute in Chicago, with a whopping 97 points. Interestingly, now that industry giants Diageo are distributing Zacapa, the '23 years old' age statement has suddenly been dropped and replaced with a somewhat more plausible claim – the rums used are aged between 6 and 23 years old and are blended together in a solera.

Data.Name: Diplomatico Mantuano Rum
Data.Description: Mantuano is a replacement for Diplomatico's Reserva Rum. A rich and rounded Venezuelan rum, this is delicious stuff, with smooth sweet fruitiness and a silky-smooth mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Captain Morgan Black Cask 100 Proof Spiced Rum
Data.Description: Legend has it, the pirates of old stored their high proof rum in charred oak casks in order to give it a smooth mellow taste. Today this tradition lives on in Captain Morgan Black Cask 100 Proof Spiced Rum, a secret blend of Caribbean rums and select spices which brings out the intensity of rum in all its original full-flavored glory.A firm favorite with the Captain, it's specially crafted to taste great with cola or as a shot.

Data.Name: Bacardi Oakheart Rum
Data.Description: Bacardi Oakheart is a spiced rum-based spirit and is so-called because some of the rums are matured in ex-bourbon oak casks. Notes of brown sugar, honey and burnt vanilla custard with a short, lightly cinnamony finish.

Data.Name: Appleton Estate Signature Blend Rum
Data.Description:
Appleton Estate Signature Blend is adored for its spicy, caramel, cinnamon and orange zest flavor notes.

This Rum is carefully distilled at Appleton Estate distillery, Jamaica.

Nose / Aroma / Smell
Toasted orange zest, spice cake, and marshmallow 
 
Flavor / Taste / Palate
Oranges, apricots, and mango with caramel and wood 
 
Finish
Sweet, with cinnamon and caramel

Data.Name: Admiral Nelson's Spiced Rum
Data.Description: A gold rum with a smooth, bold taste carefully blended with savory spices.

Data.Name: Goslings Black Seal Rum
Data.Description:
Goslings Black Seal Rum, made from a 150-year-old Gosling family recipe, uses the finest distillates aged in charred American oak casks. The smooth, full flavor is the result of a careful blend of aged pot still and continuous still distillates. One imparts flavor, the other yields a subtle elegance. The Beverage Testing Institute awarded Gosling’s Black Seal the Platinum Medal and Best Buy award.

80 Proof.

Data.Name: Bacardi Limón Rum
Data.Description: Named after the spanish word for lemon, Bacardi Limón is a carefully crafted product that infuses BACARDI rum with the essence of the royal family of citrus fruits: lemon, lime and grapefruit.

Data.Name: Bacardi Banana Rum
Data.Description: Bacardi Banana has aroma notes of fruit and candy banana, sweet brown, caramel and vanilla with an aftertaste of sweet banana with burnt sugar, sweet brown notes and butterscotch.

Data.Name: Bacardi Dragonberry Rum
Data.Description: A unique blend of ripe, juicy strawberries and exotic dragon fruit and Bacardi rum. Boldly flavored and refreshing. Enjoy this in citrus soda and tropic juice drinks.

Data.Name: Bacardi Coconut Rum
Data.Description: Carefully crafted product that infuses Bacardi rum with the essence of real coconut. Sweet, clean and refreshing. Great in coke or in tropical juice based drinks.

Data.Name: Angry Orchard Crisp Apple Cider
Data.Description: Angry Orchard Crisp Apple Cider has a bright, crisp apple flavor, just like biting into a fresh apple. It is a perfect balance of sweetness and bright acidity from culinary apples and dryness of traditional cider making apples, resulting in a complex, yet refreshing, hard cider.

Data.Name: Strongbow Gold Apple Cider
Data.Description: Strongbow Gold Apple Cider has a wonderful transparent gold color, a rich and complex aromatic array dominated by several varieties of apple and a refreshing texture with a true balance between first acidity, sharpness and sourness; and then sweetness and softness.

Data.Name: Magners Original Irish Cider
Data.Description:
A unique irish style cider made with 17 varieties of apples and a similar fermentation style to wine, for a fruity, complex character. Famous as the original over-ice brand.

 4.5% ABV

Data.Name: Wild Basin Boozy Sparkling Water Variety Pack
Data.Description:
Enjoy This Summer Variety Pack Oscar Blues Has To Offer. Includes:

Classic Lime

Cucumber Peach

Melon Basil

Lemon Agave Hibiscus

Data.Name: Victory Brewing Sour Monkey Cans
Data.Description:
Aroma is very varied with lemon, sour, and mild brettanomyces notes. Flavor follows with a tart acidity. Not dry as it finishes with a malty grain flavor.

9.5% ABV

Data.Name: Twisted Tea Hard Iced Tea Original Cans
Data.Description: Twisted Tea is brewed with real tea for a natural, refreshing flavor.

Data.Name: Twisted Tea Half & Half Cans
Data.Description: Twisted Tea Half & Half is brewed with real tea for a natural, refreshing flavor. Half hard tea, half hard lemonade.

Data.Name: Truly Wild Berry Spiked Seltzer
Data.Description:
Naturally sweet flavors of juicy California strawberries, raspberries & Marion blackberries.
Serving: 12 oz. slim can
ABV: 5%
Calories: 100
Sugars: 1 g
Carbs: 2 g
Gluten free

Data.Name: Spiked Seltzer Cape Cod Cranberry
Data.Description: Spiked Seltzer Cape Cod Cranberry has a unique combination of bright and refreshing taste and great nutritional claims - 0 grams of sugar and 90 calories per 12 oz can and 0 grams of sugar and 120 calories per 16 oz can.

Data.Name: Four Loko Watermelon
Data.Description: Four Loko makes sure Watermelon is always in season with this sweet and juicy flavor. A night with Watermelon Four Loko is like a summer fling – always unpredictable and the memories last forever.

Data.Name: Four Loko Gold
Data.Description: Tastes like Gold. Not much more we can say.

Data.Name: Four Loko Fruit Punch
Data.Description: Four Loko Fruit Punch blends together everyone’s favorite fruit flavors for one incredibly delicious drink. Cheers to the stories in the making and the nights you'll never forget.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Spiked Sparkling Seltzer Variety Pack
Data.Description: A 12 pack of 12oz seltzers. A delicious blend of crisp refreshing taste and bubbly carbonation making it the ideal drink that is perfect after work or on a bright summer day.

Data.Name: Nauti Hard Seltzer Watermelon
Data.Description: A delicate kiss of juicy, farm fresh watermelons with a crisp and effervescent finish.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ice Green Apple
Data.Description: Crisp, juicy green apple flavor. Not too sweet, and not too tart.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ice Screwdriver
Data.Description: A line of malt beverages inspired by classic freshly made mixed drinks. One of the latest and tastiest additions, this ready-to-drink malt beverage boasts a classic Screwdriver taste perfectly blended to appease your citrus cravings. Chill and enjoy Smirnoff Screwdriver straight from the bottle or in a glass over ice.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ice Tropical Fruit
Data.Description: Smirnoff Ice Tropical Fruit is packed with an invigorating blend of zesty, fruit flavors that dance across the palette with every delicious sip. With its tangy, fresh blend of irresistible fruit flavors, SMIRNOFF ICE Tropical Fruit is sure to transport your mind to an island paradise.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ice Mango
Data.Description: Smirnoff Ice brings you a new popular flavor - Mango. Add some fiesta to your next party with this fresh and tangy new flavor.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ice
Data.Description:
What does Smirnoff Ice taste like? Think citrus. The original malt beverage has natural lemon and lime flavors, so it's crisp, zesty and refreshing. If you're in the mood for something fruitier, try one of the many available Smirnoff Ice flavors.

How can you make sure you're enjoying your Smirnoff Ice to the fullest? Buy Smirnoff Ice online through Drizly. Have it delivered to your door or pickup in store. Then, simply chill, pop the top and enjoy.

Data.Name: Mike's Hard Strawberry Lemonade
Data.Description: Mike’s Hard Strawberry Lemonade is our refreshing take on the classic strawberry lemonade.  We combine the taste of juicy, freshly picked strawberries with the tartness of lemonade, making it a refreshing favorite for any occasion.

Data.Name: Mike's Hard Cranberry Lemonade
Data.Description: Sweet and tart flavors settle on opposite sides of the taste spectrum. But right in the middle is Mike's Hard Cranberry Lemonade. From the bog to the orchard, the perfect flavor combination is together at last!

Data.Name: Mike's Hard Tropical Mango Lemonade
Data.Description: Mike’s Hard Mango tastes of fresh mangos and just the right sweetness, making it a refreshing favorite for any occasion.

Data.Name: White Claw Lime
Data.Description: White Claw Natural Lime is the perfect blend of seltzer water, the cleanest tasting alcohol base, and a hint of lime.

Data.Name: Two Roads Dry And Mighty Brut IPA
Data.Description:
This emerging Brut IPA style borrows its name and some of its characteristics from the champagne world - primarily from the word “Brut” which connotes “very dry.”

Dry & Mighty Brut IPA sits at 6.8% with a provocatively citrusy aroma balanced with robust yet refined noble hop character and an effervescent champagne-like mouthfeel.

It is a sophisticated IPA created in the tony acres of Stratford, CT. That might make you want to raise your pinky finger as you toast friends old and new. Bully for you!

Data.Name: Epic Brewing Tart 'n Juicy Sour IPA
Data.Description: "We've combined the clean, puckering tartness of kettle souring with an abundance of juicy, citrus-driven hops to create a beer that’s the best of both worlds - Tart n' Juicy Sour IPA." - Epic Brewing

Data.Name: Founders All Day IPA Cans
Data.Description: The beer you've been waiting for. Keeps your taste satisfied while keeping your senses sharp. An all day IPA naturally brewed with a complex array of malts, grains and hops. Balanced for optimal aromatic and a clean finish. Founders All Day IPA is the perfect reward for an honest day's work and the ultimate companion to celebrate life's simple pleasures, and Tapster's happy to bring it to you.

Data.Name: Exhibit A Brewing The Cat's Meow IPA
Data.Description:
Aroma: “Orange-pineapple smoothie, touch of lemon, melon, mango, grapefruit. Low pine resin/herbal character. Really nice sweetness, similar to cotton candy, comes through as you dig more into the aroma.”

Flavor: “Melon and mango dominate up front, then chewy and juicy with a strong orange and pineapple presence. Finishes with a softness typical of the style. Hops are complex but there’s slightly too much bitterness to let the rest of the ingredients shine through. Medium-intense fruit flavors from hops and esters.”

Overall: “Fun recipe. The aroma is spot on with this tropical and melon aroma that is really inviting. That carries through in the flavor, but the hops bitterness slightly overpowers the complexities offered in the aroma and upfront flavor. Enjoyable. I would order another pint.”

Data.Name: Three's Brewing Pyrrhic Victory Wild Ale
Data.Description: Rustic Funk, Sweet Tart, Chardonnay Barrel, Sour Grape, Tangy. Brewed in Collaboration with Nøgne Ø. American Wild Ale.

Data.Name: Grim Artisanal Ales Midheaven
Data.Description: Midheaven is so named because it is an intersection, the best of both worlds.  Blended from 50% stainless-steel mixed culture ale and 50% golden sour aged in red wine barrels, then refermented on apricots, this beer is complex, clean, and elegant. It reveals flavors of juicy apricots and sour candy, with a sustained fruity-tart finish laden with subtle oak tannins.

Data.Name: Graft Shared Universe
Data.Description: Worlds Apart is the first of a two part collaboration with Ontario based Revel Cider. A cider that challenges both the modern and traditionalist cidermaking methods. Worlds Apart was spontaneously fermented on Gewurztraminer grape skins, blended with red & white wine grape concentrate & ferment to dryness.

Data.Name: Snowdrift Cider Co. Seckel Perry
Data.Description: Made 100% from specialty Seckel pears, this rich and full-bodied perry has a subtle sparkle and flavors of ripe pear, vanilla, allspice, honey & coconut. A wonderful introduction to the sophisticated world of perry.

Data.Name: Downeast Cider Original Blend
Data.Description: The Original Blend is made from freshly pressed Maine apples because we believe in making the best product we possibly can. We also like to support local agriculture. We use Red Delicious, Yellow Delicious, McIntosh, Cortland, and Gala apples in our cider.

Data.Name: Yuu Baal Reposado Espadin Mezcal
Data.Description: Grupo Yuu Baal a 100% Mexican owned company, a social enterprise that highlights the traditions of the native Oaxacan producers of Mezcal, that of which the complete process of production is artisanal infusing each of its products the mystical, the exotic, and the absolutely delightful taste makes this majestic drink. The quality of the “magueys” begins in the earth and looking after it as well, this means that the complete cycle of the production, the planting cutting and distillation, are done manually, all with absolute respect for our environment. A unique Golden color, full of body and aroma, with a distinguished taste of woods and dried fruits, ideal for the curious palate yearning to find a perfect mix of the natural and a bouquet of lightly smoked woods.

Data.Name: Wahaka Mezcal Espadín
Data.Description:
The embodiment of traditional mezcal. Straight or mixed, the balance of smoke and sweetness mark the start to your mezcal adventure. Wahaka Espadín agave is exclusively grown and tended on our own estate.

80 Proof.

Data.Name: Casamigos Mezcal Joven
Data.Description:
"We've created a mezcal that is as good as our tequila. Casamigos Mezcal is uniquely smooth, easy to drink and smoked to perfection." (- George Clooney and Rande Gerber)

Casamigos Mezcal is balanced and elegant, offering harmonious hints of tamarind, pomegranate, banana and mango. Fresh herbal mint aromas, dried oregano and thyme lend character to the mezcal. The delicate tones of smoke, hints of licorice and mineral nuances lead to a long silky finish.

Data.Name: Meiomi Chardonnay
Data.Description: Smooth, opulent layers of pineapple and lemon peel are heightened by sweet smells of honey, almonds, baking spices, and subtle custard notes. The full flavors are highlighted by succulent acidity and a clean, mineral-driven finish.

Data.Name: Maison Willm Pinot Blanc Reserve
Data.Description: A pale yellow with a fresh and floral nose reminiscent of elderflower; notes of gooseberries. The attack is supple. Fresh, dry and easy to drink, it goes well with Alsatian specialties (tarte flambée, charcuterie).

Data.Name: Lindeman's Bin 85 Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: An amalgam of floral and tropical notes with distinctive green apple and nashi pear flavors.

Data.Name: Yaegaki Sake
Data.Description: This fruity, dry Junmai Daiginjo has a delicate and brilliantly aromatic character. The aroma of green apples and Asian pear with a hint of resin complements its smooth and refreshing taste. Drink it chilled!

Data.Name: Makiri Sake
Data.Description:
Made with the "Kimoto" traditional method. Clean and deep flavor.
Sharp aftertaste with extra dryness. Perfect pairing with seafood or sushi.

Data.Name: Jinro Chamisul Green Grape Soju
Data.Description:
Also known as korean vodka it has a very smooth taste. It’s a clear distilled liquor made from rice and the most popular type of alcoholic drink in korea. Soju is originally from korea where it was first distilled around the 14th century. Unlike vodka soju has a natural hint of botanicals that can make for a smoother taste as opposed to vodka which can sometimes come off as harsh at the end. It is also not only lower in calorie than vodka but it is also lower in proof. 
Sweet green grape meets morning dew for the best flavor fruit juice in soju is becoming more popular and jinro green grape has unique green grape flavor and taste that everyone can enjoy. Easy to drink with an alcohol content of 13% it has such a clean and fresh flavor that will capture your heart.

Data.Name: Gekkeihan Zipang Sparkling Sake
Data.Description: Share a different kind of Sake with friends at your favorite BYOB sushi restaurant. Gekkeikan breaks away from tradition and offers a lighter and sweeter drink with a touch of carbonation. The 14-proof Zipang Sparkling Sake has been infused with tropical fruits to give it a clean and refreshing finish that is sure to please even the most discriminating aficionados.

Data.Name: Miyozakura "Panda" Junmai Sake Cup
Data.Description: A delightful and delicious Junmai that is light, dry and refreshing. From the Chubu region in the Gifu prefecture, this is a saké to enjoy with anything and everything. The Panda design makes an excellent gift.

Data.Name: Yuki Nigori White Peach Unfiltered Sake
Data.Description: This sake has a refreshing and sweet aroma of white peach. With Nigori's mellow body and smooth texture, this sake is unique and delightful!

Data.Name: Hiro Junmai Ginjo Sake Blue
Data.Description: Inspired by the ancient recipe of Hiroemon Takeda, the renowned Samurai and Japanese Sake connoisseur, Hiro is crafted by our own Toji (Master Brewer) using only specially polished rice from the Murakami plain in the Niigata Region. Hiro Blue is a new super premium Japanese Sake that bridges the heritage of the past with the way we drink today.

Data.Name: Kukusui Junmai Ginjo
Data.Description: The clear nectar contained in this gorgeous blue bottle will impress upon you a gentle, fruity aroma and a light dry finish. A charming aspect of Kikusui Junmai Ginjo is that that it draws out the inner flavors of accompanying dishes, however there is no single style of cuisine with which it absolutely must be paired. A fine choice for restaurants and beginners to sake.

Data.Name: Kikusui Funaguchi Ginjo Nama Genshu
Data.Description:
Limited Edition Funaguchi "New-Rice New-Sake" "Shinmai-Shinshu" has arrived! Brewed using 100% newly harvested, locally grown Niigata Gohyakumangoku rice, this is a Funaguchi Experience you can only get your hands on once a year.
A rich and electrifyingly vivid treat for lovers of super fresh namazake.

Data.Name: Jinro Chamisul Grapefruit Soju
Data.Description: Jinro Chamoisul Grapefruit has found a growing following among female consumers of Jinro Soju. Infused with fresh, sweet-tasting grapefruit and having a lower alcohol volume, this Soju represents a new twist on a Korean favorite. By achieving sales of 7.8 million bottles per month shortly after its launch, Jinro Chamisul Grapefruit has become the most popular fruit infused soju in Korea.

Data.Name: Dassai 50 Junmai Daiginjo Nigori Sake
Data.Description:
Rather than saké that will get someone drunk, or saké that will sell the most, Asahishuzo's aim is to create saké for tasting - to brew saké that is truly delicious and enjoyable for all. Their brand Dassai is the personification of this philosophy. We must note, however, that they have no intention of brewing elusive phantom saké that doesn't sell. This brewery makes some of the most popular and universally relatable saké in the world today.

The palate and aroma are both lively and refreshing. Unlike most other Nigori, this saké is not too sweet and leaves a lighter finish. This is truly a Junmai Daiginjo Nigori Saké with expert balance between sweetness and dryness

Data.Name: Chum Churum Apple Soju
Data.Description: This grapefruit flavored soju is very fruity and smooth. It’s a little sweeter and not as harsh as regular soju, with alcoholic content at 13%. A very enjoyable drink for any occasions.

Data.Name: Choya Umeshu
Data.Description: From olden times on to the present day, UME-fruit liqueur, Umeshu (Japanese Plum Wine) has been a familiar beverage in Japanese households well known and loved for its relaxing effect as well as its usefulness for keeping healthy. Because of the faint aroma, well-balanced acidity and sweetness of UME-fruit liqueur, Umeshu(Japanese Plum Wine), it is said to be one of the most delicious liquors in the world.

Data.Name: Herradura Ultra Anejo Tequila
Data.Description: Casa Herradura's Añejo tequila provides the base for Herradura Ultra. The Añejo is blended with premium Extra Añejo that has been aged for up to 49 months in American White Oak barrels. A hint of agave nectar is added before the liquid is filtered using our unique distillation process creating a rich, crystal-clear tequila with a full-bodied flavor.

Data.Name: Herradura Silver Tequila
Data.Description: "Tequila Herradura is all natural, estate grown and estate bottled. Aged for 45 days in white oak barrels, this 100 percent blue agave tequila is a phenomenon unto itself. This bright tequila is magnificent from bottle to glass to palate. It carries its own light. Absolutely perfect for cocktails."

Data.Name: Casamigos Reposado Tequila
Data.Description: Casamigos Reposado Tequila, aged for 7 months in premium American white oak barrels, is soft, slightly oaky with hints of caramel and cocoa and has a silky texture with a medium to long finish.

Data.Name: Casamigos Anejo Tequila
Data.Description: Aged for 14 months. Pure and complex aroma, with soft caramel and vanilla notes. Perfect balance of sweetness from the Blue Weber agaves, with subtle hints of spice and barrel oak, with a lingering smooth finish.

Data.Name: Corona Light
Data.Description: Corona Light is made for those days when all you want to do is lounge in the sun. A lighter bodied take on the original Corona Extra, it is in no way lighter in anything else. This Mexican-made lager is just as ready for beachside vibes or the ultimate staycation as it's counterpart, but with a few less calories to worry about. For those seeking an alternative to the domestic light lagers, for something with a bit of that south of the border flair, for something perfect with the addition of a lime, there is no other decision to be made.

Data.Name: Firestone Walker Mind Haze IPA
Data.Description:
From the coast of California comes Mind Haze, a free-spirited beer made to elevate your perceptions—juicy yet balanced, hazy yet lasting, and loaded with an imaginative array of tropical hop flavors.

In the words of Brewmaster Matt Brynildson, “Mind Haze offers the best of what you expect from a hazy IPA. But we’re going about it a little differently, and that’s what gives Mind Haze its own unique signature. We’re finally ready to do a hazy IPA the Firestone way.”

ABV: 6.2%

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water Lemon Orange Vanilla
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water Ruby Red Grapefruit
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water Cranberry Lime
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water Lime
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Polar Seltzer Water Lemon
Data.Description: Why be flat when you can sparkle? Enjoy naturally calorie-free refreshment made with nothing but water, bubbles and natural fruit essence.

Data.Name: Night Shift Brewing Night Fever
Data.Description: A limited release stout from Night Shift with chocolate and coffee infusions

Data.Name: Night Shift Brewing Mirage DIPA
Data.Description:
"Double India pale ale brewed with Vic Secret and Simcoe

Upon first glance, this beer appears too good to be true. Can it really be there just on the horizon? A glowing, golden double IPA that's perfectly balanced between tropical juiciness and resiny dankness? Let us assure you that it's real, and it's on the way to quench your thirst."

Data.Name: Night Shift Brewing Santilli IPA
Data.Description:
Night Shift's flagship American IPA is named after Santilli Highway, the street in Everett that the brewery calls home. This beer was first brewed in 2015 as a batch of the Morph rotating series. This batch was too good to become a distant memory, and thus, Santilli was born.

Consistent, accessible, and rooted in the spirit of innovation, Santilli makes a great addition to whatever your craft may be. In 2016, Night Shift was honored to take home the Bronze medal in the American-style India pale ale category at the World Beer Cup for Santilli.

Data.Name: Night Shift Brewing Morph IPA
Data.Description: At Night Shift Brewing,  change is a good thing. Meet Morph, their ever transforming IPA series. With new recipes from batch to batch, Morph allows the brewers to experiment with different hops and malts. The result? A wide range of IPA varieties all under one name.

Data.Name: Exotico Blanco 100% Agave Tequila
Data.Description: Premium, unaged 100% blue agave tequila produced and crafted in the highlands and lowlands of Jalisco. This perfectly clear and crisp Blacnco, has spicy undertones and a robust taste of fresh agave, hints of pepper, herbal notes and finishes with a fresh wave of heat followed by a balanced spice. Exotico Tequila Blanco is a tequila you can appreciate with a sip or easily use to elevate any drink.

Data.Name: Don Julio Reposado Tequila
Data.Description: Don Julio himself has produced premium tequilas for more than 50 years. He still personally oversees the planting and harvesting of the blue agave so only the best are hand-selected and used in his Reposado Tequila.

Data.Name: Whitehaven Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Embodies the quintessential Marlborough style – full-flavored and medium-bodied with fragrant notes of peach, gooseberry and ripe tropical fruit, followed by freshly cut herb undertones. Showcasing a brilliant straw color, this elegant wine refreshes the palate with a long, clean finish.

Data.Name: RumHaven Coconut Caribbean Rum
Data.Description: Welcome to paradise. Kick back, relax & drink in the sunshine. This premium coconut rum liqueur with natural flavors is made with real coconut water and cane sugar to send your senses on a tropical vacation. Created by one of the best rum brands, experience an unforgettable natural flavor that is so refreshing it’s like a drink with an ocean view. Get a boarding pass for your taste buds and enjoy a little taste of Haven.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo White Sangria Margarita
Data.Description: Perfect for hosting a party or an outdoor excursion, just freeze and serve.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Watermelon Margarita
Data.Description: Made with Jose Cuervo Gold Tequila, triple sec and fresh watermelon flavors, and pre mixed for your convenience and enjoyment. Perfect for hosting a party or an outdoor excursion, just freeze and serve.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Strawberry Lime Margarita
Data.Description:
Ready to drink. 19.9 proof, 9.95% alc by vol.
Made with Jose Cuervo tequila and triple sec.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Red Sangria Margarita
Data.Description: Authentic Jose Cuervo Sangria Margaritas are a blend of the brand’s Classic Lime Margarita, made with real tequila, wine and sangria fruit flavors. The Red Sangria Margarita has red wine, citrus, apple and pomegranate.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Pink Lemonade Margarita
Data.Description: Authentic Cuervo Margarita Pink Lemonade is an exciting Margarita experience, blending the classic Margarita flavor with the refreshing taste of Pink Lemonade.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Classic Lime Margarita Mix
Data.Description: Just add Jose Cuervo for the perfect margarita. Served on the rocks or frozen with crushed ice. Manufactured in Mexico.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Light Margarita
Data.Description: Jose Cuervo Light Margarita Classic Lime Ready To Serve is premixed perfectly with Jose Cuervo Especial Gold Tequila, packing the same great taste as the original but with fewer than 95 calories per serving and no guilt. Authentic Light is made ready to serve, enjoy the delicious taste of a top shelf tequila cocktail to enjoy at home, a staple in at home entertaining.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Margarita Minis
Data.Description: Four 200ml bottles. Authentic Cuervo Light Margaritas offers the same great taste as the original, but with fewer than 95 calories per serving.

Data.Name: Glenlivet 12 Year Scotch w/ 2 Glasses
Data.Description:
One of the most famous malts in the world. Glenlivet 12yo has a soft smooth balance of sweet summer fruits and the floral notes of spring flowers. 

A perfect gift set.

Data.Name: Giroux Grenadine
Data.Description: This is a non-alcoholic flavoring syrup manufactured by Giroux.

Data.Name: Fu-Ki Sake Plum
Data.Description:
Fu-Ki Plum Wine is made following a process that has been cultivated for hundreds of years in Japan.
It is delicate and light, with well-balanced acidity, and a long aftertaste.
Fu-Ki Plum wine is an excellent aperitif, as well as a delicious dessert wine. It will also strike a wonderful balance with many rich tasting foods, including Asian specialties.
It can be enjoyed straight or chilled, or as part of elegant, contemporary cocktails.

Fu-Ki Plum’s character is best described by its mellow taste and well balanced acidity.

ABV: 9%

Data.Name: Freixenet Ice Rosé
Data.Description: With its stylish bottle, the new Freixenet Ice Rosé has been specially blended to be enjoyed in a large glass over big ice cubes. It's the perfect extra refreshing drink for those long days chilling in the garden or for relaxed dinners with friends. This is a cava that talks Mediterranean spirit wherever you are.

Data.Name: Freixenet Cordon Negro Rosé
Data.Description: Freixenet Cordon Negro Rosé's bright, fruity personality goes down smooth and finishes soft. Wine lovers' senses will be enveloped in the aromas of fresh raspberry, vanilla and fruit cocktail found in the bubbly blend. This elegant cava is in a class by itself and pairs delightfully well with decadent desserts.

Data.Name: 4 Roses Single Barrel Bourbon
Data.Description: An outstanding single barrel bourbon from Four Roses. Beautifully balanced and smooth as silk, this is sweet, rich and potent with very appealing menthol notes, precious woods and delicious spices.

Data.Name: 4 Roses Small Batch Bourbon
Data.Description: A terrific small-batch bourbon from Four Roses - and in this case, Small Batch means just that – only four casks are used in the construction of each release. Sweet and spicy, with a generous dash of vanilla, this is a treat.

Data.Name: Flaming Leprechaun Cinnamon Spirit
Data.Description: Flaming Leprechaun Cinnamon Irish Spirit combines the key elements of traditional Irish distilling practices with those of modern blending and flavouring. The cinnamon drink's unparalleled taste is based on an old homemade recipe that has been handed down from generation to generation. More than one thousand hours have been spent refining and improving this formula so that it can now be brought into the modern age for the enjoyment of everyone.

Data.Name: Felipe II Brandy
Data.Description:
This highly popular Solera brandy is highly mixable and is delicious with soda, cola, juices or milk. Smooth and versatile, great for cocktails and shots.

Country: Spain

Data.Name: Dulce Vida Tequila Pineapple Jalapeno
Data.Description: Made with real Pineapple and Jalapeño, our Dulce Vida Pineapple Jalapeño Tequila is handcrafted from 100% blue agave, then infused and uniquely blended.

Data.Name: Dulce Vida Grapefruit Tequila
Data.Description: Dulce Vida Grapefruit Tequila is handcrafted from 100% blue agave, then infused and uniquely blended. Enjoy as a shot, on the rocks or simply add sparkling water.

Data.Name: Dulce Vida Lime Tequila
Data.Description: Dulce Vida Lime Tequila is handcrafted from 100% blue agave, then infused and uniquely blended. Enjoy as a shot, on the rocks or simply add sparkling water.

Data.Name: Dubonnet Rouge
Data.Description: Dubonnet is the nation's top selling aperitif, with a long and storied history that is enjoying renewed popularity as consumers return to "classic cocktails". Dubonnet was once the preferred beverage of the French Foreign Legion. Today, Dubonnet is available internationally in both Rouge and Blanc varieties and is a key ingredient in classic drinks such as the Dubonnet Cocktail and the Dubonnet Kiss. In the words of master mixologist Dale DeGroff, "with its rich ruby color, spicy aroma and refreshing flavors, Dubonnet embodies the best of the aperitif category."

Data.Name: Daily's Sweet & Sour Mix
Data.Description: This sweet and sour cocktail mix is made with real fruit juice. 100% Kosher.

Data.Name: Daily's Pina Colada Mix
Data.Description: Simply mix with rum and crushed ice in a blender. Classic, tropical flavor.

Data.Name: Daily's Grenadine
Data.Description: Personalize your margaritas, martinis and more with the great taste of Daily's Grenadine syrup. Daily's makes perfectly delicious cocktails every time.

Data.Name: Daily's Simple Syrup
Data.Description: Daily's Bar Syrup is our version of simple syrup that saves you the trouble of creating your own. It’s the fastest and most efficient way to add sweetness to a variety of contemporary cocktails.

Data.Name: Daily's Lime Juice
Data.Description: Daily’s Lime Juice, made with real limes, can liven up just about any classic cocktails. Be sure to keep on hand and try with new drinks.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Golden Rose Margarita
Data.Description: Jose Cuervo Golden Rosé Margarita is a ready-to-drink, bartender-quality margarita made with Jose Cuervo Tequila, Grand Marnier Orange Liquer and blended with the nost and taste of a Tradicional rosé wine. Just chill, pour and serve, or blend with ice for a new take on a "frosé."

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Golden Margarita
Data.Description: Blended with all the authentic Cuervo ingredients, Cuervo mix, Cuervo gold tequila and Grand Marnier to create the finest premixed margarita available.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Authentic Mango Margarita
Data.Description: Made with Jose Cuervo Gold Tequila, triple sec and fresh mango flavors, and pre mixed for your convenience and enjoyment. Perfect for hosting a party or an outdoor excursion, just freeze and serve.

Data.Name: Jose Cuervo Authentic Lime Margarita
Data.Description: Authentic Cuervo Margaritas, made exclusively with Cuervo Gold, are the world’s number one ready-to-serve margaritas.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Light in color, this Pinot Grigio has aromas of pineapple and pear. Complex flavors include green apple, citrus and melon. Clean soft finish.

Data.Name: CR Cellars Fortissimo
Data.Description:
In music terms, it means meaning "to be played very loud." A rather voluminous red wine, the CR Cellars Fortissimo packs power in a big bottle; fine for savory foods.

Wine from California.

Data.Name: Coppola Blue Label Merlot
Data.Description: Coppola Diamond Series Blue Label Merlot combines fruit from Napa, Sonoma and Monterey. The flavors and textures unique to each region harmonize perfectly to create a wine that has dark succulent fruit balanced by natural acidity. Intense aromatics of raspberry and blueberry lead to flavors of crushed berries, vanilla and leather, which are wrapped up in a soft, smooth tannin structure.

Data.Name: Coppola Ivory Label Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: For Coppola's Ivory Label Cabernet Sauvignon, they combine fruit from appellations as far north as El Dorado and as far south as Paso Robles where some of their vineyards experience diurnal temperature extremes, which slows the ripening process and enhances succulent flavors of fruit.

Data.Name: Confidencial Reserve Tinto Red
Data.Description: Ruby color. Wide range of complex aromas of ripe red fruits and vanilla. Some structure, in which the sensations of ripe red fruit are in evidence and very well integrated into the wood notes and fine tannins. Final velvety mouth, with some acidity and complexity.

Data.Name: Chivas Regal Mizunara
Data.Description:
Originally released for the Japanese market, this special edition of Chivas Regal blended Scotch whisky was inspired by a trip that Master Distiller Colin Scott took to Japan. Part of the blend was matured in Mizunara oak casks, which is rather rare in the whisky world but always intriguing.

Nose: White peach, toffee-coated pears and vanilla-rich cream. Subtly nutty.

Palate: Floral and sweet, though hints of baking spices bring balance and body.

Finish: Still packed with fruit, with a hint of aniseed hiding within.

Data.Name: Castello del Poggio Moscato d'Asti
Data.Description: "Golden straw in colour with a fine fizz, the wine has floral and fruity aromas with a hint of musk. Flavours of grapes, lychee and turkish delight are kept in balance by fruit acidity with some honey on the lingering finish. A lightweight easy drinking style."

Data.Name: Castello del Poggio Moscato
Data.Description: Light with an agile and elegant structure, but always compact, with medium freshness and low minerality.

Data.Name: Casal Garcia Sangria
Data.Description: Bright ruby color and a clear appearance. It is a very aromatic drink, especially the notes of freesia, apple, cinnamon and citrus. In the mouth a young and light profile, a velvety soft texture and a final intensely marked by the exuberance of its fruit.

Data.Name: Brugal XV Rum
Data.Description:
Brugal XV Reserve Exclusiva rum is distilled from fermented molasses. The blend of rums used are aged up to 8 years in used whisky and bourbon barrels. 
Lots of dark fruit, roasted cashew, cinnamon with overtones of vanilla on the body give way to the slightly viscous smoky finish.

Data.Name: Brugal 1888 Rum
Data.Description: This special edition from Dominican producer Brugal has been double-distilled and matured in American oak before a second maturation period in sherry casks to add a dose of dried fruit and leathery sweetness to the flavors.

Data.Name: Brugal Extra Viejo Rum
Data.Description: A Dominican rum recently enjoying a big upsurge in popularity in the UK after being taken on by a major drinks distributor. Brugal is a great mixing rum, with a distinctly different taste and is now an established player in the UK bar scene.

Data.Name: Brugal Especial Extra Dry Rum
Data.Description: Classic white rum from Dominican producers, Brugal, which is aged for at least one year to mellow out some of the overly intense qualities of rum straight from the still. This tasty rum is no stranger to cocktails and long drinks, not by a long shot.

Data.Name: Beefeater Pink Gin
Data.Description: A mix of Beefeater's classic London Dry Gin and natural strawberry flavour, resulting in a fresh and fruity blend of juniper, citrus and sweet strawberry flavours.

Data.Name: The Balvenie Doublewood 12 Year Whisky
Data.Description: One of the classic after-dinner malts, Balvenie Doublewood's extra complexity and richness are a result of a second maturation in fresh sherry casks. Great stuff.

Data.Name: The Balvenie Doublewood 17 Year Whisky
Data.Description:
Appearance / Colour:
Golden amber.
 
Smell / Nose / Aroma:
Honey and slightly spiced caramel.
 
Flavour / Taste / Palate:
Fruity tang throughout, some apples and pears with dried raisins, more honey and caramel that becomes a vanilla spice, oak wood becomes more apparent.
 
Finish:
Thick with vanilla and fruit, good and long.

Data.Name: Antioqueno Aguardiente
Data.Description:
Beginning with the very first sniff and all the way until the crisp concise finish, the tasty anise is the star. Drifting across the taste buds in soft clean rum, it has a creamy, light mouth-feel. Aguardiente is typically taken as a shot, but may also be utilized as a creative ingredient in many beverages; it would also pair fantastically with grilled meat, fried bread, tropical fruits or hard cheese.

Colombia's national alcoholic beverage is Aguardiente.

Data.Name: Absolut Lime
Data.Description: Each sip of Absolut Lime bursts with a tangy citrus kick of lime flavor that comes from its all-natural ingredients and no added sugars. This versatile Absolut vodka offers up the vibrant taste of fresh limes with a slightly sweet finish.

Data.Name: Harpoon UFO Georgia Peach
Data.Description: Refreshing with the right touch of sweetness, this easy-drinking and flavorful hefeweizen was first brewed with our friends in Georgia. We’re happy to bring this fresh-from-the-tree flavor to all!

Data.Name: Harpoon UFO Big Squeeze
Data.Description:
What it is: a sessionable 4.5%-ABV shandy.

What it tastes like: Focused pink grapefruit scents tickle the nose. On the tongue, this summery sipper is a little bit beer and a little bit grapefruit juice: Lightly sweet bready malts fuse nicely with slightly tart, biting pink grapefruit flavors. It’s like breakfast in a bottle.

What’s a shandy? Shandies are a blend of citrus juice (often lemonade or grapefruit juice) with a sessionable beer style.

Data.Name: Harpoon One Hazy Summer
Data.Description: The second brew, Harpoon One Hazy Summer is “tropical fruit, biscuit, and a touch of pithy citrus and features “intense aromas of citrus, berry, and tropical fruit in a hazy summer pale ale.”

Data.Name: Springdale Not Stirred: Mint Julep
Data.Description: A golden beer aged in ex-bourbon barrels on fresh mint to elegantly refreshing effect.

Data.Name: Springdale Numbstruck
Data.Description: Golden barrel-aged sour rested on szechuan peppercorns. Fresh, vibrant herbal aromas and flavors play off the refined acidity of the base beer.

Data.Name: Springdale Noonanbach
Data.Description: Oak-aged Flanders-style red in collab with Idle Hands Craft  to honor the late, great Greg Noonan with a one-of-a-kind collaboration. Proceeds from the beers will support the Greg Noonan Scholarship to the American Brewer’s Guild in Vermont.

Data.Name: Springdale Pearly Wit
Data.Description: Tart, refreshing and drinkable beyond belief. A country-style witbier, spiced with orange and coriander, that harkens to days before the onslaught of industrialized beer.

Data.Name: Springdale Pineapple Mayhem
Data.Description: Wine barrel aged golden sour dosed with pineapple juice to create a uniquely tart and tropical flavor profile.

Data.Name: Mount Gay Eclipse Rum
Data.Description:
Mount Gay is one of the oldest rum in the world. Since 1703 this rum has been hand-crafted at the same location, using the finest Barbados sugar cane and pure spring water.

Mount Gay Rum's heritage and legendary quality continue to be enjoyed by rum connoisseurs the world over.

Savour the legend of Mount Gay Rum with cola with your favourite mixer or on the rocks.

Data.Name: Myers's Original Dark Rum
Data.Description: Enjoy the unique taste of Caribbean rum with Myers's Original Dark Rum. With the initial aroma of mahogany and charred wood, our dark rum satisfies with a mildly sweet and moderately full-bodied palate of dark caramel and toasted coconut husks. Made with Jamaican molasses, our 100% fine Jamaican rum is expertly boiled, fermented and distilled using both column and pot stills. Matured for up to 4 years in white oak barrels, our rum adds a delicious kick to cocktails and traditional cooking recipes. Simply add with cola and pour over ice for a classic mixed drink.

Data.Name: Parrot Bay Coconut Rum 90 Proof
Data.Description: A beach in a bottle, this is a beautiful combination of the sweetness of coconut with the spicy perfection of Caribbean rum.

Data.Name: Passoa Passion Fruit Liqueur
Data.Description: A liqueur made from passion fruit juice. It is best served on the rocks, or mixed with chilled orange or grapefruit juice.

Data.Name: Licor Ponche Kuba Cream
Data.Description: Creamy. Delicate, sweet flavors with a lightly spiced aroma. Rich, sweet, exceptionally smooth and delicate.

Data.Name: Redemption Rye Whiskey
Data.Description: Beautiful flavored Rye Spice with light floral and citrus notes. Slight mint finish makes this great for sipping or mixing in a classic cocktail. True Rye flavor due to the 95% Rye in the mash bill.

Data.Name: Remy Martin XO Excellence
Data.Description: Remy Martin XO has a wide spectrum of aromas of late summer fruits, combined with rich floral notes of white flowers such as Jasmine. The perfect expression of fine Champagne opulence on the palate with mature flavors of juicy plums and candied oranges, plus hints of hazelnuts and cinnamon. Velvety, rich and lingering.

Data.Name: Risata Moscato d'Asti D.O.C.G.
Data.Description:
Color: Bright, straw, with light frizzante.

Nose: Fresh, bright citrus aromas with floral hints.

Palate: Slightly sweet with delicate flavors of peach and apricot.

FOOD PAIRINGS: 
Enjoy with appetizers, spicy Asian dishes, peach cobbler or simply on its own.

ALCOHOL: 5.5%

Data.Name: Sapporo Silver Draft Beer
Data.Description: Sapporo is the home of Japan's oldest brewery, and Sapporo Premium Beer is still brewed to this day with the same meticulous care and attention to detail. This unique rice beer uses quality ingredients, making for a refreshingly different drinking experience. Goes well with sushi or other Japanese fare.

Data.Name: Seagram's Lime Twisted Gin
Data.Description: Forget about slicing lime wedges. Just add some tonic water to Seagram's Lime Twisted Gin and you have a premium cocktail.

Data.Name: Seagram's Juicy Watermelon Vodka
Data.Description: Seagram's Juicy Watermelon Flavored Vodka is a refreshing watermelon flavored vodka with a smooth finish. Seagram's Vodka has been a brand consumers know and trust since 1857, representing quality and tradition. Produced with high quality American grain.

Data.Name: Seagram's Extra Smooth Vodka
Data.Description: Using only the finest American grain, Seagram's extra smooth vodka is distilled five times resulting in an exceptional award winning vodka, renowned for its unparalleled smoothness. Contains 40% alc./vol

Data.Name: Three Olives Vodka
Data.Description: Boasting a superior taste achieved through multiple distillation and filtration methods, Three Olives Vodka is sure to become your go-to brand. Three Olives Vodka was founded in London in 1998 by Guillaume Cuvelier and was acquired by Proximo Spirits in 2007. This delightful liquor is made from quadruple-distilled English winter wheat that's handcrafted for an unbeatable taste. Even if you've never been a vodka fan, Three Olives just might change your mind! The handcrafted unflavored vodka is exceptionally smooth and crisp, making it perfect for blending cocktails or serving up the ultimate martini. But the multiple flavor varieties appeal to just about anyone with a discriminating palate.

Data.Name: Tin Cup Whiskey
Data.Description:
This 84 proof American Whiskey is aged in new charred white oak American barrels and cut with rocky mountain water. It's blended and bottled in Denver, Colorado. Legally speaking, it’s bourbon, but what makes Tin Cup unique is its high rye content which gives it a bold and spicy flavor. The cap screws on and can be used for drinking. The Mash Bill is 64% corn, 32% rye, & 4% malt.

 Tincup, CO is an old mining town in Gunnison County, set on the western side of the Colorado Rockies and named for the old cups the miners would drink from

Data.Name: The Prisoner Red Blend
Data.Description: The Prisoner was created and inspired by the drinkable “mixed blacks” first made by the Italian immigrants who originally settled in the Napa Valley. Launched in 2003, The Prisoner soon became the most recognized innovative and unique Napa Valley Red Wine blend, leading the resurgence of blends by incorporating Zinfandel with the unlikely “mix” of Cabernet Sauvignon, Syrah, Petite Syrah, and Charbono. Features enticing aromas of Bing cherry, dark chocolate, clove, and roasted fig. Persistent flavors of ripe raspberry, boysenberry, pomegranate, and vanilla linger harmoniously, for a smooth and luscious finish.

Data.Name: Svedka Rose Vodka
Data.Description:
Sweet and balanced with vibrant fruit aromas
Flavors of strawberry and pineapple, complemented by notes of hibiscus and rose wine. Enjoy over the rocks with a splash of sparkling water. Made from the finest spring water and Swedish winter wheat.

Data.Name: White Horse Scotch
Data.Description: Another brand with a long and illustrious history, named after a famous Edinburgh hostelry. Containing around 40% malt whisky, White Horse has a pleasing honeyed palate accompanied by peaty undertones.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Bubbles Rose
Data.Description: Strawberry, cherry, and tropical fruit flavors combine with a touch of spice and a light, crisp finish. This sparking rosé is fun and fragrant.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Smooth Red Blend
Data.Description:
Combining two red grapes and making them get along isn’t always easy.
Sometimes the two fight, and that’s when problems arise. Luckily, Shiraz
and Grenache were made for each other. Soft, perfumed Grenache loves
hanging out with the boldly flavored, spicy Shiraz. The finished wine is
savoury but full of pure red fruits.

Data.Name: Kinky Blue Liqueur
Data.Description: Kinky Blue is a naughty infusion of super premium vodka distilled 5 times with succulent blackberry, raspberry and blueberry.

Data.Name: Kinky Pink Liqueur
Data.Description: A fusion of super premium vodka distilled with succulent mango, blood orange liqueur and passion fruit. Get Kinky. Enjoy over ice. Mix with lemon lime soda. Splash in Prosecco. Add vodka for a Kinki Martini.

Data.Name: The Kraken Black Spiced Rum
Data.Description:
Release the Kraken! And approach this drink with a strong nerve and steel resolve. The Kraken Black Spiced Rum is a notable import from Trinidad and Tobago, so named for the squid-like sea monster of myth and legend. It's a dark spiced Caribbean rum in an old-style bottle that will make anyone channel their inner pirate and sing yo-ho-ho.

The Kraken boasts a nutty scent with coffee, vanilla, cherryade and gunpowder, immediately setting the tone for a wonderful sensory experience. As for the taste, the spiced rum is almost cola-like in its vanilla-style spice. Slightly sweet, The Kraken offers hints of espresso coffee, cinnamon, creamy caramel, cloves and gingerbread. All this gives way to a long, peppery finish, which perfectly sums up the rum's spiciness. It's a satisfying, drinkable rum with a broad appeal.

Data.Name: Jameson the Cooper's Croze
Data.Description: The Cooper's Croze is part of Jamesons' The Whisky Maker series and has been selected by head cooper Ger Buckley to highlight the role wood plays in whiskey maturation. Using a combination of virgin oak, bourbon barrels and sherry casks, this has notes of vanilla, rich fruit and spice.

Data.Name: Jameson Black Barrel
Data.Description: Matured in a combination of American oak, sherry casks, and double charred bourbon barrels, Jameson Black Barrel is a blend of small batch grain and traditional Irish pot still whiskeys. Bursting with rich, complex flavors of fruit, caramel, toasted wood, and warm spice.

Data.Name: Jameson Caskmates Stout Edition
Data.Description:
Like all the best conversations, the one between Jameson’s Head of Whiskey Science and the Head Brewer of a local craft beer brewery, started at the bar. A swapping of whiskey and beer barrels soon after, resulted in Jameson Caskmates Stout Edition - triple-distilled, blended Irish Whiskey that has been patiently finished in Irish craft beer-seasoned barrels.

Nose: An initial aroma of freshly cut hay is complemented by a crisp orchard fruit character - green apples and pears, with a twist of lime zest. Mild pot still spices appear, deepening from green tea to hazelnut and milk chocolate.

Taste: The initial sweet mouth coating typical of the Irish pot still inclusion is quickly complemented by the subtle touch of hops and cocoa beans from the beer cask finish.

Finish: Long and sweet with Milk Chocolate and Butterscotch

Data.Name: 21st Amendment Sparkale
Data.Description:
Like a sparkler crackling against the sky at dusk, our sparkling rosé ale is a refreshing pop of fruit and fizz with tart flavors and a crisp finish. Crafted with apple, cranberry, peach and cherries, this ale is a reminder of life’s simple pleasures. Open a can and enjoy. This is your moment to shine.
5.5% ABV

Data.Name: 21st Amendment El Sully
Data.Description:
El sol estaba en nuestro ojos y no lo miramos bien, pero estás más cercas de el en este momento la mayoría tendrá la buena fortuna de ser.

Wait, sorry about that.

The sun was in our eyes and we did not get a good look, but you are closer to him right now than most will ever have the good fortune to be.

Who is El Sully? Grab a can of this Mexican-style lager, head to the nearest beach, even if it’s imagined, and perhaps he’ll come to you.

El Sully (the beer) is available year-round in six pack cans and on draft. El Sully (the legend) is a little harder to find.

Data.Name: Jameson Caskmates
Data.Description: A unique offering from Jameson with rich stout characteristics of coffee, cocoa, and a hint of hops. Caskmates has been aged in Jameson barrels that were used to finish Franciscan Well stout. The finish is long and sweet with milk chocolate and butterscotch.

Data.Name: Jameson Trilogy Gift Pack
Data.Description: A gift set containing three 20cl bottles of the Jameson's range - one each of the world - favorite blend, Select Reserve and Caskmates. A great gift for any Irish whiskey fan.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Carmenere
Data.Description: This variety disappeared from its place of origin in Médoc, north of Bordeaux, France following the phylloxera outbreak in the 19th century. It reappeared in Chile at the end of the 20th Century. In Casillero del Diablo Carmenere is smooth and delicate with intense color, smooth, round tannins, and attractive aromas of black currant and chocolate. Ideal with aged cheese.

Data.Name: Casillero del Diablo Rose
Data.Description: The wines is a vibrant, strawberry-pink color. Possesses a rich bouquet of sun-kissed red berries and wild raspberries, backed with hints of spice. This flavorful rose is packed with fresh and fruity flavors of blackberry and raspberry, backed by a nice backbone of acidity, and a clean, dry finish.

Data.Name: Casillero del Diablo Red Blend
Data.Description: Ripe, densely packed with black cherry and dark plum, slightly spicy, with a soft touch of bitter chocolate.

Data.Name: Casa Viva Pinot Noir
Data.Description: A juicy medium-bodied wine brimming with sweet fruit flavours. Classic ripe flavours of berry, cherry, coconut, cranberry, plum, cedar and oak! Silky textures typically balanced with spicy or floral tones.

Data.Name: Casas del Bosque Pinot Noir Reserva
Data.Description: Brick red in colour. On the nose rich notes of crushed strawberry and bramble are in evidence. In the mouth spicy notes of cinnamon are accompanied by a hint of cedar and red cherry. A well integrated oak backbone is backed-up by abundant, well-rounded tannins lending to excellent length and structure.

Data.Name: Carlo Rossi Chablis
Data.Description: 4L. This semi-dry white wine with its crisp, light taste and flavors of ripe pear can be enjoyed with grilled seafood, pasta dishes or salads.

Data.Name: Campo Viejo Rioja Reserva
Data.Description:
Ruby-red colour with a gold tinged rim.
Great balance between fruit and clear tones from the wood.
Smell is intensified to a more with the aromas that develop during aging in bottle.
Smooth and balanced on the palate with a permanent, long and full end of elegant taste.

Data.Name: Campo Viejo Rioja Tempranillo
Data.Description:
Ruby red in colour with sweet cherry aromas and silky oaky flavours. Light, smooth velvety texture. 

A typical Rioja wine with great fruit concentration. The sweet berry aromas of the Tempranillo grape mingle with the vanilla imparted by the oak. 

Aged 12 months in oak casks.

Data.Name: Callia Bella Syrah & Malbec
Data.Description: A balanced mouthfeel with flavors of raspberry, ripe cherry and chocolate. This enticing red blend has a touch of sweetness and a well-structured, smooth and silky finish.

Data.Name: Callia Alta Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Deliciously easy drinking, as the palate is soft and round with notes of peaches, tropical fruit and a hint of jasmine.

Data.Name: Callia Alta Malbec
Data.Description:
Appearance: Medium ruby with purplish tints. Aroma: Beautiful red fruits such as plums and cherries. 

Mouth Feel: A balanced mouthfeel with flavors of redcurrant and black cherry supported by sweet, round tannins. It culminates in a long finish with notes of cloves and cinnamon. 

Food Pairing: Excellent with barbecued dishes, burgers, spicy Mexican food such as quesadillas or tacos, roasted pork, duck, and honey baked ham.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Notes of melon, grapefruit, apple and lemon-grass, with a lingering soft finish.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
This ruby-colored wine has aromas that include raspberry and violets. Flavors of cherry and plum lead to a soft velvety finish. This graceful wine is multifaceted. It can be enjoyed by itself but is excellent with appetizers and main courses. 
The wine pairs with Brie, smoked salmon, roast beef, leg of lamb, duck and grilled swordfish.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Merlot
Data.Description: Forward fruit profile, including blackberry, plum and vanilla spice. The finish is long and soft with silky tannins.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Chardonnay
Data.Description: A great choice to go with a mid-week dinner, this California Chardonnay is light, bright, and soft on the palate. Simple, straightforward, with some nice tropical notes. Also excellent for making a cool, refreshing spritzer.

Data.Name: Crane Lake Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Rich color with notes of blackberry, cherry, raspberry and vanilla. Tannins are soft and layered.This wine pairs well with aged cheddar and gouda cheeses. Also try it with leg of lamb, rib eye steak or pasta in a marinara sauce.

Data.Name: Cycles Gladiator Chardonnay
Data.Description: Fresh and delicate aroma of ripe pear. Crisp and clean on the palate with layers of bright green apple, pear and citrus flavors that are impeccably balanced with nice acidity, a wisp of vanilla and a light, smooth finish.

Data.Name: Cycles Gladiator Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: The deep-hued Cycles Gladiator Cabernet Sauvignon is rich and lush, with intense red and black fruit character. Aromas of wild berries, chocolate and clove precede mouth-filling flavors of raspberry, dark cherry, cigar box and anise. Well-balanced with smooth tannins and refreshing acidity, this wine is as enjoyable sipped on its own as it is with food.

Data.Name: Cycles Gladiator Merlot
Data.Description: Sourced primarily from vineyards in Paso Robles and Arroyo Seco, this soft and plush Merlot shows aromas of crushed black plums and spicy cloves. Medium bodied on the palate, this wine balances jammy black fruits flavors with a touch of drying tannins. Additional flavors of cocoa powder and cedar show on the finish giving the wine a dark and rich character. The spicy flavors in this wine make it a nice pairing for grilled foods like Jamaican jerk chicken, or grilled pork tenderloin.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This fresh, pale green-gold wine displays distinctive grapefruit and honeydew character with hints of mineral and lemon zest. Cold fermentation and sur lie aging provide silky texture.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Flavors of ripe cherry, raspberry and plum are met by toasty oak notes that lend depth and length to the fruit-forward character of this wine. Hints of toffee and leather join a long, sweet finish that lingers well after the wine is gone.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Merlot
Data.Description: A graceful, balanced blend from several Napa Valley vineyards, this wine displays vibrant fruit character with lush aromas and flavors of black cherry, plum, mocha and spice.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Zinfandel
Data.Description: This rich, crimson colored, medium-to-full-bodied wine has generous fruit character with aromas and flavors of black cherry and fresh raspberry accented with anise.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Riesling
Data.Description: Medium-bodied with good acidity and balanced by a bit of residual sugar, this lovely wine offers stone fruit and pear flavors with classic mineral undertones.

Data.Name: BV Coastal Estates Moscato
Data.Description: BV Moscato offers delicious honeyed aromas, followed by apricot, pineapple, orange peel and jasmine. Graceful curves of tropical fruit and soft, fleshy apricot fill the mouth with nice weight and body. The sweetness is balanced with a touch of acidity that carries the wine into a juicy finish. A pleasant, easy drinking wine, this Moscato is ideal for sipping with friends or as an apéritif.

Data.Name: BV Chardonnay
Data.Description: BV Coastal Estates Chardonnay, California. This wine brims with ripe apple, nectarine, peach, tropical fruit and citrus character; its balanced flavors turn creamy on the lingering finish.

Data.Name: BV Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: BV Napa Cabernet Sauvignon is a blend of several outstanding Napa Valley terroirs, this medium-bodied earthy Cabernet Sauvignon expresses layers of cherry, plum, rose and chocolate balanced with toasty oak.

Data.Name: Broke Ass Red Wine
Data.Description: It's a clear, bright medium to deep violet-purple colored wine with some structure to it. There are some pretty pronounced berry notes for both your taste buds and nose. Along with this there is some low to medium astringency and some well modulated tannins. There's also an OK balance and finish. Relatively tasty. Better for sipping than dinner and could work as an every day wine.

Data.Name: Bota Box Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: 3 Liters. Bota Box Pinot Grigio offers lively aromas of white peach, nectarine, light floral and hints of lime. This delightful medium bodied wine has flavors of ripe peach and nectarine with a clean finish.    Perfect after a long afternoon hike or a long day at the office, this fresh and fruity Pinot Grigio pairs well with no-fuss dinner entrees like pork stir-fry, grilled chicken salad or adult Mac n’ Cheese with a spicy kick of chorizo.  Serve chilled.

Data.Name: Bota Box Malbec
Data.Description: 3 Liters. Bota Box Malbec is a plush, medium-bodied wine with aromas of blueberry and blackberry. Jammy, luscious flavors of blackberry jam and blueberry syrup follow, leading into soft, earthy tannins on the finish.

Data.Name: Borgo Reale Sangiovese Di Puglia
Data.Description: This lovely, fruit forward Sangiovese is sourced from the Adriatic coast of southern Italy. Very smooth and versatile with layers of bright cherry and plum fruit on the medium bodied palate. Kosher for Passover and Mevushal.

Data.Name: Borgo Reale Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The Apulian soil and sea breeze make Pinot Noir one of the most intriguing wines among the wide range of the Borgo Reale selection. The color is an intense red, but it is on the nose that the uniqueness of this wine comes out. You can feel sweet notes of berries and cassis, yet a warm sensation. The palate is elegant, harmonious and well structured. Essential for special occasions and to be enjoyed on its own.

Data.Name: Borgo Reale Moscato d'Asti
Data.Description: This wine has a wonderful aroma of white peach, apricot pear and a slight floral finish. The wine is light and delicate yet full of intense flavors of sweet ripe pear and apricots. The low alcohol content makes it a very easy, pleasant wine.

Data.Name: Borgo Reale Chianti Riserva
Data.Description:
Bright ruby red color with cherry and chocolate on the nose. Intensely fruity and velvety, yet round with soft tannins, it's broad of flavors of the earth coasts it off into a detailed complex finish.
 
Chianti is great with Italian food and food that is rich in seasoning, such as red sauces, red meat, parmesan cheese, poultry, goose, lamb, lasagna, pasta with tomato sauce, heavy veal dishes, and veal chops.

Data.Name: Borgo Reale Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Fresh, clean, lively and easy-drinking this Pinot Grigio is one of our favorites! A touch of citrus, light body, and a clean mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Borgo el Col Alto Prosecco
Data.Description: A brightly fruity Prosecco giving tropical pineapple, pear, and vibrant apple notes. This is a spumante style of Prosecco, meaning it has lots of bubbles. It is full pressure with a mushroom cork. It is also categorized as "Extra Dry," which, in sparkling wine lingo, means it is the next category of sweetness up from Brut. This wine has a fine food compatible flavor and can be used with a variety of main dishes or as an apéritif. It has a beautiful, fruity nose with a hint of apple in the flavor. The mouth feel is a little creamier than the basic Brut style.

Data.Name: Bonterra Merlot
Data.Description: Bonterra Merlot wine has aromas of black currant, black cherries and a touch of wood smoke with flavors of plums, dark berries, toasty oak and vanilla spice. In the mouth, this wine has an elegant and restrained style with nice structure and balance, soft tannins and a long finish.

Data.Name: Boneshaker Zinfandel
Data.Description: Deep red and purple in color, this wine has welcoming aromas of dark fruits with a tinge of licorice. A sip reveals a bright, delicious, and fruity wine. Pairs well with pasta dishes.

Data.Name: Bolla Soave
Data.Description: Soave means “soft” in Italian, and the soft floral bouquet and clean pear and lemon flavors help this wine live up to its name.  A delicate almond aftertaste makes it the perfect quaff to lighter fare like grilled seafood, chicken, fish-based pastas, and entrée salads. It also makes a perfect aperitif.

Data.Name: Smartfood White Cheddar Popcorn
Data.Description: Smartfood White Cheddar Cheese Popcorn lets you enjoy delicious popcorn without the guilt. Smartfood popcorn is just the thing for hosting friends on game day or movie night.

Data.Name: Rold Gold Pretzel Thins
Data.Description: Between the one-of-a-kind flavor and crispy texture of Rold Gold pretzels, you just might fall in love with this golden-baked snack all over again every time you take a break.

Data.Name: Ruffles Cheddar & Sour Cream
Data.Description: For a tasty snack everyone will enjoy, reach for a bag of Ruffles Sour Cream and Onion Chips. Whether you pair them with a creamy dip, have them on the side of your burger or eat them straight from the bag, these cheddar and sour cream potato chips are the perfect crunchy addition to any day.

Data.Name: Chester's Fries Flamin' Hot
Data.Description:
Get ready for a sizzle of flavor that will set your mouth on fire.
Turn up the heat at your next party or gathering with this shareable bag.

Data.Name: Funyuns Onion Flavored Rings
Data.Description: Funyuns Onion Flavored Rings are a deliciously different snack that's fun to eat, with a crisp texture and zesty onion flavor.

Data.Name: Fritos Original Corn Chips
Data.Description:
Enjoy on Fritos on their own or try topping with your favorite cheese and guacamole dip.
Iconic Fritos corn chips are the perfect addition to any BBQ, party, or gathering.

Data.Name: Cheetos Flamin' Hot
Data.Description: Bring a cheesy, spicy crunch to snack time with a bag of Crunchy Flamin' Hot Cheetos. Made with real cheese for maximum flavor, these spicy Cheetos will make the perfect addition to the party.

Data.Name: Cheetos Crunchy
Data.Description: Delicious Cheetos snacks are a fun on-the-go snack. Snack it up.

Data.Name: Cheetos Puffs
Data.Description: Classic Cheetos in puff form. Made with real cheese.

Data.Name: Lay's Barbecue Potato Chips
Data.Description: With a secret blend of flavorful barbeque spices and famous fresh taste, Lay's Barbecue flavored potato chips are a tasty tribute to the American backyard grilling tradition!

Data.Name: Lay's Salt & Vinegar Potato Chips
Data.Description: Delicious tangy salt & vinegar flavor.

Data.Name: Doritos Cool Ranch
Data.Description: Doritos Cool Ranch flavored tortilla chips are packed with big, bold flavor. Experience a burst of tanginess with hints of onion, garlic, tomato and spice merging together in a bold creamy, cool ranch blend.

Data.Name: Doritos Dinamita Chile Limon
Data.Description:
Hot, spicy chile flavor rolled into crunchy tortilla chips with a hint of refreshing, citrusy lime.
Enjoy the bold snacking experience on its own or try dipping in your favorite salsa or queso dip.

Data.Name: Doritos Spicy Sweet Chili
Data.Description: Add a bold, delicious crunch to snack time with Doritos Sweet Chili Chips. Whether you're having a family barbecue or watching a movie, you'll love the sweet and spicy taste these Dorito chips bring to your taste buds. Enjoy with French onion dip or your other favorite dip for a little extra flavor.

Data.Name: Doritos Nacho Cheese
Data.Description: Give your gamedays & TV marathons a tasteful buddy with this Nacho Cheese Chips from Doritos. Each nacho is flavored with that all too delicious burst of cheese; snack time has never tasted this good!

Data.Name: Lay's Wavy Potato Chips
Data.Description: Lay's Wavy Original Potato Chips. Made with three ingredients: potatoes, oil and salt. Wavy texture is perfect for dipping.

Data.Name: Tostitos Scoops
Data.Description: Place these tortilla chips in a bowl for your next game day party. Perfect for dipping with a tasty Tostitos Salsa or Queso dip!

Data.Name: Tostitos Original Tortilla Chip
