Data.Description: A great snack for your next barbecue, picnic, or get-together. Combine with a homemade dip for a perfect party snack!

Data.Name: Van Winkle Special Reserve 12 Year
Data.Description: 2 Year, 90.4  Proof Van Winkle Special Reserve is the perfect combination of age and proof. This sweet, full bodied whiskey has been described by some as “Nectar”. We agree! The 12 years of aging and medium proof of 90.4 seem to be just right in creating a very pleasant drink of whiskey. This fine bourbon can compete with any excellent cognac as an after dinner drink. The overall impression is rich and deep. “Well crafted…elegant, stately…balanced beautifully”-Paul Pacult’s Spirit Journal.  Rated 98 by the Beverage Tasting Institute.

Data.Name: Tostitos Hint of Lime Tortilla Chips
Data.Description: Bring a zesty twist to a classic crunchy snack with Tostitos Hint of Lime Tortilla Chips. Whether you enjoy them with salsa, hummus or your favorite tasty dip, these lime chips are sure to be the life of the party.

Data.Name: Lay's Potato Chips Sour Cream and Onion
Data.Description: Wherever celebrations and good times happen, the Lay's brand will be there to flavor the moment. With flavors almost as rich as our history, we have a chip or crisp flavor guaranteed to bring a smile on your face.

Data.Name: Lay's Classic Potato Chips
Data.Description: Wherever celebrations and good times happen, the Lay's brand will be there just as it has been for more than 75 years. With flavors almost as rich as our history, we have a chip or crisp flavor guaranteed to bring a smile on your face.

Data.Name: Fee Brothers Orange Bitters
Data.Description: Fee Brothers aromatic orange bitters, perfect for adding a citrus bite to any cocktail. Made, as the name suggests, from the skins of oranges grown in the West Indies.

Data.Name: Fee Brothers Aztec Chocolate Bitters
Data.Description: Ancient Aztecs would celebrate with a bitter beverage made of cacao beans, peppers, and spices. Use a few dashes of Fee’s Aztec Chocolate Bitters to expand the flavor of cocktails.

Data.Name: Fee Brothers Cherry Bitters
Data.Description: Enhance your cocktails with cherry bitters. Alcohol aficionados and creative bartenders will love this exotic ingredient and its endless possibilities. Just a few dashes add a cherry taste with a pleasantly sour bitterness that brings out the best flavors in classic cocktails, soups and sauces. This unique flavor also proves to be an asset in concocting new drinks

Data.Name: Fee Brothers Grapefruit Bitters
Data.Description: The bold citrus taste of grapefruit combines with the spice flavor of bitters to create a unique and refreshing cocktail ingredient. This exclusive bitters creation by the cocktail mix masters at Fee Brothers is a must-have for cocktail enthusiasts and creative bartenders. Opened in 1863, Fee Brothers of Rochester, New York, is in its fourth generation of manufacturing top quality cocktail mixes, bitters, flavoring syrups and other beverage ingredients. In stock and ready to ship. Features: Unique fruit flavor of bitters.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Agave Nectar
Data.Description:
100% organic agave nectar from the Jalisco region in Mexico.
Perfect finishing touch for the most popular cocktails like top shelf margaritas, plus lemonades and teas.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Lemon Juice
Data.Description: Master of Mixes Single Pressed Lemon Juice is 100% single pressed juice from Mexico.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Lime Juice
Data.Description: Cocktail Essentials Lime Juice is produced from 100% Mexican lime juice to provide the perfect touch of acidity and soft floral aroma called for in a countless number of classic cocktails, including the Margarita and Gimlet. A combination of restaurant quality, outstanding taste and versatility make Cocktail Essentials Lime Juice one of the most popular Cocktail ingredients behind any bar.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Blue Curacao
Data.Description: Illuminate your cocktails with the beautiful blue hue of Master of Mixes Blue Curaçao Premium Alcohol-Free Liqueur.

Data.Name: Master Of Mixes Triple Sec
Data.Description: A premium of natural orange exstracts and essentials oils combine with natural sweetnerers to create the perfect ingredient for a multitude of classic cocktail favorites. Excellent for Margaritas, Long Island Ice Teas, Cosmopolitans and many other popular cocktails. Essentials citrus oils are obtianed by cold pressing the outer peels to express the oil.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Mint Syrup
Data.Description:
Perfect for mint juleps and mojitos, this mint syrup is easy to use and you only need to add a small amount of syrup to impart bold flavor. 

To make a mint julep, muddle mint in the bottom of a cup and fill with crushed ice. Pour 3 oz. of bourbon and 1 oz. of mint syrup and stir. For a mojito, muddle lime wedges in the bottom of a glass, fill the glass halfway with crushed ice, and add 1.25 oz. of rum and 1 oz. of mint syrup. Fill the glass with crushed ice, soda water, and stir. Garnish your minty, cold beverages with a sprig of mint to complete your presentation.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Simple Syrup
Data.Description: From 100% cane syrup. Truly premium. Simple Syrup is an essential ingredient in many of the most classic cocktails, such as daiquiris, mojitos, Tom Collins, and more! Its uses far outnumber its ingredients including sweetening cocktails, desserts, tea, lemonade and coffee.

Data.Name: Suntory Toki
Data.Description:
Suntory Toki is adored for its oak, honey, vanilla and ginger flavor notes.

This Japanese Whisky is carefully distilled at Hakushu, Yamazaki, and Chita distillery, Japan.

Data.Name: Somrus Indian Cream Liqueur
Data.Description: This unusual rum-based liqueur hints at exotic cardamom, almond and rosewater. It's creamy but light, and would be a palate-cleansing way to end a richly spiced meal. Sip it or try the producer's recommendation to serve frozen. Enjoy!

Data.Name: Crush Orange Soda
Data.Description: When it comes to creating playful memories with bold and exciting fruit flavor, no soft drink satisfies quite like a Crush. The leader of the Crush family, Crush Orange shocks your senses with a sweet and tangy citrus flavor that is 100% caffeine free. Crush has been a classic beverage loved by every generation since 1916. With the delicious taste of Crush Orange, this is where fun meets flavor.

Data.Name: Minute Maid Lemonade
Data.Description: Made with real lemons!

Data.Name: Bolla Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Pinot Grigio has the fresh, summer fruit flavors of peaches and limes, with a taste that is soft, generous and well-balanced and light bodied.

Data.Name: Bolla Merlot
Data.Description:
Winemaking Only fully mature grapes are used, in order to achieve the maximum expression of Merlot’s varietal character. The grapes are hand-picked and left to macerate with the skins for about 15 days. The wine is fermented in temperature-controlled stainless steel tanks and then undergoes malolactic fermentation. 10% of the wine is aged for 4 months in both American and French oak barrels before blending and bottling to add structure and character.

Tasting Notes / Color: Bright ruby red. Bouquet: Cranberries, cherries, plums and raspberries. Taste: Bright black-cherry character enhanced by hints of licorice, vanilla and clove derived from the wood aging. A dry savory and harmonic taste with a distinct finish of wild berries.

Food Pairing: Ideal with grilled red meats, cold meats, and semi-aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Bolla Chianti
Data.Description: This medium-bodied red is well-balanced with an intense violet aroma and a fresh, slightly spicy taste of black cherry, plum, and raspberry.

Data.Name: Bolla Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Winemaking Process: Hand-harvested grapes are fermented in temperature-controlled stainless steel for about one week with twice-daily pumpings over to obtain color, soft tannins, and optimal extraction. The wine undergoes barrique aging, resulting in a touch of vanilla which increases the wine’s complexity without masking the aroma of this variety. 10% of the wine is then aged in French and American oak barrels for 4 months before blending.

Tasting Notes Color: Ruby red. Bouquet: Black fruit, vanilla, and clove. Taste: Well balanced with a silky pepper and blackcurrant finish.

Food Pairing Ideal with roasted red meats, rich pastas, and grilled vegetables.

Data.Name: Bolla Bardolino
Data.Description: This bright ruby red wine has hints of black cherry on the nose.  It is soft and fruit-forward, with black-fruit flavors followed by a bright and fresh finish. Serve it as the Italians do – young and lightly chilled. Pairs perfectly with fleshy fish, beef, lamb, red-sauced pastas and pizza.

Data.Name: Boeri Moscato d'Asti
Data.Description:
Color: intense hay yellow Bouquet: luscious perfume of spring flowers and honeyed melons/apricots 

Palate: lightly sweet, with frothy effervescence, light body and fresh, delicate flavors that explode on the palate

Data.Name: Black Oak Merlot
Data.Description: The Black Oak Merlot is garnet red in color, deep and rich looking. The wine is warm and layered with cocoa and ripe blueberry aromas. The fresh plum flavors, are indicative of a homemade, dense-like strawberry jam, with hints of black cherry and red licorice.  With a fine tannin structure, this medium-bodied wine is consistently smooth, all the way through to the finish.

Data.Name: Black Oak Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: The Black Oak Cabernet Sauvignon is garnet red in color, refreshing and inviting to the palate. The wine’s aromas are layered with rich plum notes and a warm cedar component.  The ripe, dark cherry flavors, are reminiscent of decadent blackberries with a nice sprinkling of dried herbs. With a mellow tannin structure, this medium-bodied wine is delicious and well-integrated.

Data.Name: Bertani Bertarose
Data.Description: Bertarose is a historic Bertani wine produced since the 1930s; today it has been given a modern makeover in order to bring out the fresh and pleasant features much sought after in a rosé. The excellent microclimate in the inland hills of Lake Garda, combined with an expert use of the variety and rigorous care in the vineyard, enables us to produces this fresh and well-balanced rosé.

Data.Name: Beringer Founders Estate Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Beringer Founders' Estate honors the pioneering sense of discovery that brought founding brothers Jacob and Frederick Beringer to California with dreams of crafting fine wine and led them to found Beringer Vineyards in 1876. Today the Beringer Founders' Estate line of wines offer concentrated expressions of the most popular varietals, steeped in quality that comes from Beringer's history of crafting great wines from all over California for more than 140 vintages.

Data.Name: Be. Fresh Chardonnay
Data.Description: Each sip starts with a politely pleasant murmur that unfolds into an invigorating, crisp green apple splash that awakens your senses and revives your spirit. This fortuitous flavor is perfectly complemented by hints of citrus reminding you of the delicious magic of a budding romance, new adventure or simple twist of fate.

Data.Name: Be. Flirty Pink Moscato
Data.Description:
This mischievous Moscato is made to be sipped with a wink and a smile. Rich berry and delicate tropical and floral notes dance on the tongue for a luscious taste and juicy finish—sealed with a kiss of pink. Serve chilled for an irresistible treat. 

This unique Pink Moscato is a blend of Muscat of Alexandria, Muscat Blanc à Petits Grains and Orange Muscat from California, with a splash of red wine to give it a dazzling pink hue. Fermentation was slowed early to achieve the perfect level of sweetness, which is complemented by mouthwatering acidity. Notes of ripe mandarin orange and pink grapefruit unfold with delicate rosewater on the palate.

Data.Name: Barton & Guestier Rose
Data.Description:
The color of this delicious rose is a fine salmon-pink. It has an elegant nose with ripe red berries aromas and hints of black pepper. It's enjoyable wine, fruit driven, with overtones of sweet red fruits and spices.

Food matches: Summer salads, exotic and spicy dishes.

Data.Name: Beato Bartolomeo Breganze Moscato
Data.Description: Just cloyingly sweet. Everywhere. In the nose, in the body, and in the finish.

Data.Name: Beato Bartolomeo Breganze Prosecco
Data.Description: The Breganze Spumante Prosecco appears pale straw with lasting lively bubbles with intense aromas of stone fruit mingled with acacia blossom on the nose. The palate crisp and clean with green apple and pear, layered with citrus and accompanied with floral of rose, creamy with persistent bubbles, the spumante finishes long with balanced sweetness and concentration with lingering almond and lemon zest. An excellent Prosecco that would be best served as an aperitif, lightly chill.

Data.Name: Barkan Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Aroma: Strawberry aromas with hints of black cherries and mint. 
Food Pairing: Grilled salmon, braised chicken dishes, or veal.

Data.Name: Barkan Merlot
Data.Description: 100% Merlot grapes picked from the vineyards of the Barkan Winery in the Galilee and Judean Plains. This wine has a superb fruity and velvet-like taste, with a long and smooth finish.

Data.Name: Barkan Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: The grapes of this most "classic" of red varieties were grown in vineyards in theGalilee and Golan. Its aroma of wild berries and cherries blends with its tobacco, vanilla barrel bouquet. The wine has fine structured, yet rounded tannins, a long rich finish and aging potential.

Data.Name: Barkan Chardonnay
Data.Description: The wine is produced from 100% Chardonnay grapes, picked from the vineyards of the Barkan Winery in the Upper Galilee region and the Jerusalem Mountains. The wine has an abundance of fragrances and tastes of citrus fruit and white peaches with a smooth and round finish.

Data.Name: Barefoot Impression Red Blend
Data.Description: Barefoot Impression Red Blend is jammy and rich with lots of black fruit. Sweet vanilla aromas and spicy flavors complement the smooth, lingering finish. Time to uncork when you want to make a good Impression. Partners perfectly with fresh fruit, light dessert and good deeds.

Data.Name: Barbi Il Ruspo Sangiovese
Data.Description:
Color: Deep ruby red.

Aroma: Intense, complex reminding  of underwood.

Tasting Notes:  Spicy, rich and full body.

Food Pairing:  Strong and savory dishes such as roasts and game, red meat and hard cheeses.

Data.Name: Barbi Orvieto Classico Seco
Data.Description: Orvieto is Umbria's majestic hilltop town. Located between Florence and Rome, this is a popular city with tourists for its cathedral, ceramics and wine. The town sits on a big chunk of volcanic rock called “tuffo” and many of the buildings in the town are carved from it. Best of all? The grape vines love it!

Data.Name: Barbi Merlot Sangiovese
Data.Description: Barbi Merlot has a modern tasting but still distinctly Italian, medium bodied red from Umbria. This too shows a nice balance. It is spicy, with cherry, raspberry and a nice freshness.

Data.Name: Ballast Stone Shiraz
Data.Description: Matured in American and French oak. Aromas of plums, blueberries and spices follow through to the generous palate, finishing with subtle pepper overtones. Made to enjoy now, with cellaring potential of up to 7-10 years.

Data.Name: B&G Chardonnay
Data.Description: A refined and intense nose, offering aromas of white fruits, followed by tropocial fruits and slightly toasty notes; an elegant wine on the palate.

Data.Name: Avanti Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Avanti is produced by Vinacola Botter, a winery founded in 1928.  At first their wine was only sold to the local market in casks. Around 1950, the second generation took over expanded sales and production. The winery is located near Venice and produces Pinot Grigio, Pinot Noir, Cabernet, Merlot, Chardonnay and Refosco under their own brand and for private labels.  Their wines are a substantial value and consistently delicious.

Data.Name: Avanti Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Ruby-red in color, it has a distinct and intense bouquet, which becomes more ethereal and elegant after the wine has been opened. The palate is dry, generous and refined, with hints of herbs.

Great wine for roasted and grilled meats. Excellent with hard, aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Au Contraire Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Aromas of violet that are sweetly inviting.Spicy and light wine with flavors of cinnamon and clove.

Data.Name: Au Contraire Chardonnay
Data.Description: This wine is a blend of Russian River Valley vineyards from the heart of Russian River Valley to the Western Edges of Green Valley touching Sonoma Coast. The variety of growing sites add layers of ripeness, fruit flavors and complexity.    Citrus and tree fruits are complemented by a hint of brioche and toast. A round, elegant mouth feel with perfect balance leads to a lingering finish with a touch of minerality.

Data.Name: Astoria Prosecco D.O.C.
Data.Description: Astoria Vini is a family owned company with the 3rd generation family member Giorgio Polegato overseeing all winemaking for the winery. The Astoria family estate consists of 50 hectares of planted vineyards in the Veneto Region of Italy. The vision of the winery is to consistently produce the highest level of wines that can be enjoyed not only in Italy but around the world. In particular the “Lounge” Prosecco which has quickly become the leading on premise Prosecco in all of Italy is prominently displayed on wine lists in the finest restaurants in Rome, Venice and Florence.

Data.Name: Antonelli Trebbiano Spoletino Trebium Spoleto
Data.Description: The Trebbiano Spoleto is a typical variety of the territory that extends from Montefalco, Trevi and Spoleto; perhaps the name comes from “Trebium” Trevi in Latin.

Data.Name: Antonelli Contrario Umbria Rosso
Data.Description: It represents a new way of interpreting the Sagrantino grape, cultivated and vinified in such a way as to obtain a young and enjoyable, fresher and very drinkable wine.

Data.Name: Antonelli Montefalco Sagrantino Passito
Data.Description: Sweet wine made from semi-dried grapes. The traditional version of Montefalco Sagrantino. The name derives from the Latin “sacer”: a holy wine destined for consumption during the Christian festivals.

Data.Name: Antonelli Montefalco Sagrantino
Data.Description:
Intense ruby red in color. A rich and powerful, ethereal and very complex nose. Typically characterised by notes of fruit and aromatic herbs, where citrus features, cherry, berry, mint and oregano. On the palate this wine is very structured, with firm and persistent tannins. A wine that is best expressed with a long bottle ageing.

Great with grilled, roasted, braised or stewed red meats, game and hard mature cheeses.

Data.Name: Antonelli Baiocco Umbria Rosso
Data.Description:
Tasting notes: brilliant ruby red in colour; the nose opens with fruity and floral notes of cherry and red fruit; on the palate it is lively and balanced with a pleasant and fresh fruity finish.
Accompanies: an everyday wine. Goes well with cold pork cuts and cheeses, light pasta dishes, main courses and light medium-aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Anderra Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
This wine is from Chile. 
COLOR: Pale gold.
AROMA: Crispy citrus, pineapple and subtle green grass.
PALATE: Refreshing, with good acidity and lingering minerality on the finish.. Fresh cheeses, salads, light pastas, fish and seafood, or sushi and sashimi.

Data.Name: Anderra Carmenere
Data.Description:
This wine is from Chile.
COLOR: Dense purple, with violet streaks.
AROMA: Black currant and blackberry aromas open up to reveal bright strawberry and cherry notes, and a subtle spicy character.
PALATE: A touch of vanilla oak complements the fruit and the ripe, sweet finish.. Savory dishes, like earthy stews; spicy dishes, like braised short ribs, chile con carne, Texas ribs, or steak au poivre.

Data.Name: Almadi Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Deep garnet red color with a bouquet of fresh red fruits. The palate is structured with soft tannins and lingering finish.

Data.Name: Alma Los Andes Reserva Malbec
Data.Description: This charred specimen smells resiny and of blackened oak, with grapy berry scents thrown in. In the mouth, this is rock solid and balanced. Heavily oaked resiny flavors rest on top of core blackberry fruit, while this shows woody dry tannins and salty baked berry flavors on the finish.

Data.Name: Allure Bubbly Peach Moscato
Data.Description: Allure Peach Moscato is scrumptious flavor of a peach bursting with ripeness combined with the floral and fruity essences of this symphony wine is summer captured in a glass. The palate is further roused by a frenzy of lively bubbles and enticing sweetness.

Data.Name: Allure Bubbly Moscato
Data.Description: A combination of floral bouquets and ripe fruit greets the senses. Aromas and flavors of gardenias, apricot, honeysuckle, and peach are profuse. The lively bubbles are accompanied by a slightly sweet finish.

Data.Name: Alias Merlot
Data.Description: On the nose, this Merlot opens with strong notes of red fruit, black pepper, and light smoke. On the palate, vanil - la, black licorice, cedar, bay leaf, and sage join to create an earthy and silky finish reminiscent of a stroll through a forest.

Data.Name: Adro Da Se
Data.Description: A Dão wine. Soft, ripe and packed with fruit. Its tannins are richly integrated with the juicy black fruits that have been smoothed by some wood aging.

Data.Name: A&D Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This elegantly structured Napa Valley Pinot Noir is fruit driven with berry and spice accents. It has a medium body, soft tannins, and a satisfying finish.

Data.Name: A&D Chardonnay
Data.Description: A&D's North Coast Chardonnay has complex citrus fruit flavors and aromas with a slight hint of oak highlight this crisp, clean release.

Data.Name: 1975 The Sum Red Blend
Data.Description: The color is a rich, deep purple garnet and gives but a small hint as to what's inside. The nose gives off soaring and wonderfully focused aromas of ripe stone fruit, vanilla, cherries, cedar cigar box, blackberries and cinnamon. In the mouth, there are layers upon layers of broad, sweet opulent fruit balanced by firm tannins, great acidity and oak. This wine truly showcases the potential of blending and is a must have.

Data.Name: 1975 Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This wine represents the true essence of the varietal and source. Strikingly focused and concentrated, it showcases wave upon wave of honeyed melon, bruleed white peach and lemon curd on both the nose and palate. The finish is linear and ultra clean showcasing fresh fruit acids and wet stone and leaves you wanting only another glass.

Data.Name: 1865 Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: The wine has a fresh, fruity taste with excellent structure, mineral nuances, crisp acidity and a long finish.

Data.Name: 1865 Malbec
Data.Description:
1865 represents a modern, elegant, and avant-garde brand with great character, whose quality and terroir are expressed in each variety.

90% Malbec &10% Cabernet Sauvignon

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Chardonnay
Data.Description: A blend of selected parcels of fruit from some of Australia's best growing areas, this wine reveals citrus and honeydew flavors nuanced by subtle oak aromas. The palate is soft yet fresh, with balanced acidity and a smooth, creamy finish. A great party wine.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Cabernet Merlot
Data.Description: The dark fruit flavours of Cabernet are given a hand by the chocolate and plum notes from Merlot. In all it's a great partnership that results in a full flavored yet supple wine.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Tree Free Chardonnay
Data.Description: Hints of citrus, grapefruit and light melon flavors. Tree-Free Chardonnay has a lighter, more crisp flavor profile than their traditional (Yellow tail) Chardonnay and has no oak aging, hence the name.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Shiraz Grenache
Data.Description:
This [yellow tail] Shiraz Grenache is everything a great wine should be – lush, vibrant and easy to drink.

Flavor:
Raspberries, blackcurrant, licorice and spice
Enjoy with:
Lamb and good conversation

Data.Name: Hurricane Rum
Data.Description: Released each year during Hurricane season. It is aged in bourbon casks imparting a wonderful golden color and distinctive whiskey flavor. Hints of caramel and vanilla along with a smoky tobacco flavor make this rum very well balanced.

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Peppermint Schnapps
Data.Description: "The piquant aroma is concentrated, candied and appropriately peppermint-like. The palate entry tastes of gently sweet peppermint candy canes; the midpalate is more herbal/vegetal, reflecting the authentic pungent and oily flavor of crushed peppermint leaves." - Wine Enthusiast

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Peach Brandy
Data.Description:
Hiram Walker Peach Brandy is a delicious blend of fine brandy spirits and delicate, sun-ripened peaches.

60 Proof.

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Blackberry Brandy
Data.Description:
With a luscious, deep blackberry flavor, Hiram Walker Blackberry Brandy is delightful when added to fruity cocktails or festive holiday drinks.

The beautiful purple hue of this favorite brandy adds a depth of unique color to beach drinks, best sipped while dipping your toes in the sand. Hiram Walker Blackberry Brandy is created by blending fine brandy with sun-ripened blackberries. This fruity brandy is delicious when poured over ice cream or sipped chilled after dinner while watching the sunset. Hiram Walker Blackberry Brandy is perfect for making Rum Runners and Blackouts at any backyard party.

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Anisette
Data.Description: Hiram Walker Anisette's sweet licorice flavor comes from carefully selected, imported aniseed.

Data.Name: Sterling Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: The Sterling Vineyards Napa Valley Sauvignon Blanc is a brilliant, light gold color in the glass and offers bright aromas of stone fruit, pear, fresh grapefruit and lemon citrus. The inviting nose leads to a quenching palate with flavors of citrus and white peach. There is good tension in the wine balanced between a core of acidity and the creamy roundness on the palate, leading to a persistent and flavorful finish. This is a classic expression of Napa Valley Sauvignon Blanc.

Data.Name: Sterling Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The Sterling Vintner's Collection Pinot Noir is a clear deep ruby, with complex, vibrant varietal aromas of briar fruit and ripe black cherries, with hints of vanilla. The fruit jumps out of the glass, with big black cherry flavors from entry to finish. The tannins are soft and there is a resonant touch of earth in the lingering finish.

Data.Name: Sterling Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Refreshing and fruity, our Sterling Vintner's Collection Pinot Grigio has peach, melon, and kiwi expression accented by honeysuckle, mineral, and spice. A healthy dash of Gewürztraminer adds even more appealing spice, making this wine delightful to pair with a great variety of lighter appetizers.

Data.Name: Sterling Chardonnay
Data.Description: The Sterling Vineyards Napa Valley Chardonnay is a luminous, light gold color in the glass with fragrant aromas of fresh lemon crème, citrus, crisp apple and toasted hazelnut. The inviting nose leads to a richly textured palate with flavors of citrus, stone fruit and a honey almond character. The wine is well-balanced between an elegant, creamy roundness and a line of bright acidity. The pleasing finish is persistent and flavorful.

Data.Name: Sterling Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: The Sterling Vineyards Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon is a brooding, dark garnet-red color in the glass with big fruit aromas of blackberry jam, ripe plum and notes of cassis. The nose leads to a full-bodied, concentrated, richly textured palate with flavors of dried black cherry, warm caramel and a pleasing umami character. The wine is dense and offers striking fruit intensity balanced with good acidity and fine, well-integrated tannins. The wine is seamless and offers a lengthy finish that hints at its ability to age for at least the next 10 to 15 years.

Data.Name: Sons of Liberty Loyal Lemonade
Data.Description:
Here's your new summer drink! This 9% ABV canned cocktail is all natural and uses fresh lemon peels to provide a bright, easy-sipping and refreshing drink. Available in 4-packs of slim 12oz cans, this is the perfect drink to share with friends by the pool, at the beach, on the boat, really anywhere.

This is not a spiked seltzer full of carbonation and this isn't a concoction of fake, sweet ingredients you can't pronounce.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Whipped Cream
Data.Description:
Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff Whipped Cream is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. Smirnoff's 60 proof vodka is infused with the confectionery taste of whipped cream for a light, decadent taste. 

Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, our whipped cream specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a sweet kick to your favorite mixed drink. Simply mix with coffee, root beer, or ginger ale.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Watermelon
Data.Description: Smirnoff Watermelon is sweet and never bitter. It's a great vodka flavor to share with friends. All you need is a mixer and a glass to enjoy it.

Data.Name: Smirnoff 80 Proof Vodka
Data.Description:
Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff No. 21 Triple Distilled 80 Proof Vodka is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. Smirnoff's award-winning, 80 proof vodka has robust flavor with a dry finish for ultimate smoothness and clarity. Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, this vodka traditionally can be taken alone or added to your favorite mixed drink. 

Simply mix with ginger beer and lime juice for a classic Moscow Mule.

Data.Name: Smirnoff 100 Proof Vodka
Data.Description: "Clear. Medium- to full-bodied. Dry. Reminiscent of lemon, white pepper, charcoal. Full, bold texture. Smoky sensation on the palate is followed by a burst of rich flavor and spice. Impeccable structure is evidenced by the long, silky finish." -Beverage Testing Institute

Data.Name: Smirnoff Vanilla
Data.Description: Smirnoff Vanilla is delicious whether you blend it with mixers or enjoy it on the rocks. It has a sweet taste and pleasant aroma that makes Smirnoff Vanilla a hit among all guests.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Ruby Red Grapefruit
Data.Description: Smirnoff Ruby Red Grapefruit is intensely citrus and fresh - rich ruby red grapefruit flavor with a slight hint of sweetness.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Root Beer 100 Proof
Data.Description: Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, Smirnoff's root beer specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to confectionery mixed drinks.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Peach
Data.Description: Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff Peach is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. This 70 proof vodka is infused with the flavor of natural, summery peach for a sweet and fruity taste. Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, our peach specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to your favorite mixed drink. Simply mix with lemonade, iced tea and simple syrup for a refreshing tasting Peach Fuzz cocktail.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Orange
Data.Description: Smirnoff Orange is a blend of six juicy orange varietals for an all-natural sweet-tart flavor with a full plump mouthfeel. The warm spice of the Royal Mandarin mingles with the tropical undertones of the Cara Cara Navel and Satsuma Mandarin to create a refreshingly complex, yet complementary, taste experience.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Lime
Data.Description: Lime is a fresh, natural flavor that doesn't skew too sweet. If you're looking for refreshment, you've found it! Smirnoff Lime is the perfect base for cocktails that will keep even the most finicky customer happy.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Fluffed Marshmallow
Data.Description: Distilled three times for a clean taste. A distinct flavor of sweet marshmallow and vanilla cream perfect for mixing. Great in martinis or mixed with your favorite soda.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Espresso 100 Proof
Data.Description:
Whether you sip it on the rocks or want to add some fun to a cup of hot cocoa, Smirnoff Dark Roasted Espresso is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. Smirnoff's 100 proof vodka is infused with a strong java taste for a rich and bold flavor. 

Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, Smirnoff's espresso specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to confectionery mixed drinks. Simply add to your favorite coffee or hot cocoa.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Cranberry
Data.Description: Premium Smirnoff Vodka is expertly mixed with the crisp tartness of cranberry juice for this ready to serve cocktail in a convenient pack.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Citrus
Data.Description:
Named for its signature, velvet-like texture. Only the finest grains and water from the Canadian Rockies. Ultra-smooth, consistent taste profile.
Mildly spicy, slightly citrus nose that also hints of honey. The smooth and light taste is rich vanilla with a touch of cinnamon on top of a grainy rye taste.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Cherry
Data.Description:
Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff Cherry is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. Our 70 proof vodka is infused with a natural cherry flavor for a bold, fruity taste. 

Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, our cherry specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to your favorite mixed drink. Simply mix with spiced rum and cola and pour over ice for a delicious, refreshing tasting Red Beard cocktail.

Data.Name: Leonard Kreusch Riesling Blue
Data.Description: This type of vinification enhances the natural fruitiness of the Riesling, which is evident in the wonderfully fresh flavors of green apple, fruity pear and hints of grapefruit. The wine has moderate intensity with good balance and a pleasant sweetness...

Data.Name: Laxas Albarino
Data.Description:
Clear, brilliant wine, straw yellow colored with green nuances. 

An intense aroma on the nose, perfectly combining the fruity and floral notes, particularly apple and stoned fruit (apricot). 

Freshness on the palate typical of Albariño, with a touch of acidity perfectly balanced with the structure and body of this wine. Meaty, sweet with a glyceric finish.

Data.Name: Lab White
Data.Description: A blend of Vital, Arinto, Moscatel and Sauvignon Blanc, this blend offers citrus aromas and lemon, lime flavours. Light to medium in body with a soft and refreshing mouth feel.

Data.Name: Joseph Drouhin Macon Villages
Data.Description:
This wine is crisp and refreshingly fruity. A lively texture gives brightness, and a light touch of acidity finishes the wine on a citrus note. 

The color of the wine is bright and limpid. The nose is floral and fruity. Very straightforward and direct on the palate, as if biting into a grape.

Data.Name: Jellybean Chardonnay
Data.Description: Ripe tropical fruit aromas dominate the bouquet of this expressive wine. On the palate, flavors of pineapple, mango, and citrus zest all converge into the wine's silky, creamy finish.

Data.Name: Ipsum Verdejo
Data.Description: Pale yellow. High-pitched citrus fruit and floral aromas show good clarity. Dry and nervy, offering a refreshingly bitter quality to the taut lemon and lime flavors. Closes tight and precise, with resonating mineral and citrus zest notes.

Data.Name: Vicente Gandia Galizeus Albari
Data.Description: 18kt gold in color with nice brilliance. Rounded tones of melon, citrus, pear and floral. For an Albarino, this is more rounded in weight and still keeps its focus; quite nice. Pairings: Hard cheeses, white meats, poultry, prawns.

Data.Name: Cantina Gabriele Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: This wine shows straw yellow color. The bouquet is composed of tropical fruit and white flower flavors, with an excellent balance of acidity and flavor. It goes well with fish dishes, white meat, risotto and pasta.

Data.Name: Frontera Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Clean and bright straw yellow in color, Frontera Pinot Grigio has lifted fresh pear aromas and is gentle, round and mouth filling on the palate. A refreshing wine with great crisp acidity.

Data.Name: Frog's Leap Chardonnay
Data.Description: Frog's Leap winery combines dedicated winemaking with a fun spirit. Aromas of wet stone, white peaches, flavors of grapefruit & lemongrass leading to layers of flint & toasted coconut. Refreshingly crisp with tart acidity and a clean bright finish.

Data.Name: Fly By Napa Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Aromas of lemon zest, key lime pie and white currant. This California Sauv Blanc is medium bodied and extremely vibrant.

Data.Name: Barbadillo Oloroso Sherry
Data.Description: Barbadillo Dry Oloroso has a nose suggestive of something sweet, with its notes of walnuts and dried fruit, so the lack of sweetness on the palate is initially something of a shock. As the layers of flavour unfold in your mouth, this is clearly a very different wine from a more commercial, sweetened cream Sherry. In addition to the nuts and raisined-depth, there is a haunting toffee-sweetness on the palate of this dry wine. The finish persists for an age.

Data.Name: Fournier Pere et Fils Sauvignon
Data.Description: Sauvignon Blanc lovers enjoy rolling the names Sancerre, Pouilly-Fumé and Menetou-Salon off their tongues as much as they love drinking the refreshing juice found inside bottles of the same. The demand for these popular Loire Valley wines often exceeds supply and the strong Euro has made most offerings, once great values, just as pricy as white Burgundy. Savvy sippers know to look for bottlings from estates such as Domaine Fournier, whose vineyard holdings in all three prime Sauvignon areas allow them to bottle juicy bargains like these under the Vin de Pays du Jardin appellation. This clean, citrusy mouthful is the perfect aperitif or picnic companion, ideal for savoring with fresh goat cheeses and tangy salads.

Data.Name: Davis Bynum Russian River Chardonnay
Data.Description: Davis Bynum Chardonnay has beautiful aromas of baked apple, citrus and white floral. On the palate the wine opens up with brioche, lemon meringue and toasty baking spices, with a lush finish that is balanced with acidity and a rich creaminess.

Data.Name: Concha y Toro Casillero del Diablo Chardonnay
Data.Description:
Casillero del Diablo offers wine lovers the very special opportunity to participate in the propagation of a century old legend known throughout the world. In the 19th century, the founder of Concha y Toro,  Don Melchor, discovered that his vineyard workers were sampling his greatest wines. To discourage this action, Melchor spread the rumor that his deepest, darkest cellar was the Calillero del Diablo (Cellar of the Devil), so that no one would dare go in there. It worked, and a legend was born. Today this mysterious and legendary cellar continues to hold the finest wines of Calillero del Diablo.

Tasting Notes:  Wine with good structure, an excellent balance, fresh and lively acidity. Medium bodied with a long and dry finish that ends with green pear and hints of white peach, complemented with a toasty overtone.

Food Pairing: Enjoy this with delicate fish such as grilled sea bass, sole or turbot, garnished with capers or herb cream sauces.

Data.Name: Chateau Fage White
Data.Description: A white wine with an original bouquet, nuanced between citrus fruit touches coming from its Sauvignon and with an expressive style brought by its Semillon. Very well balanced on the palate, this crispy wine offers freshness and fruits. Perfect to drink in its youth.

Data.Name: 3 Stars Brewing Company Raspberry Dissonance
Data.Description: Berliner Weisse with raspberries

Data.Name: Barrier Brewing Company Know Yourself
Data.Description: Collab with Kane - imperial stout brewed with tart cherries and vanilla

Data.Name: Barrier Brewing Company Luchini Mad Fat!
Data.Description: "India Pale Ale Dry Hopped with Mosaic, Columbus & Ahtanum. Collaboration with Interboro."

Data.Name: Blue Point Brewing Company Hazy Bastard
Data.Description: "Blue Point Hazy Bastard IPA is a juicy, unfiltered North Eastern-style India Pale Ale packed with tropical flavors and herbal aroma. Double dry-hopped and boasting a total hop rate of 3.5 lbs/bbl, this cloudy IPA has a full mouthfeel and a strong, lasting hop character."

Data.Name: Brewery Ommegang Fruittanomyces
Data.Description: "A dry-hopped witbier. The funky, flavorful limited edition beer is brewed with malted and unmalted wheat and oat flakes and is spiced with sweet orange peel and coriander. The beer is fermented with mango, kiwi, and passion fruit juices and dry-hopped with Citra and Cascade hops before aging in the bottle with Brettanomyces."

Data.Name: Brewery Ommegang Hennepin
Data.Description:
Inspired by the traditional rustic brews of Belgium, Ommegang's iconic American farmhouse saison is charmingly complex but eminently drinkable.

Artfully spiced with coriander, ginger, orange peel and grains of paradise, its champagne-like effervescence leads to a crisp, dry finish, delighting discerning drinkers everywhere.

While delicious on its own, Hennepin pairs remarkably well with a variety of foods, complementing shellfish, barbecue, cheeses, charcuterie, and a wide range of spicy fare.

Data.Name: Brewery Ommegang Rare Vos Amber Ale
Data.Description:
Amber ale with orange peel, grains of paradise & coriander

Ommegang's take on the smooth, easy drinking ambers poured in cafés across Belgium, Rare Vos (Strange Fox) takes its name from a tavern near Brussels known for cycling contests, pigeon races and outstanding ales. Pouring a brilliant copper with a creamy white head, this bright, beguiling beer is sensational to session, and pairs wonderfully with mussels, frites and other pub fare.

Because at the end of the day, it’s good to enjoy the end of the day.

Data.Name: Brooklyn Brewery Serpent
Data.Description:
Belgian-style golden ale aged on cider lees in bourbon barrels with Oliver's Cider and Perry cider lees additions. 

A collaboration with Thornbridge, Serpent emerges strong, dry, tart, firm, fine and funky, a full expression of their long friendship, the best of British craft brewing, the American penchant for boldness, and the microflora of Tom Oliver's orchard and the Herefordshire countryside.

Data.Name: Finback Brewery Rolling in Clouds
Data.Description: "Hazy, cloudy, blurry, foggy, fuzzy IPA. Whatever you call it, let’s be in the New Wave. Fluffy and crisp, it’s all about an easy decision."

Data.Name: Evil Twin Brewing Even More Pecan Pie Jesus
Data.Description: "A limited release imperial stout brewed with molasses and pecan extract."

Data.Name: Evil Twin Brewing Island Bliss
Data.Description: "Tropical Fruit IPA brewed with Pink Guava & Pineapple"

Data.Name: Sea Sun Chardonnay
Data.Description: A pale straw color with sunshiny highlights, Sea Sun has a subtle nose, with scents of lightly grilled mango, soft butterscotch, juicy red apple and newly ripened pineapple and apricot. Hints of a springtime meadow, fresh sea air and a trace of smokiness add intriguing layers. Entry on the palate is round and creamy, with flavors of lemon curd and brown spice on the mid-palate. This wine’s fruit flavors, oak and acidity are seamlessly integrated, with no one element standing out. The finish has a grippy, toasty quality, with notes of cinnamon and lemon squares. A final kick of bright acidity draws you back for another sip.

Data.Name: Sailor Jerry Spiced Rum
Data.Description:
In the past, a ship's captain would take a ladle of rum, add gunpowder and ignite it to provide "proof" of the rum's integrity to his crew. Sailor Jerry continues this age-old tradition of serving quality spiced rum to provide an unmatched base for mixed drinks. 

Crafted after intensive research into historical maritime rums, Sailor Jerry developed a smooth rum with a rich flavor. The result is a high-proof spirit that's perfect for mixing in your favorite cocktails, including Long Island Iced Teas, Mai Tais and Mojitos. The rum features prominent oak and vanilla flavors with hints of cinnamon and clove spices.

Data.Name: Rumple Minze Peppermint Schnapps
Data.Description: Enjoy the cooling and bracing experience of Rumple Minze Peppermint Schnapps. The unmistakable taste of fresh and crisp peppermint followed by a silky-smooth, extended finish will take your breath away. Famous for shots and daring cocktails, this 100 proof peppermint flavored liqueur is a holiday favorite and enjoyed best in the company of friends. Serve in a chilled shot glass for a refreshing tasting kick.

Data.Name: Root: 1 Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
The long growing season of the Casablanca Valley allows for the Sauvignon Blanc grape to develop natural sugars that balance its characteristic acidity. Root: 1 Sauvignon Blanc is noted for its intense flavor and fresh citrus style.

TASTING NOTES: An elegant and crisp wine with citrus notes and a fresh, clean finish.

FOOD PAIRINGS: Root: 1 Sauvignon Blanc is an exceptionally versatile food wine that pairs perfectly with chicken Caesar Salad, grilled fish, seafood, and creamy pasta sauces.

Data.Name: Root: 1 Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
The coastal breezes, intense sun and cool evenings of the Tapihue region in Casablanca Valley provide the perfect microclimate for Root: 1’s fresh, ripe and expressive Pinot Noir.

TASTING NOTES: A lively, medium-bodied wine with ripe cherry flavors and silky tannins.

FOOD PAIRINGS:Root: 1 Pinot Noir is an ideal pairing with paella, shellfish dishes, mushroom risotto, or roasted duck.

Data.Name: Root: 1 Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: The vineyards of the Maipo valley extend from the city of Santiago to the west where they meet the cool coast. Known for their distinctive renditions of well-balanced reds, the warmth of the sun and oscillating winds from the Andes provides ideal conditions for Cabernet Sauvignon. Root: 1 is particularly notable for its elegant, lush, and ripe fruit flavors.

Data.Name: Romana Sambuca
Data.Description: Romana Sambuca is a unique blend of natural flavour essences and ingredients including anise, elderberries, sugar, and a secret natural flavour formula distilled in the old world tradition.

Data.Name: Romana Black Sambuca
Data.Description: Romana Sambuca is a unique blend of natural flavor essences and ingredients including anise, elderberries, sugar, and a "secret natural flavor formula" distilled in the old world tradition.

Data.Name: Relativity Whiskey
Data.Description:
Relativity Whiskey is a marriage of small-batch distilled toasted American Oak and four traditionally-distilled whiskies from corn, wheat, barley, and rye, crafted in partnership between Brain Brew Distilling, Edrington Distillers from Perthshire, Scotland, and Eureka! Ranch of Ohio. 

Notes of barley developing on the nose followed by sweet aromas of vanilla, toffee and toasted caramel. On the palate are notes of wheat, corn and rye with hints of sugar and clove and oak and dried citrus on the finish.

Data.Name: Redemption Bourbon Whiskey
Data.Description: The high amount of corn gives this bourbon a classic sweet taste with notes of vanilla and caramel from the wood, and the rye adds some light spice.

Data.Name: Redemption High-Rye Bourbon Whiskey
Data.Description: We think you can never have too much rye, so our High-Rye Bourbon mash-bill approaches the upper limit of allowable rye grain in a bourbon mash-bill. Bottled at 92 proof the dry spiciness of the rye balances the sweetness of the corn for a really wonderful sipping experience on its own or in classic cocktail recipes.

Data.Name: Redbreast 12 Year Old Irish Whiskey
Data.Description: The Redbreast 12 Year old is a beautifully balanced pure pot still Irish Whiskey, with a warm, generous texture, rich, sweet flavours and a spicy kick. In the view of many connoisseurs, the finest Irish whiskey available. It picked up the top prize in its category at the World Whisky Awards 2010, and was named as Irish Whiskey of the year by Jim Murray in the Whisky Bible 2010, with a score of 96 points.

Data.Name: Proper Twelve Irish Whiskey
Data.Description: A mixture of malted barley & grain, tripled distilled & aged a minimum of 3 years in bourbon barrels. Smooth & approachable with vanilla, honey & fresh fruit finishing in a warming creamy toffee.

Data.Name: Pitu Brazilian Cachaca
Data.Description: Made from fresh cut sugar cane and spring water for a pure flavor to this Caipirinha, the national cocktail of Brazil. Simply pour over ice, garnish with sugar and lime and enjoy!

Data.Name: Pendleton Midnight Whisky
Data.Description: Made with pure, glacier-fed spring water from Oregon’s Mt. Hood, Pendleton Midnight thrills the senses with a complex taste and exceptionally smooth finish begging to be explored. To add complexity and fruit forward characteristics, a portion of the Pendleton Midnight blend is aged for over six years in American brandy barrels. Each batch of ninety proof oak barrel-aged whisky is crafted from premium ingredients.

Data.Name: Pendleton 1910 12 Year Old Whisky
Data.Description: Pendleton Whisky is an oak barrel-aged whisky distilled in Canada using the finest ingredients. Before bottling, glacier-fed spring water is added from Mt. Hood (Oregon’s highest peak). Pendleton® Whisky delivers an uncommonly smooth taste and rich, complex flavor.

Data.Name: Partida Tequila Blanco
Data.Description:
Tequila and mezcal are produced in different states of Mexico (though there is overlap). Tequila can only be made, by law, with one variety of agave: the Blue Agave.

Partida Blanco Tequila, redolent of Blue Agave, is brilliant, clean and crisp. It is well balanced with a natural, pure Agave flavor and a pleasant finish that lingers gently on the palate.

Data.Name: Parrot Bay Coconut Rum 42 Proof
Data.Description:
Captain Morgan Parrot Bay Coconut consists of white rum from Puerto Rico, which is aromatised with natural coconut flavour in order to ensure its tropical character. Parrot Bay Coconut is the perfect basis for tropical cocktails, but can also be enjoyed neat or with some ice cubes.

With Parrot Bay Coconut, Captain Morgan has created a drink that has a sweet and refreshing flavour, but does not neglect the roots of the spirit it is based upon. Therefore, even traditional rum lovers will hold the spirit in high esteem.

Data.Name: Paddy Irish Whiskey
Data.Description:
Nose: Fresh and lively, aromatic - a complex interplay of nutty maltiness, woodland fragrances and spice, with hints of honey and vanilla. 

Taste: Mild, soft, a distinctive mellow maltiness, a touch of sweet oil, spiciness - and again those background notes of honey, vanilla, toasted wood. 

Finish: A sweetness gently fading, mellow maltiness and mild woody notes lingering pleasingly. 

Serving: Enjoy Paddy neat or on the rocks, or with your choice of mixer.

Data.Name: Ocean Vodka
Data.Description:
Ocean Vodka is distilled from pure organic sugar cane using continuous column distillation through 103 platelets. Each platelet acts as a mini-distillation, resulting in an exceptionally pure spirit.

Ocean Vodka is the only spirit in the world made with 100% deep ocean mineral water, sourced from 3,000 feet below the Kona Coast of the Island of Hawaii. The water in Ocean Vodka contains trace minerals including calcium, magnesium and potassium, which combine to create an exceptionally smooth and distinct flavor. These minerals impart a light, crisp taste in Ocean vodka, and make a better tasting drink.

Ocean is best served on the rocks, or mixed with freshly squeezed fruit juices.

Data.Name: Oban 14 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The Western Highland representative in Diageo's 'Classic Malt' series, Oban 14yo is a superb, full-blooded fruity malt with a whiff of heather and more than a hint of smoke.

Data.Name: Mr. Boston Vodka
Data.Description: Made from the finest ingredients, Mr. Boston has a smooth, crisp taste.

Data.Name: Monkey 47 Dry Gin
Data.Description:
A good third of the ingredients for this special gin come from the Black Forest and are definitely not what you would call typical gin flavorings! In total, 47 handpicked ingredients, prepared in extremely soft spring water from our own Black Forest source, give MONKEY 47, whose pièce de résistance is the use of local cranberries as some sort of “secret weapon” typical to the Black Forest, its unrivaled complexity and quality, which is fully brought to bear through masterly distillation and maturing in traditional earthenware containers.

Whether with tonic, as a sling, martini, or gimlet, the unique and complex taste of Monkey 47 is an ideal basis for both classics and more eccentric cocktails. With the distinct and pure scent of juniper, a tangy and crisp citrus note, a sweet, floral aroma, a hint of peppery spices, subtle bitter fruit, and a deep and harmoniously balanced complexity with a tremendously racy finish!

Data.Name: Macallan Rare Cask
Data.Description: Macallan Rare Cask is comprised of 16 different sherry-cask styles, the majority of which are first fill. Rich and complex with notes of dark honey and dried fruit, this bridges the gap between The 1824 Series and The 1824 Collection.

Data.Name: Macallan Gold Double Cask
Data.Description: An intriguing single malt that celebrates the coming together of two styles, Double Cask Gold reflects a perfect harmony of flavours and natural colour. The perfect partnership of American and European Oloroso sherry seasoned oak casks creates this burnished gold whisky with a distinctive character, that leads with American oak style before giving way to classic Macallan flavours.

Data.Name: Springdale Dark And Stormy
Data.Description: A stormy blend of barred-aged beer aged on freshly shaved ginger chases the clouds away. 7.3%ABV

Data.Name: Springdale Crypto Currants
Data.Description: Brown Sour Blend aged with Currants in Oak Barels 6% ABV

Data.Name: Springdale Geography Bee
Data.Description:
A cross-continental, cross-pollinated collaboration between Nectar Creek and Springdale Beer, Geography Bee is born from Springdale's shared obsession with fermentation. They introduced honey into the grist of this saison, then laid it to rest in wine barrels on wild yeast and cranberry blossom honey from MA for six months. 
6.0%ABV

Data.Name: Ipswich Oatmeal Stout
Data.Description:
Deep, rich and malty with hints of chocolate and coffee. It's what espresso would be if it had the gumption to be beer. We use two different hop additions, specially selected crystal malts, roasted barley and oatmeal to give it a soft and silky mouth feel. Makes a great dessert or meal.
7% ABV

Data.Name: Jack's Abby Variety Pack
Data.Description: Variety pack including Hoponius Union IPL, House Lager, Post Shift Pilsner, and Blood Orange Wheat Radler.

Data.Name: Amherst Jess
Data.Description:
Brewed with malted oats and hopped with Mosaic, Simocoe and Citra.
7.3% ABV

Data.Name: Fort Hill Brewery Jigsaw Jazz
Data.Description: A double IPA with a bright, citrusy deceptively light body and dry flavor. To compose this brew, we borrowed techniques used by Belgian brewers to achieve a big beer without much sweetness. The Citra dry hop gives this beer its bright citrus notes and aroma.

Data.Name: Bent Water Jolene American Porter
Data.Description: Jolene is a heart-bustin' porter. She delivers notes of chocolate, coffee and cashew with a velvety, dry finish. She might just leave you achin'.

Data.Name: Barnstable K-Dub
Data.Description: Crisp and refreshing, a great beer for a summer day. Brewed by Barnstable Brewing.

Data.Name: Castle Island Keeper IPA
Data.Description:
Castle Island's flagship India Pale Ale is smooth but punchy; balanced yet intense. Despite the colossal amount of hops we cram into this beer, it's still remarkably approachable-for pros and rookies alike-so grab a Keeper and save the day.
6.5% ABV

Data.Name: Clown Shoes La Bestia Furiosa
Data.Description:
Mexican-style imperial stout aged in bourbon and rum barrels with chiles and spices added.
12% ABV

Data.Name: Notch Left Of The Dial
Data.Description: British malt, hard water and low gravity meets a new wave hop profile. The base malt is Fawcett Golden Promise, and that really sets this beer apart, along with a touch of Fawcett caramalt and oat malt. The hops smell of pine, resin and citrus. This is the hoppy beer to extend the good times, without the fatigue of bitterness or crushing alcohol content.

Data.Name: Small Change Little Rain
Data.Description: Simple and full of character, we brew our dry-hopped pale ale with pale and munich malt, a touch of wheat, and warrior, cascade, and mosaic hops.

Data.Name: Berkshire Long Daze Hefeweizen
Data.Description:
This traditional German Hefeweizen pours a hazy, effervescent gold. Our use of a classic German yeast strain delivers flavors of bananas and clove, followed by a slight and pleasing tartness that makes this ale exceptionally drinkable. Long Daze tastes like that perfect summer afternoon in New England – wherever (and whenever) you choose to drink it. No fruit needed for this exceptional example of the real thing.

4.7% ABV

Data.Name: Orion
Data.Description:
A dry, crisp rice lager. Orion’s company slogan is “For your happy time!” How can you argue with that? The dry, crisp Okinawan original is a staple beer to keep in the fridge. If you like Japan's Big Four (Sapporo, Kirin, Asahi or Suntory) try Orion. Refreshing and easy to drink, this is perfect on a hot day.
5% ABV

Data.Name: Collective Arts Origin Of Darkness
Data.Description: Inspired by Tasmanian black truffles and their culinary use in Australia, CA collaborated with their friends at Moon Dog Brewing in Melbourne. They combined the flavors of dark chocolate, bourbon and vanilla and added black truffles to age in the barrels. The combination is a velvety mix of earthy, chocolate and vanilla deliciousness.

Data.Name: Toccalmatto Prairie Okie Mathilde
Data.Description:
6.2% ABV
"Golden-orange color and slightly hazy clarity. Piles of fluffy white lace on initial pour, which last long into the session and provide lots of lacing.
Strong barnyard funkiness buffered by some fruit notes, primarily pear and apricot." -beeradvocate.com

Data.Name: O'Hara's Irish Red
Data.Description: Want to experience a traditional light hop flavor that balances the sweet malty caramel taste? Tapster's got it for ya, and it's O'Hara's Irish Red. The addition of a pinch of roast barley during the brewing process lends a distinctive roast bite which is balanced by a crisp dry medium bitterness.

Data.Name: Mythos
Data.Description:
Mythos was first produced in 1997 at the Mythos Brewery in Greece using the skills and know-how acquired by the brewmasters after collaborating with major European beer schools. The excellent quality of Mythos beer combined with the brand's authentic and impressive personality have won the hearts of consumers. The superiority of Mythos' recipe has also been recognised in the many tastings done by sommeliers and consumers.

Mythos beer is one of the best, Greek lager beers with a rich foam, bright blonde colour and a pleasant, refreshing taste. Mythos is brewed from the finest varieties of barley and hops, ensure maximum enjoyment in every sip.

5% ABV

Data.Name: La Fin du Monde
Data.Description:
This type of beer was originally developed by the monks of the Middle Ages to be served on special occasions. La Fin du Monde is a deluxe beer made by triple fermentation and a unique way of straining the yeast. This method produces an unexpectedly subtle flavour. With its champagne-like effervescence, it has a vigourous presence in the mouth, which accentuates its strong personality. Slightly tart, with the balanced flavours of wild spices, malt and hops, it belongs to the class of great Trappist beers and, in this regard, is a North American first.

9% ABV

Data.Name: Kronenbourg 1664 Blanc
Data.Description:
Kronenbourg 1664 Blanc is a modern, fruity and refreshing wheat beer. With its unique taste and appearance, 1664 Blanc appeals to consumers all over the world. It has an inimitable sweet and refreshing flavour, resulting from the hint of citrus and coriander spice used in brewing. With its flavour and design, 1664 Blanc embodies the elegance and taste of France.  Kronenbourg 1664 Blanc’s modern identity is perfectly expressed by its unique shiny blue bottle. 
5% ABV

Data.Name: Kirin Light
Data.Description: Kirin Light displays all the character and finesse expected from a beer with Kirin on the label, but with far few calories than most beer lovers ever dreamed. This attractive golden colored brew presents an enticing hop aroma and a surprisingly smooth, full-bodied taste considering there are only 95 calories.

Data.Name: Kinderyoga
Data.Description:
From Oedipus Brewery. A thick malt bill trying to showcase brown malt, besides chocolate, roasted and some caramel malts. Hopped with East Kent Goldings and some Chinook as late hops.

11% ABV.

Data.Name: Toccalmatto Kaleidoscope
Data.Description: A result of a collaboration with Evil Twin, Toccalmatto took a farmhouse ale on a flavor journey: sweet prickly pears, Sicily salt, lactic sourness, Bretta funk … a true kaleidoscope.

Data.Name: Pohjala Jõuluöö
Data.Description:
Translation: Christmas Night. A silky smooth chocolate-vanilla oak aged Imperial Porter brewed for the winter nights. Aged on cacao nibs, fresh vanilla pods, and French oak for a heady chocolate dessert character with a luscious vanilla taste and aroma.

8% ABV

Data.Name: Master Gao Jasmine Tea Lager
Data.Description:
A pale lager, providing a firm malty body and pronounced hoppy flavor with distinctive floral overtones of jasmine tea.

5.1% ABV

Data.Name: Traquair Jacobite Ale
Data.Description: Based on an eighteenth century recipe the ale is spiced with coriander which gives a remarkably fresh aftertaste.

Data.Name: iStout Affogato Imperial Milk Stout
Data.Description: The "i" might be in lower case, but beware - this is a capital beer. Brimming with luscious roasted coffee and chocolate malt flavours drizzled over a scoop of velvety ice cream. iStout Affogato is balanced by a brisk bitterness and bold hoppy freshness, remixed by the addition of lactose, coffee, and vanilla in the brew. As with all our beers, this beer is a very modern interpretation of this classic style.

Data.Name: Monty Python's Holy Grail
Data.Description:
Cult classic and official beer of the Monty Python team.
This brilliant and bold addition to our flock was created to commemorate the 30th anniversary of one of our finest comedic exports – the Monty Python crew!
Years later and Holy Grail is still going strong. With more hops than a killer rabbit, it’s a full-flavoured golden ale with a distinctively fruity flavour followed by the Black Sheep signature dry finish. Be warned, this beer has been tempered over burning witches! Only joking.

ABV: 4.0
Color: Golden
Aroma: Fresh hoppy notes with a tasty, zesty finish.
Taste: Citrus with inviting malty undertones.
Food Matches: Spam, spam, spam and spam!
Ingredients: Hops, Malted Barley, Torrefied Wheat, Water, Yeast

Data.Name: Hitachino Nest White Ale
Data.Description:
Hitachino Nest White Ale is brewed in the tradition of a Belgian style white beer with coriander, nutmeg, orange peel and orange juice.

5% ABV

Data.Name: Hitachino Nest Ginger Brew
Data.Description:
From Japan's most prestigious brewery, Hitachino Nest Ginger Brew is brewed with raw ginger, and has complex flavors & aromas of ginger, citrus, and malt which pair-up beautifully with spicy dishes such as shrimp salad, Indian, Thai and Vietnamese food (spiced with lime, tamarind, cilantro, chilies), crab cakes and others.
7%c ABV

Data.Name: Dugges Coffee Vanilla Black
Data.Description:
This flavored beer is a layered dream! It’s sweetly soft from the malts. It’s robust from da Matteo roasted Colombian Tabi coffee. And, it’s made elegant by the addition of plush vanilla. Serve black!

13% ABV

Loyal to the classic good taste, new image evolution more dazzling,
let you become the everyone’s focus!

Data.Name: Cherry Bänger
Data.Description:

Data.Name: Guinness Blonde
Data.Description:
A complex and flavorful lager that is hoppy and citrusy on the nose,  Guinness Blonde American Lager has a lively mouthfeel and is crisp and refreshing with a long malt biscuity finish.

5.0% ABV

Data.Name: Unibroue Blanche de Chambly
Data.Description:
5.0% ABV.

Aroma: “Coriander with a hint of coconut, nice floral notes, and sweet citrus character produce a nose that fades quickly. Light wheat sweetness. The strong coriander character is sharper and less herbal than is typical.”

Flavor: “Nice level of acidity to carbonic bite. Simple flavors of slightly musty coriander and honey wheat sweetness with very little hop flavor. Finish is a bit cloying instead of crisp.”

Data.Name: Black Nitro
Data.Description:
Brewed by Amager Bryghus in collaboration with Grassroots Brewing.

"Cascadians have become a favorite style. This is another good one. Utterly dark pour with a frothy tan head that lingers and thick lacing. Floral hop nose. Smooth, dark and hoppy. Interesting malt profile. Roasty but without the bite." -Brian T, untappd.com

Data.Name: Black Malts & Body Salts
Data.Description: Brewed by To Øl. When a brewer is stirring the kettles while steam arises from the mash and when we actually do put some effort into our work, an occasional drop of sweat will drip down into the mash. So this is a salute to all the hard working proletarian brewers around the world. Giving you the perfect amount of body salts, mixed with french press coffee and IIPA’ish amounts of bittering, flavour and dry- hops.

Data.Name: Bira IPA
Data.Description: The first IPA developed in India with the world’s most flavorful hops. Look for rich aromas of tropical fruit with a slightly malty start, complemented by a burst of citrus that ends with a spicy finish. The cycle repeats, until every taste bud feels fresh and alive with flavor. A nod to the original brew developed by the British.

Data.Name: Belhaven Wee Heavy
Data.Description: Pasteurised, export only.  Belhaven Wee Heavy has a rich deep flavor. A beer to be sipped, savoured and fully respected.

Data.Name: Amstel Light
Data.Description: Amstel Light is now the #1 imported light beer in the United States. Characteristic of this beer is a unique selection of raw materials and an intensive fermenting process. The result is a special light beer containing only 3.5% alcohol and approximately 35% fewer calories than regular lager beer. It's #1 popularity proves that great taste wasn't sacrificed along the way. It's the light with a bite.

Bring them to the office, use them in gift baskets or stock up your pantry. Packed with milk chocolate, peanuts, caramel and nougat, Snickers Sharing Size Chocolate Candy Bars make a tasty chocolate treat. Each pack comes with two Snickers Chocolate Bars, making them the ideal way to satisfy hunger and share with a friend at the same time. Remember, you're not you when you're hungry.

Data.Name: Chamisal Chardonnay
Data.Description:
Tropical notes of juicy Satsuma, ripe kiwi and mango are highlighted by aromas of candied lemon peel, apple blossom and refreshing minerality.

The palate supports the nose, revealing the Stainless winemaking with its round, weighty mouthfeel. Crisp acidity and flavors of white nectarine, papaya and key lime pie round out the clean, lingering finish.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Casillero del Diablo Wine Pinot Grigio. This Pinot Grigio is full of fresh, vibrant flavours of pear with undertones of citrus fruit, like tangerine. A light to medium-bodied wine with excellent balance and a long, crisp finish. Ideal as an aperitif or as an accompaniment to salads, fish, smoked salmon or vegetarian dishes.

Data.Name: Campanile Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Campanile Pinot Grigio is produced in the prestigious Friuli DOC of Grave in Italy. Known for its gravelly soils and cool microclimates, Grave is one of the ﬁ nest areas in Friuli for Pinot Grigio. Its perfect location between the Adriatic coast and the Julian Alps provides the essential climatic elements responsible for the unique varietal characteristics of ﬁ ne Pinot Grigio grapes. Campanile is named for the traditional Italian bell towers that are located in every community symbolizing the place where people gather.

Data.Name: CK Mondavi Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: CK Mondavi Pinot Grigio is a medium-bodied wine filled with aromas of wildflowers, peaches and pears. Fresh, tropical flavors combined with a touch of spice lead to a delightfully crisp finish.

Data.Name: August Kesseler Riesling

Pork, Shellfish, Spicy food, Poultry, Cured Meat.

Data.Name: Willm Grand Cru Kirchberg De Barr Riesling
Data.Description: Yellow with hints of green, the nose is fine and delicate, elegant and racy, presenting the aromas of fresh fruit. The attack is supple, suggesting notes of lemon that are almost menthol (camphor). The final reveals hints of ripe fruit and candied fruit. It's fat and long.

Data.Name: Bota Box Sauvignon Blanc Mini

This Sauvignon Blanc is a great match for light meals, like that salad you know you should eat, with or without grilled chicken or tuna. With a zip of citrus, melon, and a touch of minerality, it is perfect for alittle dinner al fresco at the park or on your deck.

Data.Name: Moet & Chandon Imperial Champagne Mini
Data.Description: An Impressive consistency of lemon and lime flavors, smooth, crisp and easy to drink. A good length that is clean and full of apple and honey notes. Richness and softness fills the finish with a clean aftertaste. In mini form!

Data.Name: Bota Box Chardonnay
Data.Description: 3 Liters. Bota Box Chardonnay presents bright citrus, green apple and honeysuckle aromas. This light-bodied wine is refreshing and crisp with vibrant flavors of lemon, lime, green apple and pear leading to a juicy finish. Enjoy Bota Box Chardonnay as an aperitif or as a complement to angel hair pasta with scallops, fish and chips or grilled chicken Caesar salad. Serve chilled.

Data.Name: ReaLemon 100% Lemon Juice
Data.Description: ReaLemon is 100% real lemon juice made from concentrate, and it’s a great alternative to the hassle of fresh lemons. ReaLemon is a space-saving kitchen sidekick, ideal for adding a delicious twist of lemon to your favorite seafood and poultry recipes, plus it’s great in marinades and it brightens up both hot and cold beverages. Since 1934, ReaLemon has been a trusted brand to deliver quality lemon juice. 100% lemon juice from concentrate Great for use in recipes and beverages Natural Strength Great alternative to fresh lemons One 15 fluid ounce bottle

Data.Name: Collins Simple Syrup
Data.Description: This American classic is a staple for any home bar. Made with real sugar, it's the perfect complement to any craft cocktail.

Data.Name: Tres Agaves Organic Bloody Mary Mix
Data.Description:
Tres Agaves organic bloody Mary mix is a bold new interpretation of an old classic. Taking a cue from our Mexican roots, we pair the conventional tomato base with the vibrant flavors of citrus and peppers to produce a mix with a fuller, more robust and powerful taste. 

The Tres Bloody Mary: 
1. 2 oz Tres Agaves 100% agave tequila (or your favorite vodka)
2. 4 oz Tres Agaves organic bloody Mary mix; fresh lemon wedge (optional)
3. your favorite garnish (optional). 
4. Build with ice in your favorite Collins glass. Add a squeeze of fresh lemon and your favorite garnish.

Data.Name: Tres Agaves Organic Agave Nectar Syrup
Data.Description: Made with organic agave nectar. The original. Cocktail ready. For a great margarita, mix with fresh lime juice and Tres Agaves Tequila. Makes over 12 margaritas. Agave: The essential margarita ingredient. Agave nectar enhances the subtle flavors of Tequila. It has a clean, sweet taste with the flavor of roasted agave. And it has a lower glycemic index than conventional sweeteners, so it won't spike your blood sugar. Tres Agaves Cocktail-Ready Agave Nectar is the original agave nectar designed specifically to improve all of your cocktails. World-class margaritas are now within reach.

Data.Name: Master of Mixes Pina Colada
Data.Description: An ultra-creamy blend of natural Dominican coconuts, real coconut milk and a refreshing splash of premium pineapple juice. A tropical vacation in a glass. Enjoy one today!

Data.Name: Hiram Walker Triple Sec
Data.Description: "Made from all natural flavors, Hiram Walker Triple Sec is "triple dried" with three distillations. Imported orange peel is then softened in water and added to the spirit for a clean, crisp orange taste." Tasting Notes

Data.Name: Daily's Cocktail Mixers Strawberry Mix
Data.Description: Made with real strawberries, Daily’s Strawberry Cocktail Mix is perfect for popular fruity cocktails like daiquiris and margaritas. And it couldn’t be easier, simply blend the ripe strawberry taste with your favorite spirit!

Data.Name: Bacardi Read-to-Drink Mojito

Data.Name: Mr & Mrs T Original Bloody Mary Mix
Data.Description: Serve up some fun at your next party or gathering with the premium, quality ingredients in Mr & Mrs T cocktail mixers. Available in an assortment of flavors from sweet to savory, Mr & Mrs T mixers are a guaranteed crowd pleaser. The Original Bloody Mary Mix blends the taste of ripe tomatoes with lemon juice and coarse black pepper, and it's perfected with sea salt and 95% juice.

Data.Name: Scorpion Silver Mezcal 17r Old
Data.Description: A dry bouquet, hints of lime, citrus, cucumber salt, and savory herbs, and on more warming: char, creosote, some spiciness, and a faint trace of balsam. This award-winning Scorpion Silver Mezcal is artisan-made in small batches in Oaxaca, Mexico, with a real scorpion in every bottle. This version is freshly distilled and bottled without aging.

Data.Name: Del Maguey Vida Mezcal
Data.Description:
Del Maguey Vida San Luis Del Rio Mezcal is the perfect place to start when you want to try mezcal. This Mexican liquor is a little harder to find than tequila and other options, but Del Maguey has made its Vida Mezcal easy to get and at an entry-level price. It tastes delicious in mixed drinks and will introduce you to the world of mezcal.

This mezcal is distilled twice and hand-crafted. Del Maguey uses wood-fired copper stills, which bring out fruity aromas and other sweet notes such as honey and vanilla. On your palate, experience cinnamon, banana, tangerine and even sandalwood.

Data.Description: Starbucks coffee drinks offer the bold, delicious taste of coffee with the rich flavors you know and love. This indulgence is proof that you can enjoy a little Starbucks wherever you may be.

Data.Name: Starbucks Frappuccino Mocha
Data.Description: Pop the cap. Savor the sip. Go. Mocha Frappuccino chilled coffee drink is a harmonious blend of Starbucks coffee and creamy milk with chocolaty mocha.

Data.Name: Starbucks Frappuccino Caramelized Vanilla Honey
Data.Description: Starbucks coffee drinks offer the bold, delicious taste of coffee with the rich flavors you know and love. This indulgence is proof that you can enjoy a little Starbucks wherever you may be.

Data.Name: Starbucks Frappuccino Coffee
Data.Description: A creamy blend of coffee and lowfat milk – available on the go.

Data.Name: Dunkin Donuts Iced Coffee Original
Data.Description: The new bottled Dunkin' Donuts Iced Coffee gives you a rich, smooth coffee taste that keeps you going throughout your day. Available now in four delicious flavors: Mocha, French Vanilla, Original, Espresso.

Data.Name: Lysol Disinfectant Spray
Data.Description: Lysol disinfecting spray helps protect your family and helps keep them healthy. Our products are designed to provide germ protection and can kill 99.9% of viruses and bacteria on hard surfaces, when used as directed. From counters to couches, you can depend on Lysol to kill 99.9 percent of bacteria. This spray eliminates odors and kills 99.9 percent of mildew, mold, viruses on most household surfaces. Sanitizes soft surfaces and deodorizes the air.

Data.Name: Dentyne Ice Spearmint Gum
Data.Description:
Practice safe breath and get intense freshness with Dentyne Ice Sugar-Free Gum.
Dentyne Ice has a bold, icy flavor that keeps breath fresh for up to 40 minutes after you're finished chewing.
Stay on top of your game with the laid-back minty taste of Spearmint Dentyne Ice.

Data.Name: Dentyne Ice Peppermint Gum
Data.Description:
Practice safe breath and get intense freshness with Dentyne Ice Sugar-Free Gum.

Dentyne Ice has a bold, icy flavor that keeps breath fresh for up to 40 minutes after you're finished chewing.

Data.Name: Tic Tac Orange
Data.Description:
Sweet, fun and flavorful – perfect anytime.
Made for on-the-go enjoyment anywhere.

Data.Name: Tic Tac Freshmints
Data.Description: Keeping it fresh. Just because.

Data.Name: Pop-Tarts Hot Fudge Sundae
Data.Description: With a chocolate crust, smooth vanilla filling, vanilla and fudge icing, and colorful sprinkles, this chompable sundae is a thing of beauty.

Data.Name: Pop-Tarts Brown Sugar
Data.Description: Single-serve Pop Tarts offer a delicious toaster pastry treat flavored with brown sugar and cinnamon. Each pack contains two iced pastries. Take these convenient treats with you or eat them in the office. Hot or cold, they're a great meal or snack any time of day. Enjoy for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

Data.Name: Pop-Tarts Frosted Strawberry
Data.Description: Simplify your morning routine with these delicious breakfast pastries. These frosted-strawberry Pop Tarts are a simple way to feed students, children, or employees and can be eaten as-is or toasted for warm snack. Each of these frosted-strawberry Pop Tarts is sealed in a set of two for freshness.

Data.Name: Remy Martin VSOP
Data.Description: Remy Martin V.S.O.P is the world's favorite Fine Champagne V.S.O.P an honor it has held since its introduction in 1927. Known by its frosted green bottle, this is Remy Martin's flagship brand. It is smooth, complex, yet balanced, and perfectly mature. Of all V.S.O.Ps sold worldwide, one of every three bottles sold is Remy Martin V.S.O.P.

Data.Name: Remy Martin V White Cognac
Data.Description: Remy Martin V is a 100% distilled grape spirit from the famous Cognac House of Remy Martin, but it is not a Cognac. It is not aged in wood, and as the result of the non-aging and the cold filtration process it undergoes, it is crystal clear in color. Launched in 2010, Remy Martin V, whose name is derived from eau-de-vie, is fresh, smooth, and clean with subtle hints of pear and fresh mint. It is best served in cocktails. 80 Proof.

Data.Name: Prarie Organic Cucumber Vodka
Data.Description: "The bottle is clear and tall and has a pale green label that is reminiscent of the 1920’s. The nose is crisp, clean and earthy, and does, in fact, have a faint cucumber like smell, and by that, I mean I can sense the skin and seeds as well as the meat of the cucumber. It is a mild aroma, but it definitely smells like the real thing.
