On the palate, I get that same faint cucumber taste along with a bit of salt – otherwise the taste is very clean and crisp and refreshing. The finish is smooth with a hint of pepper and lasts a medium amount of time. I really wasn’t sure what to expect from this cucumber flavored vodka, but the boys at Prairie put this one together quite nicely. " -George Brozowski fbworld.com

Data.Name: Martell VS Single Distillery Fine Cognac
Data.Description: Martell VS (Very Special) cognac was created around 150 years ago under the name of 3 stars (***) and today has a worldwide reputation. Harmonious and well balanced, its taste is fruity, mellow and with a pleasing fresh and pure feeling in the mouth. It’s an ideal mixer for long drinks and classic cocktails.

Data.Name: Hennessy Master Blender's Cognac
Data.Description:
Master Blender's Selection No. 3 is a single batch, rare blend available for a limited time, and will never be replicated.

The third edition in the series is the very first creation of Renaud Fillioux de Gironde, the 8th generation Master Blender, who carefully selected each eau-de-vie for its complementary personality and taste to define the blend’s character.

At Maison Hennessy, it is said that cognac is not made, it’s crafted. It is a precise blend of heritage, passion and transmission that are the essence of our craft. Nothing captures the spirit of craftsmanship more than the Master Blender’s Selection – a unique series of limited edition blends.

Data.Name: Remy Martin 1738 Accord Royal
Data.Description: Remy Martin 1738 Accord Royal boasts a dark, mahogany copper color with notes of caramel apple, fig marmalade, cherry crème brûlée, toffee, banana cream pie and brown spices. It finishes with a fruity, full-bodied, warming sensation rich in minty dark chocolate notes, cola and oak for a sensational experience sure to please. You'll detect a hint of exotic fruits, toast, pink peppercorn and alpine, which all add up for an intense, sweet burst of flavor that rewards you with a creamy aftertaste. All this is achieved using a careful blend of eaux-de-vie aged exceptionally well in toasted French oak casks. The result is what we like to call Cognac Fine Champagne, for there's something truly extraordinary about the 1738. Serve it neat, on ice or in premium classic cocktails such as the Sazerac or Sidecar. Any cocktail with bright citrus flavors highlight the 1738 Accord Royal best, so don't be afraid to experiment with your own concoctions.

Data.Name: Michelob Ultra Pure Gold
Data.Description: Experience Pure Gold – beer in its organic form. Michelob ULTRA Pure Gold is a USDA certified organic light lager with a pure, refreshing taste. With only 2.5 carbs and 85 calories, Pure Gold is triple-filtered and brewed free of artificial colors and flavors. Inspired by nature, enjoyed in nature.

Data.Name: 21st Amendment Tasty
Data.Description:
Curious minds are a beautiful thing and who better to take a cue from than Benjamin Franklin? Much like he discovered electricity by boldly flying a kite in a thunderstorm, we were struck with a great idea of our own – let’s take one of our favorite home-brew recipes and turn it into a standout, gold colored American IPA that we call Tasty IPA. Crack open a can and enjoy bright fresh flavors and aromas of hops, tropical stone fruits, pine and a hint of spiciness. Mr. Franklin once said, “well done is better than well said,” and this beer is sure to prove that theory.

Ingredients
Malts‍

Pale Malt, Pilsner, Light Crystal Malt
Flavor Hops

Calypso, Ekuanot, Azacca
Dry Hops

Simcoe, Calypso, Ekuanot
Bitter Hops

CTZ

6.8% ABV

Data.Name: 21st Amendment Blah Blah Blah
Data.Description:
21st Amendment Blah Blah Blah IPA is a tongue-in-cheek commentary on the popularity of this style and all the sub-styles that have become part of craft beer conversations and offerings.

This is a deep gold color, double IPA (of course) and jammed packed with hop flavors and aromas. With nine different hop varietals, on top of late-kettle boil additions, this beer has a juicy, hop chewy flavor.

IPAs are here to stay and Blah Blah Blah in many ways is a tribute to their prevalence and popularity and Tapster loves it. So, grab yourself a Blah Blah Blah IPA and celebrate this plentiful style and hoppy indulgence.

Pairs with: fried chicken, sharp cheeses, carne asada and great conversation

Pairs BEST with: a home cook meal to celebrate something special!

8% ABV

Data.Name: Yeungling Lage Cans
Data.Description: Yuengling Lager is an iconic American lager famous for its rich amber color and medium-bodied flavor. Roasted caramel malt adds subtle sweetness, while a combination of cluster and cascade hops round out this well-balanced beer. Drink this classic lager chilled, either in a beer mug or straight from the bottle.

Data.Name: Yeungling Lager
Data.Description: Yuengling Lager is an iconic American lager famous for its rich amber color and medium-bodied flavor. Roasted caramel malt adds subtle sweetness, while a combination of cluster and cascade hops round out this well-balanced beer. Drink this classic lager chilled, either in a beer mug or straight from the bottle.

Data.Name: Bud Light Platinum
Data.Description: Platinum takes the classic Bud Light and makes it even better. Its light golden color is broken up by a fast-rising carbonation that gives it a distinct crispness and lightness. With its sweet, malty aroma and mildly floral notes, as well as its more powerful 6% ABV, this is without a doubt the most refreshing and robust type of Bud beer you can get your hands on. Bud Light Platinum is a great drink for unwinding after a long workday or for hanging out with some friends over the weekend. You'll definitely want to buy this beer in bulk.

Data.Name: Game of Thrones Cardhu Gold Reserve
Data.Description:
Thankfully, there's the Mother of Dragons, Daenerys Targaryen. With a hint of clove and red apple, you will be able to feel House Targaryen's fiery dragon blood coursing through the character well loved by many fans of the series.

Just like Daenerys who has a rich back story, this whisky blended in Cardhu is inspired by two women who figured prominently in Scotland's distillery's history; Helen Cumming and daughter-in-law Elizabeth.

"At that time in the early 1800s, the industry was "almost entirely dominated by males. We really wanted to bring the spirit of Daenerys Targaryen" (a character known as the Mother of Dragons) to the scotch", Dan says.

Data.Name: Sixpoint Brewing The Crisp
Data.Description:
The Story: "We went to Germany for this one. (Well went back really: we first devised this beer while counting yeast cells in a German lab, and sinking liters in underground caves.) Anyway, when it comes to German hops, American breweries get the leftovers… the less desirable plots, amalgamated into a “hop sausage.” Instead, at Sixpoint we go straight to the source for the prime cuts — the Tettnanger and Hallertau hops in THE CRISP are sourced 100% directly from farmers in Tettnang, Germany. This way we personally select what goes into our beers.
Look, legit pilz should have an aroma that leaps from the glass, and the bright, floral aroma of THE CRISP absolutely blasts your nostrils. Follow that up with a crisp, clean finish, and you’ll be sinking this thing by the liter." -Sixpoint Brewing
5.4% ABV

Data.Name: Dale's Pale Ale
Data.Description:
Brewed with hefty amounts of European malts and four kinds of American hops, Dale's Pale Ale delivers a blast of hop aromas redolent of citrus and spice, which are then complemented by toasty and sweet malts. This brew has a silky mouthfeel with an accompanying lingering bitterness. 
6.5% ABV

Data.Name: Lagunitas Super Cluster
Data.Description: Super Cluster is a Citra-Hopped Mega Ale of intergalactic proportions. A hop-forward beer: Pale, cold, alcoholic, and bitter.

Data.Name: Bud Light Lime-A-Rita
Data.Description: Bold new Margarita with a twist. 8% ABV and perfectly balanced to deliver authentic Margarita flavor and a delightfully refreshing finish.

Data.Name: Allagash White
Data.Description:
Allagash White, the classic Belgian witbier (wheat beer), gets an American spin with this lightly golden and inviting brew. The nose is fruity and floral, yet it also comes off as warm and spicy. The taste is a delightful treat: heavy wheat mixed with banana, coriander, hay, honey, lemon zest, and pepper. The finish is rather dry, but it keeps that flavorful mouthfeel right to the mellow, creamy end. 

Some newcomers to the witbier approach may be shocked at the cloudiness of this beer, but the suspended yeast means that this beer is true to its parent style. Compared to most Belgians, Allagash White has a low alcohol percentage. Serve in a chilled tulip-style glass.

Data.Name: 21st Amendment Brew Free or Die
Data.Description:
Like Abe, we believe in freedom. Freedom from the notion that IPAs should only assail you with bitterness. And from the idea that a big, balanced, hoppy beer can’t possibly come in a can. 21st Amendment Brewing believes that those who have tasted freedom shall forever brew free.

Taste freedom!

Data.Name: Modelo Especial Chelada
Data.Description: Authentic ingredients give way to delicious, well-balanced taste. A classic collision of tomato, salt, and lime. Perfect for kick-starting your evening or relaxing at home with friends. 289 calories, 0 grams of fat per 24 ounce serving. Best served chilled!

Data.Name: Guinness Draught Cans
Data.Description: The best selling stout in the world is also one of the finest. 1st brewed in 1778 by Arthur Guinness. Roasted barley give it a dark richness. 4.2% alcohol and less calories than skim milk!

Data.Name: Elysian Space Dust
Data.Description:
Manic IPA series. The hopping is pure starglow energy, with Chinook to bitter and late and dry additions of Citra and Amarillo. 
8.2% ABV

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Flesh and Blood
Data.Description: Brewed with mouth-puckering lemon flesh, sweet orange peel and blood orange juice, Flesh & Blood balances the resinous hoppy characteristics of an American IPA with the explosive zesty fruitiness and subtle drying tartness of citrus to deliver a highly quaffable ale that’s incredibly unique and lovely to down the whole year round.

Data.Name: Corona Premier
Data.Description:
The refreshing light beer you've been waiting for has arrived with the introduction of great-tasting Corona Premier. 

Brewed to be easy-drinking, the taste is undeniably Corona. It is a superior light lager with a refreshing taste that pairs well with Mexican and citrus-infused dishes. 

Premier is a uniquely refreshing beer perfect for taking a moment to look around and appreciate all that you’ve accomplished so far. 

This great-tasting light beer contains only 90 calories is 4.0% alcohol by volume. Best served chilled!

Data.Name: Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin IPA Cans
Data.Description: Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin adds a fresh squeeze of tangy bitterness to our signature IPA. Some may say there are few ways to improve Sculpin’s unique flavor, but the tart freshness of grapefruit perfectly complements the IPA’s citrusy hop character. Grapefruit’s a winter fruit, but this easy-drinking ale tastes like summer.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Strawberry
Data.Description: Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff Strawberry is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. This 70 proof vodka is infused with natural strawberry flavor for a delicate, sweet finish. Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, our strawberry specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to your favorite mixed drink. Simply mix with soda, lemonade, or cranberry juice.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Raspberry
Data.Description: Smirnoff Raspberry is rich and robust. It complements everything well, including food, other mixers and most importantly, the conversation.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Pineapple
Data.Description: Smirnoff Pineapple Vodka is a lush tropical taste of the islands. Sipped straight or mixed in myriad cocktails. Smirnoff Pineapple is an easy way to dress up your repertoire and make your guests happy!

Data.Name: Smirnoff Passion Fruit
Data.Description:
True Passion in premium vodka is seen with Smirnoff Passion Fruit. An alluring tropical treat Smirnoff fuses the subtle sweetness of juicy mango, perfumed passion fruit and ripe orange to give us a fruity bouquet of sophistication. Loved by everyone and a classic taste of premium vodka, this is Smirnoff. At its base Smirnoff is triple distilled giving it a supple clarity and clear smoothness. A world-renowned name in infamy and stardom you can’t go wrong with a bottle of Smirnoff’s finest.

Mixer Recommendation: Lemonade, Fanta Fruit Twist, Rubicon Passion (sparkling)

Data.Name: Smirnoff Kissed Caramel
Data.Description: The authentic flavor experience of homemade caramel complete with a hint of salt for a true flavor experience.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Green Apple
Data.Description: Smirnoff Green Apple Vodka is made with the natural flavor of green apple and vodka distilled from the finest grains and filtered in a unique process.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Grape
Data.Description:
Whether you sip it on the rocks or with soda and a twist, Smirnoff Grape is the perfect addition to a cocktail party. Our 70 proof vodka is infused with natural grape flavor for a sweet and delicate taste. 

Triple distilled and 10 times filtered, our grape specialty spirit is smooth enough to be taken alone or to add a delicious kick to your favorite mixed drink. Simply mix with soda, lemonade or iced tea.

Data.Name: Smirnoff Blueberry
Data.Description: Smirnoff Blueberry is one of the smoothest Smirnoff flavors. Its fresh taste and delightful fragrance dazzle even the most sophisticated party guests.

Data.Name: Seagram's 7 Crown Whiskey
Data.Description:
Seagram's 7 blended whiskey is all American. Despite the Canadian heritage of the Seagram’s company, Seagram’s Seven isn't actually a Canadian whiskey. 

It does however taste reminiscent of its Canadian brethren: it’s both sweet and smooth while still being a little bit spicy. The nose offers up a lot of smokiness, a good amount of herbs, as well as some honey elements. Meanwhile, the taste is a lot like charred wood and apricots with just a touch of butter. Highly drinkable and easily mixable, it’s very commonly paired with 7Up for the classic 7 & 7 cocktail.

Data.Name: Ron Zacapa XO
Data.Description: This limited-release Zacapa XO Solera Gran Reserva Especial Premium Rum (in a stylish flat decanter) won Gold in the Super-Premium category at the International Rum Festival for several years after its release in 2000, and was given the Platinum award for the Super-Premium category in 2002.

Data.Name: Grand Old Parr
Data.Description:
Pour a glass of true luxury with the unique and timeless taste of Grand Old Parr 12 Year Old Blended Scotch Whisky. Distilled from fine grains in the heart of Scotland, our 80 proof whisky has been matured for 12 years to ensure a deep character and bold taste. Whether you sip it on its own or with a mixer, our scotch whisky presents a refined glass to enthusiasts around the globe. Simply serve as a classic whisky neat in a chilled glass

Born in London in 1871 by the Greenless Brothers Co., the Grand Old Parr brand has preserved its dimpled bottle design and aged whisky flavor, ensuring a strong heritage for an exceptional spirit.

Data.Name: Crown Royal XO
Data.Description:
Crafted by the Crown Royal Master Blender, XO furthers the Crown Royal signature blend from 50 of our finest whiskies, and then finishes them in cognac casks. Resulting in both an extraordinary complex and smooth expression, Crown Royal XO is an elegant whisky that is deliciously balanced with hints of vanilla, spice and rich dry fruit.

This extraordinary blend is best enjoyed neat or on the rocks.

Data.Name: Crown Royal Vanilla
Data.Description: Carefully selected whiskies are infused with the rich flavor of Madagascar Bourbon Vanilla to create Crown Royal Vanilla. The blend finishes with a vicious, warming Crème Brulee aftertaste.

Data.Name: Blue Moon Belgian White Cans
Data.Description: Blue Moon is a Belgian Style Wheat Ale brewed with Valencia orange peel for a subtle sweetness and bright, citrus aroma. Fruity & Flavorful with 5.4% ABV. Imagined in Belgium and born in Denver, Blue Moon Belgian White is one of the first Belgian-Style Wheat Ales in the United States. Blue Moon Belgian White is brewed with Valencia orange peel, a touch of coriander, oats and wheat for a complex and balanced taste that shines brighter. Garnish with an orange wheel to highlight the beer's citrus aroma. Craft a better night with a taste that shines brighter and grab a Blue Moon; Don't forget to garnish with an orange wheel. Nothing beats a Blue Moon with your friends on a long weekend!

Data.Name: Six Point Resin IPA
Data.Description: Sixpoint Resin is one of the hoppiest beers available, relying on the resin in hop cones for its eponymous name. Self-admittedly, brewmasters almost spit it out upon their first taste, citing the lupulin shift. The lupulin shift is nature's way of indicating bitterness and subsequently, poison. But you shouldn't fear the hop cone, resin or the bitterness that overwhelms your taste buds. Instead, you should embrace everything that it's bringing to you. At 9.1 percent ABV, this Double IPA has a blend of bitterness and sweetness that's good for just about any occasion.

Data.Name: Brooklyn Lager
Data.Description: Brooklyn Lager is amber gold in color and displays a firm malt center supported by a refreshing bitterness and floral hop aroma. Caramel malts show in the finish. The aromatic qualities of the beer are enhanced by dry hopping, the centuries old practice of steeping the beer with fresh hops as it undergoes a long, cold maturation. The result is a wonderfully flavorful beer, smooth, refreshing and very versatile with food.

Data.Name: Samuel Adams '76 Cans
Data.Description: By experimenting with both lager and ale yeast strains, the brewers at Sam Adams came up with the concept for a brand new beer – Sam ’76. This truly unique brew takes two active fermentations and blends them together to create a deliciously harmonious result. This process delivevers a distinct flavor that showcases the slight fruitiness of an ale with the balanced drinkability and smoothness of a lager. Sam ’76 will surprise any craf beer lover with its huge flavor and aroma along with a light-bodied, refreshing crispness. At just 4.7% ABV, this brew is perfect for those sessionable occasions. Cascade, Citra, Mosaic, Simcoe and Galaxy hops impart a tropical citrus aroma that gives way to a bright, juicy citrus hop flavor but without the hop bitterness. The brewers have been experimenting for over a year, tested over 60 iterations with multiple combinations of 12 dierent hop varieties in the nano brewery in Boston in order to perfect the Sam ’76 recipe.

Data.Name: Samuel Adams Boston Lager Cans
Data.Description: This is the beer that started it all. Samuel Adams Boston Lager helped lead the American beer revolution, reviving a passion for full-flavored brews that are robust and rich with character.  Since 1984, Samuel Adams Boston Lager has used only the finest hand-selected ingredients to create this perfectly balanced and complex original brew.

Data.Name: Samuel Adams Boston Lager
Data.Description: This is the beer that started it all. Samuel Adams Boston Lager helped lead the American beer revolution, reviving a passion for full-flavored brews that are robust and rich with character.  Since 1984, Samuel Adams Boston Lager has used only the finest hand-selected ingredients to create this perfectly balanced and complex original brew.

Data.Name: Goose Island IPA Cans
Data.Description:
Goose Island's India Pale Ale recalls a time when ales shipped from England to India were highly hopped to preserve their distinct taste during the long journey. The result is a hop lover's dream with a fruity aroma, set off by a dry malt middle, and long hop finish.  

Founded in Chicago in 1988, Goose Island is a successful craft brewery and produces some of the most popular, and award winning, beers in the U.S. Since 1989, Goose Island beers have won a variety of awards at acclaimed beer events including the World Beer Championships, World Beer Cup, World Expo of Beer and the Great American Beer Festival (GABF)

Data.Name: Goose Island IPA
Data.Description:
Goose Island's India Pale Ale recalls a time when ales shipped from England to India were highly hopped to preserve their distinct taste during the long journey. The result is a hop lover's dream with a fruity aroma, set off by a dry malt middle, and long hop finish.  

Founded in Chicago in 1988, Goose Island is a successful craft brewery and produces some of the most popular, and award winning, beers in the U.S. Since 1989, Goose Island beers have won a variety of awards at acclaimed beer events including the World Beer Championships, World Beer Cup, World Expo of Beer and the Great American Beer Festival (GABF)

Data.Name: Harpoon IPA Cans
Data.Description: Harpoon IPA finds harmony in the combination of hops, malt, and yeast so that no single ingredient dominates the drinking experience. The sturdy malt backbone provides depth of body and color and is balanced by a pleasantly hoppy finish...best enjoyed with friends.

Data.Name: Night Shift Nite Lite
Data.Description:
Nite Lite is raising the light beer standard - an unfiltered, unpasteurized, all natural, craft light lager.

Simple, light bodied, and crisp, just as a light beer should be. Slightly floral on the nose, with aromas of cracker and wheat.

Data.Name: Pseudo Sue
Data.Description:
Brewed by Toppling Goliath
5.8% ABV
"The hype surrounding the launch of Pseudo Sue in Chicago was immense so we'll cut straight to it. These cans are contract brewed in Florida and we just don't get the hype. Word on the street is the bottled Iowa version is immensely better, but unfortunately those won't be here until later this year. This is a perfectly drinkable citrus-forward IPA that Chicagoans will quickly abandon for the many superior fresh options brewed right here in town." - Deborah from thehopreview.com

Data.Name: Post Shift
Data.Description: There will be no working during drinking hours! Brewed with Bavarian malt and hops, this everyday Pilsner is bright, crisp and refreshing. We think it’s the perfect way to end the work day. Clock out, post-up and enjoy!

Data.Name: Blood Orange Wheat
Data.Description:
Blood Orange Wheat debuted in our Beer Hall and it quickly became a fan favorite. This German-style radler is fruit forward, juicy and bloody refreshing. Lean back and enjoy!
4% ABV

Data.Name: Citra Brau
Data.Description:
DRY HOPPED CITRA LAGER
Deep golden in color, this hoppy lager is bursting with aromatic American Hops. We used Citra Hops throughout the entire brewing process to give this classic golden lager a tropical, fruity flavor and juicy finish.
5.5% ABV

Data.Name: Smoke & Dagger
Data.Description:
From Jack's Abby Craft Lagers. Cloaked in Mystery, this Black Lager is brewed with traditional old world ingredients and cutting edge lagering techniques. The perfect balance between old and new.
5.6% ABV

Data.Name: Night Shift Whirlpool
Data.Description:
16 oz cans.
Whirlpool is Night Shift's flagship New England-style pale ale; crisp and citrus-forward, with notes of grapefruit and wheat; juicy and soft.

Brewed with Mosaic/Summer Hops and dry hopped with Mosaic. Notes of Grapefruit and wheat with a juicy and soft body.

Data.Name: Night Shift Santilles
Data.Description: 16 oz cans. Smooth-sipping IPA brewed in Boston with massive hop profile. Crisp, tropical and delicious.

Data.Name: Ransack the Universe
Data.Description: 16 oz cans. Galaxy hops from Myrtleford, Victoria in Australia and Mosaic hops from Yakima, Washington, USA, deliver aromas and flavors of tropical fruits, mango and citrus. Light malt body lets the hops shine through, and finishes crisp but not bitter.  A hemispheric hop mashup.

Data.Name: Ciroc Watermelon
Data.Description:
Ciroc Summer Watermelon is a rich tasting spirit made with vodka five times distilled from fine French grapes, finished in a tailor-made copper pot still in Southern France. The vodka is masterfully infused with a distinctive blend of fresh tasting, ripe Summer Watermelons and other natural flavors, resulting in a delectably juicy fresh taste accented by a sweetness and zest that carries into a smooth finish.

The liquid is packaged in a luxurious and sultry red and white bottle with sleek matte red lettering, commemorating a fiery hot summer celebration. Ciroc Summer Watermelon can be enjoyed on the rocks or mixed with a variety of fresh ingredients such as pineapple juice, cranberry juice, lemonade and lime.

Data.Name: Test Keg
Data.Description: Test Keg

Data.Name: Everclear Alcohol 190 Proof 750
Data.Description: Good ol' ever clear. Watch out.

Data.Name: Tomaiolo Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Light straw yellow. Crispy, fresh and fruity bouquet. Very elegant, soft and delicate with hints of hazelnuts to the finish. Ideal with grilled chicken, fish course or salads.

Data.Name: S.A. Prum Essence Riesling
Data.Description:
Pale gold in color. On the nose, aromatic, with scents of apricot and peach. On the palate, fresh fruit flavors of pineapple and apricot are perfectly balanced by a racy acidity and mineral character.

Enjoy on its own or with a range of light appetizers and seafood dishes.

Data.Name: Mezzacorona Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: A delightful Pinot Grigio to be enjoyed for its aromatic crisp green apple, mineral and honeysuckle notes.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: At the risk of sounding suggestive, we dare you to indulge in a little skinny dipping. That’s right, we’re asking you to experience the thrill of the naked grape in a glass of our lively Pinot Grigio. With nothing to hide behind, this gorgeous single-varietal wine bares all with bright fruit flavors and an exuberant acidity that makes you want to shout “yahoo!” and go streaking through the vines. Though we’re technically breaking the rules of Ménage à Trois by giving all our love to just one grape, we think you’ll agree that in this case, one sometimes is better than three. (Gasp! We’re not becoming monogamous, are we?)

Data.Name: Leese-Fitch Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
Leese-Fitch Sauvignon Blanc is a crisp and refreshing wine. This wine has clean aromas of lemon peel, ground ginger, and blanched almonds. The palate has a bright acidity that carries along zesy and refreshing flavors of fresh citrus and white nectarine.

This is a perfect wine for any time of the year and goes especially well with organic mixed greens in a fines herbes-lemon vinaigrette and grilled pork chops with a Moroccan glaze, almonds, endive, and fresh veggies.

Data.Name: Leese-Fitch Chardonnay
Data.Description: This medium-bodied wine, is intensely golden in color, and exudes aromas of tangerine, citrus, pineapple and green apple. The flavors are in sync and crisp with the notable presence of both orange and peach. The finish on this Chardonnay is exceptionally smooth and balanced, which makes it a wine that is easy to enjoy.

Data.Name: Kono Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Intense citrus and gooseberry flavours with notes of capsicum and passionfruit. A blend of fruits from the Awatere, Waihopai, and Lower Wairau Valleys gives this Sauvignon Blanc the classic Marlborough fruit burst with great palate weight and a clean, acid finish.

Data.Name: Joel Gott Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Joel Gott Pinot Noir has aromas of sweet cherries and baking spices with a hint of smoke. On the palate, ripe red fruit flavors are followed by elegantly balanced acidity and soft, velvety tannins.

Data.Name: J Lohr Chardonnay
Data.Description:
J. Lohr Chardonnay Riverstone exhibits youthful hues of light to medium straw. The enticing aromas are reminiscent of peaches, tangerine, yellow floral, baking spices, vanilla, and cocoa. These aromas echo on the palate and are complemented by fresh orange and apricot, balanced with creamy texture from aging sur lie. Flavors of crème brûlée and a touch of oak can be found on the long finish.

J. Lohr Chardonnay can be enjoyed with a variety of dishes, such as salmon in a creamy citrus tarragon sauce, chicken with mushroom sauce, or apple fennel salad with a citrus vinaigrette.

Data.Name: Hayes Valley Chardonnay
Data.Description:
Tasting Notes  Hayes Valley Chardonnay opens up with aromas of tropical fruits—pineapples and bananas. Pears and apples are also prevalent, with a hint of toasty oak. Flavors of baked apples, banana and vanilla carry through the palate, along with a creamy mouth feel and a hint of butter. Solid acidity makes this a great wine to pair with many dishes or to drink on its own.

Food Pairings  Chicken dishes (Chicken Piccata, Roasted or Grilled Chicken with a light sauce), Seafood (Steamed Lobster with Butter, Baked Shrimp, Roasted Halibut with a light sauce) and soft, mild cheeses (Brie and Camembert).

Data.Name: Frontera Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: "Unoaked, juicy Chilean cabernet such as this one makes a great summer standby. This has lashings of bold, ripe, classic blackcurranty cabernet fruit and a squirt of verdant, dusky spice on the finish." Jane MacQuitty’s, The Times.

Data.Name: Estancia Chardonnay
Data.Description: The appearance is a shimmering light-straw gold. Aromas of honey, tropical fruits with hints of orange and pineapple. Rich and well-balanced with a delicious, creamy textured mid-palate; ripe fruit, orange, almond, and spice flavors lead to a refreshing, smooth finish. Pairs great with smoked salmon, cream sauce pastas, poultry, pork and mushrooms.

Data.Name: Robert Mondavi Woodridge Red Blend
Data.Description:
This Red Blend combines some of the finest attributes of Petite Sirah, Zinfandel, and Syrah with a touch of other complementary reds, resulting in a deliciously rich, full-bodied blend. The wine offers warm, toasty aromas and flavors, including jammy blackberry, vanilla, and baking spices. It’s full and rich with a long, flavorful finish.

This hearty Red Blend pairs well with savory dishes like burgers, barbeque, sausages, potato skins, and other fried foods.

Data.Name: Manishewitz Concord Grape
Data.Description:
A sweet but balanced wine with a generous mouth feel. The distinct aroma and flavor of fresh Concord grapes.

All Manischewitz Wines are made and bottled under the strict Rabbinical supervision of the Union of Orthodox Jewish Congregations of America. All of our fine products carry the mark of quality that signifies adherence to Orthodox Union guidelines.

Data.Name: Capriccio Bubbly Sangria Mini
Data.Description:
Capriccio Bubbly Sangria Wine, 4-Pack, 375 mL Bottles.

Enjoy your favorite drink after a long day with this pack of Carpiccio Bubbly Sangria Wine in stock. This particular beverage is a summer favorite because of its predominantly fruity flavor, although it can certainly be consumed any time you want. Capriccio sangria is inspired by the famous Spanish drink that features a blend of rich red wine with real fruit juices. It even contains small bits of fruit. The fizzy bubbles add to its refreshing quality, more so if it's served chilled. One pack contains four bottles.

Data.Name: Bota Box Revolution Mini
Data.Description: Bota Box RedVolution reveals rich aromas of black cherry, cocoa and a hint of spice. Extending into lush flavors of dark fruit, cherry and toasty oak, this smooth, full-bodied wine culminates into a juicy, well-balanced finish.

Data.Name: Biagio Cru Lolailo Sangria
Data.Description: Lolailo is the ultimate anytime drink: light-bodied, fruity and refreshing! Available in red and white, Lolailo is made from grapes indigenous to Spain, with natural extracts of orange peels, and Mediterranean cherries and grapes.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Moscato Mini
Data.Description: You don't have to visit a farmers market to take in the rousing scents of rose, lychee fruit, and peach. Just open a bottle of our Moscato wine. A little sweet and very likeable, it speaks of the good life. Beautifully balanced, with good acidity, the creamy peach and honeydew melon will linger on your tongue. Serve while chilled, with light cheeses, desserts, fruits, and loved ones.

Data.Name: Cantina Gabriele Dolcemente Red
Data.Description:
Dolcemente's secret is the blend of the refined character of the Cabernet Sauvignon with the fruitiness of the Cesanese grape. Intense purple color, fresh floral aromas with notes of berry and cherry, very smooth tannins, and lovely sweetness on the palate makes you want to enjoy this wine at room temperature or slightly chilled.
Cabernet Sauvignon (70%) & Cesanese (30%)

Data.Name: Corona Refresca Guava Lime
Data.Description: Corona Refresca is a premium spiked refresher that brings the taste of the tropics from Mexico to you. Corona Refresca Guava Lime is a bright, flavorful malt beverage with 4.5% alcohol by volume and natural fruit flavors. Corona Refresca is crisp, yet flavorful.

Data.Name: Corona Refresca Passionfruit Lime
Data.Description: Corona Refresca is a premium spiked refresher that brings the taste of the tropics from Mexico to you. Corona Refresca Passionfruit Lime is a bright, flavorful malt beverage with 4.5% alcohol by volume and natural fruit flavors. Corona Refresca is crisp, yet flavorful.

Data.Name: Polar Arctic Summer Variety Pack
Data.Description:
Harpoon's CEO launched a spiked seltzer line with Polar. Give it a try!

The new, naturally gluten-free spiked seltzer contains 5% ABV and comes in four well-known Polar flavors: Pineapple Pomelo, Ruby Red Grapefruit, Raspberry Lime and Black Cherry. Starting this week, Atlas Distributing will ship Arctic Summer in six-packs and variety 12-packs throughout New England, New Jersey and Pennsylvania, to liquor stores and select grocery stores, and of course--Tapster.

Data.Name: Barefoot Sangria
Data.Description: Barefoot Sangria. Grape wine with natural flavors of orange, grapefruit, and lemon. Served chilled with your favorite fruits for a flavorful sweet treat. Contains 11% ABV.

Data.Name: Beringer Red Moscato
Data.Description: This innovative blend is the perfect harmony of Moscato, Zinfandel and Petite Sirah. It brings together the vivid aromas and flavors of the Moscato grape with the classic red berry characteristics of Zinfandel and ripe black cherry flavors of Petite Sirah.

Data.Name: Beringer Pink Moscato
Data.Description: Pop the cork on Beringer Vivacious Pink Moscato and let the festivities begin! This carefully crafted sparkling wine offers refreshing aromas and flavors that complemnet a wide variety of cuisine and occassions. Enjoy the bubbles at a special dinner, add a splash of fun to your next brunch, or celebrate with a toast at your next party. Serve Chilled!

Data.Name: Beringer Moscato
Data.Description: This carefully crafted wine offers immediately pleasing peach-scented and honeysuckle aromas with fresh, sweet flavors of juicy stone fruit, honeydew melon, Fuji apple and ripe pear. It is beautifully balanced with crisp acidity and a clean finish.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Riesling
Data.Description: A pure delight to drink, our Riesling wine exhibits floral fragrances, rich ripe melons, and summer peaches. Like a golden sunset, this wine will put you in the perfect mood at the end of the day. Take fresh scallops sautéed in butter, top with fresh herbs, and pour away.

Data.Name: Crown Royal
Data.Description:
The most famous Canadian whiskey of all time, Crown Royal is a smooth blend of 50 Canadian whiskies. This is no new kid on the block, either. Crown Royal has been a liquor cabinet staple since 1939, and this blended whiskey wins new fans all the time.

It has a rich, bold nose with notes of vanilla and fruit. It's an extraordinarily smooth, creamy whiskey, and you'll notice hints of oak before savoring the long, satisfying finish.

Data.Name: Ciroc Red Berry
Data.Description: Ciroc Red Berry is one of the first flavor-infused varietals from the makers of Ciroc Ultra-Premium Vodka. Distilled five times to ensure high quality, the spirit is masterfully infused with raspberry, strawberry and other natural flavors, resulting in a taste experience that is lusciously different and elegantly smooth. The resulting balance of luscious, berry-infused flavor is perfectly highlighted in the Ciroc Cosmo Martini.

Data.Name: Ciroc Mango
Data.Description: Ciroc Mango is distilled five times to ensure high quality. The spirit is masterfully infused with a distinctive blend of mango and other natural flavors, resulting in a taste experience that is lusciously different and elegantly smooth. Tapster delivers for you to enjoy on the rocks, as a shot, or mixed in your favorite cocktail.

Data.Name: Buchanan's 15 Years Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Simply pour over ice in a rocks glass for a simple, perfect serve. Includes one 80 proof 750 mL bottle of Buchanan's Select 15 Years Old Blended Malt Scotch Whisky. Every bottle is the result of more than 130 years of distillation experience, culminating in a delicate liquid with refined and gentle notes. With the perfect balance between smooth and complex, every sip of Buchanan’s offers a standard of excellence that is sure to leave a brilliant impression on your taste buds.

Data.Name: Buchanan's Master Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Buchanan’s Master Blended Scotch was created in the 21st-century by the current Master Blender Keith Law. Using his expertise and craftsmanship, he has selected the finest casks of mature whisky to create this distinctive expression, which offers rich notes of honey, citrus fruit and dark chocolate, backed by smoky, peppery spice.

Data.Name: Belvedere Vodka
Data.Description:
Rye. Water. Character.
Belvedere Vodka is the original and true expression of luxury vodka, created from 600 years of Polish vodka-making tradition. The vodka itself is always authentic, and never artificial. Created exclusively from Polish Dankowskie Rye and quadruple-distilled to create the perfect balance of character and purity; it is completely free of additives, including sugar or glycerin. Dilution with purified water from Belvedere's own artisan wells is essential, enabling the character of the rye to shine. Perfect on the rocks, in a martini or breathing character to any cocktail. Belvedere represents the pinnacle of vodka making tradition. Zero additives, gluten free, naturally smooth.

Data.Name: Corona Refresca Variety Pack
Data.Description: "Malt beverages" from Corona-- they're considered a lighter option as they come in at 199 calories per 12-ounce serving, and they have a 4.5 percent ABV. The passionfruit and guava strains will be sold in six-packs of their own while the coconut one will only be found in a 12-pack variety.

Data.Name: Poland Spring Water
Data.Description: Drink refreshing, crisp water pulled from natural Maine springs that only comes from Poland Spring Brand Natural Spring Water. These large bottles are sure to hydrate your body, even on the go. This 24-pack is perfect for a large event or gathering. The water contains naturally occurring minerals, which gives it hydrating components and a rejuvenating taste.

Data.Name: Nobilo Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
Nobilo Sauvignon Blanc represents the best of what New Zealand has to offer, with classic flavors that consistently showcase the diverse qualities of our Marlborough vineyards, year after year. Fruit was primarily selected from vineyards in Marlborough’s Wairau Valley, which provided complementary layers of tropical fruit flavors. A smaller portion from vineyards in the Awatere Valley provided balance with citrus-driven, fresh, crisp, and vibrant flavors.

COLOR: Pale yellow 
AROMA: Bright, lifted tropical fruit and herbs with notes of pineapple, elderflower, cantaloupe, and citrus. 
PALATE: Lively acidity perfectly balances the underlying fruit sweetness. Fresh and crisp on the finish. 
FOOD PAIRING: Enjoyable on its own as an apéritif or with lemon herb chicken, summer salads, or lighter seafood dishes.

Data.Name: Bulleit Barrel Strength Bourbon
Data.Description: Medium-amber in color, with gentle spiciness and sweet oak aromas. The mid-palate is smooth with tones of maple, oak, and nutmeg. The finish is long, dry and satiny with a light toffee flavor, but with deepened oak notes.

Data.Name: Patrón Extra Añejo Tequila
Data.Description: Bright dark gold, Aroma dry fruits vanilla and light banana, Taste: Fruity with notes of light agave honey and vanilla, finish: Oak , vanilla and dry fruit.

Data.Name: Blue Plastic Cups
Data.Description: A pack of 20 blue plastic cups.

Data.Name: Bicycle Playing Cards
Data.Description: Standard Bicycle playing cards for you to play your favorite drinking games with. Or to show off a slight of hand? Up to you!

Data.Name: Campo Viejo Cava Brut Rose
Data.Description: Crisp and dry Campo Viejo Brut Rose is delicious and serious; berry flavors are nicely accented with undertones of sweet earth.

Data.Name: Stones Original Green Ginger Wine
Data.Description:
Stone's Original Green Ginger Wine is still made to the same recipe by blending the finest quality raisins and pure ground ginger and is enjoyed in so many ways by millions of consumers each year.
Many enjoy Stone's on its own or over ice, but it is most famously drunk as a 'Whisky Mac' when mixed with whisky. The warmth of Stone's is a perfect complement to the smooth taste of the whisky. This perennial 'Winter Warmer' is the perfect way to relax on the long dark evenings.
Displaying its versatility, at the other extreme, Stone's creates the perfect summer cooler as a long drink combined with lemonade or other mixers such as ginger ale. In the last few years the resurgent interest in cocktails has prompted prestigious mixologists to discover an array of tempting concoctions. Some of the most stylish bars are now creating new drinks by exploiting the, perhaps, unique potential of Stone's Original Ginger Wine.
Not to be outdone, the current generation of chefs have smuggled St

Data.Name: Apothic Inferno
Data.Description: This small-batch, limited release Red Blend has been aged for 60 days in whiskey barrels to deliver a masterful and unexpected taste experience. This Wine with a Whiskey Soul emerges from the flames of the time-honored craft of whiskey-making. A time-intensive barrel-aging process enhances the wine’s rich flavors and aromas. Red and dark fruit flavors combine with layers of maple and spice, giving way to a long, clean finish.

Data.Name: Ketel One Vodka
Data.Description:
As a premium vodka, Ketel One is best enjoyed neat for the full flavor profile. Even so, you can't beat the array of cocktails born of this expertly-crafted liquid, including the quintessential Ketel One Mule. Fill a copper mug or highball glass with Ketel One, ginger beer and fresh lime juice garnished with lime for an elegant drink that stands out at parties.

Prefer a martini? Try Ketel One vodka with vermouth and a twist of lemon. For something even more refreshing, go with a Ketel Soda, which is simply Ketel One vodka and club soda with fresh cucumber and mint.

Data.Name: Bellagio Rosse Dolce
Data.Description: Deep red with violet hints. A fresh bouquet with hints of red fruits, especially raspberry and blackberry. Full-bodied, with a pleasant sweet note, well balanced with some acidity and a natural sparkling note.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Sparkling Rose
Data.Description: Are you craving a sparkling romance? Let us tickle you with playful, pink bubbles of passion and cranberry aromas, while our blissful raspberries, wild strawberries, and delicate scent of rose petals arouse your senses with flirty, fruity kisses of sweetness. We are a Sparkling Rosé, with a little Italian in us, so sparks will fly.

Data.Name: Finback Brewery Stormy Water
Data.Description: A collaboration with Maryland's Burley Oak Brewing.  6% sour ale, inspired by a dark and stormy with ginger and touch of lime and molasses. Odd and cool.

Data.Name: Foreign Objects Beer Mind/Body/Light/Sound
Data.Description: Time is already gone... Throw your mind away and fall into the sea of Galaxy & Mosaic hops obsessively layered in this New-American Hoppy Ale. Bursting with aromas of eternal existentialism, ripe stone fruit, consciousness exploration, mystical grapefruit flesh, mango-nectar, and resinous proton waves! There are some people on earth. They live with separate minds. Dissolve your body today. There is no more outside.

Data.Name: Revival Brewing Jenn's Mocha Stout
Data.Description: Dedicated to 94HJY’s mid-day rock goddess. This sweet stout conjures chocolate and coffee tones and is stone cold delicious. Roasted malt and moderate hop flavor lurking in a tall glass of this black magic woman. It’s a brewed to raise hell with a taste that slays.

Data.Name: Victory Brewing Juice Boost Cans
Data.Description: Experience tart and tangy flavors and aromas reminiscent of a delicious glass of juice from the combination of Citra dry-hopping with an expertly executed natural souring process.

Data.Name: Victory Brewing Golden Monkey Cans
Data.Description: Meet the most curious of all the monkeys. His journey to discover the truth about life lead him to meditate with monks, wrestle with lions and study the stars. Golden Monkey crafts an ale with imported malts, Belgian yeast, and a mix of magical spices resulting in mystical flavors that will enlighten your senses.

Data.Name: Troegs Independent Brewing Nugget Nectar
Data.Description:
It’s impossible to forget your first squeeze. Once a year, as the newest humulus lupulus harvest arrives at Tröegs, which then blends these super-fresh hops into an Imperial Amber Ale. Excessively dry-hopped, Nugget Nectar is an explosion of pine, resin and mango.

We taste: pine, white peppercorn, grapefruit pith, mango

Data.Name: Southern Tier Brewing Co. Samoa This
Data.Description: A delectable dessert beer with notes of chocolate, coconut, and caramel.

Data.Name: Sloop Brewing Co. Juice Bomb
Data.Description: Sloop's juicy, hazy, flagship IPA. The low bitterness and late hopping showcase the citrusy, juicy notes of American hops. A blast of tropical aroma is followed by a resiny and balanced flavor. Juice bomb features all the aspects and nuances of full hop flavor — not just bitterness.

Data.Name: Sloop Brewing Co. Coco Baked
Data.Description:
This oatmeal stout isn’t only made with half baked oatmeal — there’s also brewed totally toasted coconut!
A stout to remind you of warmer times. Like a pina colada for the winter. If pina coladas were oatmeal stouts.

Data.Name: Sixpoint Brewery Resin
Data.Description:
We’re talking about something called the lupulin shift. Ever heard of it? In nature, bitterness indicates poison. So that first sip of bitter beer doesn’t just offend the palate, it actually inspires fear. But IPA is the most popular style in all of craft beer. So how does that work?
At some point, this distaste/fear flips like a switch. The shift can happen over the course of months or over the course of a sixpack, seriously. Then the fear turns to craving. It’s like how pain and pleasure are so closely related. Don’t fear the mysterious power of the hop cone… embrace it. There are insane heights of flavors to be reached in there. Sure it stings, but it feels so good at the same time.

Now that your brain’s been shifted, and the siren song of that hoppy RESIN comes calling… we’re left with one question: Did we bring you over to the dark side, or show you the light?

Data.Name: Sixpoint Brewery Alpenflo
Data.Description: There’s your proof—Alpenflo is 100% barley malt, with hops sourced directly from family farms in Bavaria, and brewed in horizontal tanks… with absolutely nothing to fizzle it out. We’re talking about the exact right conditions to create a bright, beautiful beer.

Data.Name: Newburgh Brewing Co. Cream Ale
Data.Description: Originally brewed by ale breweries to compete with the surging popularity of lager beer, it remains a regional specialty in the Northeast United States. Newburgh's version is light-bodied and pale straw color, but uses no corn or rice as many of the original versions did. The result is a supremely malty and refreshing version of a style dear to our hearts.

Data.Name: Monday Night Brewing Ante Meridiem
Data.Description: Don’t sleep on Ante Meridiem. Monday Night's massive (13.5% ABV) Imperial brown ale is aged in Georgia’s own ASW Distillery bourbon barrels. The brewery adds locally roasted coffee from Batdorf and Bronson, Ugandan vanilla beans and maple syrup. The result is a boozy, sweet, satisfying drink that works well with chocolatey desserts, ice cream, or a Connecticut-leaf cigar.

Data.Name: LIC Beer Project Company Man
Data.Description: Classic single hopped pilsner with all Hallertau Mittlefrau hops from Germany as well as Weyerman Pilsner malt. Slightly bready with overtones of light citrus. Finishes very clean.

Data.Name: Common Roots Brewing Co. Bright Light DIPA
Data.Description: Modern style Double IPA made with all Citra hops.

Data.Name: Cigar City Brewing Jai Alai
Data.Description: Jai Alai, a game native to the Basque region of Spain, is played on a court called a fronton. Jai Alai players attempt to catch a ball using a curved mitt whilst the ball travels at speeds up to 188 mph! Proving they have a sense of humor the Spanish dubbed this game, with its ball traveling at race car speeds, “the merry game.” Tampa was once home to a bustling Jai Alai fronton but sadly all that remains of Jai Alai in the Tampa Bay area is this India Pale Ale that Cigar City brews in tribute to the merry game. The India Pale Ale style of beer has its roots in the ales sent from England to thirsty British troops in India during the 18th century. Pair Jai Alai India Pale Ale with beef empanadas, deviled crabs and other spicy dishes.

Data.Name: Captain Lawrence Brewing Co. Leaking Staves
Data.Description: American Sour Ale aged in French Oak Foudres with NY grown cabernet grapes. This beer is a complex treat. Enjoy now or lay it down for years to come.

Data.Name: Captain Lawrence Brewing Flaming Fury
Data.Description: Created by blending Captain Lawrence's Sour Golden Ale with ripe and juicy Hudson Valley peaches. Aged in French oak foundres until the tart flavors of the beer and the sweet flavors of the peaches meld into one. Enjoy on a hot Summer day with a peach in hand.

Data.Name: Weyerbacher Brewing Sunday Morning Stout
Data.Description: Sunday Morning Stout, 12.7% ABV, is an American Imperial Stout aged in bourbon barrels. Aromas of roasted coffee and bourbon awaken your senses while their flavors blend with hints of chocolate, roasted malt, vanilla and caramel. The perfect cap to a Saturday night or start to Sunday morning.

Data.Name: Hermit Thrush Brewery Supah Phunk #5
Data.Description: Who got the Phunk? We got the Phunk!  Supah Phunk is the ever-changing playground for one of Hermit Thrush's favorite yeast cultures. Each batch has the same cheesy, funky Philly yeast as the original, but after spending its whole 10-week life in a blend of red and white wine oak barrels, it kicks the funk up a notch. Plan for a tart, malty, funky saison with a mellow hop groove to make it go down smooth. Want to really get down with the funk? Try it with Twig Farm Goat Tomme, a Vermont made raw-milk goat cheese. Huah!

Data.Name: Ithaca Beer Co. Flower Power
Data.Description: Enjoy the clover honey hue and tropical nose of Ithaca Beer's celebrated flagship ale. Flower Power is simultaneously punchy and soothing with a big body and a finish that boasts pineapple and grapefruit. Ithaca hops and dry hops Flower Power four different times throughout the brewing process for a powerful floral hop experience. Rated the best IPA in New York State, Flower Power is highly regarded among the most discerning hop heads.

Data.Name: Ithaca Beer Co. Apricot Wheat
Data.Description: Ithaca Beer's smooth wheat beer is light in color and body… perfect for those looking for a lighter taste. The combination of wheat and barley gives Apricot Wheat a different malt character than our other ales. The hint of apricot gives this beer a pleasant nose and fruity finish.

Data.Name: Hermit Thrush Brewery Brattlebeer
Data.Description: Inspired by the town of Brattleboro, the unique sour ale captures the best of local flavors. Brattlebeer is slightly tart, light bodied and dry with both fruity and malty undertones, and a rocky, champagne-like head.  Fermented spontaneously with a blend of local apple cider, malt, and hops, this delicate pale ale pairs well with soft cheeses and herbal entrees, and often compliments seasonal fruit desserts.

Data.Name: Grimm Artisanal Ales Double Negative
Data.Description: This is the beer that first put Grimm on the map, and won consecutive GABF medals for imperial stout: Silver in 2014 and Gold in 2015. The newest batch is tasting RIGHT. When the weather starts getting colder, there’s nothing better. No ancho chilis, vanilla, tequila barrels, coffee, cacao, marshmallows, pumpkins or bananas necessary.

Data.Name: Foreign Objects Beer Death Posture
Data.Description: Assume the Death Posture and glean beyond this subjective experience of reality! Attain the Chaote’s gnosis - the Void-Self Perception! This Foreign Objects New-American Hoppy Ale will inspire you! Galaxy, Motueka, & Calypso hops combine to create aromas of intense citrus meringue, ripe tropical fruit ambrosia, and a frighteningly sincere understanding that the only way out of subjectivity is through the Void! Drink deeply, as sensory overload & mystical wisdom are sure to follow!

Data.Name: Casa Noble Crystal Tequila
Data.Description: USDA certified organic, 100% Single Estate Blue Agave, triple distilled for a superior taste. This Blanco is in a class by itself. Double Gold Medal - San Francisco Spirit Competition. Gold Medal - BTI. Kosher Certified.

Data.Name: 19 Crimes The Banished Dark Red
Data.Description:
Color: Dark red shrouded by purple hues. 
Nose: Intense lifted dark chocolate and vanilla aromatics balanced with blackberry and plum fruits.
Palate: Full and round on the palate with a distinct sweetness making the wine rich and mouth coating.

Data.Name: Blueshine Blueberry Moonshine
Data.Description: It’s liquor with a Maine twist! Blueshine begins with Maine barley, fermented in our large wooden fermenter and then run through our copper still. When the “shine” is ready, we add in a bucket of Maine wild blueberries and complete the potion with a subtle helping of Maine maple syrup. It’s a taste of blueberry pancakes ... with a kick.

Data.Name: Triple Eight Blueberry Vodka
Data.Description: Triple 8 Blueberry Vodka is made with wild low-bush blueberries from Maine, infused into our organic spirit. No other blueberry vodka in the world can match the true flavor, color and aroma that comes through in Triple Eight Blueberry vodka. Plain and simple, real fruit, real people, really good!

Data.Name: Bell's Two Hearted Ale 1/2 Barrel Keg
Data.Description:
Brewed with 100% Centennial hops from the Pacific Northwest and named after the Two Hearted River in Michigan’s Upper Peninsula, this IPA is bursting with hop aromas ranging from pine to grapefruit from massive hop additions in both the kettle and the fermenter.

Perfectly balanced with a malt backbone and combined with the signature fruity aromas of Bell's house yeast, this beer is remarkably drinkable and well suited for adventures everywhere.

7% ABV

Data.Name: Sunny Ridge Pilsner 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description:
This aromatic lager features a sunshine hue, herbal noble hop nose, and a dry finish. We balance pilsner malt with a blend of European hops and polish it with extended periods of cold conditioning. You’re royalty, now drink like it.

Food Pairing: Seafood, prosciutto, spiced meats, sweet vegetables

Data.Name: Samuel Adams Summer Ale 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description: Same delicious beer, brand new look. Summer Ale returns for its 21st year with limited edition packaging that’s as exciting as a summertime adventure. From the blazing yellow of the afternoon sun to the fiery orange of an evening sunset to the electric blue tint of a summer night, the colors of Summer Ale and its crisp, citrusy flavor, are your perfect companion anywhere, anytime.

Data.Name: Prima Pils 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description:
Prima! It’s a German exclamation of joy. It’s a recognition of accomplishment. With heaps of whole flower European hops and fine German malts, Victory Brewing's Prima Pils has achieved the bracing herbal bite and smooth malt flavor they sought. Prima… an exclamation of Victory! Prost!

5.3% IPA

Data.Name: Lunch IPA 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description: Lunch is an IPA by the Main Beer Company. It has intense hop flavors and aromas of tropical and citrus fruits and pine dominate, and a subtle malt sweetness brings the beer into balance.

Data.Name: Jai Alai IPA 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description:
Jai Alai, a game native to the Basque region of Spain, is played on a court called a fronton. Jai Alai players attempt to catch a ball using a curved mitt whilst the ball travels at speeds up to 188mph! Proving they have a sense of humor the Spanish dub...
The India Pale Ale style of beer has its roots in the ales sent from England to thirsty British troops in India during the 18th century. Pair Jai Alai India Pale Ale with beef empanadas, deviled crabs, and other spicy dishes.

Data.Name: Grapefruit Sculpin 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description: Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin IPA pours a deep golden orange with a moderate white head. Aroma is bitter grapefruit and lemon zest. Taste is bitter grapefruit, slightly dank, dry as a desert and some white wine. The hops are there but that bitter grapefruit just keeps coming out.

Data.Name: Stillwater Artisanal Ales Password Double IPA
Data.Description: Double India Pale Ale double dry-hopped with mosaic and galaxy.

Data.Name: Allagash River Trip 1/6 Barrel Keg
Data.Description: A companion to backyards, backwoods, and balconies alike. River Trip is a Belgian-style session ale with hop-forward grapefruit and stone fruit notes. It’s brewed in the table beer style with local grains and spiced with coriander for an extra hint of citrus. Dry hopping with Comet and Azacca contributes to the mix of melon and grapefruit notes in the beer’s aroma. Low-ABV and available in 16 oz. cans: so it’s good for any adventure.

Data.Name: Stillwater Ales Collaborations Are For Lovers
Data.Description: Collaboration with Sleeping Giant. Imperial stout brewed with mango, coffee, vanilla

Data.Name: Stillwater Artisanal Ales Extra Dry
Data.Description: Brewed with rice and designed to mimic the subtle and drinkable flavors of sake, this low alcohol saison is the softer side of Stillwater.

Data.Name: Rodney Strong Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Rich, lush, and structured, this Cabernet Sauvignon displays intense aromas flavors of blackberry, blackcurrant, cassis and crushed violet. This wine is velvety with a smooth, lingering finish of toasty baking spices, vanilla, and cocoa. Enjoy this wine now with blue cheese crostini, grilled vegetables, braised beef short ribs or cellar it for enjoyment in years to come.

Blend: 96% Cabernet Sauvignon, 3% Petit Verdot, 1% Malbec

Data.Name: Rodney Strong Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Rodney strong Pinot Noir has lovely aromas of red fruit, floral, and earth. With a soft and silky texture, on the palate dark cherry, cranberry, and baking spice characteristics shine through with balance, acidity and a nice lingering finish.

Data.Name: Rodney Strong Chardonnay
Data.Description: Toasty vanilla and spice complexities, with an elegant fullness and creamy texture on the palate. In the glass, the wine is both creamy and crisp, with golden delicious yellow apple, baked pie spices with a hint of minerality on the long finish.

Data.Name: Terra d'Oro Zinfandel Deaver Vineyard
Data.Description: The Terra d’Oro Deaver Zinfandel has a deep garnet color with lifted aromas of dark fruit, clove and spicy oak. The palate is focused with crisp and juicy layers of ripe blackberry, spicy plum and soft chewy tannins. The baked spice components add complexity to this bold wine and support a great balance of power and restraint. For a zesty pairing, serve this wine with a roasted rack of lamb or a juicy ribeye steak.

Data.Name: Terra d'Oro Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Terra d’Oro Pinot Grigio entices with a nose of ripe, bright pear and clover blossom. Rich and dense, the mouth oozes with juicy pear and stone fruit flavors, finishing with an elegant touch of toasted French oak. Try pairing this delightful wine with a mild cheese and fruit plate.

Data.Name: Terra d'Oro Petite Sirah
Data.Description:
The Terra d’Oro Petite Sirah is bold and spicy with terrific mineral details and refined tannins. A dark and opulent aubergine color in the glass, the wine has a powerful nose of sweet oak vanillin and bright, juicy fruit. The palate is focused with crisp and captivating flavors of ripe blueberry and jammy blackberry cobbler, with a warm oaky spice note on the finish.

For a delightful and mouth-watering pairing, serve this wine with roast tenderloin of wild Boar, or baked root vegetable lasagna.

Data.Name: Sutter Home White Zinfandel Mini
Data.Description: Minis! A refreshing White Zinfandel that delivers ripe notes of strawberries, melon, and raspberries. Medium sweet with smooth, soft finish. This is a wine that is refreshing and fun to drink!

Data.Name: Sutter Home White Zinfandel
Data.Description: A refreshing White Zinfandel that delivers ripe notes of strawberries, melon, and raspberries. Medium sweet with smooth, soft finish. This is a wine that is refreshing and fun to drink!

Data.Name: Sutter Home Sauvignon Blanc Mini
Data.Description: Minis! Sutter Home Sauvignon Blanc practically invites you to kick off your shoes and kick back with friends. It’s lively and brisk, with zesty citrus and passion fruit aromas that give way to a tangle of honeydew melon, grapefruit and lime flavors accented by spice and mineral notes. Our Sauvignon Blanc is exceptionally food-friendly, and its pleasant grassiness and herbal qualities make it a fantastic partner for foods featuring fresh herbs like tarragon shrimp, thyme-roasted chicken, and linguine with pesto. But when it comes right down to it, nothing beats a chilled glass of Sauvignon Blanc and a classic Caesar salad eaten on a picnic blanket.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Sangria
Data.Description: This sangria has juicy berry and citrus flavors, as well as a subtle hint of spice. This sangria is best served on ice with a fresh fruit garnish.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Riesling Mini
Data.Description: Minis! A pure delight to drink, our Riesling wine exhibits floral fragrances, rich ripe melons, and summer peaches. Like a golden sunset, this wine will put you in the perfect mood at the end of the day. Take fresh scallops sautéed in butter, top with fresh herbs, and pour away.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Sutter Home Sauvignon Blanc practically invites you to kick off your shoes and kick back with friends. It’s lively and brisk, with zesty citrus and passion fruit aromas that give way to a tangle of honeydew melon, grapefruit and lime flavors accented by spice and mineral notes. Our Sauvignon Blanc is exceptionally food-friendly, and its pleasant grassiness and herbal qualities make it a fantastic partner for foods featuring fresh herbs like tarragon shrimp, thyme-roasted chicken, and linguine with pesto. But when it comes right down to it, nothing beats a chilled glass of Sauvignon Blanc and a classic Caesar salad eaten on a picnic blanket.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Pinot Noir Mini
Data.Description: Minis! This classic Pinot Noir never disappoints. Pair it with your favorite old movie or dearest friend, this wine has it all. With layers of richness, freshness, and spice, this fruit-forward blend is here to stay—not only on your table, but front and center in our lineup of tried and true reds. This versatile wine pairs well with everything from lamb kabobs and salmon to mushroom risotto and roasted vegetables.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Pinot Grigio Mini
Data.Description: Minis! This laid-back wine is very approachable, making it an easy choice. Fresh floral aromas and sweet flavors of white peach, melon, citrus, and tropical fruits beg your palate not to forget this night or this wine. Pinot Grigio wine's crispness primes the palate for food and pairs well with all seafood, cheeses, and spicy Latin and Asian fare.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Pink Moscato Mini
Data.Description: Mini! The Sutter Home Moscato is not only a beautiful rosy-pink hue, but it is also extravagantly perfumed with luxurious aromas of creamy white peaches, caramel and honeysuckle. The luscious passion fruit and honeydew melon flavors are sweet, creamy and balanced with nice acidity. A hint of vanilla leads to an opulent finish. Enjoy this wine with an authentic vanilla bean Italian gelato or a fresh berry tart.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Pink Moscato
Data.Description: The Sutter Home Moscato is not only a beautiful rosy-pink hue, but it is also extravagantly perfumed with luxurious aromas of creamy white peaches, caramel and honeysuckle. The luscious passion fruit and honeydew melon flavors are sweet, creamy and balanced with nice acidity. A hint of vanilla leads to an opulent finish. Enjoy this wine with an authentic vanilla bean Italian gelato or a fresh berry tart.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Moscato
Data.Description: Extravagantly perfumed, with beautiful scents of white peaches, rose, and lichee. Well-balanced with good acidity and a lingering finish of sweet and creamy peach and honeydew melon flavors. Light-bodied to enjoy as an aperitif or pair with fruit, light cheeses, sorbets (strawberry, peach, pear, or apple), and other light desserts.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Merlot Mini
Data.Description: Minis! Fresh and smooth with black cherry flavors and hints of smoke and spice, this wine with moderate tannins is your easygoing, low-maintenance friend for life. Perfect with tomato-based pastas, chicken, beef, lamb, and pizza.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Chardonnay Mini
Data.Description: Minis! Crisp and fresh, our Chardonnay wine boasts an impressive lineup of flavors, leaving a lasting palate impression. Smooth, rich, and creamy tones combine with fresh fruit flavors for a long and luxurious aftertaste. It makes an ideal match for seafood or poultry, veal or pork chops, cream sauce pastas, and cheeses.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Cabernet Sauvignon Mini
Data.Description: This medium-bodied wine has no agenda other than inviting you to partake in its rich cherry flavors and toasty vanilla touches of goodness. Enjoy this wine immediately, accompanying chicken dishes, red meats, game, and mildly seasoned pastas. And in mini version! What could be better?

Data.Name: Xiloca Garnacha
Data.Description: Xiloca is 100% Garnacha with a very fragrant perfume of earthy minerality and black cherries. This tasty, friendly, value-priced offering has ample fruit as well as a sense of elegance. Drink it over the next 3-4 years. Bodegas Vinae Mureri is located just a few miles outside of the demarcation line of the more prestigious DO of Calatayud in the province of Aragon, hence the Vino de la Tierra designation. Like Calatayud, the region is known for its high altitude, old-vine, low-yielding Garnacha vines.

Data.Name: Babe Rosé Cans
Data.Description:
Built for summer, this rosé offers a crisp, bubbly, light taste making it the perfect addition to all of your warm weather activities.

Boasting a rich nose of watermelon, strawberry, and floral notes, it is rich enough to enjoy with fried foods, pizza, grilled chicken, grilled fish (perfect for a salad niçoise), burgers, and hot dogs.

Data.Name: Veuve Clicquot Rose
Data.Description: A Tapster favorite. Veuve Clicquot Rosé ensures the consistency of the House style: an intense and elegant champagne with a delightfully luscious, fruit-based charm.

Data.Name: Uppercut Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: A true Napa Valley cabernet . . . enough said. Heady dark fruit and velvety texture make this wine steak's perfect mate. Sourced from California's Napa Valley, this wine is a bit of a splurge but worth it.

Data.Name: Twomey Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
APPEARANCE 
White gold with a hint of new grass green 

AROMAS 
Kiwi, guava and passion fruit dominate the aromatics with a dense bouquet of pithy citrus and green mango 

PALATE
Juicy, tropical entry with a lively minerality on the mid-palate 

FINISH
Refreshing and balanced 

AGEABILITY 
A delicious "drink-it now" wine but "oh-so good" if you find a bottle hidden away after a couple years 

PAIRING 
Garlic shrimp and grilled swordfish

Data.Name: Tomatin 18 Scotch
Data.Description: Tomatin 18 is finished in Spanish Oloroso Sherry casks. And eighteen years is one of those perfect sweet spots in the aging cycle where you get just about as much floral aroma, dense flavor, and complexity as possible while remaining at a reasonable price point. It has plenty of character and richness and was even voted the “Best Highland single malt” in its category

Data.Name: Kent Falls Brewing Co. Dekkera
Data.Description: A small beer, simply built on pilsner malt, Connecticut grown, malted and flaked wheat with aged Wakatu hops and a well developed, bright brett fermentation character suitable to be drank fresh for more expressive hop character or aged for additional subtleties.

Data.Name: Kent Falls Brewing Co. Equinox
Data.Description: Brewed on each equinox to celebrate the change of season with its namesake hop which imparts both fresh green pepper and tropical fruit character into the beer. This is one of Kent's favorite seasonal farmhouse ales to brew for the way it expresses itself when fresh and develops a complex character as it ages.

Data.Name: Kent Falls Brewing Co. Coffee Table
Data.Description: A session brown porter brewed with a variety of roasted malts for a soft and nuanced character to complement Kent's selection of locally roasted coffee.

Data.Name: Evil Genius Beer Company Ma! The Meatloaf!
Data.Description: Ma! The Meatloaf! is a Belgian-style white ale made with a signature Evil Genius twist. Starts by brewing up a classic Witbier spiced with coriander and orange peel.  Belgian ale yeast takes over from there creating an easy-drinking, fruit-forward wheat beer, which is made totally unique by adding Mango in the fermenter. You’ve never had a wheat beer like this one before!

Data.Name: Evil Genius Beer Company #ICANTEVEN
Data.Description: Brewed with equal parts 2-row barley and malted winter wheat, hopped ever-so-gently with Warrior, and infused with all-natural watermelon, #ICANTEVEN is the most refreshing and crushable ale in our line-up. Designed to satisfy all beer drinkers, this fruit-infused wheat ale will have you saying “I can’t even..” Perfect for drinking outside!

Data.Name: Evil Genius Beer Company Han Shot First
Data.Description: Han Shot First is an American Double IPA hopped with Amarillo, Warrior and Chinook hops. This is the brewery's brightest, most intense and aromatic hoppy beer to date. American 2-row barley and British malted oats provide a soft, clean, full-bodied mouthfeel, allowing the hops to steal the show. Big, bold, hoppy notes of mango, lemon, fresh cut grass and peach with almost no bitterness whatsoever.

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Pennsylvania Tuxedo
Data.Description:
A spruce-infused pale ale, Pennsylvania Tuxedo pays homage to the flannel-suited hunters and gatherers who dwell deep in the backcountry of north-central PA.

Brewed in collaboration with family-run outdoor clothing company Woolrich, Pennsylvania Tuxedo is a sessionable concoction with a grassy citrus kick complemented by the resinous conifer notes of fresh green spruce tips. 

A dry yet doughy malt backbone lets the hops and spruce shine while still balancing out the bitterness, making this one an easy sipper.

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Siracusa Nera
Data.Description: Combining a roasty Imperial Stout with a jammy Syrah wine, this beer is bold and complex. Notes of coffee, dark chocolate and anise from a blend of roasted malts meld with flavors of plums, cherries and stewed fruits from Syrah grape must in this jet black stout. Aged on American oak to add some light toasty vanilla to the mix.

Data.Name: Dogfish Head SeaQuench Ale
Data.Description:
SeaQuench Ale is a session sour mash-up of a crisp Kolsch, a salty Gose, and a tart Berliner Weiss brewed in sequence with black limes, sour lime juice and sea salt to make this the most thirst-quenching beer Dogfish Head has ever brewed.

When we opened our geographically-enamored seafood restaurant Chesapeake & Maine in 2016, we wanted to honor its coastal roots by developing this sessionable, seafood-pairing beer that takes you to a place of briny seawater on sunny beach days. Our experimentation focused on three thirst-quenching styles with German roots, but no single style quite hit the mark and mood we were going for … so we blended them and the result was the tart and refreshing beer we were looking for!

Partnering with the National Aquarium, we replicated sea salt sourced from the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay and added sea salt from the coast of Maine to honor the Atlantic coast we love so much.

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Palo Santo Marron
Data.Description:
An unfiltered, unfettered, unprecedented brown ale aged in handmade wooden brewing vessels. The caramel and vanilla complexity unique to this beer comes from the exotic Paraguayan Palo Santo wood from which these tanks were crafted. Palo Santo means "holy tree," and its wood has been used in South American wine-making communities.

This highly roasty and malty brown ale clocks in at 12% ABV. 

At 10,000 gallons, Dogfish's two Palo tanks are the largest wooden brewing vessels built in America since before Prohibition (and we have three same-sized oak tanks right next to them).

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch
Data.Description:
This sweet yet dry beer is made with ingredients found in 2,700-year-old drinking vessels from the tomb of King Midas. Somewhere between beer, wine and mead, Midas will please the chardonnay and beer drinker alike.

For years, Dogfish Head has worked with biomolecular archaeologist Dr. Patrick McGovern to bring Ancient Ales to life.

Data.Name: Dogfish Head Fruit-Full Fort
Data.Description:
A twist on the beloved Fort, Fruit-Full Fort is brewed with four types of berries - Raspberry, Blackberry, Boysenberry and Elderberry! This juicy blend of dark berries creates depth and complexity reminiscent of a jammy red wine.

Along with adding a boatload of more berries this time around, Dogfish also punched up the malt bill with Munich malt to provide a firm backbone. The result provides balance to the tart flavors of a very berry blend.

Dark maroon in color, Fruit-Full Fort is swirling with notes of velvety cherry and berry sweetness for a full-bodied - and full-flavor - experience!

Data.Name: SingleCut Beers Jane She is a Clerk IPA
Data.Description: Soft, bright, and packed with the same hop bill as beloved Jenny Said, this IPA is dank, soft, and packed with tons of tangerine and plum/peach aroma.

Data.Name: SingleCut Beers Heavy Boots of Lead Stout
Data.Description: Super complex richness of mega-chocolate, roast, vanilla and coffee in an astonishingly smooth monster of a brew.

Data.Name: SingleCut Beers Chrissie Gose-Style Lemon Lager
Data.Description: Tart and bright with a lemon verbena infusion, and lagered for a crisp and clean finish. The ultimate thirst-quenching crusher.

Data.Name: SingleCut Beers Flatter Flatter 2xDH IPA
Data.Description: GET UNSHATTERED with this brand new yin/yang riff on beloved Charlie’s Good Tonight. Lush, full, and soft, compared to Charlie’s crisp and dry, FLATTER is packed with aroma of juicy pineapple candy, lime/mango, and a touch of black cherry, with a long medium bitter finish and a round mouthfeel. Enjoy in icy winters or short packed summers while pondering life’s let downs and lift ups.

Data.Name: SingleCut Beers Charlie's Good Tonight DDH IPA
Data.Description: Charlie's Good Tonight. Ain’t he? Backing that up is a smooth easy drinking IPA that is all tropical citrus that is in the pocket anytime.

Data.Name: Tinto Negro Malbec
Data.Description: Red Wine: Malbec, aroma of mocha & & spiced oak, flavors of cherry, raspberry, roasted coffee beans, dark chocolate & ripe black forest fruit. Pairs well with lamb & sirloin.

Data.Name: The Stag Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Med-dark garnet with crimson hues. The wine displays classic regional Cabernet aromas of blackberries and cassis with leafy background notes. The fruit is complexed with earthy scents and supporting cedary / chocolate oak. The palate is medium to full bodied, even and balanced. Ripe fleshy black currant and tobacco leaf flavours continue from the nose, and the finish is persistent with ripe powdery tannins. Built to put down for a few years.

Data.Name: Terrabianca Campaccio
Data.Description: Very silky and floral, this red reminds us of Burgundy with its bilberry, violet and raspberry aromas and flavors. The grainy tannins show the other side to this wine, which needs time for the two components to balance. Ends with a long, intense, fruit-filled finish.

Data.Name: Terra d'Oro Zinfandel
Data.Description: This savory Zinfandel displays vibrant aromas of rich, spicy clove and big, generous fruit with hints of vanilla that entice the nose. An abundance of plums and flavors of dense, juicy blackberries excites the senses with a round mouthfeel of well-integrated tannins on the finish. This wine is rich and powerful, and incredibly well-balanced. The Terra d’Oro Amador Zinfandel is enjoyable on its own, and especially complements anything barbecued.

Data.Name: Virginia Black American Whiskey
Data.Description:
Virginia Black American Whiskey is adored for its vanilla, burnt caramel, black cherry and spicy flavor notes.

This American Whiskey is carefully distilled at Various distillery, United States.

Data.Name: Tullamore Dew Irish Whiskey
Data.Description: Tullamore Dew, the original blended Irish whiskey, is known the world over for its smooth and gentle complexity. For one, it is triple distilled and patiently aged in a combination of ex-bourbon and sherry casks, developing its distinctive smoothness. Secondly, being a blend of all three types of Irish whiskey, it has a gentle complexity. The malt and the pot still whiskey we use give it citrus and spicy notes.

Data.Name: Triple Eight Vodka
Data.Description: Triple 8 Vodka is an ultra premium vodka produced on Nantucket Island. The vodka is triple distilled from the highest quality organically grown grain. It is then blended with our exceptionally clean and soft water drawn from well #888. Triple Eight outscored Ketel One in the World Spirit Championships, conducted by the Beverage Testing Institute.

Data.Name: Yes Way Rosé
Data.Description: Steely pink color. Aromas of white raspberry, sweet lilac, and ripe melon with a supple, crisp, dry-yet-fruity light body and a smooth, brisk candied carrot, blistered tomato, and pear candies finish with no oak flavor. A pleasing anytime rose.
