With layers of richness, freshness, and spice, this fruit-forward blend is here to stay—not only on your table, but front and center in our lineup of tried and true reds. This versatile wine pairs well with everything from lamb kabobs and salmon to mushroom risotto and roasted vegetables.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This medium-bodied wine has no agenda other than inviting you to partake in its rich cherry flavors and toasty vanilla touches of goodness. Enjoy this wine immediately, accompanying chicken dishes, red meats, game, and mildly seasoned pastas.

Data.Name: Stags Leap Wine Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This Cabernet Sauvignon has expressive aromas of dark berries, currants, raspberry sorbet, nutmeg and baking spices. The wine has a rich entry with round tannins and plush mouthfeel with lingering flavors of dark fruit and subtle oak undertones.

Enjoy this Cabernet Sauvignon with grilled tri-tip, braised short ribs, or pasta with wild mushrooms and prosciutto.

Blend: 91% Cabernet Sauvignon, 6% Merlot, 2% Petit Verdot, 1% Malbec

Data.Name: Sharecropper's Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Sweet aromas of blackberry, candied fruit, vanilla and brown sugar leads to a more savory palate of pomegranate, green pepper and oil cured olives. This Cabernet finishes with bright acidity and lingering tannins. We recommend opening this wine now and enjoying it at a young age, however, this will age well for 4-6 years when properly cellared.

Data.Name: Sean Minor Pinot Noir Sonoma
Data.Description: This Sonoma Coast Pinot Noir is medium-bodied with rich aromas of plum, cherry, green tea and a slight clove spice. On entry, the wine has a lean entry with rich and sweet cherry and plum flavors framed by vanilla and oak notes throughout the mid-palate. The spicy finish lingers on the palate.

Data.Name: Sean Minor Four Bears Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This Central Coast Pinot Noir displays aromas of cherry, strawberry, and raspberry fruit with a hint of earthy notes. On the palate, the Pinot offers bright flavors of strawberry and cherry combined with hints of tobacco. The bright acidity combined with sweet oak results in a lingering finish.

Data.Name: Sean Minor Four Bears Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Paso Robles Cabernet Sauvignon is ruby in color and displays aromas of lavender, cedar and raspberry fruit. Flavors of blackberries and raspberries combined with hints of savory spices coat the palate. The soft tannins and sweet oak balance lead to a long and lingering finish.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Color: Brownish red. 
Bouquet: Red cherries, raspberries, and strawberries balanced with touch of vanilla and leather. 
Taste: The light to medium palate recalls the nose and offers depth with a refreshing finish. 
Best Paired With: This wine is an ideal match for pastas, shellfish, tuna and pork.

Data.Name: Rodney Strong Merlot
Data.Description: Lush with predominant notes of black cherry and plum with a hint of dried herbs. Silky and voluptuous with soft tannins and a finish of cocoa and vanilla.

Data.Name: Rocca Delle Macie Chianti Classico
Data.Description:
Ruby red tending towards garnet. Rich, intense and complex notes of cherry, plum and spice. Dry, soft, gently tannic with good structure.

Pairs well with with red meat, roasts and game.

Data.Name: Poggio Bonelli Chianti Classico
Data.Description:
A genuine and characteristic expression of the Sangiovese varietal, Chianti Classico has a deep, dense ruby red color. Wild berries, sour black cherry, thyme and leather feature on the nose. Though bold and dry, the taste is softened by the delicate sweetness of the French oak.

Blend: 90% Sangiovese, 10% Merlot

Data.Name: Plungerhead Lodi Old Vine Zinfandel
Data.Description:
Complex and juicy, this Lodi Zinfandel explodes with brambly fruit aromas as well as toasted coconut, sandalwood, tanned leather, clove, and freshly grated nutmeg. The palate is layered with fruit and spice showcasing blueberry, strawberry pie filling, sweet cherry, milk chocolate, graham cracker, thyme, and white pepper.

This bold Zinfandel would pair exceptionally well with Mongolian BBQ or anything covered in a teriyaki sauce. Other recommended pairings would be a burger with BBQ potato chips or a meat lover’s pizza.

Blend: 84% Zinfandel, 13% Petite Sirah, 3% Tempranillo

Data.Name: Penfolds Max's Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Color is deep, dark crimson. Rich and full nose that offers notes of sun-dried tomato, blackcurrant, and black olive. Furry, firm tannins and supportive oak on the palate. Substantial, rich mid-palate. Savory.

"A refreshing cabernet sauvignon with currant and fresh herb character. Some lemon rind undertones. Medium to full body, fine tannins and a fruity finish. Shows reserve and tension." - James Suckling

Data.Name: Penfolds Shiraz Cabernet Bin 8
Data.Description:
This Penfolds Bin 8 Cabernet-Shiraz is a crimson color. A graphite and blackcurrant assertion immediately confirms Cabernet's role in the blend. A lift of tomato-leaf and sour-cherry couples with other red fruits to further entice. Background cedary oak just discernible. Medium-bodied. A summer-pudding swirl of fruits laced with red-currant conserve, praline. Varietal I.D. confirmed via green Sicilian olive, plummy fruits and spice. Fine tannins, well-concealed oak.

Blend: 60% Cabernet Sauvignon, 40% Shiraz

Data.Name: Peirano Estate The Immortal Zin
Data.Description: The color of this wine is truly Immortal. Its rich dark color goes on and on and on. The deceptively subtle aromas of red currant, raspberries, red cherries, and earthy cedar marry together to put your olfactory senses into a new dimension. In the mouth, the palate is wrapped in a mysterious, velvety layered mix of raspberry cordial, sweet mouth filling red fruit, blackberry and red currant, leading to a lengthy, rich mouth-filling finish.

Data.Name: Paul Mas Carignan
Data.Description:
Color: Intense Deep purple colour with ruby red tints. 
Nose: At first spices and blackberry, the second nose develops Underwood and cocoa aromas finishing on toasted oak notes. 
Palate: Full bodied rich and mellow with velvety tannins. Complex flavours on the middle palate, liquorice flavours on the finish. Long lasting.. 
Cellaring: If kept in good conditions (15° C and bottle laying down) this wine will age perfectly for the next 5 years.

Data.Name: Pacific Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The fruit profile includes flavors of black cherry, raspberry, and plum. also, noteworthy are hints of vanilla, toffee, and cigar leaf. the balance and finish are round and full with silky tannins leaving a satisfying impression.

Data.Name: Oracle of the Stars Pinotage
Data.Description: Inky red-violet in colour with aromas of wild berries, earth and peppery spice. Cherry and blackberry flavours merged into smoky peat elements and crushed black peppercorn in the lengthy finish. Embodying an enchanting mix of bright fruit, dense smoky earth and spice, this is a phenomenal value great for sipping by the fireplace.

Data.Name: 90+ Cellars Big Red Blend
Data.Description: Made from a blend of red grapes grown in the historic wine region of Lodi, California, this red wine is bold on flavor without the big price tag. Big aromas of cassis, blackberry and plum with traces of vanilla and cedar. Textured, full-bodied and larger-than-life, you may just have to stretch out your mouth for that first sip!

Data.Name: Hullabaloo Zinfandel
Data.Description: Hullabaloo displays aromas of boysenberry, licorice and white pepper on the nose, with well-structured flavors of wild cherry, blueberry, cola and raspberry fruit dominating the palate and ending with a nice dash of spice on the finish. This wine will continue to age gracefully for the next 5 - 7 years.

Data.Name: Nickel & Nickel Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: With its floral aromas mixed with plum and olive, the 2015 John C. Sullenger Cabernet Sauvignon blends juicy and savory notes into an impossible-to-resist perfume. On the palate, dark flavors of black cherry, tobacco, anise and toast are accentuated by a lively yet balanced acidity. These flavors are carried by a rich core of tannins that build on the middle palate, carrying the fruit into a long finish.

Data.Name: Napa Cellars Merlot
Data.Description: Napa Cellars Merlot boasts aromas of dark cherry and concentrated dark fruit notes with hints of strawberry jam and vanilla. Flavors of plum, blackberry, caramel, and cocoa coat the palate and are complemented by smoky-oak, tobacco, and cedar notes. The wine finishes with a toasted, sweeter caramel and soy-like character. This wine showcases medium bodied, concentrated tannin in the mid-palate and part acidity that pairs well with a wide range of food.

Data.Name: Montebuena Rioja Vuele KPF
Data.Description: "Vivid ruby-red. Sexy, oak-tinged red berry and floral pastille scents pick up vanilla and licorice flourishes with aeration. Juicy and focused on the palate, offering sweet black raspberry and cherry flavors that unfold and spread out steadily on the back half."

Data.Name: Annabella Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This Napa Valley Cab is a lovely dark, brooding Napa Cabernet. The nose is a bit shy at first, but will eventually bloom to show black currant, bittersweet cocoa powder, and sweet saddle leather. In the mouth, the wine’s broad, soft tannins are layered with ripe black cherry, a hint of bacon, smokey oak and a touch of nutmeg. The lengthy finish is delicately laced with vanilla bean. Built with aging potential, this striking Cabernet will reward you for decanting it before enjoying it.

Pair with pan seared aged bone-in ribeye served with bacon mashed potatoes and sauteed spinach.

Data.Name: Romagna Cagnina Dolce Red
Data.Description: Ruby red with Intense purple hues, Mi Amore Red carries scents of cherry and raspberry on the nose. Full-bodied and sweet with gentle tannins; it should be served slightly chilled.

Data.Name: Mercedes Eguren Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Deep ruby red in the glass. Flavours of black berries, blueberries and red currants mix intensive with notes of black pepper, tobacco, toffee and precious woods. At the palate balanced, silky and voluminous. Gentle tannins providing a long, lasting aromatic and retronasally aftertaste.

Data.Name: Mauro Molino Barolo
Data.Description: This wine presents a slow succession of aromas, including dark fruit, cassis, licorice, raw spice and powdered chocolate. Firm but silky tannins hold it together nicely.

Data.Name: Masi Tupungato Passo Doble Red
Data.Description:
Displays complex ripe red fruit aromas, with vegetal and licorice notes. Baked plum and cherry flavors are full-bodied with an initial spicy grassy-ness that evolves into a soft, long finish, with vanilla traces.
Pairs with a wide variety of foods, including grilled or roasted red meats, game birds, mature and strong-flavored cheeses.

Data.Name: Martin Ray Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
This Pinot Noir exemplifies the 2016 vintage, carrying all the expected traits of an exemplary growing season in Russian River Valley, as well as Carneros. The nose offers freshly macerated raspberry, cherry bramble, and spicy cola, which leads into tart cranberry, a subtle touch of nutmeg and silky refined tannins. French oak barrels lend support with hints of creamy vanilla without overpowering the fresh, fruit-forward palate.

Pair this vibrant, silky Pinot Noir with Duck Sausage, Mostarda and Brioche.

Data.Name: Viniterra Malbec
Data.Description: Baked and earthy berry aromas include notes of prune and molasses. This is rugged and a touch choppy in feel. Its salty stewy flavors settle on plum and berry on the finish

Data.Name: M. Chapoutier Les Vignes de Bila-Haut
Data.Description:
Deep garnet red in color, this blend of Syrah, Grenache and Carignan offers aromas of black cherry. On the palate, the wine is fleshy and well-structured -- a nice expression of the terroir in the Roussillon area.
Pairs well with beef and Mediterranean food.

Data.Name: Lindeman's Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Medium to full bodied combining dark berry fruit and cassis flavors with hints of chocolate and mint and subtle oak.

Data.Name: Bodegas Lan Reserva Rioja
Data.Description: 80% Tempranillo, 10% Mazuelo, 10% Garnacha. Brilliant ripe black cherry red colour with good depth. Fruity aromas with elegant nuances of fine wood. Pairs well with stews, spiced dishes, legumes and cured cheeses.

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Vinter's Reserve Merlot
Data.Description: Intricate layers of black cherry, plum, currant, and wild berry mingle with a hint of spice. The soft, delicate tannins of this Bordeaux varietal carry these aromas and flavors to a long lingering finish.

Data.Name: Justin Isosceles
Data.Description:
Bright with a deep ruby core, lighter with a bit of garnet toward the rim. Rich and aromatic with dark fruit of black cherry, cassis, exotic licorice, cinnamon, and subtle vanilla spice with sweet notes of tobacco, a little cocoa and subtle toasted cedar in the background. Full bodied with black cherry and classic black currant fruit, complex brown spice of star anise, licorice with cocoa and herbal notes of sweet tobacco and a hint of eucalyptus. The rest is classic Bordeaux cabernet sauvignon - fruit, complex spice, and mineral flavors balanced with guiding structural elements on a long, memorable finish. Drink on release or wait a dozen years, this one will be ready for you.

Blend: 85% Cabernet Sauvignon, 8% Cabernet Franc, 7% Merlot

Data.Name: Joseph Carr Cabernet Sauvignon Paso Robles
Data.Description: This wine features aromas of blackberry, chocolate, and blueberry preserves. Plush on the mid-palate with silky tannins but firm acidity, it shows rich black fruit on the long finish.

Data.Name: Joseph Carr Cabernet Sauvignon Napa Valley
Data.Description: The wine features aromas of fig, red cherry, blackberry pie, forest floor, mince meats, and cocoa. A big attack of black currant flows to layers of dense tannin, earthy chocolate, and dried fruit. Full-bodied with food-friendly acidity, flavors of nutmeg, clove, and cinnamon add complexity to the finish.

Data.Name: Jean-Luc Colombo Côtes du Rhône Les Abeilles
Data.Description:
#4 Wine Enthusiast Top 100 Best Buys of 2018
Intense purple color, seductive aromas of red fruits, coriander and bay leaf. This is a fresh and silky wine, with notes of licorice and spice on the palate.
A food-friendly wine which perfectly matches grilled lamb, pork and assorted cheeses.

Data.Name: Hayes Valley Merlot
Data.Description: Flavors: Tobacco with a hint of raspberries. Cedar and tobacco, with vanilla on the finish.

Data.Name: Hangtime Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
This wine has vivid ruby color, with aromas and flavors of wild cherry and cranberry. Silky tannins balance the vibrant fruit. Enjoy during your own favorite hangtime — like a backyard get-together.
Hangtime Pinot Noir pairs extremely well with lightly spiced foods, as well as roast pork with herbs or matched with any mushroom based dish.

Data.Name: Grande Reserve Pinot Noir Josephine Dubois
Data.Description: A fabulous introduction to the myriad of pleasures and complexities that is Burgundian Pinot Noir. Spicy red fruit and a subtle "farmyard" aroma - typical of Pinot Noir - lead on to a firm, well-rounded palate. Made with the same expertise as the Dubois Grand Cru Wines.

Data.Name: Gnarly Head 1924 Double Black Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: An ample amount of concentrated dark fruits are obvious from the start. Black cherry, dark plum, blackberry and sweet currant flavors burst on the palate and are followed by a hint of spice on a silky long finish.

Data.Name: Garnet Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This is a Pinot with power, but also with finesse. Aromas include ripe blackberries, cherry preserves, vanilla toffee and toasted French oak. Tapster loves the velvety richness of the attack. The flavors of dark red fruits and exotic spices just make this a juicy, delicious mouthful of wine.

Data.Name: Frog's Leap Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Made entirely from dry-farmed and certified organically grown grapes from our estate vineyards in Rutherford. This Sauvignon blanc is then vinified in a way that allows the wine to retain the purity and distinctiveness of this noble variety.

Data.Name: Fleur Pinot Noir Carneros
Data.Description: This delicious Pinot Noir from Carneros displays a brilliant ruby color that sets the stage for aromas of pomegranate and bright red fruit, with hints of exotic spice. While dominated by effusive fruit flavors, the wine is well-balanced with a mouthful of ripe berries and a harmonious combination of acidity and structure. This is a richer Pinot than you expect at this price.

Data.Name: Faustino VII Rioja Tempranillo
Data.Description: The Faustino VII Tempranillo displays lively red color shading to ochre with hints of vanilla and ripe red berry fruit. On the palate, the wine is very well balanced, velvety and elegant.

Data.Name: Famille Perrin Chateauneuf-du-Pape Les Sinards
Data.Description:
This wine expresses marvelously the beauty of the vintage. Intense red with purple reflections, Les Sinards expresses an intense bouquet of red and black fruit, sweet spices, noble wood and mineral notes. The mouth is incredibly balanced between freshness and volume, the tannins are fine and elegant, the finish is very long, aromatic, and sweet.
Serve at 15°C (59°F) in big glasses. Drink with game, truffles and mushrooms.

Data.Name: Estancia Zinfandel
Data.Description: Juicy and complex, bursting with raspberry, cherry and spicy cracked pepper flavors. Its medium body is fantastic for food, whether you are spooning up spaghetti, or dining on grilled filet mignon.

Data.Name: Estancia Zinfandel Paso Robles
Data.Description: Juicy and complex, bursting with raspberry, cherry and spicy cracked pepper flavors. Its medium body is fantastic for food, whether you are spooning up spaghetti, or dining on grilled filet mignon.

Data.Name: Estancia Merlot
Data.Description: A medium-bodied, dry red wine with black cherry, plums, chocolate and a round mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Viu Manent Malbec
Data.Description: Intense cherry red with violet hue. It presents a complex and elegant nose with aromas of red fruits, cherries, plums, sweet spices, violets and blond snuff. In the mouth it is a wine of medium, very balanced, fresh acidity and structure. A turn is a wine with character, intense, vibrant and long and pleasant finish.

Data.Name: El Miracle Old Vine Garnacha Tintorera
Data.Description: Aromas of rose hips and generic red fruits are restrained. A compact palate is fresh enough, while this tastes of reedy red fruits with touches of mint and oak. On the finish, any remaining fruit fades fast leaving mild oak notes and heat.

Data.Name: Duckhorn Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Duckhorn Vineyards has been producing Cabernet Sauvignon since 1978. This wine is a blend of individual vineyard lots, utilizing exceptional fruit from Duckhorn’s estate vineyards and independent growers. The final wine is a classic expression of the Napa Valley. Complex and compelling, Duckhorn Cabernet reflects the diversity of great Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon. On the nose, vibrant layers of red and black fruit mingle with hints of violet, dried herbs, black licorice and graphite. The flavors echo the aromas, with lovely black currant and licorice elements supported by firm, impeccably balanced, tannins and an excellent structure. Good acidity helps to carry the juicy dark fruit notes through to a long, satisfying finish.

Data.Name: Domaine Du Vieux Lazaret Chateauneuf-du-Pape
Data.Description: Pale plus dark red with clear purple rim. The nose is warm and beginning to show an attractive complexity characterized by understated red fruits and spice along with leather and tertiary notes. The palate is composed and lighter weight, again exhibiting a measure of bottle development in an appealing mix of red cherry and spice notes. There is a fine, balanced structure. This is an elegant, not heavyweight style expressing Cinsault and Grenache in particular, with the emphasis on finesse rather than power.

Data.Name: Domaine Allegret Laudun Côtes du Rhône Villages
Data.Description: Elegant and complex, the mouth is pleasant and round. Highly structured it has an excellent balance of acohol and tannins.

Data.Name: Cortijo Rioja Tempranillo
Data.Description: Bright ruby-red. Raspberry, candied cherry and white pepper aromas show good energy and a hint of smokiness. Slightly jammy on the palate, offering an array of red and dark berry flavors that become spicier with air. Finishes juicy and tight, with subtle tannins and a touch of licorice.

Data.Name: Frontera Concha Y Toro Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Pinot Noir is never a straightforward varietal. Eternally fussy, and extremely fickle, this wonderful grape does fit nicely into the cooler climates of Chile. Chilean Pinot Noir exudes cherry, cranberry and strawberry, and tends to follow the much-lauded mantra of “less is more” as they pursue a balanced, subtle wine.

Data.Name: Clos Dalian Terra Alta Garnacha Red
Data.Description: Mild fruit tones hide behind yeasty aromas. Plump in feel yet not overly intense, the palate deals briny flavors of almond skin, peach pit and melon. On the finish, this lingers with a hint of salt.

Data.Name: Clayhouse Syrah
Data.Description: Deep purple garnet color with aromas of violets, liquorice, cloves and blackberry. Wine has medium weight and smooth rounded tannins to compliment the juicy sweet ripe raspberry and blackberry fruit with fresh anise undertones. The wine finishes with lightly smoky spice and a lingering vanilla warmth.

Data.Name: Clayhouse Adobe Red
Data.Description: Ripe flavors of cherry, plum and vanilla bean, with rich spicy blueberry and cherry notes. The tannins are supple, and the balanced oak character adds additional vanilla notes.

Data.Name: Chronic Cellars Purple Paradise
Data.Description: Nuances of raspeberry and rose with notes of strawberry, pomegranate, and vanilla and cloves. Pairs well with an assortment of cheeses.

Data.Name: Christopher Michael Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
Christopher Michael is proud of their Cabernet Sauvignon, which gets its character and fruit from across the Columbia Valley, a widely respected region any big red would proudly call home. Eager to be opened, this wine is bursting with blue and black fruits that are framed by sweet vanilla and coco from the oak on which it was aged.
Blend: 75% Cabernet Sauvignon, 15% Syrah, and 10% Merlot.

Data.Name: Chateau De Lavernette Beaujolais-Villages
Data.Description: The taste of apple pie and cherry tart melded into one with strawberry rhubarb flavours to top it off. This Beaujolais-Villages has the enchanting fragrance of ripe red fruits from the orchard and briar. The wine has a silky entry followed by a lavish mid-palate showcased on a pedestal of fine integrated tannins.

Data.Name: Château Larose-Trintaudon Haut-Medoc
Data.Description: This Château Larose Trintaudon Haut-Medoc lives up to region's reputation not only with its intense fruit, but with stellar balance, lovely fine tannins and just the right amount of acidity. Its power and density will satisfy mightily with lamb and meat dishes, especially beef. Pour your first glass and enjoy it with a hearty Tuscan chicken liver paté on rustic toast.

Data.Name: Charles Smith Chateau Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Elegant and nicely focused to show off its bright raspberry and cherry fruit. Lightly veiled in fine tannins, picking up white pepper and cinnamon notes on the lively finish.

Data.Name: Cellar No. 8 Zinfandel
Data.Description:
Deep ruby in color, this classic Zinfandel begins with aromas of black mission figs, black cherries and vanilla. The palate is filled with intense characters of brown, baking spice, vanilla, cherries, pomegranate and fig. These flavors repeat themselves on a long, elegant finish.

Paired best with filet of beef glazed with balsamic vinegar-Zinfandel and rosemary sauce.

Data.Name: Cavit Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: With distinctive flavors of blackberries, cherries, and plums, it’s aged in oak for one year to produce this medium-bodied wine.

Data.Name: Carletto Montepulciano D'Abruzzo
Data.Description: Montepulciano d’Abruzzo is one of Italy's most famous wines, and can be found on wine store shelves all around the world. This classic, well-rounded, plum-scented Italian red is made from Montepulciano grapes grown in the Abruzzo region, on Italy's Adriatic coast. It is quite distinct from Vino Nobile di Montepulciano, which is a Sangiovese-based wine from Tuscany.

Data.Name: Caposaldo Chianti
Data.Description:
The fruit for Caposaldo Chianti comes from the hilly province of Arezzo and Siena in the Chianti region of Tuscany, grown in mineral rich soils. After handpicking, grapes are brought to the winery for a traditional vinification that produces a greater extraction of flavor, color and tannins. Thirty percent is aged in oak vats prior to bottling.

Best with pizza, and pasta with tomato- or meat-based sauces.

Data.Name: Capa Tempranillo Sweet Red Wine
Data.Description: Clear dark purple color. Clean intense and pronounced aromas reminiscent of bramble fruits, blueberries and black cherries with tasted oak sweet spices and hints of roasted coffee bean. One the palate it is dry, full bodied with firm but ripe tannins and a long finish.

Data.Name: CK Mondavi Merlot
Data.Description: This Merlot is medium-bodied with a hint of oak and flavors of cherries and plums. It is rich in the mouth and ends in a soft fruit filled finish. Enjoy this wine with barbecued chicken and ribs or Caesar salad topped with grilled chicken. Great with fondue as well.

Data.Name: Brotte Esprit Barville Côtes Du Rhône
Data.Description: This elegantly perfumed, structured wine has savory nuances of moss, herb and toast. The palate is concentrated but restrained, suggesting bright blackberries and black plums, framed by crisp acidity and fine, persistent tannins.

Data.Name: BenMarco Malbec
Data.Description: Beautiful deep purple color with perfumed aromas of ripe red fruits and roasted coffee beans. It is lush, fullbodied and penetrating on the palate with loads of chewy, currant jam flavors, bright acidity, and a touch of grip on the almost savory finish. This wine really unfolds with some air so try not to slurp it down in a rush, and it shows why the Argentine people are in love with Malbec. Some Bonarda was blended in for greater complexity and to achieve better balance.

Data.Name: Belasco de Banquedano Llama Malbec
Data.Description: Modern wine with attractive dark cherry-red color with violet hues. The nose shows great intensity. Fruit aromas of cherries, blackberries and plums stand out against a background of fine toast hints from ageing in top-quality oak. Warm, rounded and well-structured on the palate, with an explosion of fruit flavors underscored by light oaky notes. Pleasant, persistent aftertaste.

Data.Name: Brolio Barone Ricasoli Chianti Classico
Data.Description: Ruby red with purplish tinges. Aromatic delicacy of cherry, blackberry, violet and sweet tobacco. Pleasant and fresh palate with evident hints of ripe red fruit. Spicy tones in the end.    Elegant, well-balanced, pleasant with a rich bouquet: an amazing wine with a captivating taste for everyday drinking that pairs well with many different dishes.

Data.Name: Bodegas Barco de Piedra Ribera del Duero
Data.Description:
Barco de Piedra is an affirmation of the beauty and purity of the Tempranillo grape as it is grown in Ribera del Duero. The grape's thick skin naturally produces powerful, robust wines packed with flavor. Adding more power and oak to something already powerful is overkill. Raspberry and violet aromas with rose petal, blueberry and mineral notes make this wine. Barco de Piedra is one of the prettiest examples of the elegance and structure of Ribera del Duero, one of the great wine regions of the world.
Pork and veal have an essentially sweet "bass note" that is complimented nicely by Tempranillo's sweet nature, so these meats pair extremely well with Barco de Piedra.

Data.Name: Barbadillo Fino Sherry
Data.Description:
Pale straw colour with a delicate, nutty aroma.
Dry, light and elegant on the palate, with hints of almond due to the solera amturation in seasoned oak. A long, clean and crisp finish.
It is perfect as an aperitif or may be served with fish, cheese and "tapas". Serve well chilled.

Data.Name: Achaval Ferrer Malbec
Data.Description: The textbook definition of Malbec. Bright ruby red in color, this wine is fresh and floral, featuring blackberry, raspberry, and violets on the nose and palate. The wine is dense and thick with a noticeable minerality, silky tannins mark a lengthy finish. Low yields, careful vineyard management, and low intervention winemaking are the hallmark of this and all other Achaval-Ferrer wines.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Red Moscato Bubbles
Data.Description: Medium dark ruby red with good mousse; forward perfumed aromas of strawberry, peach, cherry and muscat, with hints of blackberry preserve and blackcurrent; sweet with balanced acidity, and fine refreshing bubbles, with exotic, grapy concord flavours and a strawberry jam finish.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Shiraz Cabernet
Data.Description: Full-flavored and bursting with fruit, this wine offers a delightful mixture of peppery, spicy notes, mixed with jammy flavors of black currant and blueberry. Moderately tannic, this wine pairs well with most well-flavored pork and beef dishes, especially if they are spicy.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Sweet Red Roo
Data.Description: Full of fruit flavors with aromas of naturally sweet red berries, vanilla and chocolate in each sip. A bold, expressive red blend that can also be served chilled.

Data.Name: Trivento Amado Sur Malbec
Data.Description: Trivento Amado Sur Red is a deep red color with violet hues and flavors and aromas of red fruits like strawberries, cherries and plum jam combined with soft spicy and sweet aromas. Plus, vanilla and black chocolate aromas from the oak. It has a wet entrance and gentle tannins with persistence in the mouth. Long and pleasant ending.

Data.Name: Sella & Mosca Cannonau di Sardegna
Data.Description: Bright ruby color, with purple hues, the aromas project ripe red berry, including strawberry and raspberry jam. In the mouth, coffee, spices and herbs, including an aroma of violets, plummy fruit flavors and aristocratic oak overtone. Full, round, fruit forward, consumer friendly taste profile. Oak aged for two years in large Slavonian casks with several additional months in the bottle. Medium-bodied for food-friendly matchings.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Merlot
Data.Description: Vivid red color, brilliant, with violet hints, of medium intensity. Ripe red fruits combine with fine herbs in a young and fruity aroma. To the palate it is a medium lightly bodied wine showing fruity and pasty, round, soft and ripe tannins.

Data.Name: San Felice Chianti Classico
Data.Description: This is a wine to savour with your tortellini and pecorino. A dashing, classical wine of the highest order from the finest spots on the Tuscan hillsides. Dark cherry, raspberry and sweet violets accent the restrained complexity from a particularly talented winemaker, Leonardo Bellaccini. A Chianti Classico that is genuinely a cut above the rest.

Data.Name: Ruffino Il Ducale Red Blend
Data.Description: With ruby red with violet highlights, this Red Blend's bouquet is very intense and pleasantly complex,with notes of cassis, cherry jam, plum, and vanilla. A modern Tuscan wine born from Ruffino’s century-old winemaking tradition, the 2014 Il Ducale is a well-balanced, full-bodied wine with a pleasant freshness. The first notes are bright and fruity with round, elegant tannins. The Syrah offers clean flavors of eucalyptus and spice, while the Sangiovese provides red and black fruit and aromatic herbs. The Merlot rounds out the blend. The finish is long and satisfying with refined notes of ripe fruit, black pepper, and vanilla.

Data.Name: Rodney Strong Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Rodney Strong Cabernet Sauvignon Sonoma County is grown in the rugged, rocky hills and valleys of the warmest regions in Sonoma County where rich and distinct Cabernet Sauvignon thrives. It' rich with dark cherry, plum and baking spices. The delicious fruit is accompanied by crushed violet and black pepper notes. The palate has medium tannins, lingering spicy oak flavors and a lush finish. Enjoy this Cabernet now with burgers, meat lovers pizza or grilled steak.

Data.Name: Plungerhead Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Dark garnet in color, this Cabernet Sauvignon showcases aromas of dark raspberry, cinnamon bark, fresh fig and toasted cedar. Flavors of blackberry compote, dried blueberry, blackstrap molasses, fresh oregano, and an integrated note of toasted coconut coat the palate. The finish is smooth and slightly drying with layers of dill and tropical vanilla.

Data.Name: Paxis Red Blend
Data.Description: This dark, structured wine, with its balanced blend of Touriga Nacional, Touriga Franca and Tinta Roriz, is firm with tannins and dense berry fruits. Full in the mouth, it is a concentrated wine that brings out a strongly chalky texture.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Midnight Dark Red
Data.Description: A passionate red blend bursting with dusky aromas, an extraordinarily deep color, and rich, ripe black fruit. Dont be shy turn out the lights and savor the pleasures of the dark.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Lavish Merlot
Data.Description: With its alluring aromas and lush flavors, Ménage à Trois Merlot reminds one of what it’s like to fall in love. Ripe blackberries and juicy black cherries flirt with smoky spices and sweet vanilla in a deliriously delicious way, wrapping the drinker up in a silky-smooth embrace. It’s the perfect wine to add a spark to date night, and it knows just how to romance a roast chicken or a cheeseburger.

Data.Name: LAN Rioja Crianza
Data.Description: LAN produces as consistent a value crianza as anyone in Rioja. Their 2010 shows spicy mixed berry fruits, with perhaps a plumper quality than usual, but given how delicious the wine is there is nothing wrong with that! As usual, this is another tasty effort from these folks; for $10 it's absolutely a no brainer—very good value Rioja. 100% Tempranillo.

Data.Name: Gnarly Head 1924 Double Black Red Blend
Data.Description: Gnarly Head 1924 Double Black delivers rich aromas of blackberry preserves, cocoa, raspberry and caramel, setting the stage for a juicy core of concentrated, dense blackberry and fig jam flavors that finish with a hint of baking spice. Jet black in the glass, pair this full-bodied wine with equally bold dishes: charbroiled bacon cheeseburgers, spicy sausage gumbo or pork baby back ribs slathered in BBQ sauce.

Data.Name: Frontera Malbec
Data.Description: Tapster loves this Malbec, that exhibits a deep, dark purple-red color leading to a bouquet of fresh red fruits folded with coffee notes. The palate is highlighted by mouth-filling black cherry and dark plum flavors, elegantly wrapped with subtle spice and velvety, gentle tannins.

Data.Name: Frog's Leap Zinfandel
Data.Description: Profound perfume is what comes to my mind when your nose first hits the unfolding bouquet of the 2014. Rich flavors of raspberry and mulberry are underscored with a just touch of cinnamon and white pepper. More elegance than brawn, this wine is where Volnay meets Morgon. Consider a pairing with a beautiful, roasted bird garnished with spring chanterelles.

Data.Name: Cupcake Shiraz
Data.Description: A trip to the land down under doesn’t disappoint, as the sunny days and rich soils of Southern Australia’s Barossa Valley produce rich and spicy Shiraz. Dark and inky garnet, Cupcake Shiraz impresses with a nose of ripe plums and blackberry jam. A full palate of creamy fruit, mocha and a lingering touch of black pepper follow. Aging in oak infuses supple tannins and a smooth, creamy finish.

Data.Name: Cupcake Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This Pinot Noir has a lovely garnet hue and heady aromas of black cherries and ripe strawberries. The wine opens up to a flavor of red raspberry and a hint of spice with a creamy finish. We harvest our Pinot Noir grapes at their peak and cold soak them for a couple of days. The juice undergoes a cool fermentation to preserve the bright cherry fruit. American and French oak barrels are used to age the wine for about nine months.

Data.Name: Colossal Reserva Red Blend
Data.Description: From the rolling hills of Portuguese wine country comes this red blend, rich with ripe berry aromas and spicy tasting notes. Aged in French and American oak, it drinks with complexity and intensity. Serve it alongside aged rib eye, lamb stew or spicy carnitas.

Data.Name: Chateau Larose-Trintaudon Haut-Medoc Bordeaux
Data.Description: This Château Larose Trintaudon Haut-Medoc lives up to region's reputation not only with its intense fruit, but with stellar balance, lovely fine tannins and just the right amount of acidity. Its power and density will satisfy mightily with lamb and meat dishes, especially beef. Pour your first glass and enjoy it with a hearty Tuscan chicken liver paté on rustic toast. Having a little bowl of Spanish Marcona almonds nearby wouldn't hurt either.

Data.Name: CK Mondavi Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This Cabernet Sauvignon has a classically deep red color and is rich with cherry and blackberry flavors that are perfectly balanced with a hint of oak and a long fruit finish. The wine provides a wonderful accompaniment to lamb, grilled steak, roast chicken and hearty pastas.    
ABV: 13.6%

Data.Name: Beringer Knights Valley Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet is built each vintage on the notion of a Bordeaux blend, with soft and silky tannins crafted for immediate enjoyment. Aromas and flavors of dark red fruit led by raspberry, black cherry and evident oak spice are joined with more traditional Knights Valley tones of black and blue fruits. A touch of licorice and mocha round out a lingering, pleasant finish.

Data.Name: Angeline Reserve Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Elegant, Raspberry, Vanilla, Medium-bodied    Mendocino and Sonoma Counties, CA- Lively aromas of raspberry, strawberry and a hint of tea. Bright flavors of ripe raspberries and strawberries, layered with subtle nuances of vanilla oak and a touch of spice, lead to a rich, smooth finish.

Data.Name: Achaval Ferrer Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
An accurate reflection of its variety, this Cabernet Sauvignon delivers a sharp and direct message where the fruit overcomes the mineral nuances. Originating from small patches of vineyards located in the first area in Mendoza, this wine that has very little production highlights a juicy texture filled with black and red fruitiness. 
Serving temperature between 16º and 18ºC. Tapster recommends decanting this wine at least an hour before drinking.

Data.Name: Tortoise Creek Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Burgundian and elegant, with aromas of violets and berries. Gorgeous food wine with roast meat and tuna.

Data.Name: St. Francis Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: An elegant Cabernet, it shows off firm structure, generous tannins and depth of color along with aromas and flavors of cassis, black cherry, dusty cocoa and cigar box.

Data.Name: Chateau Souverain Merlot
Data.Description: Chateau Souverain Merlot opens with dark red fruit aromas reminiscent of black cherry and plum. On the palate, notes of fresh blueberries are complemented by hints of brown spice and baking chocolate.  The wine finishes with soft acidity and a fruit-driven balance that gives the wine a polished sense of elegance.

Data.Name: Seghesio Sonoma Zinfandel
Data.Description:
Connoisseurs Guide 90 Points Spicy, lush black fruit flavors of Alexander Valley. Briary and raspberry flavors are present, along with structure of cooler Dry Creek Valley. Overall, this is a balanced and elegantly structured Zinfandel.
ABV 14.8

Data.Name: 90+ Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This glorious Cabernet Sauvignon comes from a family vineyard originally planted in the late 1700s. To achieve maximum ripeness, the fruit was harvested from low-vigor vines, and the finished wine was carefully aged in new French oak for 14 months. This is one stunning Cabernet. Taste an aromatic melody of black currant, cherry and cassis rises above a harmonious backdrop of tobacco, mocha and toasty oak.  
On the palate, juicy, dark berry fruit cascades across your tongue followed by a trickle of sweet spice and savory plums. Serve with grilled rib eye, portabella mushrooms and well aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Napa Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: "Elegant with concentrated aromas of dark fruit, juicy black currant, and hints of clove. A lush core of ripe blackberry, black currant, slate and dried cocoa coat the palate. Plush and enveloping fine-grained tannins lend to a velvety smooth finish."

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Menage a Trois exposes the fresh, ripe, jam-like fruit that is the calling card of California wine. Zinfandel, Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon add complexity and retain character, each variety was fermented separately, then blended together prior to bottling. Forward, silky and soft, this delicious dalliance makes the perfect accompaniment for grilled meats or chicken.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet Sauvignon jumps from the glass with aromas of ripe Bing cherries and blackberries plus cedar and dark, rich layers of maduro tobacco. Deep flavors of spice-infused plums, toasty oak, and espresso fill the mouth, with a rich, creamy layered texture, and powerful structure. Flavors of chocolate and black currant continue through the long, lingering finish.

Data.Name: La Vielle Ferme Cotes du Ventoux Red
Data.Description: A rich, spicy red southern stunner made mostly from Syrah and Grenache. Delicious with roast lamb.

Data.Name: La Cacciatora Lambrusco
Data.Description: La Cacciatora wines are filled with rich aroma and flavor, this is the essence of true wine. From Chianti to Pinot Grigio; from Lombardy to Tuscany, each bottle contains wine as unique and enchanting as the region where its grown. Open a bottle and the aroma expresses each region’s priceless history and passion.

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Vinter's Reserve Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This garnet gem delivers bright cherry, strawberry and raspberry fruit with elegant earthy notes infused with cola and mild spice accents. Oak aging adds a hint of vanilla and a soft smoky finish.

Data.Name: Hahn Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The Hahn Winery Pinot Noir shows red fruit flavors, a pretty lively palate and a lasting finish; a good choice with lightly grilled meats.

Data.Name: Duckhorn Merlot
Data.Description: Fundamental to Duckhorn's tradition was the early decision to focus on the production of Merlot. Dan Duckhorn felt that this elegant varietal was under appreciated in North America. "I liked the softness, the seductiveness, the color, the fact that it went with a lot of different foods; It seemed to me to be a wonderful wine to just enjoy. I became enchanted with Merlot."

Data.Name: Cupcake Merlot
Data.Description: Full-bodied yet smooth, the wine shows flavors of red cherries that evolve into decadent levels of cocoa, spice and espresso as well as a smooth finish. Moderated by the Pacific Ocean, the unique topography and climate of the sun-drenched Central Coast produces world-class wines. The Merlot grapes used are cool fermented for a slow process that retains aroma and complexity. A regimen of pump-overs extracts soft tannins and color, and grape skins are pressed before reaching dryness to preserve a lush tannin structure. Aged in American oak barrels adds more richness and complexity.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Sangria
Data.Description: A delicious mix of citrus and red wine with orange rind, citrus and red berry notes that splash onto the palate with a soft sweet-citrus flavor and a hint of spirit. The finish is clean, light and delightfully refreshing. Enjoy on its own or over ice.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Merlot
Data.Description: Medium ruby red color; candied fruit, vanilla, light spice aromas and flavours; not quite dry, medium bodied, with sweet fruit centre and a soft, lush finish.

Data.Name: Woodbridge Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Woodbridge Pinot Noir is a well-balanced wine with aromas of cherries and orange peels. This elegant wine is round on the palate, with flavors of berries and cocoa, and a touch of spicy, toasty oak from barrel aging.
Pair this velvety, versatile Pinot Noir with pan-roasted salmon, veal chops, or pasta Bolognese.

Data.Name: Sutter Home Red Moscato
Data.Description: Sharing the same sweetness of Sutter Home's regular Moscato, this Red Moscato divinely balanced with berry and rich cherry flavors. So unwind, and try pairing it with a warm berry pie. Ahhh, perfection.

Data.Name: Ruffino Chianti
Data.Description: A ruby red Tuscan wine with a vibrant and inviting aroma. The Sangiovese grapes in this Chianti Classico are characterized by notes of sweet violet, red berries and Morello cherries with slightly spicy undertones.

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Vinter's Reserve Cabernet
Data.Description: Sonoma County mountain and hillside vineyards add black cherry flavors and superb wine structure. Cabernet Sauvignon grapes are blended with Merlot for softness, Cabernet Franc for tannins, Malbec for a hint of chocolate and complexity, and Petit Verdot to enhance the mouthfeel. The coolness of the 2011 vintage enhances the elegance.

Data.Name: Clos Du Bois Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Ruby red in color. Intense aromas of cherry, dried roses, and earthy-woodsy forest floor. Flavors of sweet cherry fruit are wrapped in a silky, rich, and lush texture. The wine is well balanced with light, toasty oak.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Shiraz
Data.Description: Ripe Cherries and strawberries, spice, and vanilla aromas. Yellow Tail Shiraz is bold and well balanced, with earthy tones and lingering fruit on the tongue.

Data.Name: Oyster Bay Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Oyster Bay Pinot Noir is surprisingly a serious complex Pinot. Intense cherry and gamey, earthy notes are enhanced with quality French oak and the finish is spicy savoury and long.

Data.Name: La Posta del Vinatero Malbec
Data.Description: It's love at first sip with this classic Mendoza Malbec! Intense aromas of red rose petals and red berry fruits fill the nose. Enjoy violet, berry, and mocha flavors on the palate with just a hint of blueberry. As these flavors evolve you'll be treated to a hint of chocolate on the finish. Superb to drink on its own, but perfect with steaks on the grill or even pizza and pasta. Don't miss this one though with your dark chocolate dessert!

Data.Name: Frontera Merlot
Data.Description: "Cabernet Sauvignon offers character, complexity, and longevity, while Merlot adds softer tannins and elegance. The wine is fruity with aromas of chocolate, black plums and vanilla. A medium body gives way to black cherry flavors, soft tannins and a pleasing finish."

Data.Name: Cupcake Malbec
Data.Description:
A heady, yet dry nose of blueberries and leather opens up to a palate of intense chocolate, mocha and plums. A soft velvety texture and hint of spice leads to a finishing note of toasted oak. We carefully select the best fruit from our Mendoza vineyards, picking dark and delicious berries that mature gradually and gracefully. Rooted in stony alluvial soil, the grapes are harvested, gently crushed and left to ferment slowly with extra skin contact. Aging in oak barrels results in a full, soft, intense and rich Malbec. 

This wine is enjoyable with BBQ tri-tip or chicken  drumsticks.

Data.Name: 90+ Cellars Lot 23 Old Vine Malbec
Data.Description: This wine is made from meticulously tended Malbec grapes grown on high-elevation, old vines in the Lujan de Cuyo region of Mendoza, in the foothills of the Andes Mountains. It boasts exquisite aromas of dark berries, plum and spice, and is well balanced with ample structure and mild tannins. Dark cherry and hints of wood smoke emerge on the finish to leave an elegant and lasting impression.

Data.Name: Ruffino Riserva Chianti
Data.Description: The taste of Riserva Ducale is soft and soothing, yet full bodied and vibrant. The texture is tightly woven with lots of velvety tannins, chunky fruits notes and a fragrant acidity. The aftertaste is reminiscent of wild flowers, plums, figs and hazelnut muffins and features a refined ethereal touch, which is so typical for barrel aged Chianti Classico wines.

Data.Name: Menage A Trois Silk Soft Red Blend
Data.Description: "The flavor profile of this blend...is not the feminine creature one may imagine. On the nose, heady fragrance of freshly ground espresso beans and a meaty richness occurs. Sweet bing cherries surface in a bath of melted chocolate..."

Data.Name: Gnarly Head Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This dark, bold Cabernet has solid tannins and jammy fruit, with aromas and flavors of black cherry, currant, dried cranberry and black peppercorn followed by a trio of clove, earth and light toast. Gnarly Cabernet Sauvignon is a worthy companion to the heartiest meals, be sure to try it with grilled lamb, New York strip steak with roasted potatoes, baked manicotti or some bold blue cheese.

Data.Name: Elouan Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Tapster loves this pinot noir. Elouan Pinot Noir emulates the successful sourcing philosophy introduced with Meiomi: blending the top Pinot Noir regions together for a richer, more complex style than what you could achieve by sourcing from one small area. In this instance, our grapes are grown in the great Oregon Valleys of Willamette, Umpqua and Rogue. The diversity of these cool climate areas elongates the growing season, developing intense structure, while maintaining a vibrant acidity to differentiate it from any California Pinot Noir.

Data.Name: Hayes Valley Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This medium-bodied wine has lots of jammy aromas and flavors but also a dry palate impression and enough tannin and acidity to give it a lean finish.

13.5% ABV

Data.Name: Banfi Chianti Superiore
Data.Description:
Color: Intense ruby red. Bouquet: Fruit-forward aromas with some floral notes. Taste: Round with well balanced acidity and fruit.

Ideal with red-sauced pastas, roasted or grilled meats, and aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Big Bold Red
Data.Description: With just a touch of spice this wine is bursting with ripe dark fruits and rich, bold oak that inspired the name.

Data.Name: Leese-Fitch Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Leese-Fitch Cabernet Sauvignon offers deep purple color and wonderful fruity aromatics. This Cab blend starts off with aromas of blackberry cobbler, cassis, sandalwood, and herbs du provence. The flavors burst from the glass with notes of dark cherry, sweet leather, black currants, and toasted cardamom finishing with a hint of spearmint, dried fig, and toasty vanilla notes from a combo of French and American oak.

Data.Name: Black Box Merlot
Data.Description: Black Box Wines Merlot displays aromas of leathery plums and cinnamon-spiced oak. The palate is smooth, medium weight and aged-textured with sweet red currant flavors. It finishes long and warm with resolved tannins. This Merlot has acidity that allows versatility in pairing with food. 3L Box.

Data.Name: Arrogant Frog Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Arrogant Frog is a wine that proudly embraces its origin in the South of France. To obtain the fruit-forward, rich and elegant style that defines Arrogant Frog, its creator Jean-Claude Mas harvests its grapes at perfect maturity from the hillsides of the five main valleys of the Languedoc. This Pinot Noir has persistent aromas of red berries, cherries and soft spices with a silky palate. Serve with grilled meat, rack of lamb, pot roast, poultry, game, salmon, grilled vegetables or soft cheeses. 

13.5% Alcohol

Data.Name: 14 Hands Run Wild Juicy Red Blend
Data.Description: Juicy and fruit-forward, 14 Hands Run Wild showcases a vibrant blend of red grape varieties with flavors of ripe blueberries, black currants and black raspberries. Soft tannins, lively acidity, and a lingering finish allow for endless pairing options.

Data.Name: Barefoot Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Light but flavorful and fresh, this wine has good varietal character, medium body and good complexity, too. Aromas of red cherry and tea lead to cherry and plum flavors, mild tannins and a bit of fresh acidity for balance.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Bursts with aromas of ripe cherries and hints of dark chocolate which lead to a palate of soft spiced fruit framed in toasty oak that flows into a smooth velvet finish.

Data.Name: Louis Jadot Beaujolais Villages
Data.Description: Bright and sassy, the red-fruited Louis Jadot Beaujolais-Villages delivers fresh fruit on the palate; crisp and pretty in the finish, with berries and a hint of flowers.

Data.Name: Line 39 Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This fruit-driven Pinot Noir has fresh fruit and herbal with rich flavors of raspberries and black cherries on the palate and soft, supple tannins. This Pinot Noir pairs well with lamb, pork and pasta dishes.

Data.Name: Roscato Rosso Dolce
Data.Description: Roscato Rosso Dolce is an irresistible, delicately sweet, gently fizzy red wine from the northern Italian region of Lombardy. Made from three native grape varieties grown in this beautiful region for centuries Croatina, Teroldego and Lagrein Roscato makes a wonderful aperitif and is also incredibly food-friendly. Roscato seamlessly combines a long-held grape growing tradition with the flair of modern winemaking techniques and style. The result is a wine of enticing character that perfectly meets the surging demand for sweet red blends. With a low alcohol of 7% and just a touch of sparkle to flawlessly balance the sweetness, Roscato is the ideal complement for today's cuisine. Enjoy it with tomato-based sauces, classic Italian dishes, spicy foods and more. Serve chilled.

Data.Name: Bogle Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Bogle winemakers have sourced fruit from the best growing regions in California for the varietal. The terroirs of the cool Russian River Valley, coastal Monterey hills and the unique Clarksburg Delta all grow fruit of character and distinction. Combined, the resulting wine is and elegant, classic Pinot Noir.

Best paired with:
Swiss Chard Ravioli with Sage Butter Sauce
Mushrooms Sautéed with Garlic and Wine
Teleme Cheese with Cherry Preserves

Data.Name: Bonterra Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet offers aromas of bright cherry, currant, and raspberry with notes of toasted oak and vanilla. In the glass, you will and flavors of cherry and currant and a lingering and thoughtful finish. Good structure, a moderate weight, polished tannins and a balanced acidity promise an ever more pleasing wine to come.

Data.Name: Noble Vines 337 Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: "Ripe currant and boysenberry greet the nose and pave the way for a ripeness that plays on the mouthwatering nature of this delicious red. Dark chocolate and sour cherries seem Old World alongside the bright acidity and caramel-oak finish."

Data.Name: Agua de Piedra Malbec
Data.Description: Pours an inky purple, with aromas of plums and red and black berries. Delivers an intense wallop of rich berry fruit on the entrance. Finishes strong and smooth with root spices and a hint of earthiness. The tannins are enrobed in rich, creamy fruit, and add a lingering silkiness to the wine. Fabulous concentration for a wine of this price!

Data.Name: 19 Crimes The Punishment Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The color of this 2017 Pinot Noir is a medium intense burgundy with a youthful purple rim. Lifted notes of cherry and strawberry fruit complement rich vanillin overtones giving warm and inviting aromas on the nose of this wine. The palate is medium-bodied with soft, round tannins, cherry and strawberry fruit with sweetness which complements the vanilla and spice oak undertones. All these elements combined create a well-balanced, enjoyable wine with a long finish.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet offers easy drinking early but will cellar with confidence. Expect cassis, violets, crushed herbs and a long, soft finish with enough concentration and texture to make the wine feel more serious.

Data.Name: Hess Select Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Hess Select Cabernet Sauvignon starts with aromas of plum, ripe fruit, black cherry, spice, and a little smoke. The wine has a lush, round mouthfeel and tastes of plum and vanilla with a lot of oak and soft tannins. All those other varietals add some nice complexity to this medium-bodied wine. It finishes with lingering spice and notes of chocolate. This is a great value and a great wine to have on hand to pair with red meat, BBQ, and even with a pizza. We found the wine to be a little smoother on day 2 but it may have lost a little spice as well.

Data.Name: Bogle Merlot
Data.Description: On the nose, notes of tea leaf, cherry cola and earth tones add richness and depth to the first impression of the wine. Bright cherry, red currant and ripe fig mingle with toasty herbal tones, all combining to create a silky and smooth mouthfeel. To perfectly compliment the fruit, the wine was aged in American oak for 12 months, creating firm tannins that balance the supple and lingering finish.

Data.Name: Leese-Fitch Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Dark ruby in color, the Leese Fitch Pinot Noir boasts aromas ofwild strawberry, violets, dark plum, and vanilla spiked oak. Flavors reminiscent of dark plum, raspberry, tobacco leaf,cocoa nibs, and rhubarb finishing with a hint of earthy loam, black cherry, and toffee. The crisp acidity keeps youcoming back for more.

Data.Name: Underwood Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Self-described as a “notable every day wine” this meets the challenge. Given the price, it's a winner, with 58% of the grapes coming from the Umpqua Valley AVA. The light strawberry fruit carries herbal and bitter green flavors, yet everything is in proper proportion.

Data.Name: 19 Crimes The Uprising Red Blend
Data.Description: The Uprising, a new wine aged for 30 days in Rum Barrels, pays homage to Australia’s Rum Rebellion of 1808. Due to the Government's hindering of the rum trade, citizens and soldiers banded together to overthrow them. We aged a portion of this wine in Rum barrels lending a warm brown sugar finish to this dark jammy wine.

Data.Name: Meiomi Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The vineyards along coastal California are a combination of earth and elements, chosen to contribute to each Meiomi wine and to represent the best of their appellation. By combining their exemplary qualities into a single wine, Meiomi achieves unforgettable balance, complexity, and richness of flavor. Blending achieves wines that are easy to love and hard to forget. A rich garnet color with a ruby edge, the wine opens to reveal lifted fruit aromas of bright strawberry and jammy fruit, mocha, and vanilla, along with toasty oak notes. Boysenberry, blackberry, dark cherry, juicy strawberry, and toasty mocha flavors lend complexity and depth on the palate. It pairs particularly well with tomato-based pasta dishes, thin-crust pizza, grilled lamb, and turkey.

Data.Name: Bread & Butter Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Bread & Butter Pinot Noir is all about that juicy red fruit. Think cherries and raspberries with a touch of cassis. Delicate hints of cedar, smoke, and bay leaf cut the sweetness of the fruit, creating a nicely balanced bouquet. That luscious fruit bouquet continues onto the palate, where it’s joined by soft flavors of oak and savory notes. With a long and beautifully smooth finish, this Pinot Noir will melt in your mouth.

Data.Name: Bogle Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Full body, firm structure and well-concentrated fruit flavors make a great combination in this robust wine. It makes the mouth water for a meaty dish to enjoy it with, and it has a good palate-coating sense of richness.

Data.Name: 19 Crimes Red Blend
Data.Description: This medium bodied, deep red blend is bold with strong fruit flavors and hints of sweet blackberry. Well-balanced with medium tannins, this wine would pair well with poultry or pasta dishes.

Data.Name: 19 Crimes Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Wonderful paired with a scheme for an evening’s escape, 19 Crimes Cabernet Sauvignon conjures up red currants, dark berries and sweet vanilla oak in a passing smell. Caramel lurks in the back. Firm cabernet tannins and red fruits let the flavor linger after each nip.

Data.Name: Apothic Red Blend
Data.Description:
Apothic Red is a masterful blend of intense flavors and luscious texture creates a truly unique experience. Zinfandel lends notes of dark fruit and subtle spice while Merlot and Syrah bring hints of black fruit and a smooth mouthfeel. They are complemented by Cabernet Sauvignon that contributes a firm structure and bold flavors.
All of the varietals combine to offer layers of dark fruit that are enhanced by soft vanilla and mocha tones leading to a soft, lasting finish.

Data.Name: The Pinot Project Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Mission accomplished! The Pinot Project has accomplished its goal of being one of the greatest red wine values coming out of California. It is hand-crafted from grapes grown in notable AVA's such as Sonoma County, Carneros & Monterey. The Pinot Project has a full and silky mouth feel, with just the right amount of acidity to complement a variety of dishes. The wine is 100% stainless steel fermented with the caps receiving periodic punchdowns, before finishing dry with just a kiss of oak.

Data.Name: Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey
Data.Description:
A top-selling bottling from the Jack Daniel distillery, the mashbill is made up of 80% corn, 12% rye and 8% malt. The spirit is filtered through 10 feet of sugar maple charcoal to produce a mellow, slightly smoky character, thus making it Tennessee whiskey...

This whiskey is smooth and soft with notes of banana milkshake, a mixed nut note, a touch of caramel with crème anglaise.

Data.Name: Macallan 12 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: The Macallan 12 YO is the core of The Macallan lineup. When you walk into the local pub and simply order a “Macallan,” this is what will be poured into your glass — and they are sophisticated enough to keep a quantity of it on hand. It is not “just” finished in Sherry casks. This Speysider is aged its full twelve years in Spanish Sherry wood and for aficionados this particular Whisky defines the Sherried Whisky category. That means you get creamy toffee notes all day long with a rich rancio backdrop of fig and honey. It is the perfect Whisky to introduce a newbie to the world of single malts, but it will also be one of your favorites for life.

Data.Name: Glenfiddich 14 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description: Strong oak influence on the nose. Very fruity with nutmeg, cinnamon, fruits, dates. On the palate, bourbon sweetness, with strong fruitiness, sublimely smooth. Long nutty, toasty finish with hint of char. IWSC 'Gold Outstanding' Winner. Kosher Certified.

Data.Name: Glenlivet 12 Year Old Scotch Whisky
Data.Description:
One of the most famous malts in the world. Glenlivet 12yo has a soft smooth balance of sweet summer fruits and the floral notes of spring flowers.

You can taste notes of lemon, vanilla, toffee, and honeysuckle in this fine malt.

Data.Name: Graft Farm Flor Cider
Data.Description: A blend of wild yeast fermented cider with tart/ farmhouse barrel aged cider. Pairs well with respectable company and tasty food.

Data.Name: Chivas Regal Royal Salute 21 Year Old Whisky
Data.Description: Boasted as one of the finest blended Scotch Whiskeys in the world, Chivas Regal Royal Salute presents to you a fruity, smoky and floral fragrance with nutty, buttery and sweet flavors. Satisfyingly long in its finish. Search the world over and you will find very few whiskeys in the world can come close to the experience you'll enjoy with Royal Salute.

Data.Name: Embark Craft Ciderworks The Northerner
Data.Description: The Northerner is a refreshing semisweet cider made of 100% Northern Spy apples, one of the most famous of all American apples.

Data.Name: Downeast Cider Winter Blend
Data.Description: A reward for all that shoveling. We keep it interesting with toasted oak chips, cinnamon bark, nutmeg, and a little extra kick to help you forget you have to go back out there.

Data.Name: Downeast Cider Grapefruit Craft Cider
Data.Description: An unfiltered mix of grapefruit and apples. Something cool and refreshing to remind you spring is on the way!

Data.Name: Citizen Cider Wit’s Up
Data.Description:
There are ciders for the people, and there are ciders for the people who make the cider for the people. Wit’s Up is a classic cider maker’s cider. Drawing on the old and new traditions of cider making, it starts like an ale and finishes like the dry, sessionable craft cider that it is. It’s cider for today, it’s cider for what we believe the future of cider to be. Come, enjoy the future with us and drink Wit’s Up. 

Pairings: Bratwurst, brioche, roasted chicken, root vegetables.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider Unified Press
Data.Description:
Made from 100% locally sourced apples, never from concentrate, the Unified Press is Citizen Cider’s flagship cider that keeps you wondering where it’s been your whole life. This naturally gluten-free cider is an off-dry, crisp, clean and refreshing cider that keeps you coming back.

Pairings: Pork, soft cheese, spicy food, smoked fish, rustic bread & butter.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider The AmeriCran
Data.Description:
Throw together a bin of apples, a bushel of cranberries, and a few cider making citizens and you’ve got yourself an AmeriCran experience. The AmeriCran is a proud union of apples pressed at Happy Valley Orchard in Middlebury, Vermont, and cranberries from Vermont Cranberry Company in Fletcher, Vermont: co-fermented by Citizen Cider and delivered to you. Have your own parade, drink the AmeriCran. 

Pairings: Poultry, baked tofu, roasted root vegetables, hard cheese.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider Stan Up
Data.Description:
Citizen gave Stan the task of making the finest blend of cider possible from the fruit at his orchard. Made with heirloom blends, this year they did something a little different with Stan Up and used only 2015 apples giving this year’s cider a vintage. They aged the cider in steel tanks for 10 months starting November, bottled it in late August and then let it bottle condition for another 2 months. And Voila!  A year later we present Stan Up. 

Pairings: Braised herbed chicken, hard cheese, prosciutto, hummus.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider Lake Hopper
Data.Description:
The Lake divides us. The Lake connects us. Citizen Cider is proud to work with the good growers on both sides of mighty Lake Champlain, Vermont and New York. Made entirely with apples and cascade hops from the same landscape, and in some cases the same farms, this cider is a tribute to those things that connect us. Two States. One Landscape. One Cider. Get Connected. Drink the Lake Hopper. 

Pairings: Scallops, pork burger, Caesar salad, cheddar cheese.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider For Shore
Data.Description: For Shore is a Gose inspired cider finished with coriander seeds and sea salt. It’s dry, bubbly & best enjoyed alongside your favorite waterfront view. Citizen Cider will donate a portion of proceeds from sales of this cider to preserve and protect our home waters of Lake Champlain. For you, For us, For Shore.

Data.Name: Champlain Orchards Mac & Maple
Data.Description:
Vermont in a can. Mac and Maple pairs the well-loved McIntosh apple with just the right amount of Vermont Maple Syrup.

 A refreshing hard cider. 3.5% of proceeds of purchase go to 350.org to fight climate change and protect Vermont agriculture.

Data.Name: Bantam Cider The Americain
Data.Description: “The Americain is an easy-drinking cider with Persian spices like green cardamom, coriander, clove, cinnamon and rose petals. Those spices and rich apples give off an aromatic character that is intense and delicious. It's cloudy like an English scrumpy but American as apple pie.”

Data.Name: Bantam Cider Rojo
Data.Description: “Local heirloom and traditional New England apples make up this sweet, tart cider. It's slowly fermented with a hearty ale yeast, then aged with sour cherries and black peppercorns. It has a ruby color in the glass and gives off a fruity and spicy aroma. The taste is sour with a dry finish, making it an enjoyable casual cider.”

Data.Name: Bantam Cider Ginger Beer
Data.Description: “Smooth & spicy with a nice ginger bite. It’s delicious on its own or a great addition to your favorite cocktail. Small batch, high quality, craft product.”

Data.Name: Angry Orchard Strawman Cider
Data.Description: Strawman combines a distinct blend of juices from culinary and bittersweet apples, and is aged on oak, resulting in a complex, wine-like cider with apple and citrus notes and an earthy finish.

Data.Name: Ace Space Bloody Orange Cider
Data.Description: "Orange with red hues. Aromas of blood orange, citrus zest, and florals. Full bodied and smooth with flavors of orange and apples that are balanced by a very crisp finish."

Data.Name: Wolffer No. 139 Dry Rosé Cider
Data.Description: Evokes the style, sophistication and spirit of summer in the Hamptons. Bright shiny rose in color. Fantastic fresh floral notes fill the glass; the Crispin aromas especially stand out with fine hints of yeast. The mouth-feel is pure and clean, with a nice balance of sweet fruit, elegant acidity and fine tannins that provide a long and pleasant finish. There is a nice CO2 mousse, making it very pleasant and playful.

Data.Name: Seattle Cider Dry Hard Cider
Data.Description: One of the driest ciders on the market. The golden orange glow of this unique cider lends way to notes of lilac, blood orange and green apple on the nose. Dry and pleasantly acidic, flavors of nectarine, under ripe peach and tart cherry hit the palate with no residual sweetness.

Data.Name: Artifact Cider Project Dream A Little Dream
Data.Description: “Light and refreshing with a complex aromatic and flavor profile. Made from Empire juice aged for 9 months in French oak red wine barrels, blended with freshly fermented McIntosh juice, and assorted heirloom apple varietals.”

Data.Name: Downeast Unfiltered Double Blend Cider
Data.Description:
Five fresh apples go into every can of Downeast. Filtering them out would mean filtering out flavor. Nope. They leave the good stuff in there. 
They decided to push the envelope on their original blend to see how far it could go. Turns out, pretty far. Keep your head on a swivel, she bites.

Data.Name: Citizen Cider Dirty Mayor
Data.Description:
This cider is offered to the honorable and fully infamous mayor of the only non-town in America, Fort Ethan Allen, USA. The mayor likes his cider with a ginger nip, so in our current effort to ensure local harmony and diplomacy we offer this cider up to the mayor and his fellow citizens.
No added sugar, never from concentrate.
Apples pressed in Press House in Burlington, Vt. 
Pairings: Fried chicken, Thai cuisine, pan-seared seabass, vegetable Phó
ABV: 5.2

Data.Name: Vendange Chardonnay
Data.Description: “Aromas of apples and butter overlaid with subtle oak. Flavors are soft and smooth, with apple and tropical fruit flavors and a hint of vanilla. Not overly fat or buttery, this is an easy-drinking, fruity wine with moderate acidity, light body and a medium finish.”

Data.Name: Toasted Head Merlot 2015
Data.Description: “The Toasted Head Merlot reveals complex aromas and flavors of bright cherry, coffee, vanilla, and mint, with hints of dried herbs and spice. The tannins are firm and the mouthfeel is medium-bodied.”

Data.Name: Svedka Raspberry Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “Clear. Aromas of raspberry custard pastry and ice cream follow through on a soft, silky entry to a mildly sweet and fruity medium body. Finishes with a supple, lightly peppery raspberry lozenge and mossy mineral fade."

Data.Name: Svedka Grapefruit Jalapeno Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “Svedka is an award-winning vodka distilled five times to remove impurities. Svedka Grapefruit Jalapeno Vodka combines sweet and tart grapefruit flavors with a hot and spicy jalapeno kick.”

Data.Name: Svedka Cucumber Lime Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “To the nose, fresh, clean cucumber followed by bright citrus lime notes. On the palate, entry of subtle cucumber flesh and tart lime pulp. Mid-palate build of smooth vodka character with a citrus kick, intensifying to end with cool, fresh cucumber flavor with bright lime finish.”

Data.Name: Svedka Peach Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “Svedka is an award-winning vodka distilled five times to remove impurities. Make the ripe choice with this deliciously fruity peach-flavored vodka. Perfect for a Bitter Pink Peach cocktail!”

Data.Name: Svedka Mango Pineapple Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “A juicy, sweet blend of ripe aromatic mangoes with pineapples. A tropical blend of fruits with caramelized pineapple on the nose. Succulent mangoes on the palate with layers of juicy, sweet pineapple and creamy undertones that finish with a rich tropical fruit bouquet. Enjoy!”

Data.Name: Svedka Blue Raspberry Flavored Vodka
Data.Description: “Aromas of sweet raspberry followed by bright citrus notes. There are rich raspberry flavors on the palate that highlight bright berry character and an energetic lemon twist!”

Data.Name: Simi Sonoma County Chardonnay 2017
Data.Description: “Expressive tropical notes of mango delicate pear, and bright stone fruit. Lifted aromatics of citrus, lightly spiced with toasty oak and hints of buttery cream add a savory character. It all comes together on the palate with well-defined flavors of nectarine and peach.”

Data.Name: Simi Sauvignon Blanc 2017
Data.Description: “This wine is fresh, crisp, lively and forward on the palate, this Sauvignon Blanc has zesty notes of lime and grapefruit. The palate has a long finish with a lingering impression of green citrus, stone fruit, and mineral.”

Data.Name: Simi Merlot 2015
Data.Description:
“Deep garnet with a ruby edge. The nose is a compelling mixture of sour cherry, blackberry, and red plum with cocoa, clove, and earthy hints of cedar, bay laurel, and smoky bacon framing the bright fruit. On the palate, bright red fruit, red plum, black cherry, blackberry, and wild berry meld with light toast, vanilla, and a hint of fresh, sweet herbs, while spice lends depth and weight. The wine finishes with toasty oak and spice.

Try pairing this Merlot with garlic prawn and mushroom pizza, smoked quail, or roasted salmon with wild risotto.”

Data.Name: Simi Dry Rose 2017
Data.Description: “Simi Sonoma County Dry Rose is forward and focused with lingering tart cherry and balanced acidity that invigorates the taste buds. This pink wine pairs well with a summer salad or smoked chicken.”

Data.Name: Simi Cabernet Sauvignon 2015
Data.Description: “Aromas of baking spices, hints of cedar, chocolate and toasty oak notes frame bright fruit of red cherry, black plum, and cranberry. These aromas lead to flavors of red plum, cassis, blackberry and cherry.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Sparkling Rose
Data.Description: “Ruffino Sparkling Rose is fresh and fragrant with notes of strawberry and slight hints of rose petals. This bubbly wine has flavors of red berries and white fruits that linger through the finish.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Moscato D'Asti
Data.Description: “A refreshing and sweet wine delivering aromas of acacia, elderberry, citrus fruit with notes of peach, orange blossoms, and sage.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Modus Toscana 2015
Data.Description: “Ruby red in color, this wine offers an intense and intriguing nose, with initial aromas of mature red and black fruits -- such as cherries, plums and small black berries, typical of Sangiovese -- followed by hints of spices, sweet tobacco, and refined balsamic notes. Full-bodied with a modern Super Tuscan style, this wine is rich with silky tannins and flavors of mature blackberry fruit and cocoa. Vibrant, fresh fruit flavors from Sangiovese, Cabernet Sauvignon and Merlot weave together with finesse, each adding its own distinctive character. Modus is wonderful on its own, or with bold dishes such as duck with olives and pancetta, beef-stuffed manicotti with Bolognese sauce and aged cheeses including taleggio, pecorino and gouda.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Lumina Pinot Grigio 2017
Data.Description: “The bouquet is fresh and complex, showing refined notes of sage and mint accompanied by an elegant minerality typical of Pinot Grigio. Medium bodied, lively, and elegant. A touch of minerality lingers in the finish, with notes of lemon peel.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Lumina Pinot Grigio 2016
Data.Description: “The bouquet is fresh and complex, showing refined notes of sage and mint accompanied by an elegant minerality typical of Pinot Grigio. Medium bodied, lively, and elegant. A touch of minerality lingers in the finish, with notes of lemon peel.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Il Ducale Pinot Grigio 2016
Data.Description:
“Straw yellow with a hint of gold. Fresh and fragrant with bright aromas of pineapple, white peach, and tropical fruit accompanied by delicate white flowers and sage, followed by flavors of apple and pear. The acidity is firm but balanced, working with the ripe fruit taste profile to confer freshness and a mineral touch to the wine.

A perfect accompaniment to fresh seafood salsa, linguine, spinach gnocchi, tomato bruschetta, Parmigiano Reggiano, or Pecorino Romano.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Chianti DOCG 2011
Data.Description: “Ruffino Chianti DOCG is an approachable, easy-drinking wine that has predominantly fruity and floral aromatics, with hints of spice and hazelnut. On the palate, Chianti DOCG is soft with a medium body and nice balance, displaying pleasantly fruity characteristics.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Chianti DOCG 2016
Data.Description: “Ruffino Chianti DOCG is an approachable, easy-drinking wine that has predominantly fruity and floral aromatics, with hints of spice and hazelnut. On the palate, Chianti DOCG is soft with a medium body and nice balance, displaying pleasantly fruity characteristics.”

Data.Name: Ruffino Aziano Chianti Classico 2016
Data.Description: “Medium bodied Classico with well- balanced, very pleasing fruit notes accompanied by sweet spices and pepper with a hint of aromatic wood. The finish is long, smooth and velvety.”

Data.Name: Robert Mondavi Prvt Sel Bourbon Barrel Cabernet
Data.Description:
Robert Mondavi Private Selection Bourbon Barrel Cabernet Sauvignon 
"Layered and complex... leaps from the glass with aromas of blackberry cobbler, graham cracker, brown sugar, milk chocolate, coffee and smoke. Palate of blueberry pie, praline, sweet vanilla custard, caramel and mocha is framed by soft chewy tannins and a hint of toasted oak"

Data.Name: Kim Crawford Sauvignon Blanc
