The perfect light, refreshing lager to enjoy with your buds in cans or bottles. Pack sizes for all occasions: 6, 12, 15, 18, 24, 30, and singles. For those who thirst for more, we are the World's Most Refreshing Beer. Light & Refreshing with 4.2% ABV. Coors Light is always lagered below freezing to give our beer its cleaner, crisper taste . Every brew of Coors Light is made with traditional two-row lager malt which is made from our unique high county barley and four hop varieties; these are selected for their delicate aromatic properties. Coors Light delivers quality and a history you can taste.

Data.Name: Budweiser Cans
Data.Description: Budweiser was first introduced by Adolphus Busch in 1876 and it's still brewed with the same high standards today. Budweiser is a medium-bodied, flavorful, crisp American-style lager. Brewed with the best barley malt and a blend of premium hop varieties, it is an iconic beer, celebrated in America. This Bud's for you. The King of Beers, crisp, refreshing American-style lager. Pairs well with pizza, burgers, or fried chicken.

Data.Name: Bud Light Cans
Data.Description: Introduced in 1982, Bud Light is a premium light lager with a superior drinkability that has made it the best-selling and most popular beer in the United States. Bud Light is brewed using a blend of premium aroma hop varieties, both American-grown and imported, and a combination of barley malts and rice. The light-bodied beer features a fresh, clean and subtle hop aroma, delicate malt sweetness and a crisp finish that delivers the ultimate refreshment. Brewed in the U.S.A. 4.2% alcohol by volume.

Data.Name: Heineken Light Cans
Data.Description: Heineken Light is a light beer brewed by Heineken for the United States market. It was introduced in 2005. Heineken light reportedly has: 99 calories per 12 oz. bottle and 6.8 grams of carbohydrates. The beer has fewer calories, less carbohydrate, and less alcohol than lager beers such as the Heineken Pilsener.

Data.Name: Heineken Cans
Data.Description: Heineken Lager Beer, or simply Heineken is a pale lager beer with 5% alcohol by volume produced by the Dutch brewing company Heineken International. Heineken is well known for its signature green bottle and red star.

Data.Name: Corona Premier Cans
Data.Description:
The refreshing light beer you've been waiting for has arrived with the introduction of great-tasting Corona Premier. Brewed to be easy-drinking, the taste is undeniably Corona. It is a superior light lager with a refreshing taste that pairs well with Mexican and citrus-infused dishes. Premier is a uniquely refreshing beer perfect for taking a moment to look around and appreciate all that you've accomplished so far. This great-tasting light beer contains only 90 calories is 4.0% alcohol by volume. Best served chilled.
Contains only 90 calories per can!

Data.Name: Corona Light Cans
Data.Description: Corona Light has approximately 30% less calories than Corona Extra with the same refreshing taste, and is also brewed with the highest quality ingredients.

Data.Name: McManis Family Vineyards Chardonnay
Data.Description: Light golden straw in color with bright fruit aromas of pear, melon, and peach. The palate is driven by notes of stone-fruit, banana, vanilla, and a hint of buttered popcorn. Rich and decadent, our Chardonnay can be enjoyed on its own or with a delicious meal.

Data.Name: McManis Family Vineyards Zinfandel
Data.Description: This Zinfandel is a dark purple wine, loaded with notes of ripe red currant, strawberry, caramelized sugar, and toasty oak. The savory red fruit on the palate leads to soft, supple tannins and a smooth finish.

Data.Name: McManis Family Vineyards Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: This Pinot Grigio is light straw in color and crisp and refreshing on the palate. Driven by notes of lemon, lime, and grapefruit with a touch of minerality, this wine is a go-to palate cleanser.

Data.Name: McManis Family Vineyards Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This Pinot Noir is light purple in color and is bursting with aroma and flavor, leading with ripe red cherry, strawberry cream, and raspberry notes. The wine is silky on the palate with red fruit and vanilla undertones, culminating in a clean, lasting finish.

Data.Name: McManis Family Vineyards Merlot
Data.Description: This Merlot is medium-ruby in color and abundantly fruit-forward. The wine opens with notes of blackberry, vanilla cream, and baking spices and leads into a mid-palate dominated by black fruit, closing with a pleasing, toasty finish.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description:
Crafted using grapes from three of Chile's coastal regions. This cooler climate brings out the best qualities as the grapes ripen later, allowing the intense fruit flavours to shine through.
A refreshing light-bodied Sauvignon Blanc with zesty peach, citrus fruit and gooseberry flavors.
Perfect to savor on its own or with fish, shellfish, salads or soups.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Hero's Salute Red Blend
Data.Description: Deep ruby red in color. Blueberry, plum and cassis fruit aromas along with spices and vanilla, coffee and tobacco notes from the barrel-aging. The palate has a sweet attack and evolution, with good volume, depth, and a fruity finish that leaves a refreshing mouthfeel. Serve with pasta dishes with meat or black pepper sauce, grilled or stewed red meats, pork and cheese.

Data.Name: Santa Rita Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Enticing citrus aromas are immediately evident as luscious grapefruit and floral notes seem to leap from the glass. The citrus is joined by juicy apricot flavors on the palate with just a touch of herbs, which make this a great white for seafood and poultry.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
The expression of cassis in this wine perfectly represents the Valle Central and its richness in fruit such as cherries and plums. The barrel ageing length thanks to the toast and coffee notes.
Best paired with red meats, well-seasoned dishes, and aged cheeses such as Gruyere or blue.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Pinot Noir
Data.Description:
Casillero del Diablo Reserva Pinot Noir is a delicate and bright ruby-red colored wine with enticing aromas of ripe red fruits with notes of strawberry, raspberry and subtle hints of spice and toasted French oak. On the palate the wine offers a medium body and is fruit-forward in style. Flavorful and fully textured, this Pinot Noir has a balanced acidity and a pleasant and persistent finish.
Casillero del Diablo Reserva Pinot Noir is the perfect accompaniment to a wide range of meats including pork, chicken and lamb. Also elegant with vegetarian and fish dishes.

Data.Name: Pacifico Sur Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: "It is a vibrant and smooth perfectly balanced wine with clean expressive fruit and a subtle touch of oak black berry fruits with dark black pepper notes."

Data.Name: Borgo Del Col Alto Rosé Prosecco
Data.Description: A delicate pink sparkling wine made from the Raboso grape grown in fertile vineyards of north east Italy in the region of Treviso. It is fragrant with summer fruit aromas, fresh and lively on the palate, dry, crisp and easy to drink.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description:
This Cabernet Sauvignon was the first wine that Josh Cellars made. It is round and juicy, with flavors of blackberry, toasted hazelnut and cinnamon, complemented by hints of vanilla and toasted oak.
This Cabernet is best paired well-seasoned meats like beef, pork, or lamb, and indulgent chocolate desserts.

Data.Name: Korbel California Champagne Sweet Rosé
Data.Description:
Korbel Sweet Rosé is made from a selection of both red and white grape varieties.  The blend is designed to have very bright fruit flavors and aromas.  Korbel harvested some red varieties such as Zinfandel and Sangiovese early in the ripening process helps them achieve the style they wanted for this cuvée.
Serve Korbel Sweet Rosé as an aperitif or with fresh fruit or chocolate.  You'll also enjoy Sweet Rosé with appetizers such as grilled prawns with mango salsa or a selection of aged cheeses.

Data.Name: Korbel California Champagne Extra Dry
Data.Description:
Korbel Extra Dry is blended using four different grape varieties, each of which plays an important role in the final blend.  Chenin Blanc gives the blend a soft, fruit-forward character.  Chardonnay provides the structure, backbone and citrus and baked apple flavors.  French Colombard contributes to the blend by adding bright, crisp flavors and a hint of spice to the finish.
Korbel Extra Dry is a perfect aperitif wine.  It's delicious with nuts, dried fruit, cured meats and patés.  It also works well with a wide range of shellfish and spicy Asian foods.

Data.Name: Big House Wine Co. Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Big House Pinot Grigio boasts a nose full of citrus fruits and a round, soft palate, with flavors of grapefruit and honeydew melon to leave you quenched. Big House Wine Co's juice is fermented in temperature controlled, stainless steel tanks combined with aromatically gifted yeast to preserve and enhance the pleasing fruit characters of this wine.

Data.Name: Château de Beauregard-Ducort Entre-Deux-Mers
Data.Description: This is a Bordeaux-style White blend with a green, herbal wine, very crisp, still young with acidity, mineral acidity and a bright, lively aftertaste. The wine is tangy with citrus at the end. Keep for six months to a year. Screwcap.

Data.Name: Bota Box Cabernet Sauvignon Mini
Data.Description: Bota Box Cabernet Sauvignon offers aromas of black cherry and red currant in the glass with just a touch of cedar and vanilla. Medium in body, this wine is supple and juicy with rich flavors of ripe cherry, plum and spice on the finish.

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Aromas of lush black cherry, blackberry and cassis draw you in. Round, rich seamless tannins provide a robust backbone and supple mid-palate. Notes of cedar, vanilla and a hint of mocha linger on the finish.

Data.Name: Kendall-Jackson Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Luscious honeysuckle, ripe pear and fresh lemongrass intertwine in this medium-bodied Sauvignon Blanc.

Data.Name: Bread & Butter Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: This Cabernet Sauvignon expresses captivating aromas of mocha, ripe berries, violets, and blackcurrant with intertwining layers of subtle black pepper, toasted oak and rich vanilla. Lively and complex, this beautifully crafted Cabernet Sauvignon enters the palate with layers of ripe blackberry and chocolate covered cherries. The round and luscious mouthfeel is accented by soft tannins and a hint of spice that weaves into a smooth, lingering finish.

Data.Name: Bogle Vineyards Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This wine's bold, tropical grapefruit and pineapple flavors and bright acidity make for a refreshing mouthfeel. A slight touch of sweetness rounds off the otherwise vibrant, citrusy personality.

Data.Name: CBD Oil Hemp Gummies
Data.Description: Delicious mango flavored CBD gummies.

Data.Name: Goldfish Carton
Data.Description: A whole carton of the best snacks on earth.

Data.Name: Tiga Ping Pong Balls (6)
Data.Description: Six ping pong balls

Data.Name: Bud Light Keg
Data.Description: Large Bug Light Keg, good times ahead!

Data.Name: André Peach Moscato Champagne
Data.Description: André Peach Passion California champagne is deliciously sweet with flavors of ripe fruit, hints of orange blossom, with a muscat-type varietal flavor.

Data.Name: André Extra Dry Champagne
Data.Description: A blend of varietal whites with a light touch of sweetness and light mouthfeel. Fruity flavor with a hint of sweetness. Crisp finish.

Data.Name: André Blush Pink Champagne
Data.Description: Somewhat sweet, this pink champagne offers lots of fruit and a very easy almost sweet-tooth behavior; chill well for proper service.

Data.Name: Ruffino Rosé
Data.Description: Ruffino Sparkling Rosé is fresh and fragrant with notes of strawberry and slight hints of rose petals. On the palate this wine has elegant bubbles and refreshing acidity, offering alluring flavors of delicate red berries and white fruits that linger through the finish.

Data.Name: Ruffino Prosecco
Data.Description: Crisp, clean and delicate with fine bubbles on the palate. Intense flavors of apples and peaches lead to a pleasant finish with lingering fruit and floral notes.

Data.Name: Big House Wine Co Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Big House Pinot Grigio boasts a nose full of citrus fruits and a round, soft palate, with flavors of grapefruit and honeydew melon to leave you quenched.

Data.Name: Pacific Rim Riesling
Data.Description: Floral and soft, with delicately sweet white peach and tropical fruit flavors. Drink now. 50,000 cases made.

Data.Name: Relax Riesling
Data.Description: Relax Riesling is a refreshing, crisp, authentically German Riesling. Slightly dry with an enticing fruity bouquet, it shows intense flavors of apples and peaches with a hint of citrus. Serve chilled.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Pink Moscato
Data.Description: A refreshing, sweet wine with bright strawberry flavors, hints of sherbet and delicate floral notes. The wine has a fine and enticing fizz with a vibrant fresh softness on the palate.

Data.Name: Yellow Tail Riesling
Data.Description: The lemon and lime aromas of this light, refreshing Riesling will leap from your glass and you may even catch the hints of orange blossom.

Data.Name: Matua Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: All the varietal zing you’d expect from the granddaddies of Sauv Blanc in New Zealand. Look at it in a glass – it’s just about singing with freshness. The lively nose shows tropical and citrus fruits with subtle herbaceous characters. Its crisp fresh palate offers classic Marlborough acidity, structure and length.

Data.Name: Louis Tête Beaujolais-Villages
Data.Description: This simple wine offers red berry and banana flavors. With its light structure and soft fruit, it is open and ready to drink.

Data.Name: Trinity Hill Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This offers ripe nectarine and pineapple, showing ample weight for its modest alcohol level. Hints of snow pea and melon add nuance, while the plump body and succulent, citrusy finish beg for another sip.

Data.Name: Montpellier Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Medium in color and body, this wine has flavors of fresh berries and plum. The mouthfeel is of vanilla and hints of spice. This wine pairs well with your favorite red meat dish. It also pairs well with chocolate.

Data.Name: Ravenswood Zinfandel
Data.Description: This Zinfandel explodes with blueberries, black plums, vanilla, and cocoa. Lush and mouth-filling, with incredibly silky tannins.

Data.Name: Cielo Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: "This simple white opens with aromas of honeysuckle and pear while the easygoing palate offers hints of nectarine and green apple. Fresh acidity gives it a brisk finish. Drink soon."

Data.Name: Fancy Pants Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Not-too-dressy and not-too-casual, this wine is always stylish and always delicious. Made from grapes sourced from premier California vineyards, our Cabernet is playful and approachable, with lush flavors of dark berries, sweet vanilla, and toasty oak character.

Data.Name: Beringer White Zinfandel
Data.Description: In making Beringer's White Zinfandel, their focus was to highlight the fresh red berry, citrus and melon aromas & flavors, and round them out with subtle hints of nutmeg and clove.

Data.Name: Wild Horse Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Flavors of sweet oak, vibrant fruit, light herbs, and bramble spice. Aromas of blackberry, and cassis with notes of blue fruit, vanilla, and cola spice. Pairs well with grilled steak, blue cheeseburger with sautéed mushrooms and truffle fries. 88% Cabernet Sauvignon, 10% Petit Verdot, 2% Malbec.

Data.Name: Glen Ellen Chardonnay
Data.Description: Medium bodied, brimming with crisp apples and pears. it's crafted in a way to enhance the typical fruit flavors of the Chardonnay grape.

Data.Name: Rosemount Estate Shiraz
Data.Description: This Shiraz is full-bodied, well-defined and juicy-sweet with blackberry, plum and cherry flavours complemented by the subtle richness of oak.

Data.Name: The Beachhouse Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Bright pale gold with deliciously inviting fleshy peach gusto, fresh citrus zeal and succulent pineapple appeal and a riveting fresh finish. Perfect for easy drinking on its own, or with light pasta, fish and seafood or snacks like mezze, anitpasta, cold meats and creamy cheese.

Data.Name: Barefoot White Zinfandel
Data.Description: Southern flavors like Georgia peach, sun-ripened strawberries, succulent pears and (even further south) pineapple create perfection. Try Barefoot White Zinfandel over ice, y’all.

Data.Name: Barefoot Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Do you want an inexpensive but consistently refreshing white wine? Then Barefoot Pinot Grigio is your go-to. With tart green apple, citrus and notes of crisp peach, this light wine pairs perfectly with dishes like tilapia or sole, basmati rice, haricots verts or lemon chicken. You're probably going to want to enjoy this in warmer weather because this is the adult equivalent to a chilled glass of lemonade. But if you're craving it in the colder months, serve it chilled to cut through hearty, warm dishes thick with dairy like raclette, fondue or heavy chowders.

Data.Name: Barefoot Pink Moscato
Data.Description: Aromas of Mandarin orange and sweet jasmine crash into each other to create a deliciously sweet sea of pink goodness. Subtle flavors of cherry, raspberry, and pomegranate complement the lingering and vibrant finish.

Data.Name: Line 39 Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This Sauvignon Blanc opens with vibrant aromas of grapefruit and lemon with subtle grassy characters and a crisp clean finish. This wine is a fine accompaniment to shellfish or on its own after a long day.

Data.Name: Line 39 Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Line 39 refers to the latitude where many of the great wine growing regions of the world are found in Lake County. Line 39 starts with aromas of bright red fruits, blackberry, tobacco and cedar. This elegant wine offers chewy black fruit flavors with subtle tannins on the finish that will not overpower this easy-to-drink Cabernet Sauvignon.

Data.Name: Folie à Deux Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Deeply concentrated aromas of strawberry jam and black cherry, with subtle hints of cola and spice, framed by a palate of cherry, cranberry, toffee, leather and tobacco.

Data.Name: Bota Box Chardonnay Mini
Data.Description: Bota Box Chardonnay offers aromas of bright citrus, ripe melon and warm toasty oak, followed by vibrant flavors of zesty lemon, apple and graham cracker. This wine is medium-bodied, balanced and provides a rich, juicy finish.

Data.Name: Bota Box Merlot Mini
Data.Description: Bota Box Merlot offers aromas of cherry, blackberry and sweet herbs complemented by flavors of black cherry, ripe plum and hints of spice that extend into a juicy, concentrated finish.

Data.Name: Bota Box Moscato Mini
Data.Description: A light-bodied, sweeter-style wine offering delicate citrus blossom, honeysuckle and white peach aromas with flavors of nectarine, tropical fruit, and honey that extend into a juicy, concentrated finish.

Data.Name: Bota Box Pinot Grigio Mini
Data.Description: Bota Box Pinot Grigio offers lively aromas of nectarine, white peach, and light floral notes. This delightful medium-bodied wine has flavors of ripe peach, nectarine and bright citrus with a refreshing, clean finish.

Data.Name: Bota Merlot Mini Box
Data.Description: Good balance, traditional flavors and a great price make this wine an easy-drinking gem. It tastes dry and slightly tannic in a good way that gives it texture, and has Merlot's typical plum and light herb notes.

Data.Name: Bota Moscato Mini Box
Data.Description: A light-bodied, sweeter-style wine offering delicate citrus blossom, honeysuckle and white peach aromas with flavors of nectarine, tropical fruit, and honey that extend into a juicy, concentrated finish.

Data.Name: Simi Chardonnay
Data.Description: James Suckling-Sonoma County, California - "A rich and flavorful chardonnay with sliced cooked apples and pineapple and hints of cream and vanilla. Full body, lots of fruit and a long and flavorful finish. Drink now..."

Data.Name: Trebbiano Tentimenti
Data.Description: Grapes: 100% Trebbiano d'Abruzzo. Color: straw-yellow with green shadings, Aroma: fruity citrus aroma with pleasant flower hints. Taste: dry, fresh and balanced.

Data.Name: Bieler Et Fils Rosé
Data.Description: The aromas and flavors are all so finely knit together that it’s almost hard to write a tasting note at times: from the more savory lavender and rosemary to rose petal notes to citrus, wild raspberry, and tart cherry. There’s acidity on the tongue yet a hug of richness.

Data.Name: Bieler Et Fils Red Blend
Data.Description: The resulting wine has loads of dark berry fruit, along with classic Provence garrigue notes (rosemary, thyme, sage), and a broad, rich and super textured palate. Tannins are quite soft and inviting.

Data.Name: Copper Moon Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Paired best with pork, spicy food, mushrooms, and any cured meats.

Data.Name: Wicked Wines Shiraz
Data.Description: Boasts flamboyant aromas of pepper, spices, chocolate and black plums.

Data.Name: Wicked Wines Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Dry and crisp with delicately fragrance and light citrus flavor. Goes well with seafood, chicken, roasted vegetables and Gershwin’s Rhapsody in Blue.

Data.Name: Wicked Wines Moscato
Data.Description: Packed with flavors of honey, sweet cantaloupe and apricots.

Data.Name: Wicked Wines Chardonnay
Data.Description: Unoaked with flavors of tropical pineapple and peach. Wicked tasty with light pasta dishes, grilled chicken, and Alfredo sauce.

Data.Name: Santa Rita Sauvignon
Data.Description: Crisp and refreshing, the fruity aroma of citrus blossoms and peaches is well balanced by delicate herbal undertones. Light and zesty, this Sauvignon Blanc is fresh with a pleasantly lingering finish. Try with seafood or lighter dishes.

Data.Name: Jillian Louise Rosé
Data.Description: Brilliant light. Pleasant nose suggestive of red fruits.  Round palate offering up a savory fullness and precise aromas bursting with enthusiasm. A nicely crafted rose.

Data.Name: El Brazo Abarino
Data.Description: Albariño is a white grape grown predominantly in northwest Spain and Portugal, where it is also known as Alvarinho. It typically produces lightly colored but aromatic and high acid light-bodied wines that often exhibit ripe citrus and stone fruit flavors.

Data.Name: Santa Rita 120 Red Blend
Data.Description: Deep ruby red in color. Blueberry, plum and cassis fruit aromas along with spices and vanilla, coffee and tobacco notes from the barrel-aging. The palate has a sweet attack and evolution, with good volume, depth, and a fruity finish that leaves a refreshing mouthfeel.

Data.Name: Culitos Chardonnay
Data.Description: A refreshing Chilean white wine. Pale yellow in color with crisp, bright fruit notes, it is round and fresh on the palate with hints of melon and lemon zest.

Data.Name: Casillero Del Diablo Malbec
Data.Description: Native of Cahors, France, this variety truly shines in Casillero del Diablo’s outstanding Malbec featuring concentrated sweet fruit and round tannins with aromas of blackberries and black plums with a touch of black pepper and vanilla, while flavors of spices and black plums meld perfectly on the palate.

Data.Name: Pacifico Sur Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Pacífico Sur Estate Sauvignon Blanc has a bright yellow tint with glints of green. Its prominent aromas of lime and grapefruit blend harmoniously with herbs and floral notes. In the mouth it is soft, citric and refreshing to the palate.

Data.Name: A to Z Wineworks Chardonnay
Data.Description: This Chardonnay has primary aromas of tangerines, lemon curd, white flowers, apricots, lime zest, kumquats, honeydew and wet stones. As the wine opens, aromas evolve to include beeswax, nutmeg and honey over time. A juicy and succulent attack has floral and citrus flavors while the mid-palate mirrors the aromatics with a burst of flavors offering tremendous depth balanced by perfect acidity and concentration.

Data.Name: A to Z Wineworks Pinot Noir
Data.Description: The generous 2015 vintage delivered rich, dark color to the 2015 A to Z Oregon Pinot Noir. Striking aromas of black cherries, blackberries, blueberries and raspberries are overlaid with a cornucopia of spices. As the wine opens, aromas expand to include pipe tobacco, fennel and red currants. The palate initially mirrors the aromatics with complex, pure red and blue fruit flavors.

Data.Name: San Huberto Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Paired best with beef, lamb, and poultry.

Data.Name: San Huberto Chardonnay
Data.Description: Perfect with fish or seafood. It's richness fairs particularly well cantonese style shrimp. Creamy lemon flavors carry over intact on the palate, full and bright, with a rich, full-bodied texture and sufficient acidity for balance.

Data.Name: San Huberto Bonarda
Data.Description: Paired best with beef and venison. A very rich and intense red wine, made from the La Rioja region of Argentina.

Data.Name: San Huberto Cabernet Syrah
Data.Description: Paired best with lamb, beef, spicy food, mature and hard cheese, and poultry. Made with Shiraz/Syrah grapes and Cabernet Sauvignon grapes from the La Rioja region of Argentina.

Data.Name: Kaiken Malbec
Data.Description: Though simple on the nose, with classic notes of black fruit and plentiful violet bouquet, this wine is pleasantly tannic and earthy, saving it from being just another fruity Malbec.

Data.Name: Norton Malbec Reserve
Data.Description: James Suckling-Mendoza, Argentina - "A malbec with purity and structure with a linear backbone giving the wine form and tension. Full body, blue fruits and a lively finish. Fine tannins. Made from 83-year-old vines. Barrel fermented. Real Argentine malbec."

Data.Name: Layer Cake Red Wine Blend
Data.Description: The Layer Cake Sea of Stones red blend is extremely dense and concentrated. Opaque purple, almost black in color, the aroma is full of ripe black fruit, grilled bread, pencil lead, wet stones, lavender, blueberry pie, and black cherry. On the palate there is layer upon layer of savory fruit, spice notes, espresso, and dark chocolate as well as rich, creamy texture. The aromas and flavors carry on long after the wine is gone from your mouth, the finish taunting you to have another sip.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Sauvignon Cabernet
Data.Description: Layer Cake Cabernet Sauvignon truly expresses the depth and complexity of the grape. Perfumed with violets and wild berries, it shows strong varietal characters and rich, ripe plum fruit. Seamless and elegant, this wine shows big black fruit on the palette, fine grain soft tannins and a long coffee chocolate finish.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Malbec
Data.Description: Big, brooding, black fruit, then rich earth, truffles and dark cocoa are at the front. The Sea of Stones vineyard is at its core, always evident with the thread of minerality that the deep alluvial cobblestones lend. This wine is elegant in the mouth with fresh-picked blackberries, simmering chocolate sauce on the stove, and somewhere someone’s cooking bacon…so many layers, so little time. Drinking a bottle of this wine will certainly lead to, well, opening another.

Data.Name: Crios Rosé of Malbec
Data.Description: Deep, vibrant rosé color. On the nose shows intense berries with reminiscences of wild strawberries. On the palate, the flavors of young cherries come rushing in. An amazing elegant finish rounds out the mouth.

Data.Name: Crios Malbec
Data.Description: Beautiful reddish-purple color. Aromas of crushed blueberries, cherries and blackberries. In the mouth, sweet red fruit flavors are in perfect balance with a subtle oakiness and a core of perfectly ripe berries. The palate is fresh and balanced.

Data.Name: Mauro Molino Langhe Nebbiolo
Data.Description: We recommend you pair this red and savory wine with a lamb dish. Made of Nebbiolo grapes from the Langhe region of Piedmont, Italy.

Data.Name: Mauro Molino Dolcetto D'Alba
Data.Description: Dolcetto is a lively, exuberant variety without a ton of complexity in most cases, and as such is best paired with simple, flavorsome foods such as pasta, pizza and simple meats—anything an Italian farmer might consume after a long day in the field.

Data.Name: Villa Marchesi Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: [click image to zoom] image may not be actual bottle available  This refreshing, crisp and dry Pinot Grigio is bursting with aromas of exotic fruit and fragrant white flower on the nose. The palate offers tart green apple, melon and juicy citrus alongside lively acidity.

Data.Name: Le Versant Grenache Rosé
Data.Description: Paired best with Aperitifs, tapas, cold soups, grilled white meat with spices, ratatouille, tandoori chicken, monkfish tagine, red fruit crumble. Pale pink colour with salmon tints. Delicately perfumed nose combining sweet hints of red fruit (strawberry, raspberry) and more floral aromas of rose and orange flower. Sweet and silky palate, wonderfully balanced, enlivened by hints of citrus zest. Lovely long-lasting aromas with hints of fresh mint.

Data.Name: Vanderpump Rosé
Data.Description: Provence, France - Elegant nose with delicate red currant and hints of pepper as well as sweet citrus.On the palate, it reveals a touch of strawberry, tangerine and peach in a dry, classic style.

Data.Name: Côté Mas Rosé
Data.Description: Grenache 50%, Cinsault 30%, Syrah 20%. Pale salmon color. Complex nose with cherry and strawberry notes evolving towards soft candied fruit. The palate is rich and smooth with ripe red fruits and a well-balanced acidity. Best served with light dishes, salads or on its own as an aperitif. This wine can be kept two to three years.

Data.Name: Côté Mas Blanc
Data.Description: 35% Grenache Blanc, 25% Vermentino, 25% Chardonnay, 15% Sauvignon Blanc. Medium lemon color. Intense nose with notes of citrus, grapefruit, and a touch of tropical fruits. Vibrant with aromas of citrus fruits and a hint of tropical fruits. Easy-going and fruity wine with a well-balanced acidity. Pairs well with chicken, fish and curry; also great on its own.

Data.Name: Côté Mas Rouge
Data.Description: Grenache noir 45%, Carignan 25%, Cinsault 15%, Merlot 10%, Syrah 5 %. Medium garnet with ruby tints color. Intense and fruity nose with aromas of ripe black fruits, blackcurrant and a touch of licorice. Smooth and soft with notes of concentrated and ripe berries and a touch of licorice. Best served at 60°F with red meat, a platter of cheese and charcuterie, or simply by itself!

Data.Name: La Motte Chardonnay
Data.Description: The perfect food pairing with this Chardonnay is a cheese plate of cheddar and gruyere. This wine has a buttery complex, and is made of Chardonnay grapes from the Franschhoek Valley of the Western Cape of South Africa.

Data.Name: Ken Forrester Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Lovely complexity with mix of tropical fruit, tangy grassy notes, fig leaves & nectarine nuances with crisp dry finish.

Data.Name: Ken Forrester Renegade
Data.Description: With 60% Shiraz, 14% Mourvedre, and 26% Grenache, this elegant Rhône blend displays Old World Style with New World fruit. Hint of Grenache's earthy rusticity and Shiraz's noble spice with hints of nutmeg and salty black olive on the finish. Balanced with soft integrated tannins.

Data.Name: Iona Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Beautiful purity of limes and ripe gooseberry, with tropical, floral and fine herbal notes, ruby grapefruit and white pear drop on the finish. This is cool climate Sauvignon blanc – vibrant, mineral, elegant, balanced and delicate, with a long, layered and complex finish.

Data.Name: Sophie Rosé
Data.Description: Delicious strawberries, wild berries, cranberries and a hint of sweet spice on the nose. Sophie le Rose is fresh and vibrant, with a hint of candied fruit on a textured finish.

Data.Name: Sophie Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Paired best with a garden salad, roast chicken, shell fish or Thai stir-fry. Vibrant pure fruit of cut green apples, zesty limes, gooseberries and tropical notes with white flowers and subtle mineral undertones.

Data.Name: Light Horse Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: Paired best with beef, lamb, or poultry. Light to medium bodied with red berry notes tartness.

Data.Name: Light Horse Pinot Noir
Data.Description: This silky Pinot Noir showcases sumptuous sweet cherries, cherry pie, and subtle, earthy aromatics of morning dew and pine. Mouthwatering red berry flavors blossom on the palate, while supple acidity and mellow tannins contribute to the wine’s innate elegance.

Data.Name: The Pinot Project Rosé
Data.Description: The Pinot Project Rosé shows pure PINOT aromas and flavors of raspberries and roses, unoaked to enhance the pure PINK fruit qualities. Outfitted in a stellar new package, this wine is a sure showstopper for all meals, seasons, and occasions.

Data.Name: Block Nine Pinot Noir
Data.Description: California- Shows a deep, rich color. The aromas show generous bright fruit with a mix of strawberry, violets, dark cherry and a hint of leather. Flavorful in the mouth with good body and a velvety texture. Wild strawberries and hints of toasted French oak to complete its finish.

Data.Name: Hahn SLH Chardonnay
Data.Description: Hahn SLH Chardonnay has crisp aromas of honeysuckle, vanilla, hints of citrus and banana. Full bodied flavors with viscous, round mouth-feel of citrus balances the acidic finish.

Data.Name: Hahn Merlot
Data.Description: Lovely aromas of black cherry, cassis and raspberry complement the soft grip of tannins on the palate. Flavors of plum meld with seductively dark chocolate and mocha. The finish is smooth and pleasing.

Data.Name: Hahn GSM
Data.Description: Hahn GSM takes its inspiration from the Rhone Valley of southern France where Grenache, Syrah and Mourvèdre are some of the most popular grape types grown. Each of the three grape types blended into this wine adds distinctive aromas and flavors. Grenache contributes raspberry, strawberry and cherry flavors, while Syrah lends color, tannins and hints of blueberry and black pepper.

Data.Name: J. Lohr Chardonnay
Data.Description: Tropical fruit flavors, apricot, nectarine and a toasted oak bouquet make Riverstone the perfect companion for roast chicken and seafood dishes.

Data.Name: Layer Cake Chardonnay
Data.Description: The nose is reminiscent of Meyer lemons, preserved then diced up later in the year, wet stones and lime blossoms waft in and out as well. The wine builds in body and texture as it sits in your mouth. Layers of Kaffir lime, guava, and pineapple pour in at first, and then the light creamy texture of whipped lemon curd fills in.

Data.Name: Begonia White Sangria
Data.Description: Begonia is a premium sangria fashioned to communicate the bright orange citrus flavors of the Mediterranean. All its ingredients are natural and of high quality. It exhibits bright citrus aromas and fresh red berry flavors. It is smooth and delicious!

Data.Name: Begonia Rosé Sangria
Data.Description: Begonia is a premium sangria fashioned to communicate the bright orange citrus flavors of the Mediterranean. All its ingredients are natural and of high quality. It exhibits bright citrus aromas and fresh red berry flavors. It is smooth and delicious!

Data.Name: Begonia Red Sangria
Data.Description: Begonia is a premium sangria fashioned to communicate the bright orange citrus flavors of the Mediterranean. All its ingredients are natural and of high quality. It exhibits bright citrus aromas and fresh red berry flavors. It is smooth and delicious!

Data.Name: Abigail Rose Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This pale yellow sauvignon blanc from Marlborough, New Zealand has an intense floral note with aromas of lime, pineapple, and stone fruit that will dance in your glass.  Its lively acidity and silky entry combine to provide a long and pleasant finish.

Data.Name: Beringer Cabernet Sauvignon
Data.Description: It has aromas of vanilla and blackberry with a deep ruby color. A medium-bodied, balanced wine with layers of ripe fruit flavors.

Data.Name: Beringer Merlot
Data.Description: Grapes for the California Collection Merlot were picked at the peak of maturity to maintain the fruit's rich, ripe flavors in the finished wine. Winemaking focused on accentuating the deep red fruit flavors from the grapes with the sweet spices of oak, resulting in a smooth, fruit-forward wine with a pleasing finish.

Data.Name: Beringer Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: This wine has a refreshing bite of juicy white peach and citrus, finishing with a flinty-minerality.

Data.Name: Jacob's Creek Moscato
Data.Description: The Sparkling Moscato is a deliciously refreshing wine with hints of luscious berry fruit flavours and a light, fresh taste. Simply chill and enjoy it with friends.

Data.Name: Borgo Del Col Alto Rosé
Data.Description: A delicate pink sparkling wine made from the Raboso grape grown in fertile vineyards of north east Italy in the region of Treviso. It is fragrant with summer fruit aromas, fresh and lively on the palate, dry, crisp and easy to drink.

Data.Name: Raboso Rosato Rosé Prosecco
Data.Description: "A delicate sparkling pink wine made from the Raboso grape, grown in fertile vineyards of northeast Italy in the region of Treviso. It is fragrant with summer fruit aromas, fresh and lively on the palate, dry, crisp and all too easy to drink. Perfect as an aperitif, but matches well with fish soups, grilled fish and mushroom dishes."

Data.Name: Flama D'Or Brut Rosé
Data.Description: Pair with fish, shellfish, white and red meats. "Pleasant in the mouth. Good carbonic formation, rich and dense. Its evolution reveals the character of the grape variety, both fresh and complex at the same time, a thick texture but also light, bringing out, above all, the red wild fruits, with the strawberry standing out."

Data.Name: Flama D'Or Brut Imperial
Data.Description: Best paired with shellfish, white and red meats, and fish.  A fine, fresh nose and fruity, combined with notes of long raising in bottle makes a rich and complex cava in aromas.

Data.Name: Flama D'or Brut Cava
Data.Description: This champagne has fine, persistent bubbles. Bright appearance. Accentuated aroma of fresh grapes, with signs of ripe fruit and of citric fruits, very pleasant and characteristic of aging in the bottle. In the mouth it is extremely vivacious, compensated for by a pleasant equilibrium and elegance. Aftertaste is fruity, evoking the apple, pear and a hint of citric. Balanced, fruity and persistent.

Data.Name: Bonterra Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This Sauvignon Blanc gives aromas of citrus, grapefruit, and fresh cut grass (in a good way).

Data.Name: Bonterra Chardonnay
Data.Description: This Chardonnay offers the flavors of crisp green apples, pears, and citrus.

Data.Name: Vino Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: This Pinot Grigio has an essences of lilac, tangerine, alpine strawberry, golden straw, and Italian melon.

Data.Name: Vino Moscato
Data.Description: Best paired with spicy Asian takeout or Mexican dishes. Elderberry blossom and wisteria perfume rises from the glass leading to a mouthful of apricot, orange blossom, honeysuckle, boysenberry and ripe peach. This one is for the table, porch or picnic.

Data.Name: Vino Rosé
Data.Description: Delectable. Delicate pink color. Compelling aromas of Italian melon, faint cherry, camellias, dried herbs. Mouth-watering. 100% Sangiovese. Pure, mineral, satisfying.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Pinot Noir
Data.Description: Best paired with roasted turkey, soft cheeses like Brie or Comté, or hearty vegetables like sautéed mushrooms.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Chardonnay
Data.Description: Pairs beautifully with shrimp, steamed mussels, creamy pastas, roasted chicken, and grilled vegetables.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Pairs beautifully with seafood appetizers, summer salads, and grilled chicken as well as light and simple foods all year long. This wine is especially well suited for summertime sipping in the sun.

Data.Name: Cecelia Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Best paired with pasta, shellfish, cheese, lean fish, cured meat. Made from Pinot Grigio grapes from the Friuli-Venezia Giulia region of Italy.

Data.Name: Cadaretta SBS Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: Paired best with salmon, tuna, shellfish, sweet desserts, and poultry. From Columbia Valley.

Data.Name: Angeline Chardonnay Reserve
Data.Description: This Chardonnay has a delicious bouquet of ripe golden pear, tropical pineapple, and sweet honeydew melon, along with aromatic apple blossom, and creamy vanilla bean.

Data.Name: Jacob's Creek Shiraz
Data.Description: Fruity, friendly, and robust, this full-bodied red wine has lots of spice.

Data.Name: Jacob's Creek Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: Best paired with pork, spicy food, and mushrooms. Made from Pinot Grigio grapes from South Eastern Australia.

Data.Name: The Velvet Devil Merlot
Data.Description: Best paired with a burger with all the fixin's, grilled steak, and anything with bacon. This smooth Merlot offers pure velvet, deep and delicious black fruit, cedar, tobacco and cassis. It conveys concentrated richness and yet purity and focus.

Data.Name: Chateau St. John Chardonnay
Data.Description: This Chardonnay has both sweet and savory notes including lemon crème pie, nectarine and toasted almond and spiced tea. The nose rings true on the palate with layered flavors of cantaloupe melon and mango, lemon curd and baking spice. The well structured wine is balanced with a warm, rich texture and expressive acidity.

Data.Name: PopCrush White Blend
Data.Description: Best paired with pasta, pork, shellfish, and poultry. Made from Gewürztraminer, Muscat Blanc, Riesling, Viognier, and Chardonnay grapes.

Data.Name: PopCrush Red Blend
Data.Description: Deep, dark color with flavors of ripe red berries, blackberries, and even some hints of cherry. PopCrush Red Blend, made with Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Syrah, Zinfandel, and Petite Sirah, has a good tannic backbone for body and a delightfully smooth finish.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Legacy Red Blend
Data.Description: Best paired with BBQ ribs, leg of lamb, and grilled skirt steak. A rich, velvety red blend bursting with flavors of ripe plum, black cherry and toasted cedar with scents of dark fruit and pepper.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Zinfandel
Data.Description: This wine smells spicy, almost like tobacco, and tastes plummy and pruney.

Data.Name: Josh Cellars Merlot
Data.Description: Best paired with soft cheeses, or meat-based pasta dishes (yum). This Merlot has flavors of blueberry, raspberry, and milk chocolate, with scents of violets and vanilla.

Data.Name: Kung Fu Girl Riesling
Data.Description: Paired well with spicy ramen, Sriracha pork tacos, and Chinese takeout. White peach, mandarin orange and apricot are delivered with a core of minerality that makes this dry Riesling shimmer with energy and freshness.

Data.Name: Boom Boom Syrah
Data.Description: Paired well with saucy BBQ ribs and lamb meatballs. "Zesty and easygoing, with lively raspberry, pepper, and grilled anise flavors." -Tim Fish, Wine Spectator December 2017

Data.Name: Eve Chardonnay
Data.Description: A shimmery, brilliant, green golden of a wine. Aromatic pear, tangerine, guava, but more than anything, true Chardonnay flavor. Add a vein of minerality running through the middle. Long and satisfying. Pair with golden squash with sauteed shrimp.

Data.Name: Fetzer Eagle Peak Merlot
Data.Description: This Merlot has a deep, rich ruby color. Layered aromas of boysenberry and black plum are accented with notes of cocoa nib, black licorice, coffee and a suggestion of soy. Round, smooth tannins in this juicy, approachable Merlot complement flavors of blackberry and toast before a lingering finish.

Data.Name: Kenwood White Zinfandel
Data.Description:
The fresh flavors of White Zinfandel make it an ongoing favorite among many wine drinkers. Kenwood Vineyards creates crisp fruit qualities and balanced flavors in this wine by gently pressing Zinfandel grapes. This is followed by a cool fermentation in stainless steel. The wine is bottled after minimum aging to preserve its youthful appeal.
White Zinfandel is delicious as a summer aperitif. It also pairs well with many foods including poultry, salads and spicy Asian cuisine.

Data.Name: Bogle Essential Red
Data.Description: A compelling blend of Californias finest plantings of Old Vine Zinfandel, Syrah, Cabernet Sauvignon and Petite Sirah, this wine surpasses all expectation for pure enjoyment and approachability.

Data.Name: Fetzer Valley Oaks Pinot Grigio
Data.Description: This Pinot Grigio is clean and fresh, with a fruit-forward character and a crisp acid backbone. Vibrant aromas of mango, pear, orange spice, lemongrass and pineapple segue to an inviting palate of tropical fruit, apple, pear and orange citrus. A pleasing hint of minerality is underscored by a wonderfully round finish.

Data.Name: Fetzer California Sauvignon Blanc
Data.Description: This Sauvignon Blanc opens with classic aromas of freshly cut grass, accented by layered notes of Kaffir lime, kiwi and citrus blossom. On the palate, this medium-bodied wine is bright and crisp, with flavors of melon, grapefruit, pear and pineapple, all framed by an inviting mouthfeel and a lingering finish.

Data.Name: Fetzer Sundial Chardonnay
Data.Description: Aromas of tropical fruit like mango, pineapple, banana, ripe kiwi and honeydew melon alongside notes of cinnamon, vanilla bean, lemongrass and hints of hazelnut and cloves. Fruit-forward, medium weight, with crisp citrus and lingering melon, pear and creme fraiche flavors.

Data.Name: Miller Lite
Data.Description: Miller Lite is the original and most gold medal awarded light beer. More taste. Half the carbs of Bud Light. 96 calories and 3.2g of carbs per 12 fl. oz. serving. Miller Lite established the light beer category in 1975 and introduced the perfect balance of lightness and flavor nationally. It’s a real Pilsner, brewed to have more color and taste with only 96 calories per 12oz. Since day one, our mission has been to deliver uncompromising quality through a great-tasting American-style Lager. Miller Lite has a golden color and deep flavor, yet is delicately balanced to be light on calories. Our unique process is more time consuming, but has earned us more gold medals for taste than any other light beer.

Data.Name: Miller High Life
Data.Description:
Miller High Life is a crisp American Lager with a slight sweetness balanced by bitterness.It's Light & Refreshing with 4.6% ABV. A favorite among bartenders, brewers and beer lovers in general, Miller High Life was launched as Miller Brewing Company’s flagship beer in 1903. Its crisp, easy-drinking flavor is the epitome of the American lager category. True to its original recipe, it’s brewed with a proprietary blend of malted barley, Galena hops from the Pacific Northwest and Miller yeast. 

It's the perfect beer for celebrating any occasion big or small, whether with a 12 pack or a 30 pack, for a holiday party or New Years Eve Party, a Memorial Day barbeque or cookout, or to just stock your bar or pantry. Light & Refreshing. 

4.6% ABV.

Data.Name: Miller Genuine Draft
Data.Description:
Miller Genuine Draft is an American lager style with fresh from the tap taste. It's the original cold-filtered packaged draft beer that uses a proprietary "cold-filtered four times" brewing process. Light & Refreshing with 4.6% ABV. 

Miller Genuine Draft delivers a fresh from the tap taste through its proprietary "cold-filtered four times" brewing process. Introduced nationally in 1986, Miller Genuine Draft was born as the original cold-filtered packaged draft beer. Today, Miller Genuine Draft is reinforcing its status as the best draft beer in a Bottle.

Data.Name: Michelob Ultra
Data.Description: Michelob Ultra is the superior light beer with no artificial colors or flavors. With just 2.6 carbs and 95 calories, you can enjoy the crisp, clean taste of Michelob Ultra without compromising your active lifestyle.

Data.Name: Heineken Light
Data.Description: Heineken Light is a well balanced light beer with a bright, golden color, with a mild malty aroma and striking citrus, hop aroma from the Cascade hops. Medium body, crisp, clean refreshing aftertaste, with only 99 kcal per bottle

Data.Name: Corona Extra
Data.Description:
Corona Extra is a pale lager produced by Cervecería Modelo in Mexico for domestic distribution and export to all other countries besides the United States, and by Constellation Brands in Mexico for export to the United States. The Corona brand is one of the top-selling beers worldwide. 
Outside Mexico, Corona is commonly served with a wedge of lime or lemon in the neck of the bottle to add tartness and flavor.

Data.Name: Coors Light
Data.Description: Coors Light is a light beer that delivers Rocky Mountain cold refreshment, well-balanced flavor with a malty note, low bitterness and light body. The perfect light, refreshing lager to enjoy with your buds in cans or bottles.

Data.Name: Bud Light Lime Cans
Data.Description: Bud Light Lime is perfect for a hot summer day. Brewed with real lime peels, you'll enjoy a clean and crisp taste with a hint of natural lime flavor in every sip. Made with essential ingredients and at 4.2% ABV, it's a refreshing take on America's light lager -- with a real twist!

Data.Name: Bud Light
Data.Description: IIntroduced in 1982, Bud Light is a premium light lager with a superior drinkability that has made it the best-selling and most popular beer in the United States. Bud Light is brewed using a blend of premium aroma hop varieties, both American-grown and imported, and a combination of barley malts and rice. The light-bodied beer features a fresh, clean and subtle hop aroma, delicate malt sweetness and a crisp finish that delivers the ultimate refreshment. Brewed in the U.S.A. 4.2% alcohol by volume.

Data.Name: Budweiser
Data.Description: Budweiser was first introduced by Adolphus Busch in 1876 and it's still brewed with the same high standards today. Budweiser is a medium-bodied, flavorful, crisp American-style lager. Brewed with the best barley malt and a blend of premium hop varieties, it is an iconic beer, celebrated in America. This Bud's for you. The King of Beers, crisp, refreshing American-style lager. Pairs well with pizza, burgers, or fried chicken.
